    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, hidden depth leads your approach. Let the firm hand of worsted wool and the strict cut of a crisp cotton poplin shirt provide the foundation. Support this internal structure with sharp, straight lines and a single gleam of cool metal at the collar. A forced detour to the dry cleaner on a Tuesday morning provides no excuse to drop your standards. Demand exact precision from every backup garment. If your secondary icy grey trousers lack a strict crease, bypass them. Reach only for stark navy pieces that offer absolute certainty. Keep the overall finish matt and deliberate.",
      "sectionIntro": "Define your baseline for professional environments, ensuring strict standards remain unbroken.",
      "tests": [
