      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Let clean geometry lead in low light. Close quarters demand exact edges. Late evening plans offer no permission to soften your silhouette. Maintain your cool colours at all times. Opt for an ink dark overcoat or a charcoal fine ribbed merino knit. These pieces draw sharp lines in dim rooms. Select cold silver or platinum hardware to act as your one polished signal, catching whatever ambient lighting remains. Gauge the material in the dark. It must feel firm and deliberate against your fingers. Reflections fade, but structural integrity holds steady. Choose matt textiles to keep the focus entirely on the cut.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control exactly what your materials communicate when the lights drop and the distance closes.",
      "tests": [
