      "text": "Keep your metals uniformly cool and highly reflective. Your strategy relies on {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Treat these cold, bright materials as your standard for both structural zips and personal jewellery. Steer clear of faux vintage brass, beaten copper, or any finish designed to look old. These introduce visual noise into a modern aesthetic. Anchor your choices in high shine cool tones instead. Exclude {excluded_finish} hardware entirely. Weigh the item in your palm before you commit. Polished plating mimics quality, but physical density confirms it. Solid construction feels substantial. Clean geometry demands absolute precision from its hardware. Let that heavy, cold impact on your skin guide your decisions.",
