    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Crush it tightly in your fist. If the creases stay, it fails your transit check. Imagine enduring a five-hour journey in a cramped seat. If you cannot emerge looking pristine, leave the material on the rack. Reject {texture_bad_2}. Run your thumb over the surface. If it lacks a cool, dry touch and feels artificially slick instead, it disrupts your foundation. Your strategy relies on projecting one polished signal. A cheap sheen instead of a true matt finish actively fights that goal. Grasp the fabric to find its true character. The glass reflects a false image. The physical drape gives you the facts. Steer clear of {texture_bad_3}. If it catches or drags when you sit down, it restricts your stride.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to brutally evaluate materials and reject anything that fails you under pressure or in transit.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Let bodily sensation dictate your choices. Visuals create illusions, but tension reveals the reality. Pick up {texture_good_1}. Raise both arms straight out to your sides. Assess the shoulder seams. If the material traps your arms or the hem hitches up to your ribs and stays there when you drop your hands, abandon the piece. You require mobile layers that recover their shape instantly. Pair {sweet_spot_keyword_1} directly against {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Seek out a cool, smooth surface that catches the light. Matt textiles absorb energy, so keep them strictly away from your face.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your texture combinations by testing how a material performs in motion.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is strictly cool. Build a functional base from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Substitute {core_colour_3} anywhere others use standard white, and structure the clean geometry of your silhouette using {core_colour_4}. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent. Apply your relief tone sparingly as a soft note to ease stark contrasts. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green. Let tactile feedback override visual appeal. Watch for the hard shell trap. When your routine accelerates, you might instinctively grab technical jackets or stiff utility garments for protection. Drop them. Swap that rigid exterior for brushed cotton. It shifts just as fast and physically supports you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your foundation by treating colour as a strict functional system.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Stark navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Icy grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Optical white",
          "role": "white_substitute"
