      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Administer a blind friction check. Run your bare hands across the weave to reveal the truth about any garment before you try it on. Reject {texture_bad_1} immediately. It snags against rough fingertips and clings uncomfortably. Leave {texture_bad_2} on the hanger. It crushes in the fist and refuses to recover its structure. You require materials that hold their own form to support one polished signal in your silhouette. {texture_bad_3} fails this standard because it sags at the seams and loses tension after a single afternoon of wear. The moment a surface feels slippery rather than cool and dense, drop it. Your presentation demands structural independence. Let the sensory feedback from your palms dictate what makes the cut.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the fabrics that compromise your structure before they ever touch your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Find the exact point where {sweet_spot_keyword_1} meets {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing builds clean geometry without adding unnecessary bulk. Anchor your silhouette by placing {texture_good_1} over a crisp shirt. Scrutinise the weave by pressing the cloth flat against your palm. If the fabric feels hollow, drop the item on the spot. Pure heft delivers a cool, matt reality. Let your fingertips measure the substance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock in your signature tactile pairings to construct an uncompromising foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep your temperature strictly cool. Construct your foundation using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Reach for {core_colour_4} when you need a light neutral lift. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon entirely. Deploy your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to create hidden depth. Treat {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as deliberate accents designed to focus the eye. Watch out for dissolution. Stacking sheer pale layers with nothing solid underneath causes your outline to vanish completely. Fix this immediately by restoring a strict internal line. Add a bias-cut slip that tracks the body, a fitted base layer, or a firm dark anchor piece worn directly on the skin.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your choices in a precise palette and deploy tones with absolute intention.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
