    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the office, clean geometry dictates your choices. Build your outfit around a strict cut in dove grey brushed wool or an inky navy jacket. Let unseen complexity support this rigid structure. A deep teal silk lining or the dense drape of cashmere does the work. Finish the look with a solitary metallic accent, perhaps a cool, matt steel cuff. Rely entirely on your tactile senses to judge these pieces. A mirror will deceive you. The sheer mass of full-grain leather never will. Run the Cinder test daily. A freezing midnight trip to the petrol station demands exactly the same rigorous cut as a day at your desk. Never let convenience blur your edges. If a piece collapses between your fingers, leave it behind.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your working hours requires strict physical discipline, so let us establish the rules for your office attire.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "When lighting drops in intimate spaces, hidden depth takes the lead. You must rely on tactile friction over sharp visibility. Layer heavy, deep teal cashmere over flat, cold silk. The contrast does the work in the shadows. Keep a cool platinum watch catching the dim light at your wrist. Do not surrender your structure to the dark. Remember that transitioning from a restaurant to a taxi demands a strict silhouette. If you are standing under harsh streetlamps, your outerwear must still hold a crisp shoulder line. Throw an inky navy, full-grain leather jacket over your knitwear. Rely on the heavy drape of thick brushed wool to maintain your edges when the room goes dim.",
      "sectionIntro": "Prepare your wardrobe for the spaces where light drops and proximity increases.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat routine tasks as an active drill. Never suspend your rules for a quick walk around the block. A morning coffee run still deserves a strict silhouette in dove grey cashmere. Test your foundational garments by assessing their heft. Heavy brushed wool and structured full-grain leather must provide rigid boundaries. If a piece sags or loses its shape, discard it immediately. Maintain a cool temperature across every layer, anchoring a deep teal foundation with a single piece of heavy silver. Your baseline demands the exact same equation regardless of the context. Whether you are sorting mail or stepping out into the rain, your standard must remain clean geometry + hidden depth + one polished signal.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply the exact same structural rigour to a Tuesday morning errand as you would to a formal appointment.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Anchor your hardware strategy in a cool foundation. Build your collection around {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Before you purchase a belt or watch, lift the item from the table. A solid buckle or clasp drops with real heft into your palm. Rely on physical resistance as your absolute guide. Avoid blinding chrome or highly reflective surfaces. A high-shine finish clashes violently against muted cashmere and brushed wool. To preserve clean geometry, restrict your metals to matt or {excluded_finish} textures that absorb light. This ensures your structural pieces anchor the garment without breaking the cohesion of your palette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as the structural framework of your garments rather than an afterthought.",
