    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your clothing establishes the clean geometry and secures the hidden depth. An accessory exists solely to deliver that one polished signal. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with handbags. Demand full-grain leather in a cool palette. The body must be fiercely matt, interrupted by a single reflective clasp. Apply the float test to every potential purchase. Place the empty bag on a hard surface. If the leather slumps or collapses without internal support, reject it. You require dense, self-contained architecture that stands upright alone.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat accessories as the definitive punctuation mark for your wardrobe.",
