    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "When evaluating scarves, demand matt silk. Lift the fabric shoulder-high and drop it. A synthetic blend falls instantly. True silk catches the cool air and takes a slow, deliberate path to the floor. Rely on that physical behaviour as your absolute gauge. A fabric's descent reveals its true value. Knot a dove grey scarf tightly at the neck to preserve sharp clean geometry. Avoid sprawling drapes that disrupt your contained edges. The flat, muted finish provides necessary hidden depth against a structured coat. Anchor it closely at the collarbone.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply strict physical tests to soft accessories before they touch your skin.",
