    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your fabrics must provide absolute softness to balance your clean geometry. Train your hands to run the collapse test before you check a fabric label. Pick up a garment and drop it onto a flat surface. If the piece holds its own rigid shape, leave it on the rack. It must surrender instantly into a fluid puddle. Look for {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Seek out {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Rely on {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Finally, source {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. Let the immediate drape of the textile verify its worth. Consult this hierarchy of core textures.",
