  "venus_aquarius__moon_gemini__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean geometry + light movement + one polished signal",
    "closing": "Always tune out the mirror and let the strict physical weight of your garments guide you directly to clean geometry + light movement + one polished signal.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe systematically, but dress with immediate flexibility. Trust the physical sensation of readiness as your ultimate compass. When you pick up a garment, feel its weight and structure. Apply the flight test. Ask yourself if you could sprint for a departing train or navigate a crowded airport terminal in this exact piece without feeling restricted or overheated. If a jacket binds your shoulders or a trouser demands constant adjustment, drop it immediately. Looks lie. Constriction is a design failure. Your garments must serve your physical reality first.\n\nBase every outfit on a reliable equation. Your core style formula is clean geometry + light movement + one polished signal. Picture a highly structured overcoat worn open over a lightweight, fluid knit that responds to your breath. Finish this base with a single piece of highly reflective, cool hardware at the wrist or collar. The tailored outer layer provides the geometry. The responsive knit provides the movement. The single hardware piece provides the necessary polish. Anchor this combination with shoes built for actual walking. Rely on this exact balance when you need to assemble a complete look under pressure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat these rules as your architectural foundation, a strict physical standard you can use to assemble any look without hesitation.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your foundation relies on materials that hold clean geometry without stiffening your joints. Administer the mobility check. Lift your arms, twist your shoulders, and check if the garment flies with you or fights back. If it restricts you, leave it. Rely on your body to judge mass. Mirrors deceive. Heaviness drags you down. You require fabrics that deliver light movement and a cool, polished finish. Rely on {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Use {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement. Select {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. Prioritise this exact list, preparing the canvas for one polished signal.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the fibres that build your foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
