    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Evaluate the density in your grip. Optics trick the eye. True gravity reveals poor construction. Launch the fabric upwards. Throw the material into the air and watch it settle. If it plummets downward instead of catching the breeze, it fails. {texture_bad_1} is a trap. It drags across your skin, trapping heat and destroying any clean geometry. Pick up {texture_bad_2} and crush it in your fist. A harsh, scratchy bite means it lacks the cool ease you require. Your core formula demands light movement and one polished signal. Materials that feel stiff or dense block this entirely. When {texture_bad_3} feels like a matt, lifeless sheet of plastic, drop it immediately. Always trust your hands over the reflection.",
