    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Look for the exact boundary between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Toss an item across the room onto a chair. Watch how it travels through the air. If it lands like a dead weight, leave it on the rack. The fabric must settle into clean geometry. Let your fingertips decide. A silhouette on a hanger means nothing if the garment feels burdensome. Build your foundation on cool, precise surfaces paired with pliant structures that guarantee light movement. Button a crisp {texture_good_1} cuff over a fine ribbed knit to set the stage for one polished signal.",
