    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is strictly cool. Build your structural foundation using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, {core_colour_3}, and {core_colour_4}. These shades allow you to construct the clean geometry of your silhouette without visual clutter. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate focal point. Treat your relief tone purely as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green completely. Watch for the hard shell trap. When the day accelerates, you might instinctively reach for armour like technical jackets or stiff utility layers. Correct this error instantly. Swap the rigid shell for a brushed cotton layer that acts just as fast, guaranteeing light movement and holding its form while allowing one polished signal to draw the eye.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your colour roles to keep your foundation sharp and deliberate.",
