      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your fabrics must deliver clean geometry without fighting your body. Seek out a cool finish. Prioritise {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. For close-to-body base layers, choose {texture_good_2} for sharp lines and easy movement. Anchor your lower half in {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. Before buying, apply the wrist-flick test. Pick up a sleeve and snap your wrist. If the fabric ripples with light movement and settles immediately back into shape, trust it. Let the material hold the structure, leaving room for exactly one polished signal to complete the outfit. Hunt for these specific textures.",
