      "text": "Reject any fabric that disrupts your clean geometry. Run your bare hand over {texture_bad_1}. If it feels stiff or drags against your knuckles, leave it on the rail. Subject {texture_bad_2} to a quick drape check. Snap a sleeve sharply away from your body. The cloth must resettle instantly. If it drops like a dead weight or clings awkwardly, it lacks the light movement you require. Sight deceives, but gravity reveals the truth. Depend entirely on this tactile reality. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. It traps heat, creates static, and ruins the crisp lines you need.",
