    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Build your core combinations around the tension between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. When assessing a new garment, trust your hands over the label. Tug the hem and release it instantly. If the material drops straight down and holds a crisp edge, you have the correct weight. A flimsy piece will ripple and collapse. Discard it. You require items that support clean geometry without restricting your joints. Look for {texture_good_1} that snaps back into place the moment you drop your arm. Keep the surface matt and cool. Your best combinations depend entirely on this strict selection process.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your exact material pairings to build outfits that hold their shape.",
