    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your underlying temperature is cool. Build your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Swap harsh white for {core_colour_3}. Ground everything in {core_colour_4}. For a deliberate accent, select {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Ensure these shades support clean geometry across your silhouette. Walk past Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green. Leave them on the rail. Beware unanchored prettiness. A completely pale or soft look seems charming initially but turns forgettable by lunch. Cure this with one solid anchor. Introduce a sharply tailored blazer, a structured flat, or a grounding piece in {core_colour_4} worn where the eye lands first. Let the raw drape of the fabric dictate your choice. A heavy weave hangs with intent.",
