      "text": "Commit entirely to a cool metal strategy. Build your hardware around {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Always pick a piece of jewellery or a heavy clasp up in your hand before wearing it. A highly polished finish looks impressive, yet only solid mass confirms quality. This literal weight provides the physical anchor required to ground the light movement of a technical nylon jacket or a crisp poplin shirt. Reject tarnished bronze, beaten copper, and any hardware manufactured to look old. Faux-vintage details create visual noise that disrupts the modern clarity of your wardrobe. Maintain sharp boundaries by eliminating any {excluded_finish} finish. Rely on the pristine, mirror-like reflection of {metal_1} or {metal_2} to keep your components focused.",
