      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Subject every garment to a rigorous stress test. Grasp the material firmly and stretch. If {texture_bad_1} goes slack and fails to recover its rigid shape, leave it on the hanger. A fabric that cannot hold its own structure will destroy your clean geometry. Scrunch a sleeve of {texture_bad_2}. When it retains a crushed crease or feels artificially slick in your fingers, it fails. Brush your palms down {texture_bad_3}. A surface that drags or feels like cheap plastic offers no utility. Reject any material that sags, wrinkles deeply, or loses its crisp edge under pressure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn the exact tactile failures that disqualify a garment before you even try it on.",
      "tests": [
        "the two-hands test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot marries {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Test a piece of {texture_good_1} by gripping the hem with one hand and the collar with the other. Pull them sharply apart. You must feel immediate resistance. That crisp tension holds clean geometry around your frame. Pair that resilient shell with a cool, smooth base. The resulting friction builds a consistently polished finish. Drop any item that collapses into limp puddles when you pull it taut.",
      "sectionIntro": "Locate your exact structural balance by testing every weave before you wear it.",
      "tests": [
        "the two-hands test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette temperature is decisively cool. Build your base using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Employ {core_colour_3} as a sharp neutraliser, and set dark boundaries with {core_colour_4}. Strike with {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your sole focal point. Reserve your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. This strict division enforces the clean geometry your structure requires. Step entirely away from Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green. These colours weaken your crisp lines. Beware the styling pendulum, where you wear head-to-toe airy mesh one month and stiff workwear the next. Stop oscillating. Bridge the extremes by keeping one piece from the opposite extreme in every single outfit you build. If a shade makes you hesitate, drop it immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce strict functional jobs for your colours to build an efficient, working system.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Stark navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Icy grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
