    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Leave {texture_bad_1} on the rail. It collapses under its own weight and pools where it should hold a sharp edge. Run your fingers across {texture_bad_2}. If the weave catches on your skin or feels spongy, drop it. Catch the cuff of any flexible piece, stretch it an inch, and let go. You require an immediate, crisp return to form. If the item puddles or hesitates, it will distort your silhouette. Let physical resistance dictate your choices. Flimsy materials instantly dilute your one polished signal. Keep your layers strict and cool.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify structural failure in the hand before it ever touches your skin.",
