          "failure": "swaddling: layer upon layer of shapeless grey and the silhouette dissolves entirely",
          "fix": "restore one defined line, a structured collar, a neat cuff, or let the keepsake pendant sit visibly at the neckline"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the desk, clean geometry establishes your baseline. Build outfits from sharp inky navy trousers or a structured silk shirt. Let soft margins support these strict forms. Layer a cool dove grey cashmere wrap over your shoulders to temper the rigidity. Provide exactly one polished signal with a heavy sterling silver cuff. A sprint to the early train or a quick midday coffee run never requires you to surrender your shape. Reach for a deep teal brushed wool coat even on a hurried morning. Verify these pieces through touch. Visuals deceive, but density remains constant. Pick up a full-grain leather briefcase and feel the thick stitching. Heavy hides and sturdy wools ground your focus while you work.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your work garments as functional tools, requiring both strict discipline and tactile yield.",
      "tests": [
        "a school run or a corner shop dash does not require surrendering your softness (Cove)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light and close quarters, blurred edges take the lead. Drop stiff fabrics. Choose fibres that absorb shadows instead of reflecting them. A quick midnight walk to the local shop does not justify rigid nylon. Keep your grey cashmere close. Pull the teal brushed wool outer layer over an inky navy silk slip. Rely on cool metals to catch the dim illumination. Slip on a matt white gold ring or a bright platinum cuff. Ignore the reflection in the glass. Touch dictates the truth. Let the garments yield to your frame.",
      "sectionIntro": "Curate the garments you reach for when the lighting drops and distances close.",
      "tests": [
        "a school run or a corner shop dash does not require surrendering your softness (Cove)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Dress for the mundane errand exactly as you would for an appointment. A rainy dash to the corner shop does not demand surrendering your structure. Reach for an inky navy wool overshirt and heavy silk trousers. Check your reflection to confirm your base remains correct. Keep your cool palette consistent. Your rule remains unchanged for every context. You must always deploy clean geometry + blurred edges + one polished signal. Fasten a heavy silver watch over a thick sleeve. The supermarket queue requires the same exacting standards as a private desk.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply your standard to the mundane requirements of an average Tuesday.",
      "tests": [
        "a school run or a corner shop dash does not require surrendering your softness (Cove)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your hardware strategy demands a decisively cool foundation. Ground your choices in {metal_1} and {metal_2}. Before you commit to any piece, lift the item from the counter. Let the metal rest heavily in your palm. Polish tricks the eye, but sheer mass reveals true quality. Drop hollow hardware immediately. High-glare pieces disrupt the quiet surface of full-grain leather. A brilliantly polished {metal_3} clasp cuts aggressively against your cool wardrobe colours. Bypass that jarring contrast entirely. Reject any {excluded_finish} treatments and insist on matt or brushed textures to force visual cohesion. This deliberate restraint allows your hardware to maintain strict clean geometry while respecting the blurred edges of your garments.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your wardrobe with hardware that aligns with your precise physical requirements.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select {stone_1} and {stone_2} to anchor your jewellery. When examining a new piece, lift it from the counter. Ignore the bright display lights. Physical gravity tells the truth. A proper gem sits heavily in the hand. Depend on that undeniable heft to verify quality. Maintain clean geometry in the shape of the cut. Beware of gleaming surfaces. Highly reflective silver accents shatter the quiet focus of your muted, cool colours. Fix this glaring issue by insisting on brushed or matt settings, keeping the complete look perfectly cohesive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every stone and piece of hardware to strict physical tests before adding it to your rotation.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Assess the {metal_1} piece by taking it off the display tray and weighing it in your palm. A hollow item feels flimsy and compromises your foundation. Rely on gravitational pull to confirm the integrity of the object. Next, examine the surface. A mirror finish creates an unwanted distraction against a cool wardrobe. Shiny chrome destroys the quiet mood of your garments. Demand matt or brushed textures instead. A muted surface finish keeps the attire unified and protects your blurred edges. Choose austere, solid shapes to enforce clean geometry. Let a dense {stone_1} draw the eye rather than relying on glaring metal.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test your hardware with gravity and evaluate its surface.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments establish the clean geometry and construct the blurred edges. Your accessories step in to provide the one polished signal. Adopt a strict limit of one or two strong pieces per look. Handbags lead this approach. Look for full-grain leather bags with a completely matt body, punctuated by a single gleaming clasp. Evaluate every item using the keepsake test. Pick the object up and ask yourself if it feels substantial enough to leave behind in a wooden box for the next generation, or if it feels like a flimsy seasonal trend. Trust your physical instincts as your ultimate compass. A photograph cannot convey actual density. If the leather lacks a cool, heavy gravity in your palm, leave it on the shelf.",
      "sectionIntro": "Deploy your accessories with strict control to anchor your quiet wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Handbags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather, matt body with one polished clasp"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the keepsake test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Turn to scarves to manipulate the line of your neck and shoulders. Select heavy silk with a strict matt finish. Avoid high-shine satin that reflects light cheaply. Apply the same generational test before purchasing. Close your eyes and run the fabric through your fingers. If it feels flimsy, drop it immediately. The piece must feel dense enough to fold into a cedar box for decades. Trust your hands to evaluate this permanence. The camera lies, but true thickness cannot be faked. Fold a cool grey silk scarf flat to establish clean geometry against a stiff lapel. Let the lower ends drape heavily over your collarbone to introduce blurred edges.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use textile accessories to actively dictate the final structure of your silhouette.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "silk, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the keepsake test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Maintain clean geometry across your waistline. Fasten a full-grain leather belt secured by a cool, brushed buckle. For lasting jewellery, seek out pieces demonstrating mixed patina and polish. Pick up an aged brass ring featuring a solitary polished gold accent. Feel its density in your palm. Subject it to your strict standards of permanence before moving on. Weigh the item against your skin. Strip away anything that feels like fragile decoration. If it fails to anchor your cool palette with undeniable physical weight, leave it behind.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your remaining functional hardware and private tokens.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Keepsake jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "aged brass with a polished gold accent, mixed patina and polish"
        },
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather, brushed buckle"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the keepsake test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor the clean geometry of your tailored pieces with {recommended_pattern_1}. Let your fluid garments handle a different weight, allowing silk and fine wool to carry {recommended_pattern_2}. Keep all pattern contrast low and tonal. A cool palette requires strict restraint, meaning the motif must barely register from a distance. Employ the lamplight test to verify this. Examine the piece under dim evening illumination. The print must dissolve entirely, melting into a soft texture rather than holding a rigid shape. Look for blurred edges in your subtle woven fabrics to maintain a strictly self-contained appearance. Pass over stark, graphic prints completely. Reject {avoid_pattern_1} without hesitation. Leave {avoid_pattern_2} on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your rules for prints and weaves, ensuring every motif serves the structure of the garment.",
      "tests": [
        "the lamplight test (melt into a soft texture)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Apply the shadow test. Hang your {recommended_pattern_1} across the room in low evening light. Step back. Look for blurred edges where the motif meets the background fabric. If the print remains rigidly sharp, leave the piece on the rack. It must dissolve into a dense, cool shadow in the dimness. This guarantees your aesthetic remains entirely self-contained. Let your tailoring provide the crisp shapes. Let the fabric surface melt away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every patterned garment to a strict visual distance test before you buy it.",
      "tests": [
        "the lamplight test (melt into a soft texture)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_aquarius__moon_libra__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean geometry + cool composure + one polished signal",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on clean geometry + cool composure + one polished signal.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your sensory compass relies on absolute structural balance. Trust your hands to find garments that feel precisely calibrated in their weight and drape. If a piece feels excessively flimsy or restrictively rigid, leave it on the rack immediately. Your foundational logic is clean geometry + cool composure + one polished signal. Picture a crisp woven shirt tucked into sharply cut trousers, finished with a single high-shine watch. Every element carries its own weight without overwhelming the whole. Build your collection methodically, but adapt your daily combinations fast to meet the environment.\n\nYour daily adaptability requires impeccable garments to function properly across different contexts. Always apply the seam test before you commit to any new acquisition. Turn the piece inside out and drag your thumbnail straight down the longest internal seam. If the stitching wavers or the fabric puckers under the pressure, leave the item in the changing room. A poorly executed joint destroys the tension of the entire garment. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Construction does not.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is the structural logic that governs every piece you allow into your wardrobe.",
