      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your fabrics must build clean geometry without fighting your physical instincts. Look for {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Choose {texture_good_2} for close base layers that keep sharp lines but allow easy movement. When selecting trousers, trust {texture_good_3} to drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little, serving as your one polished signal. Always apply the bounce test in the shop. Squeeze a corner of the material and release it. If wrinkles stay locked into the surface, leave the garment on the rail. Your materials must recover instantly to maintain cool composure. Hunt for these textures first.",
      "sectionIntro": "Touch is your first physical filter for function and form.",
