    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Certain textiles actively sabotage your lines. Grab a sleeve of {texture_bad_1} and twist it. Release the cloth to check its resilience. If the fibres hold those stubborn creases instead of snapping back to clean geometry, leave the piece on the hanger. Sluggish fabrics drag you down. Run your bare palm over {texture_bad_2}. If the surface feels erratic or catches on your cuticles, it fails your standard. Trust your touch over your eyes. Weight and friction reveal the truth. Avoid {texture_bad_3} when it clings rather than dropping cleanly. You require materials that hold their own shape to maintain a cool presence.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify failing materials before they touch your skin.",
