        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your entire selection operates on a strictly cool temperature. Build your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Select {core_colour_3} as your white substitute neutral. Anchor these lighter layers with {core_colour_4} to establish clean geometry. When an outfit feels too stark, integrate a soft note used sparingly to temper the contrast. Pass over Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green entirely. Introduce {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent against the base neutrals. Watch out for the beige-out trap. Wearing every piece at the same pale value looks unfinished rather than minimal. Rescue it with a {core_colour_4} anchor piece or a {accent_colour_1} accent, and let one change in weave restore the depth. Trust this tactile instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
