    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Cool composure takes the lead in close quarters. Drop excess fabric and demand strict margins. Pick up a stark navy fine ribbed merino and pinch the ribbing. Avoid anything draped or slouchy. Even a quiet morning coffee requires a sharp outline. Check the collar of an icy grey cotton poplin shirt. Ensure it stands crisp against your neck rather than collapsing. Cool metal provides a crisp edge when shadows deepen. Fasten a steel watch or a rigid silver cuff to your wrist. Rely on pure contrast and clean geometry to define your shape.",
