    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat every mundane errand as a strict styling drill. A quick trip to the pharmacy still deserves a deliberate outline. When picking up a prescription, maintain your baseline. Require crisp cotton poplin or worsted wool even on a rainy Tuesday morning. Keep the cool temperature intact with icy grey outerwear. Your core logic remains clean geometry + cool composure + one polished signal. Do not let fatigue dictate your trousers. Select stiff technical nylon over soft jersey. Let the raw weight of the cloth guide your morning choices.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce your standard across every mundane errand.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your hardware strategy is exclusively cool and strictly consistent. Anchor your entire collection around {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. A flawless, reflective surface provides the essential spark against your worsted wool or technical nylon foundations. Maintain this clean geometry by rejecting artificially aged surfaces. Hammered copper, antiqued brass, and any faux-vintage patina read as pure clutter next to sharp tailoring. Keep every zip and buckle rendered in a high-shine, mirror-like finish instead. Reject any item featuring a {excluded_finish} or matt treatment. Before accepting a new belt into your collection, lift the piece to gauge its density. Heaviness confirms the quality. Solid metal drags the hand downwards.",
