    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Your stones must offer absolute clarity and structural density. Whether you select {stone_1} or {stone_2}, examine how the facets refract light. Lift the object. Sheer physical mass proves its worth. Rely on that tactile gravity as your true measure of quality. The metal setting requires equal strictness. Avoid artificially tarnished alloys, beaten copper, and any hardware imitating age. Such cluttered surfaces disrupt a present-tense collection. Instead, lock your stones into highly reflective silver, pristine white gold, or cool mirror chrome to project clean geometry.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your accessories by demanding density, precise clarity, and uncompromising metal settings.",
      "tests": [
