    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories provide your finishing touch. After you establish clean geometry and secure your cool composure, deploy exactly one polished signal. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with silk scarves. Look for a dense silk band that provides a soft glow at the collar or cuff. Evaluate every addition for true physical function before you wear it. Fasten the knot, turn your head, and pay attention to how the fabric behaves. Rely on your own physical instinct here. A slipping tie exposes weak friction. If the item demands constant readjustment, leave it on the shelf. A capable addition stays exactly where you put it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select and test the final details that complete your look without causing physical distractions.",
      "rankedItems": [
