    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Let tailored garments pull their structure from {recommended_pattern_1}. Allow fluid pieces to carry the exact lines of {recommended_pattern_2}. Because your collection must adapt across shifting contexts, employ a flexible approach to pattern contrast. Scale from strictly cool tonal weaves up to sharper graphic edges as the situation dictates. Select prints that reinforce clean geometry rather than breaking it. Put new items through the desk test. Place the garment three feet away from your workspace. If the print reads as a crisp, legible texture from that distance, keep it. If it dissolves into a muddy blur, reject it. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your visual depth by treating patterns as architectural tools rather than mere decoration.",
