      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Hang the piece over a chair back and step away to assess the surface. At this precise distance, a proper {recommended_pattern_1} must lose its internal lines and blur into a unified, matt texture. This optical shift is how you preserve clean geometry across your outfits. If the motif still demands attention from across the room, it shatters that necessary cool composure. Put the item back on the rail. The print must function as a quiet surface block from a distance and only reveal its strict details upon close inspection.",
      "sectionIntro": "Execute the desk test to establish strict physical boundaries for every printed garment.",
