  "venus_aquarius__moon_sagittarius__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean geometry + fast movement + one polished signal",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on clean geometry + fast movement + one polished signal.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical snap of a garment in your hands. If the cloth feels dead or drags against your skin, drop it. Your wardrobe operates on a precise baseline of cool, balanced efficiency. Every outfit you construct must rely on this exact equation: clean geometry + fast movement + one polished signal. Picture a razor-cut wool blazer worn open over a lightweight silk shell and heavy crepe trousers. The tailoring provides the structure. The silk gives you immediate mobility. A single light-catching lapel detail delivers the finish. This is your baseline. Look for garments that feel simultaneously sharp and weightless.\n\nBuild your wardrobe as a modular grid, shifting your silhouette based on the specific demands of your day. To maintain this flexibility, subject every new garment to a rigorous combination test. Before you buy a piece, mentally force it against three distinctly different items you already own. Pair a strict tailored jacket with fluid wide trousers, a rigid woven shirt, and a dense knit sweater. If the new item requires an entirely new supporting cast to function, leave it on the hanger. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. The item must adapt instantly to your established structure. If it hesitates, it fails.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact equation that governs your wardrobe and the physical tests required to enforce it.",
      "tests": [
        "the combination test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "To build clean geometry, your materials must hold a sharp boundary. Start with {texture_good_1} for shirting that creates pure separation between layers. Anchor these top layers with {texture_good_2} to maintain strict lines against the body while allowing fast movement. For trousers, seek out {texture_good_3}. This material drapes cleanly and resists creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} for mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs nothing. Always run the tension check before you buy. Pull a small section of the fabric tight and release it. The material must rebound instantly to its original shape. If the fabric bags or slumps, leave it on the rail. Let the structural memory of the textile secure your one polished signal.",
      "sectionIntro": "Trust your hands to identify the materials that actively construct your silhouette.",
