    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pick up a piece of {texture_bad_1} and stretch it slightly. Observe the recovery. If the textile slumps back into place instead of springing to attention, leave it on the rack. Your wardrobe requires clean geometry. Fabrics that pool or pill fail this requirement. Run your fingers over {texture_bad_2}. If the surface catches on your bare hands or feels muddy to the touch, it will disrupt your visual clarity. Rely on your fingertips to detect these flaws. When a garment lacks internal structure or tension, it cannot support your pace. Avoid anything that feels lifeless in your grip.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the textiles that compromise your framework before they leave the hanger.",
      "tests": [
        "the snap test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Pair {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build your base. Gauge the resistance in your hands. Pinch the edge of a {texture_good_1} cuff and pull. Let go. Listen for the sharp snap. That rapid return proves the fabric has the structural memory to sustain clean geometry. Avoid limp knits that collapse into folds. You need architectural strength to keep the shape strict. Anchor the look with cool metals and matt surfaces. Let the tight weave do the work.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your baseline texture pairings by testing the structural tension of the cloth.",
      "tests": [
        "the snap test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your correct temperature is strictly cool. Build a base with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}, treating {core_colour_3} as your white substitute and {core_colour_4} as a structural dark foundation. Trust your eyes on the rack. If a hue lacks bite, drop it. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent to inject fast movement. Apply your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to break up heavy shades. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green completely. Watch out for the trap of a lifeless solid block of dark dye that leaves you restless by noon. Correct this dullness with a rigid white cotton collar, a sterling silver structural ring, or a vivid athletic runner. These sharp additions enforce clean geometry and restore your visual speed.",
