      "text": "Keep patterns strictly functional. Tailored items take structural weaves like {recommended_pattern_1}. Fluid layers demand precise rhythmic repeats like {recommended_pattern_2}. Adjust pattern contrast to your environment. Build tonal combinations for a quiet baseline, or switch to sharp graphic contrast when the setting requires a harder edge. Test every garment from a distance. If the motif looks muddy or confusing in that first split second, drop the hanger. Rely on strict clean geometry to guide your eye. Evaluate the physical reaction of the cloth itself. The mirror gets tricked by clever design, but your hands immediately detect a sluggish drape. Discard anything that lacks fast movement. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}. Ensure cool temperatures remain dominant across all printed fabrics.",
