    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on clean geometry + honest fabric + one polished signal.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical sensation of precision and temperature. Look for sharp architectural edges and fabrics that feel cool to the touch. Run your hands over the garments before you put them on. If a material drags, stretches unpredictably, or clings, drop it. Your wardrobe must function as a self-contained system that adapts to external shifts. Build this modular foundation slowly. Deploy the pieces fast when circumstances change. You are dressing to operate on your own terms in any environment. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Structure and friction do not.\n\nYour exact operating code is clean geometry + honest fabric + one polished signal. Picture a sharply cut structural trouser worn with a stiff woven shirt, anchored by a single piece of reflective hardware at the wrist. The lines are absolute. The materials refuse to distort. The final detail catches the light. Before you step outside, apply the treaty test. Ask yourself if the garments negotiate the physical demands of the day without surrendering your personal boundaries. If the clothes force you to adjust your posture to suit the room, they fail. Take them off.",
