      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} entirely. Run your thumb across the surface. If it feels dusty, limp, or catches rough against the skin, drop it. A polished finish requires materials that hold sharp edges. Execute the corner check on {texture_bad_2}. Hold the piece in a dimly lit space. If it swallows the light and turns into a muddy void rather than retaining a warm, defined boundary, it fails. Test the resistance on a flat table. If {texture_bad_3} puddles into a formless heap instead of holding a crisp fold, walk away. Grip the cloth tightly. Visuals can be faked. Tactile tension gives you the absolute fact.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject failing materials before they touch your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot relies on a deliberate collision between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Layer a crisp shirt in {texture_good_1} over something slick and highly reflective. To check if a piece belongs on your body, lift the cloth to a bright window. Look at the stark outline it casts against the glass. If the boundaries diffuse or the cloth collapses inward, it fails. You need absolute containment. Combine these dense, warm surfaces to guarantee sharp edges. Touch every item before you hand over your card. If it feels flimsy or matt, put it straight back on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your signature surface pairings to build firm visual boundaries.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your spectrum runs strictly warm. Build your foundation directly on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} to anchor your choices. Use {core_colour_3} as your strict white alternative. Bridge these deep tones with {core_colour_4}. Treat your relief tone exclusively as a soft note used sparingly to break up visual weight. Introduce sharp edges through a precise application of {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Reject muddy pastel, icy grey, and dusty sage immediately. They wash you out. Beware the costume trap. Piling on rigid leather, heavy studs, severe lip paint, and dramatic eye makeup at the same time turns aggressive into theatrical. Stop this slide instantly. Isolate a single flash of molten heat, then push every remaining detail into flat, matt black.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your baseline by keeping strict limits on the tones you allow in.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Deep bronze",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Golden camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
