          "failure": "costume: leather, studs, red lip, gold hardware and a smoky eye all at once tips drama into fancy dress",
          "fix": "hold the line at one molten flash and return every other element to matt black"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let sharp edges lead your office choices. Support those strict borders with a single hot focal point and a clean, unyielding structure. A deep bronze collar pin piercing crisp cotton poplin delivers focused, warm heat. Apply the pharmacy test to every tailored piece. If a rigid blazer forces you to suffer while waiting for a prescription, discard it immediately. Establishing bold, polished boundaries does not demand physical pain. Look for construction that delivers severe geometry while leaving your body entirely unimpeded.",
      "sectionIntro": "Define your weekday parameters with strict intent and absolute physical freedom.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim settings, let clean impact lead. Dark rooms devour detail. Rely on heavy silk satin in deep bronze to catch ambient illumination. Maintain your sharp edges with a tailored wool twill coat. A warm palette ensures your garments read clearly even when visibility drops. Force your metallic elements to clash deliberately. Pair a heavy gold cuff with bright silver rings to capture the candlelight. Apply the midnight cab standard to your evening clothes. Standing on the pavement in the rain waiting for a taxi must not require enduring a pinching waistline or restrictive sleeves. If your patent leather boots cause agony by the time the car arrives, leave them in the box. Garments must support your frame without inflicting distress.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the mechanics of dressing for close quarters and low lighting.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Demand absolute consistency from your morning choices. A routine run to the post office to drop off parcels should never require pinched toes or restrictive waistbands. Let your skin evaluate the garments. The mirror flatters falsely. The physical restriction of your stride delivers the absolute reality. If the fabric catches or binds, discard it. Build the foundation with crisp cotton poplin and sharp wool twill. These materials move with you. Your daytime decisions must strictly follow your equation. Maintain clean impact + sharp edges + one hot accent. Wear a matt golden camel coat and finish the look with patent leather boots. Mix your metals deliberately. Pair a chunky silver ring with a warm gold collar necklace over a deep bronze silk shirt. If a piece feels limp or dull, leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Run your standard routine through a rigid filter of absolute visual consistency.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Divide your hardware into two absolute zones. For jewellery sitting directly against the skin, demand {personal_metal_1} or {personal_metal_2}. For the structural elements, the belt buckles and heavy zips, deploy {structural_metal_1} or {structural_metal_2}. A beaten, blackened, or artificially aged {excluded_finish} surface reads as fatigued and blurs your visual focus. Exclude these textures completely. Insist on a high-shine warm execution that reflects the sun from the opposite pavement. This gleaming precision perfectly upholds the sharp edges of your garments. When assessing a thick {personal_metal_1} collar, lift it off the velvet tray before inspecting the clasp. Retail presentation creates illusions. Pure mass gives you the exact truth. If the piece lacks profound physical density, drop it and walk away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control the exact structural parameters for every buckle, zip, and ring.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Lift the piece off the glass counter to check its density. Halogen bulbs manipulate depth. The brutal drag of an object against your palm confirms its value. A genuine {stone_2} resting in your hand drops with undeniable heaviness. Demand this density. Choose unyielding cuts with sharp edges that maintain their strict borders. Steer clear of beaten, tarnished, or artificially aged settings. These clouded textures ruin the architecture and look completely exhausted. Require a mirror-like, gleaming warm metal base that flashes from fifty paces away. A heavy {stone_1} relies on uncompromised boundaries to perform. If the jewellery feels hollow or the setting diffuses the glare, leave it on the tray.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate stones and their settings by testing their undeniable density and demanding an absolute, gleaming boundary.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Pick up every {metal_1} cuff or {stone_1} ring and judge its heft in your palm. Rely entirely on this visceral bodily response to assess quality. Polish can be faked. True heft cannot. If a piece feels light or hollow, leave it on the tray. You require dense, solid hardware to deliver clean impact. Reject any metal that is blackened, beaten, or scuffed. These degraded textures look fatigued and destroy the severe precision of your look. Instead, seek an immaculate, liquid-smooth shine. Commit strictly to high-gloss, warm metal buffed to a mirror gleam that throws a hard reflection from a distance. That brilliant exactness maintains your sharp edges.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every piece of hardware by its sheer physical density before allowing it into your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Execute the final stage of your wardrobe strategy. You have built a foundation of clean impact. You have framed the silhouette with sharp edges. Now, deliver one hot accent. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Clutter destroys intent. Begin with statement jewellery. Look for a high-polish yellow gold cuff. Subject every addition to the single bulb test. Stand in a completely unlit space and flick on one overhead light. If the metal does not throw a brilliant, warm flash out of the darkness, discard it immediately. Your tactile intuition operates as your compass. Surfaces create illusions. Density guarantees quality. Lift the metal to confirm its solid structure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Command your finishing hardware to lock your aesthetic into place.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Statement jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "high-polish yellow gold cuff, high polish"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select footwear cut from high gloss patent leather. Treat this polished finish as your guaranteed method to deliver one hot accent at the base of your silhouette. Look for reflective surfaces catching warm light. Run the sensory deprivation check to verify the material. Close your eyes and trace your hands over the shoe. You must feel a slick, impenetrable barrier that terminates at a severe point. If the surface drags, catches, or yields under your thumb, put the object down. You require rigid structure and uncompromising gloss. A pointed golden camel pump or an architectural mahogany loafer provides exactly this necessary voltage.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your footwear as the rigid foundation of your entire aesthetic geometry.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "patent leather, high gloss"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Look for structured bags that carry physical weight. Choose a warm golden camel patent leather top-handle design finished with highly polished hardware. These rigid, reflective surfaces provide one hot accent against a heavy silk satin coat. Trust your grip when you test the bag. If the frame collapses, leave it behind. A successful structured bag delivers clean impact and unyielding borders. Finish by stepping into a shaded corridor. Look at your reflection in the darkened glass. If your silhouette blurs into the background, the geometry is too weak. Your sharp edges must remain entirely legible, even in heavy shadow.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess your final geometry before you step out the door.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Structured bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "patent leather top-handle, polished hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored garments pull their pattern from rigid, structural geometry. Fluid pieces take theirs from precise, high-definition repetition. Insist on strict, high-contrast graphic separation between warm hues in every print you test. Subject the garment to the distance check. If a motif loses its defined borders and blurs into a single mass from ten paces away in a dim room, it fails. Trust your physical reaction to a pattern's visual density. Showroom lights flatter. Stark structural clarity provides the unvarnished reality. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} to secure this separation. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. Deploy a decisive print as your one hot accent against solid blocks of colour.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as a strict architectural tool, not a decorative afterthought.",
      "tests": [
        "the low-light rule (must still read as intent from ten feet in dim light)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Walk to the far end of the hallway and study your {recommended_pattern_1} under ambient lighting. If the shapes blur into confusion, leave it on the rack. The design must maintain sharp edges even in shadow. You need distinct, warm geometry that reads as deliberate intent from a distance. Test the contrast by squinting at the garment. It must preserve one hot accent jumping out from the background, rather than dissolving into a soft wash. Demand absolute visual clarity before you buy.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every print to a strict legibility test before you commit.",
      "tests": [
        "the low-light rule (must still read as intent from ten feet in dim light)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_aries__moon_aquarius__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean impact + mobile layers + one hot accent",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on clean impact + mobile layers + one hot accent.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Ground your choices in physical mobility and temperature. Trust the weight of the fabric in your hands as your ultimate physical compass. If a garment feels rigid or fights your movement, drop it immediately. Seek out warm tones and polished finishes that adapt to your body in motion. Your governing structure is clean impact + mobile layers + one hot accent. Picture a crisp, precision-cut base layer topped with a fluid overcoat that shifts as you walk, anchored by a single intense accessory catching the light near your face. This creates a balanced silhouette that responds to your environment without overpowering it.\n\nBuild your collection slowly, deploy your layers fast, and drift your styling by mood. Your garments must serve as a highly functional toolkit. When assessing any new item, apply the seam test. Run your thumb over the internal joins at the shoulder and armhole. If those stitches feel thick against your skin or pull when you reach forward, leave the piece on the hanger. The internal architecture must sit completely flat and support absolute freedom of movement. Demand flawless interior construction. Let the physical reality of the structure dictate your final decision.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your foundational operating system, designed to anchor your physical instincts.",
      "tests": [
        "the seam test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your mobile layers on a foundation of polished, warm materials. Look for {texture_good_1} when selecting shirting that requires clean architectural boundaries. For close-to-body base layers, choose {texture_good_2} to maintain sharp lines and easy movement. Anchor your lower half with {texture_good_3} trousers that drape perfectly and resist creasing through a long day. Top this off with {texture_good_4} for lightweight outerwear that blocks wind without adding bulk. Always apply the recovery test before buying. Crush the sleeve tightly in your fist for five seconds and release. If the fabric fails to spring back to deliver clean impact, return it to the rail. You need textiles that bounce back instantly. Focus entirely on this ranked list.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select materials that perform under pressure and demand zero maintenance.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Worsted wool",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day"
        },
        {
          "name": "Technical nylon",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little"
        },
        {
          "name": "Lightweight gabardine",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "transitional jackets with rigid structure and no heavy drag"
        },
        {
          "name": "Matt silk",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "a frictionless fluid layer added without bulk"
        },
        {
          "name": "Crisp linen",
