          "useCase": "breathable separation over fluid drapes in warmer weather"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Scrunch the material to check its resilience. If the fibres stay flat and creased when you open your palm, the piece fails. Your wardrobe relies on textiles that hold their shape, building a crisp base to support one hot accent. Reject {texture_bad_2} entirely. It feels clammy against the skin and traps warm air, ruining the geometry of your silhouette. Drag your knuckles across the surface. If the weave catches, clings, or feels hollow, leave it on the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to quickly identify and reject textiles that fight your silhouette.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your optimum material combination anchors {sweet_spot_keyword_1} next to {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing guarantees clean impact. Build a warm base using {texture_good_1} and always check the spring of the yarn. Fold a section of the leg and press hard. Let it drop open. If the folds stay behind, walk away. You need materials that snap back to shape immediately. Measure longevity by snap and resilience.",
      "sectionIntro": "Nail your sweet spot by contrasting two distinct material weights.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette relies on a warm undertone. Construct your mobile layers using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} as your primary base, introducing {core_colour_3} as your sharpest neutral option. Ground these elements with a {core_colour_4} bridge piece. Focus the eye with {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate burst of heat. Deploy your relief tone sparingly, dropping it in only when the visual needs a soft pause. Pass over icy pastel, neon brights, and cold blue-grey. Watch out for the beige-out. When every garment shares an identical pale wash, the result reads as lacking intent rather than achieving minimalism. Rescue this flat look by dropping in a {core_colour_4} anchor piece or injecting a {accent_colour_1} focal point, then allow a structural shift like crisp cotton poplin to bring back the depth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your foundation with deliberate tones, and train your eye to reject the wrong temperature.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Warm taupe",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
