    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let sharp edges lead your weekday decisions. Build your foundation with strict tailoring in deep bronze wool twill. Support these precise borders with an uncluttered silhouette to ensure clean impact. Introduce one hot accent through a heavy silk satin blouse in a vivid warm hue. Test the internal canvassing of any prospective jacket. Squeeze the lapel tightly. If the structure collapses under pressure, return the item to the rail. True structural integrity never caves. Maintain these rigid standards regardless of specialist care requirements. A weekly trip to the dry cleaner for a golden camel blazer represents the basic cost of enforcing your baseline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply your exact standards to the workplace without compromising your baseline.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In intimate evening settings, clean impact must dominate. Dim lighting blurs fine details, requiring severe structure to anchor your silhouette. Select a deep bronze heavy silk satin jacket and inspect the seams. The fabric must hold absolute geometry. If the shoulders droop or the cuffs lack stiffness, discard the garment. Collecting formalwear from the dry cleaner does not grant permission to tolerate a crushed lapel or a limp hem. Demand strict edges at all hours. Anchor golden camel wool twill trousers with high-gloss patent leather boots to provide one hot accent. Layer thick gold chains alongside heavy platinum jewellery. Gauge the dual register metals in your palm to confirm their heavy density. Keep the palette intensely warm and the construction ruthless.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat low lighting as a magnifying glass for your silhouettes, not a hiding place.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A wet Tuesday morning trip to the post office does not excuse a collapsed silhouette. Your daily standard demands discipline. Your core rule is clean impact + sharp edges + one hot accent. Enforce this mandate through bodily intuition. A shop mirror flatters falsely, but the rigid weight of crisp cotton poplin pressing against your collarbone tells the truth. Keep your textiles strictly warm. Build your morning foundation in golden camel or deep bronze wool twill. Demand a polished finish rather than a matt surface. Step into a stiff patent leather boot. Anchor the outfit with a thick, dual register chain of bright yellow gold and white platinum. Your wardrobe serves you alone, creating a fully self-contained system.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the baseline of your wardrobe by treating ordinary errands as strict testing grounds.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Divide your hardware into two distinct operations. Wear {personal_metal_1} or {personal_metal_2} directly against your skin as a primary layer. Keep your structural elements strictly separate to maintain clean impact. Secure your bags, belts, and heavy zips with {structural_metal_1} or {structural_metal_2} to reinforce your sharp edges. Reject the {excluded_finish} lane entirely. Hammered or oxidised surfaces look dull and compromise precise boundaries. Require a gleaming, warm finish that flashes brightly from fifty paces away. Assess every buckle and clasp manually before purchasing. A hollow metal shell betrays the look. If the hardware lacks serious gravitational pull, leave it in the display case.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as the final lock on your boundary.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
