    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Scrutinise the physical presence of {metal_1} or {stone_1} before handing over your card. Pick the item up and close your eyes. If a cuff feels delicate or a pendant lacks cold, heavy density, drop it on the glass and walk away. You require solid mass to construct a self-contained armour. Inspect the reflection next. Any texture that diffuses the room's lighting ruins your clean impact. Insist on a strictly polished, warm finish that operates like a mirror. High-gloss hardware is non-negotiable for maintaining sharp edges and locking in your one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate the weight and surface of your hardware to ensure it meets your standard for intensity.",
