    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Direct your attention to footwear. Look for patent leather that throws light back at the viewer. Insist on a high-gloss finish across every shoe and boot. This guarantees clean impact from the floor up. Hold the leather under a bright beam and examine the reflection. If the surface blurs the glare, discard the pair. You need a warm mirror finish that bounces a hard, blinding circle of illumination. Squeeze the toe box to gauge the internal reinforcement. The profile must maintain sharp edges rather than a rounded, soft front. Pair a deep bronze patent heel with a golden camel trouser, and let the extreme shine act as your one hot accent.",
