  "venus_aries__moon_cancer__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean impact + hidden depth + one hot accent",
    "closing": "Always trust the uncompromising weight and mirror-bright polish of your garments to direct you towards clean impact + hidden depth + one hot accent.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust your hands to find your baseline. Run your thumb across the surface of a garment. If it drags or absorbs the light, drop it. You require a warm, polished finish that holds a sharp edge. Build your wardrobe slowly, piece by rigorous piece, and deploy it fast. Your overarching strategy relies on clean impact + hidden depth + one hot accent. Picture this. You wear a sharply cut outer shell over an intricately woven inner layer, finished with a single brilliant accessory. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.\n\nEvery garment must justify its place on your frame. Apply the radius test. Stand perfectly still and assess the physical space you occupy. Your outline must establish a definite, uncompromising boundary. You are building a self-contained structure, avoiding anything that bleeds into the background. If a sleeve billows out of control or a hem softens your perimeter, it fails the test. You need garments that project bold authority on their own terms. Keep your edges sharp, your surfaces sleek, and your central focal point undeniably striking.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your foundational style mechanics and define the rigorous structural rules for your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the radius test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe requires clean impact. To achieve it, train your hands to seek fabrics that hold a sharp line and catch warm light. Run the bounce test on every garment. Crush the sleeve in your fist and release it. If the fabric stays crumpled, leave it on the rack. You need {texture_good_2} for knife-edge tailoring that springs back into shape and never begs for a steamer. Layer {texture_good_1} beneath it for shirting that holds a rigid crease. Build hidden depth with inner layers of {texture_good_4} that gleam heavily under low light. Finally, anchor the look with {texture_good_3} on your footwear, ensuring your accessories reflect maximum light. Prioritise these four foundational textures.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the precise materials that do the heavy lifting for your wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
