    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Your structure demands crisp edges and reflective polish, so eliminate {texture_bad_1}. If a piece feels limp against the skin, it will drag down your boldest cuts. Apply the tension test to everything you pick up. Squeeze a handful of {texture_bad_2}. If it stays flat instead of springing back, it lacks the architectural rigidity to frame one hot accent. Reject the dull surface of {texture_bad_3}. Run your thumb over the weave. A scratchy, matt finish absorbs the warm light you need to reflect. Drop the piece and move on.",
