    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your signature texture pairing requires {sweet_spot_keyword_1} laid directly over {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing builds your baseline of clean impact + hidden depth + one hot accent. The combination establishes a warm tension that forces your silhouette to stay self-contained. Check the structural integrity with your own hands. Gather the material in your grip and let go. The textile must snap open immediately. If it snaps back to a flawless line, wear it. If it sags or holds a permanent fold, reject it. You need textiles that build rigid, polished architecture. Incorporate {texture_good_1} to secure the final shape.",
      "sectionIntro": "Locate the precise combination of materials that gives your wardrobe its essential structure.",
      "tests": [
        "the bounce test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your colour palette demands a warm temperature. Build your foundation strictly with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Use {core_colour_3} for stark contrast and rely on {core_colour_4} to connect disparate layers. Achieve clean impact, hidden depth, and one hot accent by striking these heavy bases with a single bold flash of {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Deploy your soft relief tone sparingly to give the eye a brief rest. Bypass Muddy pastel, Icy grey, and Dusty sage entirely. They blur your sharp edges. Guard against the trap of swathing yourself in a suffocating dark block of fabric that erases your stark outlines. Fracture that dense column immediately by adding a thick polished gold cuff or a sharp vermilion shoe to snap the visual tension back into place.",
      "sectionIntro": "Take control of your colours using absolute discipline.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Deep bronze",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
