    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1} entirely. Trust your hands over the label. Run your fingers down a sleeve. If the surface catches your skin or feels squeaky, drop the garment immediately. You require a base of unbroken calm to support your one hot accent. {texture_bad_2} fails this test because it carries a rigid synthetic stiffness that refuses to drape. Leave {texture_bad_3} on the rail. Squeeze the hem tightly. If the material crushes into sharp creases that refuse to release, it cannot serve you. A warm, self-contained style requires elements that move with absolute silence. If a piece rustles, shines cheaply, or fights your movement, walk away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Reject inferior materials immediately by learning their tactile signals of failure.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your ideal tension lives right where {sweet_spot_keyword_1} collides with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Pair a dense {texture_good_1} base with a yielding layer. Test every new piece in the dark. Assess the drape without looking. If the surface feels thin or hollow against your palm, leave it on the rack. Rely strictly on tactile feedback before evaluating the colour. This strict material contrast creates clean impact without unnecessary noise. Keep the finishes strictly matt to capture warm light. Let these opposing forces do the heavy lifting.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact point where two opposing surfaces collide.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is warm. Anchor your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Introduce {core_colour_3} for structural weight, and rely on {core_colour_4} as your grounding earth tone. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly to provide visual breathing room. Execute your strategy of clean impact by assigning {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} to lead the look. Reject stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. Do not drown in unstructured, top-to-bottom black. Fracture those dark layers with a warm focal point, perhaps a beaten brass bangle or a horn hairpin. Rely on your immediate bodily response to a colour. Mirrors distort the truth, but your visceral reaction does not.",
