    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let hidden depth dictate your working hours. Ground your silhouette in a stark shell of bitter chocolate heavy silk crepe, then add a single spark of warm gold at the collar. Grasp the fabric in your fist. If the cloth stands away from your body in stiff folds, leave it on the hanger. A packed day does not call for rigid worsted armour. It requires pliant layers that can sprint. Rely on garments that yield, then bury a complex layer of dark mahogany washed silk completely out of sight.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply these specific boundaries to your working hours.",
