    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Low light changes how materials behave. In close settings, hidden depth takes the lead. An evening indoors demands fluid construction rather than hard tailoring. Opt for soft garments that breathe. Select a dark mahogany shirt in heavy silk crepe or a washed silk slip in bitter chocolate. These choices hold a warm tone and offer subtle variations in matt and polish. Pair them with yellow gold jewellery. A brushed gold cuff or a smooth amber ring provides sufficient illumination in dim rooms. Let your physical senses guide you. If a piece feels restrictive at the dinner table, leave it on the rack. The objective is total physical ease.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master low-light settings by prioritising physical ease over rigid structure.",
      "tests": [
