      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A punishing schedule asks for kinetic freedom. When the calendar piles up, reach for materials that move fast. Do not bind yourself in rigid tailoring. Choose cloud-soft lambswool or washed silk that yields as you stride across the city. Picking up a prescription from the local chemist does not give you permission to drop the standard. Maintain clean impact + hidden depth + one hot accent every time you dress. Pair a dark mahogany boiled wool jacket with a matt gold collar. Rely on the warm palette and the mobility of the cut to serve you from early morning errands to late afternoon appointments.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your daily schedule as a proving ground for your baseline standard.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Limit your jewellery to a warm spectrum of {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. A mirror-polish finish slices harshly across soft, muted tones. Keep the visual field cohesive by demanding matt and brushed textures instead. Because you are working within a unified temperature, you have complete freedom to mix a brushed {metal_1} buckle with a matt {metal_3} watch case. Evaluate every clasp and link by its literal heft. Pick the item up. Gleaming exteriors mislead, but pure mass proves its worth. Rely on this gravity to assess quality. This self-contained hardware approach ensures your styling delivers clean impact.",
      "sectionIntro": "Take command of your hardware by strictly controlling finish, temperature, and true mass.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
