    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Demand {stone_1} and {stone_2} for your jewellery. Pick the piece up before you put it on. Gauge the true value by holding the object. A dense stone grounds your silhouette. Stark, glossy settings cut too sharply against soft muted tones. Such high-shine finishes break cohesion and distract the eye. Stick strictly to brushed or matt textures to maintain a warm seamless quality. This restrained metal approach allows the density of the stone to take precedence. It creates clean impact through pure weight alone. Let the piece rest against your skin. Choose stones that hold their own physical space.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your stones and metals through physical mass and tactile restraint.",
      "tests": [
