    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories provide your one hot accent. Once you establish clean impact and weave in hidden depth through your garments, stop adding cloth. Turn to your hardware. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Apply the anchor test by lifting the object to judge its physical gravity. If the piece feels hollow, it fails. A true piece grounds the outfit by pulling the lighter layers into reality. Handbags require this dense weight. Demand full-grain leather with a completely matt body, interrupted by a solitary polished clasp. That single piece of warm metal sitting on a bitter chocolate flap brings all the necessary heat.",
      "sectionIntro": "Accessories act as your final punctuation, demanding strict editing and dense physical weight.",
