    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Scarves perform a specific duty. Source pure silk in a strict matt finish. Pick up the fabric. Assess the textile's inherent drag. If the material flutters like a flimsy decoration, drop it. The item must ground your warm palette in absolute certainty. Wrap a bitter chocolate length around your collar. It must guarantee clean impact. Examine the tight weave of the fibres. That dense construction supplies hidden depth. Find a solitary spun gold thread or a burnt ochre hem to serve as one hot accent. The silk must stay completely matt. Gloss catches unnecessary light and compromises the solidity of your profile. Rely entirely on the physical pull of the material.",
