    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Look at a patterned garment and divide your strategy. Demand {recommended_pattern_1} for tailored jackets or sharp trousers. Let your fluid, draped layers take their visual rhythm from {recommended_pattern_2}. To secure hidden depth, hold strictly to a low-contrast tonal rule. The colours within the print must sit closely together on the warm spectrum. Apply the twilight test. Dim the lights in the room and evaluate the fabric. The motif must recede and merge into a rich, deep texture. If the design fights for attention in low lighting, leave it on the hanger. Pass over stark borders, rigid graphic blocks, and {avoid_pattern_1}. These disrupt your self-contained frame. Trust a print only when it reads as a subtle vibration in the cloth.",
