        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the office, clean impact leads the composition. Build your foundation using crisp cotton poplin and worsted wool in warm taupe or camel. Introduce light movement strictly as a supporting player. A fine ribbed merino knit offers necessary flexibility without sacrificing shape. Complete the combination with one hot accent, using dual-register metals at the wrist. When evaluating these professional garments, check the construction. A superior lining responds smoothly as you slip it on. If the lapel feels insubstantial, pass it by. Your structural standards must hold firm through long hours. A late deadline does not justify a collapsed shoulder.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your working hours as a laboratory for precision.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light, rely on one hot accent to lead the eye. A camel worsted wool jacket absorbs dim room lighting, so you must anchor the look with a polished gold cuff or a warm ruby pendant. Feel the heavy chill of the hardware against your skin. Close proximity requires tactile precision. Pinch the hem of a fine ribbed merino sweater to test its gauge. If the yarn yields too easily, move on. Evening settings demand a defined silhouette, so never let loose garments obscure your frame. Maintain your underlying structure with crisp cotton poplin shirting cut close to the body.",
      "sectionIntro": "Navigate low light and close proximity by letting texture dictate your choices.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A late-night trip to the petrol station for milk demands exactly the same precise silhouette as a scheduled appointment. Never drop your standards for mundane errands. Build your off-duty foundation on camel or warm taupe. Select a casual jacket and study its natural hang. Rely on your own body to feel the difference between proper drape and cheap stiffness. Cloth that restricts your stride belongs in the bin. Apply your dressing rule consistently across every hour of the day. You must achieve clean impact + light movement + one hot accent. Ground the shape in technical nylon or a simple cotton poplin shirt. Ensure the collar sits flat, secure a dual-register watch, and proceed.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your morning routine as a strict mechanical check of every layer before you step outside the door.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Operate on a dual register. Restrict structural hardware on zips and buckles to {structural_metal_1} and {structural_metal_2}. Confine personal jewellery worn against the skin to {personal_metal_1} and {personal_metal_2}. This strict division guarantees clean impact. Always insist on a warm, highly polished finish. Artificially aged surfaces and hammered textures create visual clutter against your crisp clothing. Keep exclusively to highly reflective {structural_metal_1} and mirror-finish {personal_metal_1}, rejecting any matt or {excluded_finish} pieces outright. Test every buckle and chain manually. Assess the weight. Shiny coatings frequently mask cheap alloys. The physical heft in your hand provides the honest measure. The item must possess genuine mass to ground any light movement in your outfit. This creates a solid baseline before you introduce one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Govern your metals with strict boundary lines to build a flawless foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Integrate {stone_1} and {stone_2} to secure one hot accent against warm fabrics. Seek out stones with high clarity and crisp facets. Examine the mounting closely before you acquire it. A poorly constructed gallery betrays itself in the hand. Let your fingers trace the prongs to confirm their structural integrity. Avoid any settings that incorporate deliberate oxidation or rustic texturing. Such rough elements register as visual noise. Rely exclusively on flawlessly smooth, highly reflective constructions to deliver a sharp finish.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select stones and settings that act as precise tools for capturing light.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Assess the hardware by its physical resistance. Flimsy clasps ruin a silhouette, while substantial components ground your clothing. Shun deliberately scuffed surfaces and unrefined texturing. They introduce unnecessary friction. Choose a warm, completely polished finish in {metal_1} instead. A dense, brilliant {metal_1} chain or a substantial {stone_1} ring provides exactly one hot accent without overwhelming the overall composition. Let the flawless, reflective surface do the work. Rely on the uncompromising solidity of the piece.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every piece of hardware before it touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
