    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, your core formula dictates your foundation: clean impact + athletic space + one hot accent. Construct your strict silhouette using sharp wool twill and crisp cotton poplin to set a rigid outer shell. Keep the garments loose enough to permit unhindered movement. You must remain self-contained. Finish the arrangement with a warm, polished metal watch to break the uniformity. A mundane commute or a long morning in the boardroom does not require surrendering your bold expression. Avoid soft knits that compromise your edges. Choose heavy silk satin blouses or stiff patent leather shoes to maintain your boundary. Your workplace attire must remain uncompromising.",
      "sectionIntro": "Deploy your strict personal baseline in a professional environment without diluting your edge.",
      "tests": [
        "a school run or a corner shop dash does not require surrendering your softness (Cove)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, apply your exact equation: clean impact + athletic space + one hot accent. Keep your layers stark. A heavy silk satin slip dress in deep bronze provides the foundation and the breathing room. Add thick gold cuffs to bring warm metal into the frame as the final focal point. Do not dilute your edges for intimacy. Even a late dinner requires architectural precision. Layer crisp cotton poplin under a matt camel coat. Select a saturated ruby ring to catch the candlelight. Grasp the density of the cloth before you buy. Rely entirely on the physical heft of the material. Flimsy fabrics fail when the lights drop.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master close-quarters dressing by controlling exactly how your garments behave in low light.",
      "tests": [
        "a school run or a corner shop dash does not require surrendering your softness (Cove)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A Tuesday morning grocery run does not mean surrendering your high-gloss armour. Do not reach for a worn grey sweatshirt. Anchor your daily errands in an oversized leather bomber jacket layered over rigid cotton trousers. Step into a rich oxblood patent leather boot. Maintain a strict, self-contained boundary between you and the pavement. Your standard always requires clean impact + athletic space + one hot accent. Keep your metal hardware warm and highly reflective. Look for a shining gold bag clasp or a bright brass belt buckle. Pin a vivid fire opal to your lapel before leaving the house.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply your standard rigorously, refusing to dilute your polished finish for mundane tasks.",
      "tests": [
        "a school run or a corner shop dash does not require surrendering your softness (Cove)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your strategy relies entirely on warm metals. Confine your jewellery and structural hardware strictly to {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. You need substantial zips and buckles that hold their own inside an athletic space. Steer clear of {excluded_finish} surfaces. Beaten, aged, or tarnished textures appear exhausted and ruin your sharp geometry. Anchor your choices in highly reflective warm metals that flash visibly from a block away. Pick up the clasp or chain before making a decision. A gleaming photograph deceives the eye. Gravity provides the only honest metric for quality. If a {metal_1} ring feels light or hollow in your palm, leave it behind.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as structural equipment, choosing metals that enforce your strict geometry.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Require absolute clarity and high-shine refraction in your gems. Select {stone_1} or {stone_2} to serve as your one hot accent against a bare collarbone. Apply a strict test of mass before you commit. Weigh the piece in your hand to ensure it possesses genuine substance. Hollow settings will not anchor your look. Avoid clouded or raw stones entirely. An opaque finish drains the energy from your presentation and looks distinctly tired. You need strictly polished, warm settings that throw a blinding reflection. Keep the overall construction slick and self-contained to maintain a flawless boundary.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your presence by testing every stone for pure density and high-gloss refraction.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Demand unyielding density from your hardware. Fasten a {metal_1} chain or slide on a {stone_1} ring and assess how heavily it sits against your skin. A piece must drag slightly on the fabric to claim an athletic space around your body. Leave brushed, matt, or intentionally distressed surfaces on the shelf. Those subdued finishes look dull and compromise the sharp boundaries of your presentation. Rely strictly on an ultra-reflective warm sheen that projects total authority. A pristine gloss acts as a rigid mirror and delivers the clean, definitive geometry you require.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware with a strict physical check before adding it to an outfit.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments provide the necessary structural athletic space. Your accessories exist solely to deliver one hot accent. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with heavy jewellery. Seek out a massive yellow gold cuff. The surface must carry a brilliant high polish to project your warm palette. Judge the item blindly by its raw weight before looking in the mirror. Subject your choices to the corridor test. Look down a long hallway and ask if the bold silhouette registers clearly from the opposite end. If the metallic details blur into the background, leave the piece on the counter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Accessories serve one specific function in your system. Treat them as deliberate punctuation, not decoration.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Statement jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "high-polish yellow gold cuff, high polish"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the stage test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Your footwear frequently acts as your one hot accent. Look for high gloss and rigid structure. Choose rich oxblood or warm tan patent leather that refuses to absorb light. When evaluating a shoe, set it on the floor under a single bright bulb. This is your spotlight check. If the toe box does not bounce a sharp beam straight back at the ceiling, leave it in the box. You require a mirror finish that stands completely alone. A polished, warm gleam grounds the foot in total self-containment. Check the soles for thick, unyielding leather. Flex the toe slightly. If the surface wrinkles into a matt crease rather than maintaining a stark curve, the hide is too weak.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply the exact same strict requirements to your footwear, demanding structural rigidity and uncompromising shine.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "patent leather, high gloss"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the stage test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Select structured bags that maintain strict architecture empty or full. A patent leather top-handle bag featuring polished warm brass hardware delivers clean impact. Before stepping outside, execute a distance assessment. Back away ten paces from the mirror and check the outline of the bag against your coat. Your accessories must reinforce the athletic space required for unimpeded movement. If the overall shape dissolves into a flat, matt block from across the room, you lack the necessary contrast. Fix this by stripping away any soft scarves and carrying a clutch in a brilliant gold finish as your one hot accent. Let the rigid geometry speak first.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your final silhouette with strict architecture and a decisive visual check.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Structured bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "patent leather top-handle, polished hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the stage test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Pattern delivers clean impact when you engineer the scale correctly. Confine {recommended_pattern_1} to rigid tailored layers. Deploy {recommended_pattern_2} across fluid garments to add movement without losing structural control. Demand high-contrast graphic separation in every warm print you evaluate. Apply the twenty-foot rule in the fitting room. If the motif collapses into a murky blur at that distance, drop the piece. The graphic separation must strike the eye like a sharp architectural blueprint from the far end of a room. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. They introduce unnecessary visual clutter into your athletic space. Anchor sharp prints by pairing them with stark, solid blocks of {core_colour_1}. Complete the silhouette with one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use pattern to manipulate scale and project aggressive clarity across a distance.",
      "tests": [
        "the twenty foot rule (bold and entirely legible from twenty feet)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Drape the garment over a chair and step to the opposite side of the shop floor. Turn around and evaluate the graphic shape. If the lines of {recommended_pattern_1} bleed into a muddy wash, leave the item on the rail. You require strict boundary lines to secure clean impact. Look for absolute visual clarity. A bold motif printed on a heavy canvas skirt must read instantly as deliberate geometry. It must never dissolve into a vague texture. Test the scale of your pieces rigorously. If you deploy a warm silk pocket square as your one hot accent, the design must remain distinct from a distance. Do not settle for visual confusion. If you must squint to understand the borders, the pattern fails.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply the twenty-pace test to secure total graphic legibility.",
      "tests": [
        "the twenty foot rule (bold and entirely legible from twenty feet)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_aries__moon_sagittarius__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean impact + fast movement + one hot accent",
    "closing": "Navigate your wardrobe by demanding absolute physical boundaries and dense, warm materials, locking in clean impact + fast movement + one hot accent.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the sensation of momentum and sharp boundaries. Look for garments that feel aerodynamic and precise against your skin. If a piece drags, adds bulk, or demands constant readjustment, drop it. Your foundation relies on this sensory compass. Build your wardrobe slowly and methodically through rigorous curation, but deploy your outfits fast. Your core formula is clean impact + fast movement + one hot accent. Picture a sharply tailored outer layer worn over a frictionless base, anchored by a single piece of high-gloss hardware. This combination builds an impenetrable, polished shell.\n\nKeep your temperature warm and your finish entirely resolved. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not. Run every final combination through the entrance test. Stand in front of the mirror and check if the silhouette cuts a definitive, hard boundary between your physical space and the outside world. The outfit must stand entirely on its own without relying on external context to make sense. If the edges blur, if the shape softens, or if the focal point competes for attention, take it off immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural foundation and the primary filter for every garment you own.",
      "tests": [
        "the entrance test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your materials must deliver clean impact and fast movement. Seek out {texture_good_1} for sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually. Choose {texture_good_2} for knife-edge tailoring that never begs for a steamer. Add a warm flash to this base with {texture_good_3} for statement footwear and accessories that reflect maximum light. Deploy {texture_good_4} for slip dresses and linings that gleam under low light to carry that one hot accent. Before buying, apply the shadow test. Drape the fabric over your arm and look at the deepest fold. If the shadow looks flat or swallows the light, drop the garment. You need a polished surface that bounces light back sharply. Let gravity and friction guide your choices over visual appeal. Build your core from the following.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your foundation on materials that hit hard and hold their shape.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually"
        },
        {
