    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Grab the material in your fist. If it crushes into a lifeless lump, drop it. It ruins your demand for clean impact. Reject {texture_bad_2} completely. It drags against your skin and stops fast movement dead. Test your garments by checking their structural integrity under tension. Pull the textile taut across your knuckles. If the threads separate or the surface absorbs ambient light into a muddy void, the item fails. You need materials that bounce a warm glow outward. A weak textile like {texture_bad_3} dulls your edges. You require a firm surface that isolates one hot accent. Keep your choices crisp and self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and reject the materials that actively work against your geometry.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot sits squarely between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Ground the look with {texture_good_1}. To guarantee clean impact, you must run the bulb test. Hold the piece under a stark overhead light. If the surface absorbs the beam and casts a blurred shape, drop it. You require textiles that slice through the glare and throw a hard, precise outline. This sharp boundary ensures fast movement across your silhouette. Warm, polished finishes reflect the environment without letting anyone inside. Keep the friction high and entirely self-contained. Finish the combination with one hot accent in a high-gloss finish to snap the focus.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact friction point where your textiles collide.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette operates on a strictly warm temperature. Build a deep foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Deploy {core_colour_3} as your crisp substitute neutral. Rely on {core_colour_4} to bridge tonal shifts. Strike with one hot accent by choosing {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Treat your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Rely on your physical senses when combining these shades. Your body registers harmony before the mirror does. If a combination feels disjointed on your shoulders, take it off. Leave muddy pastel, icy grey, and dusty sage on the hanger. Beware the costume trap. Piling on patent leather, sharp studs, dramatic cosmetics, and heavy metal hardware all at once pushes bold expression into fancy dress. Fix this instantly. Limit yourself to a single molten flash. Ground every other piece in a flat, matt {core_colour_1}. This strict visual restraint guarantees clean impact and fast movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Deploy your palette with strict physical discipline.",
      "rankedItems": [
