    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim settings, clean impact leads your strategy. Reach for a golden camel shirt in heavy silk satin, and notice how the material catches a warm glow. Apply this rule to close-quarters dressing. Long dinners call for fluid garments that maintain a strict boundary without suffocating the wearer. Anchor the foundation with a sharp wool twill trouser. Fasten heavy, deep bronze jewellery near the face to direct attention. Assess the density of the metal in your palm. Substantial materials hang properly when you sit, while flimsy synthetics buckle. Avoid lightweight items for evening events. Let the pure weight of the objects guide your final selections.",
      "sectionIntro": "Scale your proportions and textures for close proximity and low light.",
      "tests": [
