    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your metal strategy requires dominant warm tones to secure the outfit. Choose {metal_1} or {metal_2} with a fiercely polished surface to guarantee pure clean impact. Scratched or distressed hardware looks exhausted and absorbs light when you need it to flash. Keep your warm metals utterly pristine so they reflect the sun instantly from a distance. Restrict any secondary {metal_3} to tiny functional rivets. It must never compete with the primary metal. When testing a thick cuff, lift the piece. Weigh the solid drag in your palm to verify its quality. A high-shine {metal_1} collar serves perfectly as your one hot accent. Keep every piece devoid of {excluded_finish} treatments. Absolute slickness maintains fast movement from head to toe.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat hardware as the crucial final strike that seals the silhouette.",
      "tests": [
