  "venus_aries__moon_libra__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean impact + cool composure + one hot accent",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on clean impact + cool composure + one hot accent.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your physical instinct is adaptability. Trust your hands to find garments that feel both structured and fluid. Look for a polished surface that moves with you. Build your wardrobe slowly as a modular toolkit. Deploy it fast when the environment changes. Warm tones must form the foundation of this kit. Touch the fabric before you check the mirror. If it feels rigid or restrictive, put it back on the rail. You need a supportive weight that allows immediate movement. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.\n\nYour baseline equation is clean impact + cool composure + one hot accent. Picture a razor-sharp tailored trouser, a fluid silk shirt left unbuttoned at the collar, and a single sculptural high-shine boot. You must subject every piece to the fall test. Lift the garment by the shoulders and let it drop into your hands. It must fall cleanly and hold a memory of its own shape. If it collapses into a lifeless pile, reject it. It lacks the internal architecture you require. Let the cut do the heavy lifting.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural foundation. Read it, memorise it, and apply it to every garment you pick up.",
      "tests": [
        "the fall test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your foundation demands clean impact and cool composure. Achieve this by selecting warm textiles that maintain strict physical boundaries without stiffness. Choose {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Use {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement. Ground the lower half in {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. Test the weave before you buy and apply the edge test. Pinch the hem tightly between your thumb and index finger. If the fold collapses into mush, leave the garment on the rack. You need materials that hold their shape to successfully anchor one hot accent. Proceed with the ranked list below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your physical foundation on materials that pass strict tactile tests and support your core formula.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
