    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the desk, cool composure takes the lead. Establish this state using worsted wool trousers paired with crisp cotton poplin shirting. Keep the palette anchored in warm taupe or camel. These matt fabrics ensure your silhouette delivers clean impact at a glance. Run the breeze test before you leave. A turbulent schedule gives you no excuse to surrender your proportions. Leave oversized knits on the hanger. Maintain strict lines with fine ribbed merino that skims the ribcage without restricting your arms. Once the shape is set, introduce one hot accent. A heavy gold and silver chain or a bright silk scarf provides exactly enough heat to activate the outfit.",
      "sectionIntro": "Construct your workplace uniform by applying your core style formula.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "A dim room softens sharp outlines. Compensate by trusting the physical reality of the cloth. Select a fine ribbed merino sweater in warm taupe or camel and let the dense knit drop straight to the hem. A late supper does not require abandoning proportion. Check the shoulders in the mirror. If the seam slides down your arm, put it back. Mix your dual register metals. Pair a heavy silver ring with fine gold jewellery to catch the candlelight. If you require a sharper silhouette, a crisp cotton poplin shirt provides instant structure. Ground the frame in worsted wool trousers to ensure your clean impact survives the evening.",
      "sectionIntro": "Navigate low-light settings by relying on shape and cloth over surface details.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A quick run to the chemist provides no reason to drop your structural standard. Buying fresh produce requires the exact same baseline as a scheduled meeting. Build your foundation with matt dark denim and a camel gabardine jacket. Apply your guiding equation every single time you get dressed. Your standard remains clean impact + cool composure + one hot accent. Evaluate the construction of your casual wear rigorously. Heavy seams and rigid drape tell the truth. Fasten a polished silver cuff over a warm mahogany silk sleeve to provide necessary heat. Grip the fabric behind the collar. If it feels weak, leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your morning routine as a deliberate and exacting drill.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your hardware strategy operates on two separate tracks. For jewellery sitting directly on the skin, select {personal_metal_1} or {personal_metal_2} to establish a warm baseline. Treat structural elements differently. Secure your zips, shoe buckles, and bag clasps strictly with {structural_metal_1} or {structural_metal_2}. Steer clear of artificially aged hardware. Oxidised copper, tarnished brass, and beaten surfaces create visual clutter against a modern silhouette. Maintain an immaculate polished finish by choosing bright silver, mirror-finished steel, or brilliant white gold, and exclude {excluded_finish} entirely. Evaluate a belt or bag by lifting the metalwork. Focus entirely on its solid, uncompromising weight. Rely on that sheer density to anchor the garment and deliver clean impact.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical metalwork that fastens and finishes your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select your stones for high density and pristine clarity. Choose {stone_1} or {stone_2} to capture light effectively. Weigh the setting in your palm before you put it on. A heavy, dense gem successfully anchors a warm palette. Ignore opaque or clouded inclusions. They diffuse the light and weaken the stone's presence. Restrict the surrounding mount to mirror chrome, platinum, white gold, or polished silver. This bright foundation delivers clean impact. Let the flawless finish secure your cool composure, allowing the pure stone to serve as your one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your stones and metal finishes by their physical mass and visual clarity.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Test every piece of jewellery by its resistance to gravity. A proper piece pulls downward against your hand. Depend on this tactile gravity to screen your choices. Discard any item with blackened grooves or simulated wear. Require an immaculate, perfectly polished exterior instead. A substantial, brilliantly mirrored {metal_1} link or a dense {stone_1} signet resting against a warm sleeve effortlessly secures your one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware using the primary test of mass.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Establish your base for clean impact. Secure your silhouette for cool composure. Rely on your hardware and textiles to deliver exactly one hot accent. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with silk scarves. Seek out a narrow silk band that provides a polished, soft glow against a wool collar. You must enforce the one-signal test. Put the item on and assess the focal point. If a warm metallic watch dial catches the eye, leave your neckline bare. If you knot that silk band at your throat, keep your wrists empty. Let physical weight rather than visual noise guide your final edit.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess your accessories using strict limits and physical instincts.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Silk scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "silk band, soft glow"
