      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-signal test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "When selecting fine jewellery, look for a thin gold chain with a high polish finish. The reflective surface acts as one hot accent against a flat collar. This chain must deliver exactly one clear flash of warm light. If the design introduces multiple pendants or complicated textures, it fails the aesthetic brief. Keep the metal warm and the surface strictly glassy to maintain your cool composure. Evaluate the construction directly with your hands. Drop the chain into your palm. It must pool smoothly like heavy liquid, not clatter like cheap industrial hardware.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess your delicate metals strictly by how they handle light and gravity.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Fine jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "thin gold chain, high polish"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-signal test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Choose a small structured crossbody bag in smooth leather. Rub the surface to ensure it lacks any pebbling or grain. Inspect the fine hardware. A dual register mix of metals works perfectly here, provided the finish remains highly reflective. This bag frequently operates as your one hot accent against warm worsted wool. Before you step out, execute a final scan. Count the competing elements in the mirror. If a high-shine clasp fights against heavy neck chains, you are broadcasting noise. Strip away the loudest item until the entire look transmits clean impact.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your final anchoring piece and run a strict diagnostic check on your complete outfit.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Small structured bag",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "smooth leather crossbody, polished fine hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-signal test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Ground your structured tailoring in precise geometries like {recommended_pattern_1}. Let your fluid garments take their rhythm from softer spacing through {recommended_pattern_2}. Your versatile approach requires an adaptive contrast rule. Keep tonal variations subtle to project cool composure in daily utility. When shifting gears, deploy a high-contrast {recommended_pattern_3} over a warm base to anchor your one hot accent. This ensures pure clean impact without overwhelming the eye. Verify every print with the straight-edge test. Step back three metres from the mirror. The boundaries of the motif must remain crisp and true. If the lines bleed into a muddy wash, drop the garment. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1}, {avoid_pattern_2}, and any scale that distorts when stretching across your shoulders. Rely on your spatial instincts to filter out visual static.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as a precision tool for visual weight rather than simple decoration.",
      "tests": [
        "the straight-edge test (lines stay crisp and true at three metres)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Evaluate the legibility of {recommended_pattern_1} across a room. Hang the garment on a rail and evaluate the printed borders from afar. If the shapes merge into an indistinct blur, leave the piece behind. You require rigid geometry to anchor your cool composure. The print must remain sharply defined from across a shop floor. Prioritise this distant clarity over the fitting mirror up close. When you introduce one hot accent through a motif, the graphic must slice cleanly through the surrounding warm background. A pattern fails instantly if the boundary between colours loses its discipline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce strict visual boundaries on your prints to ensure they perform correctly.",
      "tests": [
        "the straight-edge test (lines stay crisp and true at three metres)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_aries__moon_pisces__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "clean impact + blurred edges + one hot accent",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on clean impact + blurred edges + one hot accent.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your styling rests on a single equation. Master it as clean impact + blurred edges + one hot accent. Picture a heavy, unlined coat falling in a strict architectural line. Beneath it sits a fine knit melting softly against your collarbone. Finally, add a single sharp point of warm light at the cuff. This is your template. Trust your hands when sourcing these pieces. Pick up a garment and feel its density. A piece must have enough physical gravity to stand independently of your body. If it feels flimsy or clings, reject it immediately.\n\nTreat your wardrobe as a closed system. Build it slowly over seasons, editing with ruthless precision. When it comes to dressing, deploy the pieces rapidly in one decisive movement. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Apply the breath test before making any purchase. Pull the garment over your shoulders and inhale deeply. The structure must adapt to accommodate your lungs. If the seams restrict your ribcage or force you into rigid attention, the piece is a failure. You need garments that shield you without demanding your energy in return. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise these functional rules to anchor your styling and evaluate every garment before it touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Focus your hands on materials that deliver clean impact without rigid boundaries. Test every new purchase against your skin. Hold the textile to your lips and blow out softly. If the warm air moves through the weave, the piece will serve you. If it blocks the ventilation, leave it on the rail. Seek {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Rely on {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Pick {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Build your outer layers with {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge, keeping your blurred edges intact.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the textiles that build your private sanctuary.",
