    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} the moment your fingers meet it. Trust your hands. They know when a fabric feels slick and artificial. Test {texture_bad_2} by pressing the weave directly over your mouth. Force a sharp exhale. If that air traps inside the fibres instead of passing freely, walk away. Your aesthetic requires natural airflow to maintain a warm, self-contained environment. Synthetic barriers suffocate the skin and dictate false shapes. A stiff {texture_bad_3} creates harsh boundaries where you need soft margins. Keep your foundation entirely natural and reserve any extreme synthetic finish exclusively for your one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify material failure in the hand before it ever reaches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This exact pairing delivers clean impact. Lift a piece of {texture_good_1} to your face and breathe into the cloth. You must feel immediate thermal regulation. If the material traps heat against your cheek, abandon it. Rely on this physical sensation to guide you. A self-contained wardrobe requires materials that physically perform. Anchor these fabrics with heavy yellow gold or warm brass. Mirrors mislead. Your fingertips tell the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your materials by physically testing them before they ever reach your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Maintain a strictly warm temperature across your wardrobe. Build your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} serving as a warm base neutral. Anchor these with {core_colour_3} acting as a structural dark neutral, and {core_colour_4} as an earthy green neutral. Treat the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Bring in {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent. This provides your one hot accent, guaranteeing clean impact alongside blurred edges. Bypass stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. Watch for the trap of dissolution. Stacking pale gauze on pale gauze makes the silhouette disappear entirely. Fix this fading effect by restoring a single defined line. Introduce a bias-cut slip that traces the body, add a fitted base layer, or wear {core_colour_3} closest to your skin.",
