      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Gauge every piece against the friction it generates. Trust your fingertips when they tell you a fabric fails the endurance trial. Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Pick it up and feel how it refuses to yield when you bend your arm. Leave {texture_bad_2} on the hanger. It irritates the neck and traps heat instead of breathing. You need materials that disappear against the skin. This baseline ease frees you to build a warm palette around one hot accent. Notice how {texture_bad_3} catches on your knuckles. Trust your skin. Stiff fibres offer zero compliance. If a material binds, bites, or resists your movement, put it back.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to spot the materials that actively fight your body, so you can leave them on the rack.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing builds a structured shell that holds its shape. Layer {texture_good_1} underneath to absorb the light. Put the garment on and sit in a rigid shop chair for two minutes. If the collar chokes or the armholes dig into your shoulders, discard the piece immediately. Your self-contained strategy relies on exact execution. Anchor the base to secure clean impact and sensory comfort, then introduce one hot accent in a warm metal or stone. Run your bare hands over the weave to verify the finish. Smooth, matt surfaces will never betray you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the precise intersection of structure and ease.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette relies entirely on warm undertones. Establish your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Let {core_colour_3} function as your white substitute, while {core_colour_4} acts as your bridging neutral. To guarantee clean impact, select either {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your one hot accent. Keep a soft relief tone in reserve, deploying it sparingly when the eye requires a pause. Pass over icy pastels, neon brights, and blue grey. Watch for the barricade reflex. When your schedule intensifies, you may grab stiff outerwear or rigid technical gear without thinking. Trust your hands to detect the stiffness. Drop the item. Exchange that heavy shield for a supple brushed cotton top that matches your velocity while securing your required sensory comfort.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your colours as strict tools for precise execution.",
