    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Treat hardware as structural light. A dense {stone_1} or a perfectly clear {stone_2} provides a precise focal point. Hold the item to verify its density. A heavy setting guarantees the grounding necessary for true sensory comfort. Stone settings demand strict execution. Rough facets, raw crystals, and unpolished surfaces create visual static against a modern silhouette. Reject them entirely. Protect your self-contained aesthetic by insisting on brilliant, mirror-smooth polished warm metals to house your gems. High-shine surfaces reflect light evenly, turning a simple ring or cuff into an architectural component rather than mere decoration.",
