          "failure": "the beige-out: every piece at the same pale value looks unfinished rather than minimal",
          "fix": "rescue it with a graphite anchor piece or a bottle green accent, and let one texture change restore the depth"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, clean impact leads. Support this precision with an honest fabric like a crisp cotton poplin shirt tucked into camel worsted wool trousers. Require the identical sharp cut for reviewing spreadsheets at your desk as you do for leading a Monday morning briefing. If the garment fails that standard, leave it on the hanger. Trust your own grip to judge quality. If a warm taupe fine ribbed merino knit feels thin to your fingers, discard it immediately. Visuals can be engineered. Tactile density cannot. Maintain a self-contained shape with zero trailing hems. Finally, deploy one hot accent to direct the eye. A heavy mixed-metal watch blending silver and gold provides exactly this focus.",
      "sectionIntro": "Filter your work garments ruthlessly, keeping only what performs without needing your constant attention.",
      "tests": [
        "a hardware store run deserves the same clean fit as a Monday meeting (Flint)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In a shadowed room, let clean impact dictate your choices. High contrast disappears in low light. Rely entirely on silhouette and weight. Select fine ribbed merino in a warm camel. Trust your hands in the dark. If a garment feels lifeless, reject it. A solo evening reading by the fire deserves the exact same crisp cotton poplin as a crowded private dinner. Never drop your standards just because the audience shrinks. Finish the look by mixing a matt gold chain with a polished silver ring to catch the ambient candlelight. Shadows obscure construction, but sheer mass proves quality.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master intimate environments by letting shape and texture take control.",
      "tests": [
        "a hardware store run deserves the same clean fit as a Monday meeting (Flint)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "You do not suspend your standards to buy lightbulbs. A run to the hardware store deserves the exact same clean fit as a Monday meeting. Treat a quick trip to the post office as a reason to wear your worsted wool trousers and a matt technical nylon shell. Your core method remains absolutely constant across all environments. Build every outfit on clean impact + honest fabric + one hot accent. Keep your silhouette tight and entirely independent of the venue. A warm taupe knit provides a polished base. Add a sliver of polished gold or bright silver at the wrist to finish the look. Give no ground to careless dressing.",
      "sectionIntro": "Approach your daily routines with the exact same rigour you apply to a formal presentation.",
      "tests": [
        "a hardware store run deserves the same clean fit as a Monday meeting (Flint)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Separate personal jewellery from structural fasteners. For pieces worn directly on the body, choose {personal_metal_1} and {personal_metal_2}. For bag clasps, coat zips, and belt buckles, rely on {structural_metal_1} and {structural_metal_2}. This dual register builds a self-contained wardrobe. Avoid {excluded_finish}. Faux-vintage patinas and heavily textured surfaces register as noise. Demand highly reflective, pristine metal surfaces instead. Always lift a buckle or clasp to judge its gravity. A mirror shine can hide cheap casting, but sheer physical density proves the value. Heavy, solid hardware anchors honest fabric. By demanding dense, immaculate metal in a warm tone, you guarantee clean impact and provide the absolute foundation for one hot accent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as the ultimate structural test.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Anchor your accessories in stones that project a warm temperature. Choose {stone_1} or {stone_2} to deliver one hot accent without overwhelming the eye. Lift the piece from the tray to gauge its density. A photograph lies. The undeniable heft of a natural mineral in your palm gives you the final answer. Drop anything that feels light or hollow. Your hardware must remain strictly polished. Pre-tarnished finishes and artificially hammered surfaces register as historical clutter against your clean impact. Keep your dual register of hardware buffed to a mirror shine. This ensures your look remains entirely self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your hardware by evaluating its material truth and final polish in your own hands.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Pick up the item and weigh it in your palm. Surface treatments mimic luxury. Raw weight proves it. Rely on the literal gravity of the object in your hand. Hollow hardware undermines your self-contained approach. Reject hammered, deliberately oxidised, or artificially weathered surfaces entirely. Those manufactured patinas create unnecessary visual static, ruining your clean impact. Keep your metal finishes strictly polished and highly reflective. Brilliant, smooth {metal_1} anchors a warm palette without adding clutter. A gleaming {stone_1} can serve as one hot accent, provided its setting remains flawlessly sleek.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware by its literal mass and demand an immaculate surface.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Enforce a strict limit of one or two strong pieces per look to maintain clean impact. Build the underlying structure with honest fabric, then finish the mathematics with one hot accent. Begin with eyewear. Seek out a thin metal frame in polished silver. Do not buy a pair without applying the function test. Put them on and shake your head. If they slide or wobble, put them back. Trust your physical senses. Mirrors flatter. The literal friction against your temples dictates whether a frame belongs to you. Let this polished silver cut sharply against a warm palette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select and test your finishing hardware with the exact same physical rigor you apply to your heaviest garments.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Eyewear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "thin metal frame, polished silver"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Evaluate your bag based entirely on mechanics. Pick up a smooth leather crossbody and sling the strap over your shoulder. Work the hardware blindly. If the polished zips drag or the fastening requires two hands, leave the bag on the shelf. Trust your grip to judge the engineering. A storefront display hides poor construction. Seamless mechanical operation exposes quality. Look for treated calfskin that remains rigid when completely empty. This firm foundation creates an ideal vehicle for one hot accent. Let a high-shine brass or bright silver clasp provide that focal point against a warm camel worsted wool coat.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test the mechanical limits of the items you carry.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "smooth leather crossbody, polished zips"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your foundation with smooth leather footwear finished to a clean gloss. The surface must reflect light to maintain visual tension. Introduce a high polish steel case watch to cut through warm core tones. Weigh the watch in your palm to verify its density. Gauge the steel casing in your grip. Polished surfaces distract, but cold mass confirms a solid mechanism. Keep the surrounding hardware quiet to leave room for one hot accent elsewhere. Before leaving, apply the motion test. If the leather sole slides on wet tarmac, or the watch dial turns invisible under harsh glare, remove it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your final practical details with an unsentimental eye.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "smooth leather, clean gloss"
        },
        {
          "name": "Watch",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "steel case, high polish"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
