  "venus_cancer__moon_aquarius__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "soft shelter + mobile layers + one sentimental keepsake",
    "closing": "Navigate by touch, reject the illusion of the mirror, and build your foundation exclusively through soft shelter + mobile layers + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Dress by touch. Trust your hands to find the heavy, silent drape of garments that hold their shape without restricting yours. Your physical instinct demands a cool, balanced equilibrium in everything you wear. Translate this directly into your core formula: soft shelter + mobile layers + one sentimental keepsake. Picture a fine-gauge knit worn under an unlined overcoat, anchored by a heavy pendant resting against your collarbone. This is how you construct an outfit. Reject stiff linings and rigid tailoring. Look for garments that move exactly when you do.\n\nBuild your wardrobe deliberately over years. Assemble your outfits in minutes. When you evaluate a new piece, rely on the breath test. Put the garment on, drop your arms to your sides, and exhale completely. If the seams pinch your shoulders or the waist requires you to hold tension, leave the item on the hanger. A proper piece of clothing must absorb a full, deep exhalation without pulling or shifting. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Structure and weight do not. Accumulate garments that grant you complete physical autonomy.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your mechanical baseline, the foundational logic you will use to evaluate every garment before it touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe requires fabrics that build a soft shelter against the elements while functioning as mobile layers. Rely on tactile feedback. Run the touch test on every piece before you check the label. Squeeze a sweater made of {texture_good_1}. It must compress under your fingers and spring back without creasing. When selecting shoes or a daily bag, seek out {texture_good_2} that will soften and develop a muted patina with daily friction. Construct your tailored coats from heavy {texture_good_3} to maintain a clean structure over years of wear. For blouses and internal linings, rely on {texture_good_4} to provide cool, fluid movement against the skin. Let density govern your choices. Appearance deceives. Substance remains constant. Build your foundation from the materials below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Let your hands evaluate every garment before your eyes look at a label.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Suede",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "shoes and accessories with quiet matt texture"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine merino",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers soft against the skin and resilient through washes"
        },
        {
          "name": "Linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "warmer-weather pieces whose natural wrinkle reads as authentic"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Close your eyes and run your fingertips over the weave to test the truth of a fabric. Weight and friction reveal poor quality immediately. Pick up {texture_bad_1} and drag it across your skin. If it catches or feels brittle, put it down. Crush {texture_bad_2} tightly in your palm. If it springs back with a hollow crunch or holds a rigid crease, walk away. Cheap, slick finishes disrupt a cool, muted approach. Even the solid metal of one sentimental keepsake cannot rescue a garment that feels papery and weak. Reject anything flimsy.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify and eliminate materials that fail upon contact.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "To build your soft shelter, combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing relies on matt, muted finishes in a cool palette to maintain equilibrium. Your body knows the correct answer. Execute a friction check by closing your eyes and dragging your bare thumb across the surface of any {texture_good_1}. If the threads feel harsh or dry, drop the item immediately. Seek out pieces that drape cleanly and offer quiet protection. Combine structured items with pliable materials to balance the silhouette. Look for subtle texture contrasts rather than stark divides. Demand fabrics that feel secure but never rigid.",
      "sectionIntro": "Combine your materials to create a secure, balanced foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is resolutely cool. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3} for your primary garments. Rely on {core_colour_4} as your strict white substitute. Inject {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent introduced through your mobile layers. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over vivid saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon entirely. Watch for the trap of dissolution. When you layer pale gauze over pale gauze with nothing underneath, your silhouette completely disappears. Fix this immediately by restoring a single structural line. Add a bias-cut slip that traces the body, or wear a dark fitted base layer closest to the skin.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your palette by memorising its precise roles and strict limitations.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Deep teal",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Dove grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Moonlit ivory",
          "role": "white_substitute"
        },
        {
          "name": "Faded denim blue",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Smoked mauve",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Sage grey",
          "role": "earthy_green"
        },
        {
          "name": "Faded rose",
          "role": "accent"
        },
        {
          "name": "Deep berry",
          "role": "accent"
        },
        {
          "name": "Muted plum",
          "role": "accent"
        },
        {
