      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Pinch the hem tightly. If the cloth squeals or pushes back against your grip, drop it immediately. Your foundation requires layers that yield, not stiff plastics that restrict your physical movement. Reject {texture_bad_2} completely. Crush a sleeve in your fist. If it crinkles like a discarded wrapper or feels unnaturally slick, it fails the test. These harsh synthetics trap heat. They disrupt your cool, muted palette and will never sit in harmony beside your one sentimental keepsake. Train your fingers to detect poor construction instantly.",
