    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is decidedly cool. Build a self-contained foundation using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3} for your primary garments. Rely on {core_colour_4} as your strict white substitute. This muted base establishes your hidden depth. Reserve {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} for singular, deliberate accents in matt silk or brushed wool. Use your relief tone sparingly, applying it as a soft note to lift a heavy cashmere sleeve. Leave hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon on the rack. Avoid the trap of head-to-toe black. An unbroken dark column flattens your silhouette. Break it up with a {core_colour_4} knit layer, a {accent_colour_1} scarf, or a {core_colour_2} full-grain leather belt.",
