    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, let soft shelter lead your decisions. Judge a garment by its capacity to move. A brutal fourteen-hour shift requires pliable fabrics that sprint with your stride, not stiff armour that fights your body. Rely on fluid silk shirts and unstructured cashmere jackets. Let hidden depth support this base. Seek out matt finishes and heavy twills that only reveal their complex weave upon closer inspection. Anchor the entire composition with one sentimental keepsake. Fasten a cool silver locket or a vintage lapis pin to your collar. Trust the physical weight of that private detail to ground you, leaving the pliable wools to carry you through the day.",
