    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories anchor your daily equation. They sit against the soft shelter of your garments and ground the hidden depth of your layers. Treat a chosen piece of metal as the one sentimental keepsake that finishes the structure. Apply the rule of removal before crossing the threshold. Take off any item that clamours for attention. One strong piece is sufficient. Begin this process with handbags. Seek out dense full-grain leather or thick suede. Inspect the clasps and buckles. The metal must be cool and matt brushed. Assess the mass when you lift a bag. Heavy hardware confirms craftsmanship. Thin zips and hollow chain links feel flimsy to the touch. Reject them.",
