    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "For your specific needs, the touch test is absolute. Drag the yardage across your inner wrist. If the weave scratches or snags, drop it. You are engineering a cool refuge, not tolerating friction. Avoid {texture_bad_1} entirely. It snaps with static and clings exactly where it should glide. Leave {texture_bad_2} on the rack. It sits stiffly against the collarbone and chafes the neck. Pass on {texture_bad_3}. It loses its muted finish and pills under the arms after a single day of wear. Your garments must offer complete tactile silence so that one sentimental keepsake remains the sole anchor. If a fabric argues with your bare skin, reject it.",
