    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep your palette strictly cool. Rely on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_3} as your primary base. Ground them with the structural weight of {core_colour_2}, and use {core_colour_4} to lift the eye. Introduce {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} to create hidden depth beneath an open collar. Deploy the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Leave hard black, harsh neon, and heavy earth brown on the rack. Dressing in head-to-toe black reads like a surrender to the morning rush. Break up the block with a {core_colour_3} layer, one {accent_colour_1} scarf, or a {core_colour_4} belt.",
