    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, hidden depth dictates your strategy. The remaining elements serve strictly to support this core. Let a heavy silk crepe shirt act as your quiet sanctuary beneath a rigid blazer. This keeps your approach self-contained, while a private silver pendant rests out of sight. Taking the dog through the freezing fog demands the exact same standard of dress as a quarterly board meeting. Never downgrade your materials for a minor task. Pair deep teal boiled wool trousers with dove grey washed silk on a routine Tuesday morning, just as you would for a keynote address. The standard never drops simply because the audience changes. Rely on the cool, matt finish of these pieces to do the work.",
      "sectionIntro": "Dictate the terms of your professional environment by letting your most private elements take the lead.",
      "tests": [
        "walking the dog deserves the same standard as a meeting (Moss)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Pouring a quiet cup of tea at midnight deserves absolute material perfection. Hidden depth takes the lead in close, low-light settings. Select dense silk crepe in deep teal or incredibly soft lambswool in dove grey. Choose cool metals like matt white gold or brushed platinum to sit closely on the skin. Rely on tactile feedback to evaluate these garments. Appearance deceives, but the physical ease of the fabric never lies. Keep your lines close to the body and avoid anything that needs adjustment. Every piece must serve your own comfort first.",
      "sectionIntro": "Curate your private hours by treating your solitary environments with the same exactness as your public spaces.",
      "tests": [
        "walking the dog deserves the same standard as a meeting (Moss)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat a simple errand with serious intent. The requirement for quality remains absolute. Pull on deep teal lambswool and a matt platinum ring even when buying milk at the corner shop. Treat every garment as a deliberate choice. Discard anything stiff or restrictive. Look for cool tones and muted finishes. Your baseline always remains soft shelter + hidden depth + one sentimental keepsake. Guard these standards fiercely. Dress for yourself alone.",
      "sectionIntro": "Maintain your standards through every mundane errand.",
      "tests": [
        "walking the dog deserves the same standard as a meeting (Moss)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Anchor your cool dominant strategy in {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Avoid {excluded_finish}. Highly polished silver strikes a sharp, distracting note against subdued colours. Keep the visual field cohesive by insisting on matt and brushed textures for every zip and buckle. Evaluate every buckle by lifting it. A brilliant gleam offers nothing, but sheer mass confirms quality. Rely on solid, dense metals to ground your layers. Build the entire system around one sentimental keepsake, worn against the collarbone as your sole piece of jewellery.",
      "sectionIntro": "Take absolute control of your hardware by applying strict physical tests to every metal detail.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Look for dense, opaque minerals like {stone_1} and {stone_2} that absorb light rather than throwing it across the room. Always weigh the piece in your hand. An unyielding heaviness in your palm confirms the stone possesses true substance. Because your garments function as soft shelter, your hardware must align with this cool reality. Steer clear of high-gloss chrome or mirror-polished silver. Such intense shine clashes with muted fibres. Anchor these stones in brushed or matt metal settings to maintain total cohesion.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your stones and hardware for density and restraint.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Lift the {metal_1} from the counter to assess its heft. A substantial piece anchors your wardrobe, providing physical gravity where you need it most. Avoid high-shine, reflective hardware entirely. A brilliant, polished finish creates a sharp, jarring distraction against soft clothing. Instead, insist on matt or brushed textures to keep the aesthetic cohesive and strictly cool. A frosted surface integrates perfectly, honouring your preference for hidden depth. Demand dense, quiet metal over an empty, glaring polish.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware by its physical density, and rigorously filter out reflective finishes.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments act as soft shelter. Your textures create hidden depth. Accessories provide the final element, serving as your one sentimental keepsake. Follow the principle of one or two strong pieces per look. Strip away the extra pendant or the secondary ring. Handbags carry this load literally. Demand full-grain leather or thick suede. Run your thumb over the buckles and straps. Accept only matt brushed hardware cast in cool metal tones. Drop the bag onto a table and listen for a heavy, dull thud. Substantial materials never rattle.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your accessories by testing their physical weight and functional purpose.",
      "rankedItems": [
