    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Look for generous silk or fine wool scarves with a strictly matt finish. Gather the fabric and let it pool in your palms to confirm its density. A large scarf in cool dove grey should provide soft shelter from the chill. Avoid anything shiny. Put on your chosen wrap and examine the result. If the garment disrupts your self-contained lines, take it off. One strong anchor is always enough. Pure hidden depth relies on these quiet layers instead of competing focal points.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply these material rules to select the scarves that will anchor your silhouette.",
