    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Let pattern provide hidden depth. Keep your contrast strictly tonal and low. Tailored garments must draw their markings from the loom itself. Fluid garments take their prints from {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2}. Step back from the mirror and soften your focus. If the motif blurs into a unified texture, keep the piece. If it remains sharp and demands attention, drop the garment. Pass over stark borders, high-contrast graphics, {avoid_pattern_1}, and {avoid_pattern_2}. Every print must sink into your cool colour palette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the rules of pattern to control the volume of your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
