  "venus_cancer__moon_gemini__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "soft shelter + light movement + one sentimental keepsake",
    "closing": "Trust the tension between drape and density to guide your daily rhythm, always returning to soft shelter + light movement + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Dress by touch. Trust the physical sensation of adaptability. Feel the give in a garment before you check the mirror. If the textile feels rigid or demands a stiff posture, drop it. Your core style formula is soft shelter + light movement + one sentimental keepsake. Build this out in practice. Pull on a heavy knitted jumper over a fluid dress, then finish the look with an inherited pendant on a simple chain. The outfit works through the tension between the enveloping layer and the liquid fabric underneath.\n\nBuild your wardrobe slowly but deploy it fast. Your garments must pivot with your changing rhythm. Apply the combination test to every new acquisition. Ask yourself if the item can anchor three entirely different silhouettes without looking forced. Seek out cool temperatures and matt finishes that absorb light. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not. When you pick up a piece, feel its drape and gauge its capacity to layer. If it cannot adapt to your movements, leave it on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your operational blueprint, the central logic you will use to filter out distractions and build a wardrobe that functions seamlessly.",
      "tests": [
        "the combination test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation on fabrics that provide a soft shelter against the elements. Start by handling {texture_good_1} for shirting that maintains clean architectural boundaries. Layer this over {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers that offer sharp lines. Rely on {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} as mobile outerwear to block the wind and guarantee light movement. Apply the snap test to every new garment. Pull the fabric taut between your hands and feel for a crisp recoil. A sluggish return means the weave lacks the structural tension required to anchor your cool palette and matt finishes. Let the textile's immediate bounce guide your purchasing decisions. The materials ranked below will consistently pass this physical threshold.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to evaluate a garment by its touch before you ever consult a mirror.",
      "rankedItems": [
