    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Leave {texture_bad_1} in the shop. Pick the item up and test the elasticity. Pull the material gently from side to side and feel for a harsh recoil. If the threads bite back or feel rigid against your knuckles, reject the piece immediately. Avoid {texture_bad_2} entirely. The tactile tell is a slick, clammy surface that traps heat against your neck. These dense synthetics suffocate the wearer. They distract the eye rather than creating a quiet backdrop for your one sentimental keepsake. Press your palm into {texture_bad_3} and notice the abrasive scratch. Your hands know when materials fail. Rely on touch to weed out anything stiff or grating before it ever reaches your closet.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise failure before you ever put the item on.",
      "tests": [
        "the snap test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot lives where {sweet_spot_keyword_1} meets {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing builds your required soft shelter while permitting light movement. Grab a piece of {texture_good_1}. Pull the hem taut and release it suddenly. Watch the recoil. The item must spring back to its exact shape immediately. If the weave slumps, drop the garment entirely. Your cool palette needs this underlying structure. Look for a matt surface that carries its own weight.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact physical tension your layers require.",
      "tests": [
        "the snap test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your colours are strictly cool. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} as a daily white substitute, and deploy {core_colour_4} as a structural dark neutral. Introduce {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate focal point. Apply your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green. Abandon them immediately. Avoid the trap of a single-shade uniform that feels lifeless by noon. Fix this visual flatline by adding a stiff white poplin collar, a silver architectural ring, or a bright geometric sneaker. Creating soft shelter requires these exact tones. Pick up every new garment and verify its undertone before buying.",
