    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, soft shelter leads. Your daily environment requires pliable protection, not rigid tailoring. A heavy schedule does not demand stiff armour. It asks for forgiving layers that can sprint from morning briefings to late reviews. Rely on worsted wool trousers and fine ribbed merino to provide this yielding structure. Let light movement support your base. A crisp cotton poplin shirt worn loose gives breathability and physical ease. Ground these cool, muted fabrics with one sentimental keepsake. A steel watch or a familiar silver ring tucked under an icy grey cuff provides a necessary, quiet focal point.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your work attire by its physical capacity to sustain you through a demanding day.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, visual details fade and touch takes over. Prioritise soft shelter here. Let the environment dictate pliable fibres that bend and adapt seamlessly. Reach for heavy silk or brushed cashmere. These materials absorb dim light and offer a muted surface under hand. Keep all metals cool and subdued. Avoid high-gloss synthetics that feel cold or slippery. Choose items that drape closely without restriction.",
      "sectionIntro": "Scale your choices for close proximity and low light.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Wait for your prescription at Boots in the exact same clothes you wear to a major meeting. An unpredictable day requires pliant worsted wool that can sprint across the train platform and a technical nylon shell that wards off sudden rain. Test the shoulder tension on that crisp cotton poplin shirt. If the seams restrict your arms, walk away. Your baseline remains constant. Hold fast to your formula, soft shelter + light movement + one sentimental keepsake, for every ordinary Tuesday. Anchor the look with stark navy and icy grey. Let your hands verify the weave before you buy.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your most mundane errands as the absolute proving ground for your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "To anchor a soft shelter, your hardware strategy must remain strictly cool. Select {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} to integrate cleanly with your wardrobe. Steer clear of any buckles or zips treated to look vintage. Scuffed bronze or oxidised copper creates unnecessary noise against your contemporary garments. Stick strictly to pristine, reflective surfaces. Pick up every watch, ring, or clasp before you commit. A polished exterior can fake quality, but physical density reveals the truth. Grasp a solid {metal_1} chain and register its cold heft. This heavy anchoring provides crucial contrast to garments designed for light movement. Ensure every fastening completely avoids {excluded_finish} textures.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as structural anchors, testing their temperature and density before you wear them.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Test the density of your gems. Hold the piece in your bare hand and gauge the gravitational pull. Let this solid weight anchor your light movement. Select dense, cool stones like {stone_1} and {stone_2} with a muted surface. Set these pieces exclusively in polished silver, solid platinum, white gold, or mirror chrome. Avoid any setting that mimics extreme age. Faux tarnishing and intentionally distressed borders act as visual clutter against a modern aesthetic. Keep your gemstone boundaries sharp to contrast against soft shelter cut from worsted wool or technical nylon.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your stones and metals by testing their physical density in your hand, relying on clean finishes to anchor your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Assess the structural integrity of your accessories. Evaluate the physical heft of every buckle or piece of jewellery directly. Heavily hammered alloys read as visual noise against your versatile foundation. Skip anything textured to resemble an antique. Instead, anchor the light movement of your garments with pristine, cool hardware. Lean entirely on {metal_1} or the pure clarity of {stone_1}. Trust this sheer physical presence to direct your choices. Sleek, polished finishes cut through the clutter and contrast sharply against matt fabrics, keeping your orientation balanced.",
      "sectionIntro": "Weigh your hardware in your palm before you attach it to your frame.",
      "tests": [
