    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You have secured your soft shelter. You know how to introduce light movement. Ground the outfit by selecting one sentimental keepsake. Keep your additions deliberate by restricting yourself to one or two focal items per look. Begin with silk scarves. Select a crepe de chine square or a slim band with a perfectly matt finish. Execute the friction test before committing to a purchase. Rub the folded silk slowly between your fingers and assess the cool weave. If the fabric catches against your worsted wool or feels excessively slippery next to technical nylon, reject it. Let physical resistance dictate your choice.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess your accessories with the exact same physical rigour you apply to your garments.",
