    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Evaluate fine jewellery using the glare test. Suspend a thin chain from your fingers and twist it slowly under a bright bulb. If the links throw sharp reflections, discard the piece. You require cool, brushed silver that absorbs harsh light. Seek small drops that introduce light movement over an icy grey worsted wool collar. A flat, muted finish provides necessary visual calm. If a clasp catches on your technical nylon jacket or resists sliding smoothly, it fails. Look for delicate pieces that sit quietly and rest seamlessly against your collarbone.",
