    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Finding soft shelter means giving your structured worsted wool pieces a geometric grounding. Let tailored items carry {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2}. Conversely, ensure light movement in your fluid nylon layers by choosing {recommended_pattern_3} or {recommended_pattern_4}. Your versatile approach requires an adaptive pattern contrast. Dial the contrast up to a crisp graphic division when you need sharp definition, or lower it to subtle tonal weaves for quiet days. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}. They agitate a cool palette and disrupt the visual balance. Apply the distance test to any new print. Hang the garment on a door and step back ten feet. If the motif dissolves into a muddy grey blur in the first split second, leave the garment behind. The design must remain distinct. Let your chosen sentimental keepsake sit against these clean patterns without fighting for visual space.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as a dial you turn up or down to suit the physical demands of the day.",
