      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "the all-earth sink: brown on olive on bark, all matt and all heavy, can swallow you whole",
          "fix": "lift it: an oatmeal cream layer at the collar, one piece of polished leather, or the washed blue relief"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, light movement takes the lead. Build your base with fluid silk blouses and dove grey trousers that drape freely. The gentle weight of brushed wool tailoring grounds this fluidity. Anchor the arrangement with a muted silver ring or a handed-down watch. Apply a strict rule to maintenance. A silk shirt waiting behind the counter at the dry cleaners does not excuse stiff cotton on a Tuesday morning. Keep enough deep teal and inky navy cashmere knitwear in reserve to ensure you never rely on inferior garments while your main pieces undergo care. Test the silk's fluid drop against your wrist. Inspect the stitching on your full-grain leather tote. If a piece requires constant pulling or adjustment during a meeting, discard it entirely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Maintain strict standards for your working garments and never settle for rigid alternatives.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low-light settings, shift your focus to deep, tactile layers. Reach for deep teal brushed wool or inky navy silk paired with a cool silver chain. Seek out muted surfaces that absorb the ambient shadows of a restaurant or theatre. Maintain your structural requirements here. A formal invitation does not justify enduring rigid waistbands or restrictive shoulders. If an evening piece pinches your collarbone or feels stiff across the back, leave it in the wardrobe.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the intimate environment by dressing for the immediate senses.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A quick errand to collect a parcel provides zero reason to compromise. Start a standard Thursday by selecting dove grey wool trousers and an inky navy knit. Layer a muted, full-grain leather jacket over the top. Demand quality from your practical staples. The heavy drape of a dense cotton tee will prove its worth in transit. Your daily protocol demands strict adherence, so ensure your clothing always equals soft shelter + light movement + one sentimental keepsake. Fasten a cool platinum chain at the collar. Require every finish to remain definitively matt.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your mundane routines with the same exacting precision you apply to your finest events.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your metal strategy relies on a strictly cool temperature to anchor your subdued garments. Lean heavily into {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} for both personal items and structural zips. Glossy, highly reflective hardware will slice right through your muted tones, creating a jarring distraction. Steer entirely clear of {excluded_finish}. Seek out matt, heavily brushed, or oxidised textures instead, maintaining a cohesive, quiet blend against your textiles. Examine every clasp directly. Lift a {metal_1} buckle to verify its density. Hollow alloys ruin a garment, whereas solid construction anchors the cloth properly. Sturdy structural hardware provides the exact grounding required when layering your soft shelter over light movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your hardware with the exact same strict discipline you apply to your silhouette.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Choose stones that absorb light rather than refract it. Select {stone_1} or {stone_2} in cool, muted tones to serve as your one sentimental keepsake. Press the mineral against your wrist. Genuine stone carries an unmistakable, lasting chill. Avoid faceted gems that scatter bright flashes across your clothing. A gleaming setting creates a sharp distraction next to your subdued hues. Demand heavy, unpolished bezels to keep the integration cohesive. A solid {stone_3} works perfectly here, resting quietly against the skin.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware choices through physical density and light absorption, treating stones as grounding tools.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Drop the {metal_1} clasp or {stone_1} ring onto a wooden table. Listen for a dull, resonant thud. Hollow costume pieces clatter, while genuine, dense materials announce their quality through sound. Avoid high-gloss chrome entirely. A mirror polish creates a harsh glare against subdued colours. Select strictly cool, matt surfaces to integrate your hardware seamlessly. Your baseline of soft shelter demands this level of tactile harmony. Rely on substantial weight and understated textures to properly anchor the garment.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply this physical test to ensure your hardware anchors your garments properly.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your accessories fulfill the final term of your formula. They provide that one sentimental keepsake to crown your foundation of soft shelter and light movement. Enforce a strict limit of one or two structured pieces per look. For handbags, demand dense full-grain leather constructed with heavy, buffed matt hardware. Put every potential item through the shadow test. Place the piece in a dim corner and verify that it maintains a quiet, cool depth within your outfit, functioning like a single piece of slate anchoring a flowing stream.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every accessory through physical touch and dense weight before wearing it.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Handbags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather, brushed matt hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-ember test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Look for scarves in fluid silk or fine brushed wool. Avoid high shine and demand a completely matt finish. Scrutinise every deep teal or dove grey textile for absolute colour consistency. Require light movement from the drape. Wrap it around your neck and confirm that the material falls cleanly to provide soft shelter over the collarbone. Judge the fibres by running them across the back of your hand. A premium weave glides without scratching. Flimsy blends snag and resist.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject your secondary accessories to strict material evaluations before they touch your skin.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "silk or fine wool, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-ember test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor the waist with a medium full-grain leather belt. Inspect the hardware closely, requiring an entirely matt buckle that refuses to catch the light. Introduce keepsake jewellery next. Seek out aged silver and oxidised finishes that feel definitively cool and heavy in the palm. Treat these metals as grounding weights within your soft shelter. Perform a final visual check in the mirror. Scan the outfit for competing focal points. If an oxidised ring and a belt buckle fight for attention, the balance fractures. Remove the louder item. Keep exactly one quiet point of interest against the dove grey cloth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your foundation with strict metallic rules, then test the final result.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "medium full-grain leather, matt buckle"
        },
        {
          "name": "Keepsake jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "aged silver, oxidised"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-ember test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored garments must draw their pattern from the physical weave of the cloth. Rely on {recommended_pattern_1} to construct soft shelter against the elements. Fluid silk garments dictate a different approach. Channel their light movement through low-contrast tonal prints like {recommended_pattern_2}. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and any rigid {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. Keep all pattern contrast strictly subtle. Apply the twilight test to every woven piece. Drape the fabric beside a shaded lamp to verify that the motif deepens and absorbs the cool shadows, sinking quietly into the cloth. If the design jumps out sharply, discard the garment. Your chosen patterns must remain understated, blending into a unified, matt block of texture from a few steps away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Pattern introduces visual rhythm, but you must tightly govern its contrast to protect the integrity of the cloth.",
      "tests": [
        "the firelight test (deepen and warm by lamplight)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Subject any {recommended_pattern_1} to a strict distance evaluation. Hang the garment across the room and step ten paces back. A successful weave blurs its edges, receding completely into the textile. It must never read as a loud graphic block from afar. Artificial store lighting creates artificial contrast. Natural shadow strips away the noise. Build soft shelter only with patterns that quietly dissolve into a cool, solid plane as you walk away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every pattern to a strict low-light inspection before committing.",
      "tests": [
        "the firelight test (deepen and warm by lamplight)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_cancer__moon_leo__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "soft shelter + athletic space + one sentimental keepsake",
    "closing": "Navigate by gravity, temperature, and touch, letting every choice reinforce your foundation of soft shelter + athletic space + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe with glacial patience. Acquire garments slowly, then dress with absolute speed. Trust the physical instinct of withdrawal as your compass. When you pick up a piece, assess its weight and interior finish. If the lining feels harsh against your skin or the silhouette demands constant adjustment, leave it on the rail. Your structural blueprint relies entirely on soft shelter + athletic space + one sentimental keepsake. Let this equation dictate every purchase. You are not dressing for an audience. You are engineering a self-contained, cool climate. Look for matt surfaces that absorb light rather than reflect it.\n\nPicture an enveloping overcoat worn over wide-leg technical trousers and a small inherited pendant. This combination succeeds because it provides physical insulation, grants absolute freedom of movement, and grounds the look with a private focal point. Execute the wrist test to guarantee this mobility before buying. Extend both arms straight out in front of you. If the cuff binds your joint or the shoulder seams pull tight, the garment fails. True luxury in your system lies in the total absence of friction. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Restriction does not.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural foundation, the set of immutable physical laws that govern how you assemble garments.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe around fibres that offer a true soft shelter. When you pick up a garment, apply the collapse test. Hold the piece by the collar and drop it onto a flat surface. If the fabric holds a rigid shape, walk away. You need materials that immediately pool into a cool, heavy puddle. Seek {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Use {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Rely on {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Finally, choose {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. These specific fabrics grant you the necessary athletic space to move while keeping your presentation entirely contained. Prioritise this list.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to verify the physical integrity of a fabric before you ever put it on.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Washed silk",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cloud-soft lambswool",
