    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pick up {texture_bad_1} and squeeze it in your fist. If it crushes into rigid peaks rather than settling into cool, matt lines, reject the item. Fabrics must yield and drape without trapping you. Brush {texture_bad_2} against your collarbone. If it scratches or catches, it fails the baseline standard for your physical ease. You require materials that move softly around your body. Never accept hard boundaries. A stiff weave or a raspy cuff will clash instantly against that one sentimental keepsake you keep close. Visuals deceive. Only tactile feedback matters.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject the materials that compromise your comfort.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Anchor your daily wear in the tension between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing creates your ideal soft shelter. Trust your hands when assessing a weave. Gauge the mass instead of staring at the cut. Drop the piece onto a table. Watch how it yields. If it retains a hollow, stiff structure, abandon it. The proper {texture_good_1} will sink immediately into a heavy, fluid puddle. Demand this exact drape. It ensures your clothing acts as a quiet retreat from outside noise. Combine a muted, cool finish with a dense weave to lock in this self-contained state.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact combination of weight and drape to form your foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is resolutely cool. Ground your base with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_3}. Anchor them with the deep structure of {core_colour_2}. Reach for {core_colour_4} when a pale neutral is required. Avoid hard black, harsh neon, and heavy earth brown. They disrupt your self-contained presentation. Apply {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} strictly as your single deliberate accent. Treat your relief tone as a quiet, sparing note. Beware the trap of swaddling. Stacking shapeless pieces makes your silhouette vanish into a blur. Correct this error by restoring a sharp boundary. Reveal a structured collar, fold back a crisp cuff, or let a pendant drop visibly at the neckline. These precise lines allow you to construct a soft shelter that retains its architecture.",
