    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, let soft shelter dictate your primary garments. Choose a deep teal boiled wool blazer or a heavy silk crepe tunic that forms a quiet, cool boundary. Support this leading element with generous room in your dove grey trousers. A chaotic morning commute does not mean you abandon proportion. Keep your silhouette deliberate. Trust your own muscles and joints to tell you what fits. If a sleeve restricts your reach, drop the garment immediately. Mirrors deceive, but tangible comfort is absolute. Finalise the uniform with a single matt silver heirloom ring to ground your presentation.",
