      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pinch the fabric tightly. If it refuses to collapse into a soft puddle and instead fights your grip, let it go. Your wardrobe requires cool, matt surfaces that breathe and yield. Avoid {texture_bad_1} entirely. It carries a flat, dead shine that traps heat and feels stiff on the body. Drop {texture_bad_2} if the threads catch on rough skin or rustle when you bend your arm. These rigid materials betray the quiet luxury you are building. Only choose textiles that drape silently and provide a calm backdrop for one sentimental keepsake.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and reject failing fabrics before you even reach the fitting room.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing creates your ideal soft shelter. Examine every new piece manually. Gather the cloth into a tight ball. It must soften in your palm rapidly. If it stays rigid, put it back. You require a matt surface that gives slightly under pressure. Introduce {texture_good_1} in a cool shade to ground the softer elements. Rely entirely on touch. A textile's actual heft reveals its quality far better than its appearance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your signature tactile pairing by relying strictly on touch.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in cool tones. Build a foundation using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Treat {core_colour_4} as your light neutral substitute. Introduce your single deliberate accent via {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Deploy the relief tone purely as a soft note used sparingly near the collar. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon. Watch for the sofa drift. If you relax the structure of every piece, you end up dressed for a nap. Correct this by restoring one architectural line. Choose a legitimate rolled lapel, trousers retaining a gentle crease, or a rigid leather bag to frame the yielding materials. This single firm boundary guarantees your soft shelter and cool composure remain intact.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your colours by assigning each tone a strict physical job.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Deep teal",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
