          "role": "relief"
        }
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "the sofa drift: soften every piece far enough and one day you are simply in loungewear",
          "fix": "restore exactly one line: a rolled but real lapel, a trouser with a soft crease, or a firm leather bag against all that give"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, cool composure dictates your baseline. Build this foundation with a structured deep teal jacket or a firm inky navy full-grain leather tote. These pieces communicate focus, but they require a soft shelter to preserve your physical equilibrium. Layer a dove grey silk blouse or a fine cashmere knit closest to the skin. Base these selections on touch. Sight is easily fooled. Heft is absolute. Run the pharmacy test before leaving the house. If standing under harsh fluorescent lights waiting for a prescription at the end of a long Tuesday feels physically punishing, change your outfit immediately. You do not suffer for an aesthetic. Finish the look with a sentimental silver pendant tucked beneath your collar.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your working hours in garments that perform without restriction and demand zero physical compromise.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, soft shelter leads. Rely on your tactile senses rather than the mirror. Utilise the heavy drape of inky navy cashmere or the matt finish of dove grey silk. Avoid garments that demand constant fussing. If an evening piece requires you to adjust a waistband or tug a hem while queueing at a dimly lit cloakroom, discard it immediately. Discomfort serves no aesthetic purpose. Keep your colour choices muted and your overall palette cool. Finish the outfit with a single sentimental piece of jewellery in muted white gold or silver. Feel the cold metal against your skin before putting it on. Let tactile ease and dark fabrics anchor you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Navigate intimate environments by letting your tactile instincts dictate your choices.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Dress for a standard Tuesday morning. Running local errands should never involve restrictive waistbands or stiff outerwear. Reach for an inky navy cashmere sweater and a muted brushed wool coat. Add a simple silver chain. Maintain your baseline by keeping strictly to soft shelter + cool composure + one sentimental keepsake. Let the matt finishes and cool tones handle the visual weight. Rely on deep teal layers that yield when you bend and stretch. Choose full-grain leather boots that soften and support your instep over time.",
      "sectionIntro": "Prepare for ordinary routines with the exact same precision you apply to grand occasions.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your hardware strategy relies on a cool, dominant palette. Restrict your selections to {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} for everything from daily jewellery to jacket zips. These muted tones anchor your cool composure. High-shine, reflective pieces create a sharp, jarring distraction next to subdued colours. You must avoid {excluded_finish} finishes entirely. Always demand a matt or brushed surface to keep the visual field cohesive. Pick the item up and test its heft in your palm. Appearance deceives, but gravity reveals the truth of the cast. Solid metal grounds a soft shelter. Heavy, unpolished hardware ensures the structure of your garments remains secure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the hardware that fastens and finishes your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select {stone_1} and {stone_2} to anchor your cool composure. Avoid mirror-gloss hardware that glares and distracts next to subdued clothing. Choose brushed or matt metal settings to keep the entire arrangement cohesive. Evaluate the stone by its physical weight. A genuine mineral asserts its mass directly in your hand. Demand stones that absorb the ambient light rather than casting sharp reflections. Choose opaque, domed cuts over faceted crystals. Let this quiet, heavy density rest exactly at your collar.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select heavy, opaque stones that ground your uniform rather than distract from it.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold the hardware blindly. If the {metal_1} feels hollow or light, leave it on the tray. Do not rely on surface appearance. Avoid highly reflective finishes entirely. Brilliant, mirror-like surfaces create harsh, glaring interruptions against muted fabrics. They fracture the visual continuity of your soft shelter. Demand heavily brushed or purely matt {metal_1} to secure your cool composure. This guarantees a seamless transition between the woven fibres of your clothing and the solid mass of your accessories.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate the physical reality of every piece before it joins your collection.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Clothing builds soft shelter. Layering maintains cool composure. Accessories complete the equation by providing one sentimental keepsake. Limit your selection severely. Choose one or two strong pieces per look. Start the evaluation with handbags. Seek thick full-grain leather mounted with brushed matt hardware. Apply the ripple test before buying. Press your thumb firmly into the hide. High-quality skins break into tiny, soft waves around the pressure point. Corrected surfaces merely dent and spring back. Rely on this tactile feedback. A rigid coating deceives the eye. The structural yield tells the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate accessories through strict physical testing, limiting your selection to items of absolute material integrity.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Handbags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather, brushed matt hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Rely on matt silk and fine wool scarves to provide soft shelter. Put the fabric through the pool test. Gather the ends in your fist and let the length drop onto a flat surface. Watch how the peaks and valleys catch the overhead bulb. A successful textile drinks the light. A failing textile throws back a sharp glare. Reject high-shine satins. You require muted finishes that absorb light darkly in a cool colour like deep teal. The material must carry enough physical weight to drape heavily over a lapel, staying exactly where you place it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject your fabric accessories to the exact same physical scrutiny as your garments.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "silk or fine wool, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Choose belts cut from medium full-grain leather. Demand a strictly matt buckle. For jewellery, seek out aged silver and oxidised pieces. These finishes project cool composure without fighting the structure of your deep teal and inky navy garments. Keep the metals subdued. Finally, check for visual friction. Scan the silhouette from collar to hem. If a gleaming buckle or polished ring creates a sharp reflection that breaks the muted fluidity of your clothes, remove the piece immediately. The details must dissolve into the whole.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your grounding accessories and execute the final visual check.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "medium full-grain leather, matt buckle"
        },
        {
          "name": "Keepsake jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "aged silver, oxidised"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Rely on physical sensation as your primary guide to pattern. Appearance deceives. Substance matters. Enforce a strict low-contrast tonal rule across your wardrobe to maintain a matt, muted finish. Tailored garments take their pattern from the structural weave of the cloth. Fluid garments take theirs from subtle dye variations. Select {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} for their understated depth. Pass over anything high-contrast or demanding. Reject {avoid_pattern_1} entirely. Apply the dusk test when evaluating a new motif. Notice if the visual rhythm allows you to settle into a cool, moving texture as daylight fades. If the pattern disrupts this peace, leave the garment on the rack. Seek subtle motifs that build soft shelter while projecting cool composure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master pattern by treating it as an extension of texture, never a distraction from it.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Test prints in failing light. Hang the garment in a dim room, turn off the overhead bulb, and step back three paces. Watch how the motif behaves in the shadows. A successful {recommended_pattern_1} will lose its sharp boundaries and dissolve into a matt, atmospheric wash. Trust your own vision as the environment darkens. If the design remains starkly defined and refuses to blur, leave it on the rack. You are aiming to build soft shelter through muted blending. Avoid any graphic focal point that demands immediate attention. The motif must recede into quiet depth. This subtle integration maintains cool composure, ensuring the print reads as a textural surface rather than a sharp shape.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use this visual test to ensure a print will recede gracefully rather than demand attention.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_cancer__moon_sagittarius__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "soft shelter + fast movement + one sentimental keepsake",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on soft shelter + fast movement + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. Your aesthetic requires a cool temperature and a matt finish. Rely on the immediate sensation of fabric against skin rather than visual noise. Build your wardrobe slowly, scrutinising every seam and weave in isolation. When you actually dress, deploy fast. Drift by your daily mood rather than rigid occasions. Your core style formula is soft shelter + fast movement + one sentimental keepsake. Picture a dense wool overcoat worn open over a frictionless athletic layer, grounded by an inherited ring. The outer layer protects, the inner layer allows immediate action, and the detail remains entirely self-contained.\n\nKeep your presentation closed off from outside influence. Apply the melt test to every potential purchase. Put the garment on, close your eyes, and stand perfectly still. The piece must dissolve into your physical awareness until you forget you are wearing it. If the fabric resists your natural stance, or if a stiff collar demands your attention, leave it on the hanger. A heavy hem or a rigid cuff will only disrupt your focus. Choose items that let you move silently and efficiently. If you have to adjust a sleeve during the day, the garment has failed. Trust your hands to know the difference.",
      "sectionIntro": "Start here to calibrate your physical instincts and define the strict rules of engagement for your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe on fabrics that offer soft shelter and permit fast movement. Seek out {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Rely on {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Choose {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Layer over it all with {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. Before purchasing, apply the collapse test. Drop the garment onto a table and watch how it settles. If it holds a rigid shape, leave it behind. The material must pool into a cool, liquid puddle.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to evaluate fabrics before you ever try them on.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Washed silk",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cloud-soft lambswool",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Heavy silk crepe",
          "role": "rank 3",
