    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Subject the fabric to a severe physical check. Crush the yardage in your fist and release it. If it springs back into an unyielding, harsh structure, it offers no defensive boundary. Reject {texture_bad_1} immediately. The physical tell is an abrasive, slick slide against your skin, a sensation that ruins your cool baseline. Avoid {texture_bad_2} entirely. Rely on your touch to identify surfaces that snag or drag. Your strategy depends on protective layers and rapid transit, anchored by one sentimental keepsake. Leave {texture_bad_3} on the rail if the threads feel stiff or brittle. Anything that compromises your self-contained system is a liability. Visuals deceive. Demand that every fibre proves its worth through sheer tactile comfort.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the materials that actively work against your baseline.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your core tension relies on pairing {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Use {texture_good_1} to construct a soft shelter. Test every piece before buying. Gather the material in your arms and let it slip through your fingers. It must fall into a dense, quiet shape, retaining zero architecture of its own. If the shoulders sit up or the sleeves form a hollow tube, walk away. Stiff materials demand attention. You require discreet, heavy drape. Look for items that drop cleanly, showing only a cool, matt surface.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact tension between your defining materials.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Establish your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_3}. Assign {core_colour_2} to dense, structured tailoring. Swap stark whites for {core_colour_4} to ensure a matt finish. Bring in {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} solely as deliberate accents, perhaps in a silk tie or leather glove. Deploy your relief tone, a soft note used sparingly, to gently lift dark layers. Keep every shade strictly cool. Ignore Hard black, Harsh neon, and Heavy earth brown. Beware the sofa drift. Pushing the softness of every item too far leaves you wearing loungewear. Correct this immediately. Reintroduce exactly one crisp line. A rolled but structured lapel, a trouser with a definite crease, or a rigid leather bag cuts through the softness, providing the structure necessary for fast movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your palette to guarantee every item works together without hesitation.",
