    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Make soft shelter the lead element of your working hours. Layer a heavy silk crepe blouse or a dove grey boiled wool blazer to create a physical buffer. Support this boundary with pieces engineered for fast movement. Cut your trousers so you can walk with sudden speed without restriction. Pin a single inherited silver ring inside your lapel to serve as your grounding anchor. Test your consistency when leaving the office. Running to the bakery for a midday loaf must never force a drop in your cool, muted presence. Keep your deep teal layers closed and preserve your self-contained perimeter, even on a brief walk down the street.",
