    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light and close quarters, let soft shelter take the lead. Trust the heavy drape of silk crepe in deep teal. It absorbs the dim room without reflecting a glare. Keep the temperature strictly cool. A white gold chain works best here, gleaming faintly rather than flashing. Never break your cool mist just because the setting changes. Checking the post at dawn requires the exact same muted, unreadable perimeter as a midnight supper. Wrap a dove grey boiled wool coat over the silk. Feel the heavy yarn drop precisely into place to secure your boundary. Gravity confirms quality. Leave stark contrasts behind.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your perimeter when the lights go down.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Collecting a prescription does not mean stepping outside your muted atmosphere. Measure every morning choice by verifying it delivers soft shelter + fast movement + one sentimental keepsake. Choose deep teal washed silk trousers. Pick up a cloud-soft lambswool sweater and put it on. Assess the drape in the mirror. It must feel completely private. It must allow you to walk briskly down the pavement. Anchor the fabrics with a cool silver pendant you never remove. Do not downgrade this standard for a quick dash to the pharmacist.",
      "sectionIntro": "Dictate your own environment from the moment you step outside.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Execute a strictly cool metal strategy. Rely entirely on {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Refuse any {excluded_finish} surfaces completely. Treat hardware as an architectural detail rather than decoration. Lift every chain, zip, and buckle in your palm before buying. Appearance deceives, but gravity tells the truth. A high-shine, mirror-polished clasp creates a sharp, distracting glare against your muted colours. Secure your soft shelter strictly with matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware with the same ruthlessness you apply to your fabrics.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Target stones that absorb light rather than scatter it. Bright, faceted cuts pierce through muted cool tones, generating unwanted visual noise. Stick to flat, raw, or heavily brushed settings so the whole combination stays visually unified. When evaluating {stone_1} or {stone_2}, hold the piece directly against your skin. A twinkling facet often misleads the eye, but undeniable physical density reveals true quality. Heavy, opaque stones provide the grounding anchor required for your soft shelter. Opt for gems with an internal, cloudy depth rather than clear, icy brilliance. Secure a dense {stone_3} to lock the visual field down.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate hardware by its physical density and its ability to absorb light.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Lift a {metal_1} cuff or a coat zip from the table. Let the object drop into your palm to gauge its sheer substance. Flimsy hardware betrays a garment instantly. Highly reflective finishes look jarring and break focus beside your cool, muted layers. A bright gleam distracts from the quiet depth of a {core_colour_2} wool collar. Correct this by demanding dulled and tarnished effects for all fastenings. A subdued surface keeps the visual narrative cohesive. Rely on this solid, unpolished density to ground the soft shelter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess every piece of hardware before it touches your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Wrap yourself in soft shelter. Maintain space to allow fast movement. Now, ground the entire composition with one sentimental keepsake. Limit your additions strictly to one or two strong pieces per look. Start by evaluating your handbags. Seek out dense full-grain leather or thick suede, anchored by cool, matt brushed hardware. Always apply the ripple test. Fold an empty corner of the hide over your knuckle and press down. If the surface splinters into tiny, stiff wrinkles, drop the bag. It must roll back in a smooth, heavy wave.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your rules for selecting the precise hardware and leather structures required to anchor your garments.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Handbags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather or thick suede, matt brushed hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select generous scarves of washed silk or fine lambswool to act as soft shelter against the cool. Keep the finish strictly matt. Never buy a piece without applying the suspension test. Hold the textile by one corner and observe how it hangs. It should drape quietly like a deep teal curtain, settling into heavy, fluid columns. If the fabric catches the light or holds a rigid peak, leave it behind. You require pieces that yield completely to your physical form.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject your final layers to strict physical scrutiny before they touch your neck.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "generous silk or fine wool, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Secure wide full-grain leather belts featuring a matt brushed buckle. Turn to keepsake jewellery with absolute physical density. Pick up a ring with a deep stone set in oxidised, aged silver or brass. Trust the heavy weight of the metal in your palm. This solid, cool element provides an anchor for the pliable fabrics that construct a soft shelter and enable fast movement. Run the surface disruption test. Stand in front of a mirror and view your silhouette as a still pool of water. If a buckle or a stone creates a jarring visual flash across the quiet fabric, take the item off immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use these final details to ground your layers, and aggressively edit anything that breaks the calm.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "wide full-grain leather, matt brushed buckle"
        },
        {
          "name": "Keepsake jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "deep stone set in aged silver or brass, oxidised"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored garments take their pattern directly from the weave. Fluid pieces draw it from the dye. Enforce a strict low-contrast, tonal rule across all your choices. Quiet luxury demands that a motif recedes into the background. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} to create soft shelter. Pass over stark outlines, sharp geometric repeats, and any high-contrast graphic. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} on the hanger. Apply the dusk test to every print. Settle the fabric in fading light. The print must blur into a cool, moving texture. If the shapes stay harsh in the shadows, they will snag your fast movement. Drop the piece.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as an extension of texture, never as an applied decoration.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Verify your prints in motion. Put the patterned garment on and walk rapidly past a long mirror. A successful {recommended_pattern_1} will lose its sharp borders and dissolve into a cool, matt shadow. The motif must blur into a single wash of colour during fast movement. Rely on this kinetic feedback to approve or reject a design. If the pattern stays stark and demands attention as you walk, discard it. Your textures must retreat into the cloth, never announcing themselves before you do.",
      "sectionIntro": "Run this visual check to vet any new pattern before buying.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_cancer__moon_scorpio__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "soft shelter + quiet undercurrent + one sentimental keepsake",
    "closing": "Trust your physical instincts to judge the weight of every piece, retaining only the cool, matt garments that successfully build your soft shelter + quiet undercurrent + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Assess the weight and temperature of a garment before you try it on. Your instinct operates on touch and structural precision. Run your hands over the seams and gauge how the material drops. A piece must feel cool and substantial to pass your filter. If a garment reflects light instead of absorbing it, or if it disrupts your sense of quiet containment, drop the item and walk out. Looks lie. Weight does not.\n\nBase every outfit on this exact equation: soft shelter + quiet undercurrent + one sentimental keepsake. Picture this. An unstructured, heavyweight topcoat worn over a fine knit, anchored by a single heavy ring. Build your wardrobe slowly, vetting every seam and finish. Deploy these garments fast. When the foundation is matt and precise, you never have to second-guess the execution.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the core logic of your wardrobe before you acquire another piece.",
      "tests": [
        "trust your gut and walk away"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your soft shelter with cool materials that carry a matt finish and keep your physical boundaries intact. Always perform the collapse test before buying. Drop the garment onto a hard surface. If it holds an empty shape, leave it. If it falls into a heavy puddle, it will serve you. Let your hands dictate the purchase. Demand {texture_good_1} for heavy knitwear that compresses under your grip and springs back. Seek out {texture_good_2} for shoes and bags that mould to your posture over time. Build your quiet undercurrent with {texture_good_3} to hold the sharp lines of a tailored coat. Keep {texture_good_4} close to the skin for fluid linings. Prioritise the materials on this list.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to read fabric weight before you ever look at a garment label.",
