    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Crush the fabric in your fist. If it falls into a deflated, lifeless heap when you open your hand, it fails. You need materials that stand up on their own. Avoid {texture_bad_1}. It feels slick and traps heat against your skin, turning clammy by midday. Reject {texture_bad_2}. It catches on rough skin and frays whenever it rubs against your one sentimental keepsake. Take a sleeve of {texture_bad_3} and rub the surface between your thumb and forefinger. If it squeaks or creates a static shock, leave it on the hanger. You require quiet, matt materials that absorb sound and light, never stiff plastics that broadcast your movements.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify the inferior materials that will fail against your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to engineer your soft shelter. Ground the pairing with {texture_good_1}. Test the drape of every item before you commit. Throw the fabric across a chair. Stiff fibres pitch into hollow peaks, while the correct weave settles into a dense, silent mass. Choose the mass. Keep cool tones completely matt to trap the light. Build a self-contained wardrobe by letting your tactile response make the final ruling.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to combine your core fabrics into a coherent physical system.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Maintain a strictly cool foundation. Ground your base in {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Substitute {core_colour_4} whenever an outfit requires a lighter neutral. Bring in your relief tone purely as a soft note used sparingly near the face. Introduce a single deliberate accent, selecting either {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} to hold focus. Leave hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon on the rack. They overwhelm a matt spectrum. Dressing in unbroken black from top to bottom signals a surrendered morning. Fracture that void immediately. Drape a {core_colour_2} cashmere jumper over the shoulders, knot a {accent_colour_1} silk scarf, or secure a {core_colour_3} full-grain leather belt. Keep the rules strict to build a true soft shelter.",
