    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on soft shelter + sensory comfort + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Curate your collection with glacial patience. Acquire garments slowly and deliberately. When it is time to dress, move fast and drift by mood. Trust the physical architecture of the clothes to do the work. Your stylistic mandate is soft shelter + sensory comfort + one sentimental keepsake. Picture a dense wrap coat worn over fluid, lined trousers, finished with an inherited ring. Anchor your choices in a cool palette. Keep every surface entirely matt. Your clothes must act as an inward retreat. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.\n\nTo guarantee absolute ease, apply the wrist test. Slide your hand through the cuff of a heavy sweater and assess the immediate friction. A self-contained wardrobe demands zero irritation at the boundaries. If the hem binds your joint or the knit disrupts your internal focus, abandon the garment. Evaluate construction with your eyes closed. Run your fingers over the interior seams of a tailored jacket and assess the drape against your shoulder. If a piece requires constant adjustment, it fails the mandate. You dress strictly for your own private sanctuary, never for the observer.",
