    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Seek out the physical tension between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Pick up {texture_good_1} and test the density. Press the cloth over your mouth and exhale firmly. If you feel a draft on your palm, put the item down. You require complete insulation, a true soft shelter built from heavy yarns and matt surfaces. Combine a dense pile with a smooth grain to anchor your shape. Keep your finishes subdued and cool. You dress to enclose your own boundaries. Trust the absolute mass of the material in your hands to build that quiet, self-contained space.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control the physical friction between your materials to enforce a self-contained boundary.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Maintain an entirely cool temperature across your garments. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Swap stark shades for {core_colour_4} as your dependable light base. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} when you require a single deliberate accent. Treat your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly to break up solid blocks. Bypass Hot saturated red, Stark optic white, and Harsh neon. Watch out for the swaddling trap. Wrapping yourself in endless layers of shapeless grey will dissolve your silhouette completely. Correct this immediately. Restore a single defined line to the outfit. Expose a neat cuff, add a crisp structured collar, or let a cherished pendant sit visibly at the neckline. This discipline guarantees sensory comfort while retaining shape.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat this exact sequence of tones as the structural blueprint for your wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Deep teal",
          "role": "cool_base"
