    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject anything that feels rigid or brittle in the hand. Pull a length of {texture_bad_1} taut and release it. If it rebounds with a harsh, rubbery snap, leave it on the hanger. Your clothes must yield to your shape. Avoid {texture_bad_2} that squeaks when pinched. It traps heat and creates an unyielding shell rather than adapting to you. Run your palm over {texture_bad_3}. If it feels slick and coats your fingers in a static charge, it fails the test. These aggressive textiles will catch on your one sentimental keepsake and disrupt your self-contained silhouette. Trust your physical instinct. Shop mirrors deceive. Gravity tells the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every textile against your own senses before you let it near your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the snap test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Perform the tension check on every new garment. Pinch a fold of {texture_good_1}, stretch it firmly, and drop your hold. It must recoil into a clean profile immediately. Sluggish recovery means weak yarn. Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to construct your necessary soft shelter. Ground these responsive weaves with matt hardware and cool tones. Trust your fingers completely. Glass reflections distort reality. The immediate rebound of the cloth never will.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify the precise surface tension that works for your environment.",
      "tests": [
        "the snap test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is decisively cool. Trust your own immediate reaction to a hue. Illumination deceives. Your eyes know the truth. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} as your primary base. Rely on {core_colour_3} as your strict white substitute, using {core_colour_4} as your heavy dark element. Deploy {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} strictly as single deliberate focal points. Introduce the relief tone sparingly as a quiet note to break up solid blocks. Reject mustard, rust, and warm olive green entirely. Leave them on the rack. Avoid the trap of an unvarying single shade that loses its appeal before lunch. Break the monotony immediately. Add a stark poplin collar, a matt structural silver ring, or a vivid geometric trainer. This sharp disruption provides essential contrast whenever you wear a soft shelter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assign every hue a strict job, treating your palette as a precise tool.",
