    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Bring deliberate preparation to your desk. At work, soft shelter leads. Materials like crisp cotton poplin and worsted wool provide necessary structure. Keep your palette disciplined in stark navy and icy grey. An honest fabric guarantees your garments will hold their form through long hours of sitting. A sentimental keepsake supports this utility as a purely private detail, a cool, matt metal object worn out of sight. Run your fingers over every seam. Rely on the physical weight of fine ribbed merino to maintain its shape. If an item requires constant adjustment, leave it behind.",
      "sectionIntro": "Prepare for your desk with the precision of selecting practical equipment.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dimly lit dining rooms, honest fabric leads your strategy. Visual noise disappears in the shadows, so rely on the tactile reality of worsted wool or fine ribbed merino against your skin. Keep your palette cool and muted. Stark navy and icy grey absorb dim light rather than reflecting it. Check how the cloth behaves when you lean across a small table. If a garment requires perpetual smoothing, leave it on the hanger. Opt for pieces that let you remain entirely self-contained. Apply this exact rigor universally. A crisp cotton poplin shirt worn under technical nylon demands the same attention to cloth as a midnight dinner. A matt steel ring catches low light just as effectively as evening candlelight.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat close-quarters environments as a prompt to pull focus inward rather than projecting outward.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Do not let a sudden trip to the pharmacy dilute your presentation. Buying root vegetables remains a distinct occasion. Dress for it. Anchor every morning in soft shelter + honest fabric + one sentimental keepsake, regardless of your destination. Maintain your internal logic across all hours of the week. Evaluate every item by how it operates through mundane tasks. If a stiff twill coat restricts your arms while carrying heavy boxes, discard it. Seek out dense worsted wool trousers that bend without buckling. Rely on icy grey knitted layers to anchor your cool palette from dawn until dusk. Choose a silver chain with a matt finish to conclude the daily uniform.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your daily baseline as a strict, non-negotiable floor.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Establish your cool hardware baseline with {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. These icy elements secure your garments without competing for attention. Exclude {excluded_finish} entirely. Lift every ring, zip, and buckle before you buy. Assess the mass in your hands. A dense zip grounds your soft shelter. Flimsy hardware compromises your self-contained boundaries. Avoid pre-tarnished alloys, hammered copper, and artificially weathered brass. They introduce unnecessary visual clutter into a clean system. Fix this error by seeking out pristine {metal_1}, crisp platinum, and mirror-smooth {metal_2} in a flat, matt finish. The right metal acts as a silent structural anchor.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your hardware to serve as silent utility, testing every piece for genuine physical density.",
      "tests": [
