    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select dense minerals that hold light rather than scattering it. Evaluate {stone_1} or {stone_2} in unadorned settings. Lift the jewellery off the table. Weigh the piece in your palm. Density cannot be faked. A heavy stone provides a grounding point that pairs perfectly with an honest fabric. Reject intentionally weathered copper, darkened brass, and faux-vintage metals. These manufactured patinas read as noise against a modern wardrobe. Correct this immediately by choosing highly polished silver, solid platinum, pure white gold, or reflective chrome. These bright, cool elements cut cleanly through muted garments. Finish your uniform with a single sentimental keepsake cast in these sharp metals.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your stones and metals by their physical weight, selecting hardware that reinforces your self-contained discipline.",
