    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold every clasp and link before making a decision. The eyes will miss what the hands instantly grasp. A weighty piece provides a grounding anchor when worn over your soft shelter. Steer clear of blackened hardware and faux-vintage patinas. These elements introduce visual clutter that disrupts a present-tense aesthetic. Anchor any honest fabric with dense, uncompromised {metal_1} instead. Keep the surface crisp and cool. Restrict your hardware to sleek mirror polishes or a clean {stone_1} that catches light precisely. Treat your supporting details as carefully as your chosen sentimental keepsake.",
