    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Scale your pattern contrast to your immediate context. You need versatile adaptability. Let tailored worsted wool carry strict, architectural lines like {recommended_pattern_1}. Allow your fluid garments to take organic movement from {recommended_pattern_2}. Anchor these printed pieces with soft shelter and let solid honest fabric do the heavy lifting everywhere else. Subject every motif to a harsh visibility test. Step back ten feet and shut your eyes. When you snap them open, the shapes must remain sharply defined in that first split second. If the design bleeds into a muddy, confusing wash, abandon the garment entirely. Pass over any motif that dictates the rest of the outfit. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as a dial you turn to adapt to your environment.",
