      "text": "Subject any piece of {recommended_pattern_1} to the distance check. Hang the garment across the room. Close your eyes, count to three, and open them for a split second. The shape must register immediately. If the print reads as an ambiguous blur, drop the hanger. You require a self-contained system where every item pulls its own visual weight. A successful design remains crisp from a distance. It should reinforce your soft shelter and complement your cool palette rather than introducing static. Trust this immediate instinct. Optic reality never lies.",
      "sectionIntro": "Run every printed garment through a strict visual calibration.",
