  "venus_capricorn__moon_aries__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "enduring structure + sharp edges + one living texture",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on enduring structure + sharp edges + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe slowly over years and deploy it fast when required. Trust the physical weight of a garment against your skin as your primary compass. Pick up a piece of tailoring and assess its density. If the fabric feels flimsy, chaotic or requires constant adjustment, leave it on the rail. You require heavy, matt textiles that absorb light and hold their shape independently of your body. Let a warm temperature anchor this discipline. When evaluating a new piece, rely on an immediate physical boundary. If a garment demands that you adapt to its construction, trust your gut and walk away.\n\nExecute your core formula every time you dress. That formula is enduring structure + sharp edges + one living texture. Picture a heavy wool overcoat cut with exact, geometric shoulders, layered over a crisp poplin shirt, finished with a brushed suede boot. The silhouette remains contained, rigorous and completely private. Look for garments that create a clear boundary between you and the outside world. Trust your hands to verify the finish. Every surface must be muted, refusing to reflect light. If an outfit lacks that single, tactile living element to ground the sharp geometry, start again.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this architectural blueprint to anchor every sartorial decision you make.",
      "tests": [
        "trust your gut and walk away"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in enduring structure. Trust your hands to assess every fibre. Squeeze a {texture_good_1} jumper. It must compress and bounce back instantly. A {texture_good_2} bag needs enough density to map to your grip and patinate over the years. Demand a {texture_good_3} blazer that holds sharp edges without sagging. Contrast these rigid frameworks with one living texture. A {texture_good_4} blouse provides fluid movement against dense fabrics. Examine the garment under a dim, warm bulb. Verify the surface stays thoroughly matt and absorbs the glare. Rely on the drag of the cloth to guide your choice. The eye deceives, but gravity tells the truth. Hunt for the materials ranked below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise materials that serve your structural needs before you check a label.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Suede",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "shoes and accessories with quiet matt texture"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine merino",
