  "venus_capricorn__moon_cancer__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "enduring structure + hidden depth + one living texture",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on enduring structure + hidden depth + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Rely on the physical weight and precise friction of your garments. Trust the heavy drop of a dense weave and the soft resistance of a matt finish beneath your fingers. Build your wardrobe slowly through strict editing, and deploy it fast on the day. Your core style formula is enduring structure + hidden depth + one living texture. Picture a sharply tailored heavy wool overcoat layered over a fine-gauge knit that carries a warm, muted undertone, finished with a raw silk scarf that shifts slightly as you breathe.\n\nApply the decade test before making any new addition to your wardrobe. Pick the garment up, inspect the inner seams, check the finishing on the hems, and ask yourself if the architecture will still hold its exact shape ten years from today. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. Leave items on the rack if they feel flimsy, lack internal reinforcement, or rely on temporary styling tricks to create their visual interest. Your foundation requires pure physical integrity from the inside out.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your absolute foundation, the physical compass you will use to evaluate every garment before it enters your wardrobe.",
