    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your enduring structure from {texture_good_3}. It holds a clean shoulder for years without sagging. For your one living texture, rely on {texture_good_1}. Squeeze the sleeve. If it springs back instantly, buy it. Ground these choices with {texture_good_2} for your bags and shoes. Let them patinate to the shape of your hand. Slip {texture_good_4} underneath it all as your hidden depth, bringing fluid movement against your skin. Subject every surface to the candlelight test. Hold the material near a low, warm flame. If it swallows the glow into a flat void, leave it on the rack. If it catches the light with a matt, muted finish, it belongs to you. Seek out these specific materials.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your hands will tell you more about a garment than its label ever could.",
