      "text": "Trust your hands to spot frauds. Pick up {texture_bad_1} and crush it in your fist. If it springs back with a rigid, synthetic squeak, drop it immediately. Reject {texture_bad_2} the moment it brushes your collarbone. It will sit like a cold film against the skin and trap heat. Inspect any prospective garment under a dim bulb. If the material throws a flat, artificial glare rather than absorbing the ambient light to reveal hidden depth, it fails. Proper cloth drinks the light and retains a rich, matt shadow. It does not bounce back a harsh, grey sheen. Avoid these inferior weaves entirely.",
