      "text": "In low light and close quarters, depth takes the lead. Reach for a rich toffee silk blouse or a camel cashmere sweater. Keep finishes matt to absorb ambient light. Treat an evening hosting friends at your dining table with the same material strictness you apply to the office. The close proximity requires absolute tactile integrity. Allow a warm gold chain to rest directly on the collarbone. Feel the drape of the fabric with closed eyes. Rely on touch as your primary guide. The mass of the textile reveals its true quality. Drop stiff synthetics immediately. They reflect harsh glare and ruin the quiet intent.",
