    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Turn to your scarves next. Source only pure silk or fine brushed wool in a strictly matt weave. Ground the accessory in warm tones like rich toffee or camel. Test the piece in your hands before wearing it. Wrap the fabric tightly around your knuckles to gauge its resistance. The textile must provide enduring structure to your neckline while revealing hidden depth within the yarn. A flimsy blend betrays itself instantly under the grip of your hand, failing the demands of true longevity.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical tests required to evaluate soft accessories and woven textiles.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "silk or fine wool, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
