        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pick up {texture_bad_1} and drag your bare thumb across the surface. If the material squeaks or catches against your skin, drop it. Evaluate {texture_bad_2} for airflow before buying. Press the fabric directly against your mouth and blow forcefully into the weave. If the air bounces back into your lungs, the garment fails. These synthetics trap heat and completely undermine the enduring structure required for your foundation. You need a warm base of natural fibres to function correctly. Anything with a flat, artificial finish that repels air blocks true softness. Seek only a matt surface that breathes cleanly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject materials that fail the skin and trap heat.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot lives in the tension between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Build your outfits around genuine softness. Pick up a piece and assess the mass in your hands. Then hold the material close to your face and exhale outward. If warm air passes through freely, keep the item. If the weave blocks the current, leave it on the rack. Ground these lightweight layers with a matt surface to supply the required one living texture.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical tension that makes your outfits work.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build your foundation with warm base neutrals. Rely on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} to establish enduring structure. Bridge these deep tones with {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Keep your entire palette strictly warm. Add a single deliberate accent using {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Apply your relief tone sparingly as a soft note to break a dense block of colour. Reject icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels immediately. Avoid the trap of sinking into an unshaped, entirely dark silhouette. Fix this flat void by bringing in a warm point of light, perhaps sliding on a hammered gold cuff or securing a tortoiseshell comb. Judge garments with your bare hands. Dyes deceive the eye, but the raw drape of the yarn tells the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your colours strictly to build a disciplined, intentional wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Rich toffee",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
