          "useCase": "breathable separation over fluid drapes in warmer weather"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Test how a fabric reacts to pressure before you purchase it. If a material binds across the shoulders when you lift your arms, reject it. Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Fold the sleeve over itself. It holds a stiff crease and prevents the light movement you require. Leave {texture_bad_2} on the rail. It traps warm air against the skin and gives off a hard glare instead of a muted, matt surface. Trust your hands to detect these physical failures.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to spot the materials that fight your body.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to establish your physical baseline. Anchor this pairing with {texture_good_1}. Rub the material between your fingers to verify the finish remains warm and matt. Check the weight distribution on every garment. Lift the fabric, release it, and observe the drop. You require enduring structure that falls cleanly and retains its shape. Avoid any surface that feels slick or frail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your materials by how they behave in your hands, not how they look on a hanger.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build a strictly warm foundation from your deepest shades. Anchor your base in {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Gauge the colour profile under natural light to ensure the tone absorbs rather than reflects. When you require a substitute for harsh white, reach for {core_colour_3}. Deploy {core_colour_4} to bridge contrasting items. Restrict your single deliberate accent to {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Introduce a soft note used sparingly when dense blocks require breathing room. Pass over Icy pastel, Neon brights, and Cold blue-grey immediately. These clash with your matt lane. Watch for the rigid carapace trap. When demands escalate, you might automatically grab stiff technical jackets or heavy utility garments for protection. Drop the rigid shell. Swap it for a brushed cotton layer that reacts rapidly but still anchors you. This guarantees enduring structure without heavy armour.",
      "sectionIntro": "Deploy your colours as a strict visual toolkit rather than a random collection of shades.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Warm taupe",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
