      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, allow your materials to do the talking. A technical nylon coat layered over a fine ribbed merino shirt catches the dim light while maintaining light movement. Keep the overall finish completely muted. Pair these with worsted wool trousers in warm taupe to absorb the shadows. Mix your dual-register metals directly against the skin. Fasten a matt brass cuff alongside a brushed silver ring. Moving from a restaurant to a waiting car should not compromise your physical baseline. Wrap yourself in camel layers to block the evening chill. Grip the worsted wool and gauge its heavy drape against your collarbone. Rely on the physical drop of the cloth to provide enduring structure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your clothing choices for dim spaces and close proximity.",
      "tests": [
