    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, strict structure leads. Let sharp seams and heavy lapels set the outer boundary. Treat space as your supporting asset. A generously cut sleeve or a relaxed trouser leg provides necessary mobility inside that rigid framework. Let your body dictate the fit. If an item restricts your stride, take it off. Introduce a living material, like heavy silk or brushed camel hair, to soften the geometry. Apply a simple test to everything you own. Navigating a wet commute requires the exact same rigorous standard as a formal board presentation. If a coat feels too precious for damp pavement, do not wear it. Choose matt, warm fabrics that absorb light. A rich toffee cashmere layer provides pure insulation.",
      "sectionIntro": "Define your professional silhouette by establishing a strict material hierarchy.",
      "tests": [
        "walking the dog deserves the same standard as a meeting (Moss)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, enduring structure leads. Dim illumination obscures subtle details. Rely on a firm silhouette to define your shape. Pick up a full-grain leather jacket or a cashmere knit in camel. Shadows hide poor seams, but they cannot fake structure. Grasp the material and gauge its heaviness. Warm, matt fibres catch dim light perfectly. Maintain your standards regardless of the audience. A late drink at a local bar demands the identical calibre of dressing as a private dinner. Seek out heavy silk pieces that hold their form. Avoid flimsy garments that collapse in the dark. Examine the hang of the cloth before you dress. If the fabric sags from the rail, leave it there.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your evening presentation by controlling your silhouette and material density.",
      "tests": [
        "walking the dog deserves the same standard as a meeting (Moss)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Buying toothpaste at the local chemist does not suspend your baseline. Walking through the park demands the identical brushed wool or cashmere quality as attending a formal meeting. Demand complete consistency. Your foundation relies on enduring structure + athletic space + one living texture. Maintain this constant in every context. Reach for a camel overcoat or a rich toffee jacket. Check the hardware on your belts. It must remain warm and matt. Avoid anything stiff or shiny. Test the drape by rolling your shoulders. If a sleeve limits your reach, discard it. Every item must earn its keep through ordinary movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Maintain your physical standard during every ordinary errand.",
      "tests": [
        "walking the dog deserves the same standard as a meeting (Moss)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Select {metal_1} and {metal_2} to ground your warm baseline. Treat {metal_3} strictly as a quiet accent. A high-gloss, reflective surface slices harshly against muted colours. Bypass {excluded_finish} entirely. Seek out brushed, antiqued, or matt surfaces to keep the ensemble cohesive. Hardware must support an enduring structure without adding visual noise. When evaluating a heavy zip or a piece of jewellery, judge its physical footprint. Real density acts as your compass, so confirm the solid heft of the metal before you commit.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat hardware as the critical anchor that calibrates the temperature of your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Seek stones that swallow light. When assessing {stone_1} or {stone_2}, evaluate their core gravity. A piece must sit heavily and densely in your palm. Because your palette is warm and muted, highly polished settings act like a harsh glare next to soft fabrics. They pull focus and disrupt the balance. Select heavily brushed or entirely matt finishes instead. This dulled surface absorbs light perfectly. It ensures your hardware integrates smoothly, grounding an athletic space without demanding undue attention.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate stones and metals by how they anchor your garments, measuring physical density against light absorption.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
