    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments establish enduring structure. They provide an athletic space to breathe. Accessories serve as the final component, supplying the one living texture your outfit requires. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with handbags. Demand full-grain leather and brushed matt hardware. Run your fingers over the surface to gauge the quality. Apply the one-ember test to every item you consider. A single, perfectly warm coal radiating steady heat does more work than a roaring fire. If a bag glares with highly polished metal, put it down. Let the muted finish and the undeniable physical reality of the hide guide your choice.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use these rules to select the final, crucial touches that ground your silhouette.",
