    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "When selecting scarves, insist on silk or fine wool. The surface must remain strictly matt. Wrap the fabric around your neck to ensure it leaves athletic space, never restricting your movement. Anchor the scarf against a heavy camel coat that offers enduring structure. Implement the same ember rule here before purchasing. Crush the material in your fist. Look for a single, warm flash of colour buried within the muted threads. Avoid anything highly reflective or entirely flat. Depend purely on touch to make the final decision. The genuine friction of matt silk against your collarbone provides the definitive answer.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your secondary accessories through strict material requirements and physical tests.",
