    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your waist with a medium full-grain leather belt. Select a warm, matt buckle to establish your primary metal baseline. Treat your keepsake jewellery differently. Choose aged, oxidised silver for rings or cuffs. These heavy components secure the enduring structure your wardrobe demands. Observe how they handle in your grip. Solid metal drops into the palm with dense gravity. Before stepping out, check the visual heat of your metals. Locate the single glowing accent among your hardware, perhaps that darkened silver band, and remove every other piece that competes for oxygen.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your foundation with hardware that functions first, then strip back the excess before stepping out.",
      "rankedItems": [
