      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Subject your prints to the evening shadow test. Bring the {recommended_pattern_1} into a completely darkened room lit by a solitary lamp. Observe how the contrast behaves. The design must absorb the light and grow rich and warm in the corners. It must never turn harsh or lose its legibility. This environmental check preserves your need for enduring structure. If the lines blur into chaos away from the sun, leave the garment behind. You require prints that deepen at night while maintaining clear definition. Look for patterns that leave sufficient athletic space between the shapes. This prevents the motif from collapsing into a dense block of colour.",
      "sectionIntro": "Run this environmental lighting check on every print before purchasing.",
      "tests": [
        "the firelight test (deepen and warm by lamplight)"
      ]
    }
