  "venus_capricorn__moon_libra__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "enduring structure + cool composure + one living texture",
    "closing": "Trust your hands above the mirror, grounding every choice in the physical absolute of enduring structure + cool composure + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe with deliberate patience and wear it without hesitation. Let the cloth settle on your frame. Feel for a heavy, warm drape in the fabric before you check the mirror. Looks lie. Weight does not. Rely on the physical sensation of density against your collarbone to tell you if a piece belongs to you. Apply the host test before you leave the house. Put on the jacket and ask yourself if you feel like a visitor borrowing a coat or the person who holds the deeds to the property. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. If the garment feels tentative, drop it.\n\nYour dressing rhythm relies on a strict equation. Memorise enduring structure + cool composure + one living texture. Picture a sharp, dense wool overcoat falling straight to the calf. Layer it over a fine gauge knit that sits close to the ribs. Finish the combination with a brushed suede boot. The overcoat provides the architecture. The knit offers total calm. The suede adds the necessary friction to stop the outfit looking flat. Keep the finish matt across every surface to maintain balance. You are looking for materials that absorb light rather than reflect it. Check the seams. Pull the fabric. If the construction lacks substance, walk away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this foundational logic to anchor your physical instincts and stop buying clothes that do not serve you.",
      "tests": [
        "the host test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe around fibres that offer enduring structure without stiffness. Trust your hands when you evaluate a fabric. Apply the breath test. Hold the garment against your mouth and exhale. If the warm air moves through it easily, keep it. If it traps the heat, put it back. Look for {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Choose {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Rely on {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Finish with {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. These materials deliver the one living texture your foundation requires. Rely on gravity to confirm your choices. The mirror deceives, but the downward pull of heavy cloth remains an absolute constant.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the fibres that will build your foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Washed silk",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cloud-soft lambswool",
