    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your spectrum is strictly warm. Establish your base with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Anchor these light tones using {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} to carve out distinct lines. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent to maintain cool composure. Treat the relief tone purely by its role. It is a soft note used sparingly when a combination feels too dense. Leave stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel on the rack. Watch for the all-earth sink. This trap occurs when dark shades and heavy matt weaves stack up and swallow you whole. Lift the outfit immediately. Place a pale contrasting layer at the collar, introduce one piece of polished leather, or bring in the soft relief tone. Assess the harmony of your layers by tracing the seams blindly.",
