      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1}. It catches on dry hands and lacks the dense substance required for enduring structure. Press {texture_bad_2} directly to the most sensitive skin on your inner wrist. If it scratches, bites, or traps heat, drop the piece immediately. A warm, muted wardrobe demands absolute tactile integrity. Cheap stiffness betrays a poor weave. Run your bare fingers over the surface. If the threads register as slick, brittle, or hollow, leave the garment on the hanger. You need materials that yield gracefully.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your skin is the final judge of any material, so learn to spot the substandard weaves before you even put them on.",
