  "venus_capricorn__moon_scorpio__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "enduring structure + quiet undercurrent + one living texture",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on enduring structure + quiet undercurrent + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the weight of a garment in your hands before you put it on your body. Look for a warm, matt finish that absorbs light rather than reflecting it outward. Heavy, dense fibres block out noise and hold their shape. Your exact styling directive is enduring structure + quiet undercurrent + one living texture. Picture a heavy, tailored wool overcoat worn over a seamless fine-gauge knit, anchored by a raw, unpolished suede bag. The outfit requires no explanation and demands nothing from the viewer.\n\nConstruct your wardrobe slowly and methodically, adding only pieces that serve your internal architecture. Apply the melt test to every potential purchase. Ask yourself if the item melts seamlessly into your existing foundation or if it fights for visual space. If a garment requires you to adjust your posture, pull at a hem, or mentally justify its presence, leave it on the rack. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Clothes must do the work of holding you securely, leaving your mind entirely self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your architectural master plan for building a wardrobe that functions strictly on your terms.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe demands an enduring structure built around one living texture. Choose {texture_good_3} for blazers that hold a permanent line. Soften that architecture with a warm, quiet undercurrent of {texture_good_4} in your linings. For knitwear, look to {texture_good_1}. Clench the knit tightly. It must compress and bounce back without a crease. Rely on {texture_good_2} for shoes and belts that patinate into a muted finish. Run the breath test on any woven purchase. Hold the cloth to your mouth and exhale sharply. If the air hits your palm on the other side, the fibre breathes. If the material stifles the air, reject the garment. Let the physical response guide your purchase. Appearances deceive, but gravity speaks truth. Select from the materials below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply a rigorous physical standard to every fibre before it touches your skin.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Suede",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "shoes and accessories with quiet matt texture"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine merino",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers soft against the skin and resilient through washes"
        },
        {
          "name": "Linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "warmer-weather pieces whose natural wrinkle reads as authentic"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Observe how materials behave against your skin. Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Crush the fabric in your palm. It betrays itself through a rigid, synthetic squeak between your fingers. Stay away from {texture_bad_2}. It catches sharply on bare knuckles. These materials disrupt the quiet undercurrent your style requires. Check the ventilation of every piece. Press the cloth over your mouth and exhale deeply. If the hot air traps itself and bounces back into your lungs, drop the item immediately. Synthetic barriers suffocate the body and ruin a warm, matt surface by introducing a flat, lifeless sheen.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify poor materials by learning exactly how they fail in the hand.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your ideal surface pairing sets {sweet_spot_keyword_1} against {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Establish a firm foundation with heavyweight weaves, then introduce {texture_good_1} close to the skin. This specific contrast builds a quiet undercurrent that remains strictly warm. Assess the porosity of every new cloth. Force air through the fabric from an inch away. If the draft fails to penetrate the fibres, abandon the purchase. You require layers that respire with your body heat. Keep the face of the cloth completely matt. Your selected pieces should absorb light rather than reflect it. Rely on tactile feedback when inspecting the weave. Mass never deceives the hands.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your material combinations relies on strict physical boundaries.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build your palette in a warm climate. Use {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} as your foundation stones. Bridge to lighter garments with {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. These base tones uphold your enduring structure. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent to sharpen a simple combination. For a visual pause, use a soft relief tone sparingly at the collar or cuff. Pass entirely over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels. Beware the lounging trap. Soften every garment to chase comfort and you will find yourself dressed in pure sleepwear. Fix this by restoring exactly one definite line. Add a rolled but real lapel, press a soft crease into your trousers, or carry a firm leather bag to ground the softer fabrics.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your tones exactly as you select your fabrics, relying only on those that serve your structure.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Rich toffee",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Taupe",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
