      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe relies on sensory comfort to ground its clean shapes. Trust your fingers to find it. Grab a knit of {texture_good_1} and squeeze it in your fist. It must spring back with reassuring resistance. For your belts and bags, demand {texture_good_2} that will patinate as it moulds to your grip. Build enduring structure in your outerwear by inspecting the weave of {texture_good_3}. It needs to hold a crisp line without feeling stiff. Underneath it all, look for {texture_good_4} to drape smoothly against your skin. Apply the candlelight test to every surface before you buy. If the fabric drinks in a warm, matt glow rather than reflecting a harsh shine, you have found your one living texture. Hunt for these reliable foundations.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to read the rack before you ever try a garment on.",
