      "text": "Reject any material that fights the skin. Pinch {texture_bad_1} between your thumb and index finger. If it slides with a slick, synthetic friction, leave it on the hanger. Run your palm over {texture_bad_2}. A stiff, brittle drag indicates a total failure of sensory comfort. Take the garment into a dim, warm room. If the surface throws back a flat, glassy glare rather than a quiet, matt glow, drop the item immediately. Crush {texture_bad_3} in your fist. A piece that holds a sharp, rigid crease lacks the natural pliancy you require.",
