    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Look for the contrast of {sweet_spot_keyword_1} against {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. A quiet, matt cloth provides a solid base. Layer {texture_good_1} over the top. Examine how these materials absorb ambient lighting. Take the item into a shadowy corner. The warm ambient light must sink into the weave. The threads should swallow the glow to confirm a muted finish. Reject any material that throws a severe reflection back at you. Pick up the piece and twist it. It must provide enduring structure, meaning the item holds a defined shape but bends easily around your joints. Discard anything that scratches or clings.",
