    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Grab {texture_bad_1} and crush it in your fist. If the material collapses into a lifeless clump and refuses to spring back, leave it on the rack. Rely on tangible mass over visual appeal. A flimsy weave deceives the eye but gives itself away in your grip. You need reliable tension to anchor one clever contrast. Weak textiles drag the entire outfit down. Test {texture_bad_2} by throwing your arm out to snap the cuff. Whip your hand away from your body. If the sleeve slumps and trails behind your movement instead of snapping into place with cool precision, it fails. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely when it catches on dry skin or feels clammy in your palm.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify failure in the fabric before you ever put the garment on.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your foundational tension relies on pushing {sweet_spot_keyword_1} against {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. When evaluating a potential {texture_good_1} item, give the hem a sharp downward tug. It must snap back to its original shape immediately rather than sagging. This structural integrity guarantees you achieve crisp separation from head to toe. Keep the dye temperature cool. Anchor the textile combination with a matt surface, especially as you mix your hardware without restriction.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your primary textile pairing ensures your foundations never hang flat.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your entire wardrobe operates on a strictly cool temperature scale. Build your daily foundation on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Use {core_colour_3} as your bright neutral and rely on {core_colour_4} for deep structural tailoring. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green. They muddy your clarity. Treat your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly, introduced through a fine ribbed merino knit or technical nylon tote. Apply {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} to establish crisp separation. Avoid the trap of prettiness lacking weight. Soft shades worn head to toe read charming but become forgettable by lunch. Fix this drift by providing a heavy grounding element. Add a sharply tailored worsted wool blazer, a structured flat, or {core_colour_4} placed where the eye lands first.",
