    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light, the crisp element leads. Shadows muddy soft edges, so a structured dark shirt provides vital definition. Anchor the outfit with something clever, perhaps a bright silver cuff against matt icy grey worsted cloth. Keep the tones cool. Your baseline routine never wavers. Fetching a glass of water demands the identical level of care as dressing for a dimly lit supper. Check the cloth under your fingers. A dark room hides minor visual flaws but amplifies poor material. Rely on fine ribbed merino to hold its shape close to the body. Mix metals freely. A white gold chain resting over dark fabric catches the ambient light and guides the eye.",
