    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Apply the rule of daily constancy. Taking the hound out in freezing rain requires the exact level of intention as a formal briefing. Do not downgrade your garments to collect a prescription from the local chemist. Maintain your discipline. Wear a stark navy cotton poplin shirt beneath an icy grey technical nylon raincoat. Keep the metals mixed freely on your hands. Combine a polished platinum signet with a matt brass band. Your binding geometry is always crisp separation + mobile layers + one clever contrast. Test every piece before you leave the house. Lift your arms to ensure the fabric accommodates full extension. Drop the item entirely if it restricts your stride.",
