      "text": "Your metal approach grants complete freedom to combine \"{metal_1}\", \"{metal_2}\", and \"{metal_3}\". Because your baseline remains strictly cool, these elements interact without friction. Position these hardware details across your mobile layers to anchor the garments. You can confidently place a high-shine zip next to \"{excluded_finish}\" belt buckles. Shun antiqued brass, hammered copper, or any artificially aged pieces. Such treatments introduce visual debris against a present-tense wardrobe. Confine your choices strictly to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome. To verify the quality of a chain or clasp, lift the piece in your palm. Surface appearances deceive, but sheer gravity tells the truth.",
