    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is strictly cool. Build a foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}, rely on {core_colour_3} as a light neutral, and ground the look using {core_colour_4} for structural weight. Deploy your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to interrupt heavy blocks of worsted wool. Keep deliberate accents restricted to {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2}. Pass over Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green immediately. Watch out for outfits that dissolve into an unbroken blur by lunch. Fix this dullness instantly by introducing a sharp poplin collar, an architectural metal ring, or a geometric trainer. This practice ensures every garment combination retains its hidden depth.",
