    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let crisp separation dictate your working hours. Establish stark visual boundaries between cool icy grey and stark navy. A demanding itinerary does not call for stiff worsted wool. It requires pliable fine ribbed merino that can keep pace with a sprint. Allow the remaining parts of your formula to support this lead. Build concealed depth by laying matt cotton poplin against slick technical nylon. Introduce a solitary, smart opposition by placing a polished silver ring beside a matt gold watch. Test every item before you buy it. Bend your elbows and crouch. If the seam bites or restricts, leave it on the rack. Your bodily reaction is the definitive metric.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your working hours around strict boundaries and functional movement.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "When the lights drop, sharp structural lines take control. An evening gathering does not demand rigid tailoring. Seek out fluid worsted wool that gives way when you move. Let your fingertips gauge the density of the cloth. Reflections lie, but the heft of the weave is absolute. Demand a clean break where a cool icy grey poplin shirt meets stark navy trousers. Blend your hardware without hesitation. Situate a high-shine silver ring next to a matt steel watch to fracture the dim lighting. Grip a piece of fine ribbed merino and confirm its substantial drape before putting it on.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master close quarters and dim lighting by relying entirely on touch and clear lines.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Running errands does not grant a pass to wear formless fleece. An unpredictable routine demands structural integrity. Construct a functional baseline using technical nylon that withstands a sudden downpour while holding an architectural edge. Grab a stark navy poplin shirt and crush the sleeve. It must spring back without creasing. Maintain the identical strictness you apply to professional tailoring. Anchor your morning choices in your constant rule of crisp separation + hidden depth + one clever contrast. Keep the palette cool, throwing matt cotton against bright hardware.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your daily errands as the strict proving ground for your functional wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Treat your hardware as structural scaffolding. Because your palette temperature remains cool, mix {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} without second thought. Maintain crisp separation across your details. Avoid hammered copper and artificially aged brass. These distressed surfaces create visual clutter against sharp lines. Stick to pure silver, mirror chrome, and polished white gold. Eliminate any {excluded_finish} pieces immediately. Generate hidden depth by contrasting these sleek finishes. Weigh the metal in your hand. A thick plating might trick a glance, but raw gravity reveals the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your metals ensures your hardware anchors your garments rather than distracting from them.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Look for {stone_1} and {stone_2} that slice clearly through shadow. You require dense, cool materials that refuse to scatter focus. Test the object by holding it loosely. A proper {stone_3} must possess undeniable heft for its scale, providing vital hidden depth. Steer clear of textured or tarnished settings. Irregular boundaries disrupt your geometric precision. Secure your gems using unpatinated silver or pure platinum.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your gems and settings to anchor your look with uncompromising physical density.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Gauge the jewellery by its sheer physical pull. Plating offers a temporary illusion, whereas actual weight proves structural integrity. Toss the item into your palm and check for a solid impact. Discard anything treated to look old. Blackened borders and hammered dents generate a messy friction that dismantles your crisp separation. Lean on a flawless {metal_1} paired with a compact {stone_1} to ground the silhouette and establish hidden depth. Ensure the metallic finish stays resolutely cool.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every piece of hardware to a strict physical assessment before it makes the cut.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your additions supply the one clever contrast that completes the silhouette, enforcing the crisp separation and hidden depth established by your garments. Restrict yourself to a single definitive piece. When handling a matt crepe de chine scarf, let your fingers evaluate the silk. Subject the square to the rotation test. Confirm it imparts a cool finish to a worsted wool coat just as successfully as it upgrades a technical nylon shell. If it fails to link three entirely different outfits, abandon it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat accessories as the precise mechanism to lock your outfit in place.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Silk scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "crepe de chine square, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the rotation test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select fine chains and bands in narrow profiles. Mix your metals freely by resting brushed matt gold directly against cool polished silver. This tactic builds hidden depth against stark navy shirting. Execute a friction check before acquiring a new piece. Drag the links across the back of your hand. If the metal catches or scratches, throw it out. True quality glides effortlessly. Let your skin evaluate the polish. Demand geometric precision to guarantee crisp separation at the neckline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Curate your jewellery to ground your core textures.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Fine jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "thin mixed gold and silver, mixed polished and brushed"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the rotation test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Pick up a structured bag in smooth leather. Squeeze the top-handle and measure its rigidity. The architecture must hold upright without collapsing. Look for fine hardware that mixes cool metals freely. These metallic closures supply hidden depth, preventing vast sections of dark cloth from dissolving into a void. They actively enforce crisp separation. Run the Substitution Check. Swap the bag for an alternative while keeping the garments identical. If the exchange forces you to change a shoe or tweak a collar, the accessory is controlling the silhouette rather than serving it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finalise the system by testing your structural anchors.",
      "rankedItems": [
