    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let crisp separation lead your tailoring. Build clear boundaries dividing your trousers and your blouses. Support this structure with hidden depth in your fabrics, favouring deep teal silk or brushed wool over flat synthetics. Ground the look with an unexpected pairing, perhaps a cool silver watch case pressed against a matt inky navy cuff. An ordinary morning at a desk or a rainy dash to the office does not excuse a drop in your requirements. Demand the exact same precision from your work attire as you do from your finest outerwear. Judge dove grey cashmere entirely by its tactile response. Ignore the visual drape and demand heavy, full-grain leather to anchor your professional structure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Approach your working hours as a laboratory for precision, never a compromise of your standards.",
      "tests": [
