    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Require cool, opaque stones like {stone_1} and {stone_2}. Hold the piece in your bare hand before acquiring it. Weigh it. True gravity grounds your accessory choices. Use these heavy, light-absorbing pieces to establish crisp separation against woven cloth. They provide hidden depth through clouded or cabochon cuts rather than faceted sparkle. Beware of high-gloss finishes. A mirror polish acts as a jarring interruption against your subdued wardrobe. Demand exclusively matt or brushed settings to keep the aesthetic cohesive.",
