      "text": "Pick up the piece and weigh it in your palm. Assess quality strictly through gravity. A heavy, brushed {metal_1} watch case or a dense {stone_1} ring provides crisp separation at your cuffs. Avoid high-gloss finishes entirely. Highly reflective hardware acts like a mirror, throwing unwanted light and clashing awkwardly with your muted garments. Stick strictly to cool oxidised metals and matt textures. These subdued finishes absorb light and reveal hidden depth, anchoring your look without competing for attention.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess every buckle, clasp, and ring with your hands before you check the mirror.",
      "tests": [
