    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You have mastered your crisp separation. You have structured the necessary hidden depth. Accessories now provide your one clever contrast. Keep this discipline strict. Anchor your outfits with exactly one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with handbags. Demand dense full-grain leather finished with brushed matt hardware. Lift the item by its strap. Grip the metal directly. Rely entirely on your physical reactions to the materials. Physical resistance exposes poor manufacturing. Apply the one-ember test. Place the bag on a dark table in a dim room. It must catch a single sliver of fading light with a muted, cool glow. It must never flash a bright reflection.",
