      "text": "Tailored pieces take their pattern from the weave. Fluid garments take their pattern from the dye. Keep your overall contrast strictly low and tonal. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} in brushed wool or {recommended_pattern_2} woven into silk. These choices secure your required hidden depth. Avoid {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. Pass over bold, global, or expansive prints on sight. When assessing a patterned piece, observe how the colours behave under artificial illumination. Watch how the tones deepen by lamplight. If the cool anchor muddies or the contrast spikes, drop the garment. Bright retail lighting disguises cheap dye. Shadow exposes it.",
