    "closing": "Train your hands to verify the friction of your garments, ensuring your daily execution always delivers crisp separation + light movement + one clever contrast.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Feel for fabrics that keep the skin cool and regulate your temperature as you shift between environments. Your garments must adapt to your changing physical reality. Execute your core formula daily. This formula is crisp separation + light movement + one clever contrast. Picture a sharply structured jacket worn open over a lightweight, fluid trouser that sweeps the floor, grounded abruptly by a heavy, matt technical boot. The jacket provides the strict boundary. The trouser delivers the kinetic flow. The boot forces the necessary friction.\n\nBuild your collection horizontally over time. Collect distinct separates that pivot easily between contexts, and deploy them rapidly based on the community you are engaging with on any given day. Subject every top to the half-mirror test. Sit at a table and assess only your reflection from the sternum up. If the structure of the collar does not actively support the face you present to your peers, take the garment off. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "Understand your foundational architecture before you buy another piece of clothing.",
      "tests": [
        "the half-mirror test"
      ]
