    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe formula demands crisp separation and light movement. To achieve this, rely on your hands and a simple physical check. Pick up a garment by the hem and snap your wrist. If the fabric ripples cleanly and settles back into its original shape without dragging, it passes the wrist-flick test. Rely on your grip to confirm quality, as physical drag reveals what a mirror hides. Use this standard to find {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Source {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement. For trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day, seek out {texture_good_3}. Finish with {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little, creating one clever contrast against your cool tones. Focus on the selections below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the exact materials that build your foundation.",
