    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe relies on crisp separation between layers. Any material that clings or pills destroys that clean boundary. Test {texture_bad_1} with the wrist-flick test. Snap your arm upward. If the fabric drags heavily over your forearm rather than snapping cleanly back, leave it on the hanger. Pick up {texture_bad_2} and crush it in your hand. If it feels dead and refuses to spring open, it will hang flat and dull against your frame. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. It traps heat and forces a stiff, suffocating silhouette. Let your tactile senses override visual promises. Textures that drag, stick, or refuse to breathe will actively sabotage your cool colour palette. Look for spring and slide. Reject the rest.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to spot the materials that actively fight against your frame.",
