        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your defining temperature is strictly cool. Build your foundation on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} as your clean alternative to stark white, and deploy {core_colour_4} when an outfit requires structural weight. Pick up {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent to enforce crisp separation within the outfit. Introduce your relief tone exclusively in small doses to soften a harsh edge. Leave Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green on the rack. Beware the drift into unmoored lightness. Wearing solely pale, soft tones reads pleasant in a morning meeting and fades from memory by noon. Anchor the silhouette. Add a sharply tailored blazer, a rigid flat shoe, or a dense dark garment right where you want the eye to rest first.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your foundational palette by testing how each tone anchors the rest of the outfit.",
