    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, crisp separation leads. Build your foundation with stark navy worsted wool to establish clear boundaries. The remaining elements provide a deliberate counterpoint. Introduce subtle flow through fine ribbed merino to ease the strictness. Finish with a singular point of friction. A matt silver watch dial resting on icy grey cotton poplin breaks the uniformity without breaking consensus. Run the dry cleaner test on your collection. Dropping your primary wool trousers at the shop is no excuse to accept slouching shapes. Your reserve pieces must hold the exact same cool geometry.",
      "sectionIntro": "Set your working standards with these structural rules.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim rooms and close company, establish sharp boundaries immediately. Low light devours subtle details, so force crisp separation between stark navy worsted wool and icy grey cotton poplin. Mix your metals and finishes freely. A polished silver cuff against a matt brass buckle catches whatever ambient glow exists. Keep the fabrics tactile and cool to the touch. Reach for fine ribbed merino that rewards proximity. A delayed trip to the dry cleaner does not grant you permission to lower your standards. If your preferred choice is absent, pivot to a technical nylon shell that holds a rigid edge. Test the cloth blindly between your fingers. If the edge feels soft, drop it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Close settings require you to calibrate your approach for proximity and shadow.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat a morning run to the post office as a strict test of your baseline. A mundane errand does not suspend your standards. Construct your clothing around cool tones. Layer an icy grey nylon jacket over stark navy poplin. Let your hands verify the fabric. Sight is easily tricked, but actual drape is not. Pick up the shirt and crush the collar. If it lacks resilience, discard it. Blend your finishes and metals without hesitation. Combine a matt silver buckle with polished brass rings. Apply your core equation every morning to guarantee readiness. Your baseline demands crisp separation + light movement + one clever contrast.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your daily baseline in garments that require zero translation across your routine.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your approach to hardware relies on complete freedom across the spectrum of {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Blend these cool metals freely across a single outfit to force crisp separation between your layers. Weigh an item in your palm to confirm its density. Surface appearances deceive the eye, but actual physical heft reveals true quality. Avoid artificially aged hardware or an overly distressed {excluded_finish}. These treatments read as visual clutter against your present-tense garments. Instead, maintain absolute clarity. Keep your structural elements strictly to polished iterations of {metal_1} or {metal_2}. Combine a flat matt piece with a bright polish to create light movement across your body.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your hardware to anchor your garments with cool, deliberate intent.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Test {stone_1} and {stone_2} by their sheer density. Assess the physical gravity of a setting in your bare hands to bypass visual manipulation. A dense stone grounds your structure while maintaining a strictly cool temperature. Apply this same exactness to the metal settings. Antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal introduce historical clutter against your present-tense clothing. Anchor your hardware entirely with polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome. This creates the necessary crisp separation against your textiles. From this strict baseline, you can harness light movement through the clear facets of the stones themselves.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select stones and hardware that ground your structure without muddying the waters.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
