          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Let gravity vet your additions. An accessory's mass tells a more reliable story than its shine. If a buckle or collar pin feels hollow, put it back. Avoid artificially aged brass and hammered copper entirely. These distressed surfaces act as visual debris, ruining your modern lines. Rely on cool, highly polished {metal_1} or bright chrome instead. A sharp, gleaming edge ensures crisp separation against your fabrics. This dense, solid hardware grounds the light movement of your garments.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every piece of hardware by holding it before you wear it.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
