    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select a technical nylon crossbody bag. Look for brushed metal zips sitting next to one polished ring. Mixing these finishes keeps the piece functional. The strap must allow light movement when you walk. Test the hardware under actual conditions. Fill the compartments and carry it. A poorly balanced strap will pull uncomfortably on your shoulder, overriding any aesthetic appeal. Trust your immediate kinetic feedback. A stark navy shell works perfectly with your cool worsted wool garments. Pick it up and check the seams.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your bag as a practical tool, judging it by its hardware and balance.",
