    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your footwear with a clean leather boot. Seek a minimal profile in cool dark slate or stark navy. A smooth upper guarantees crisp separation below the hemline. Avoid heavy hardware. Evaluate the construction blindly. Squeeze the sole and test its flexibility. A thick rubber foundation drags, and you require light movement through the foot. Before stepping out, audit the entire silhouette for visual excess. Inspect the complete structure and eliminate the single component working too hard. If a mixed metal cuff disrupts the stark geometry of your structure, leave the jewellery on the table.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finalise your accessories by applying a strict reduction.",
