    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject anything that fights your own skin. Run {texture_bad_1} between your thumb and forefinger. If the fibre repels your touch or whines faintly under pressure, drop the garment. Your strategy relies on crisp separation. Materials like {texture_bad_2} and {texture_bad_3} cling and drag over underlayers. They disrupt the clean lines you require. A cool, muted palette demands organic integrity to succeed. If a piece lacks density or creates static, it will always look thin. Base your rejection solely on touch.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject what your eyes might excuse.",
