        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep your palette strictly cool. Build your foundation with {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3} for suiting and cashmere layers. Reserve {core_colour_4} for shirting. Relying on these exact shades enforces the crisp separation your look demands. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon. Drop them at the rack. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent, perhaps a silk pocket square or a painted leather edge. Apply the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly near the neckline. Watch for the trap of gilt overload, where an outfit tips into excess. Fix this error instantly. Hold the line at one molten flash and keep every other metal moment small, matt, and supporting.",
