      "text": "A Saturday trip to the greengrocer requires strict geometric discipline. Avoid shapeless cottons entirely. Look for dense knits that hold their shape. Maintain your standard even in the post office queue. Always deploy crisp separation + blurred edges + one clever contrast for your daily errands. Pair a dove grey cashmere jumper with deep teal brushed wool trousers. Rely on your fingertips to gauge the weave. Judge a garment by its gravitational pull, ignoring its surface appeal. Pick up a matt silver ring and slide it onto your hand. Notice how the cool metal interacts with the soft knit. Step out the door knowing exactly how the silhouette moves.",
