      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pick up a garment and rub the cloth between your thumb and index finger. If the material feels squeaky or pushes back against your skin, drop it immediately. This tactile test catches {texture_bad_1} instantly. It mimics the look of luxury but betrays a stiff, unyielding finish. Reject {texture_bad_2} for the same reason. It holds a rigid shape but lacks the drape necessary to maintain crisp separation within a cool palette. A matt surface must still yield to the hand. Treat tactile resistance as a strict boundary.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every fabric by hand before allowing it near your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your ideal tactile pairing anchors a cool wardrobe. Blend {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build a quiet undercurrent of subtle depth. Layer in {texture_good_1} to amplify the sensation. Test every piece before buying. Grasp the fabric firmly. If the yarns fight your grip or produce unnatural friction, abandon the item entirely. Evaluate the pure density of the weave. Appearance easily deceives the eye, but the heaviness of a garment reveals its true quality.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your signature textile pairings by relying entirely on touch.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette runs strictly cool. Anchor your foundation with {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon. Rely instead on {core_colour_4} as your light substitute. This ensures the crisp separation you require. Use {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a solitary, deliberate accent, supplying one clever contrast. Deploy the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to break up dense solids. Watch out for the woodland sink. Piling murky greens over thick soil shades creates a flat, matt mass that swallows you. Evaluate the physical impact. If the combined shades feel oppressive as you assemble them, they will drag down your posture. Lift the outfit immediately. Slip a pale layer under the collar, add a slice of smooth calfskin, or weave in the relief tone.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your shades by testing how they interact in your hands, not how they sit on a hanger.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
