      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Crisp separation leads your approach at the office. Support this sharp outline with a quiet undercurrent, anchoring a structured brushed wool blazer in dove grey with a fluid silk shirt in deep teal. Introduce one clever contrast through a sudden shift in finish to break the uniformity. A demanding Tuesday presentation requires the exact same soothing comfort as a local errand. Assess a full-grain leather document case by lifting it by the handles. Let the sheer heft of the hide confirm its durability. Keep the entire palette cool and resolutely matt. A brushed silver watch provides that final sharp focus at the wrist.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your professional uniform by letting structure lead and keeping ease close.",
      "tests": [
        "a rainy Sunday paper run deserves the same gentle standard (Ripple)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close quarters and low light, crisp separation leads. Dim rooms swallow subtle shifts in tone. Build distinct boundaries using inky navy silk layered over brushed dove grey wool to form a quiet undercurrent. Proximity amplifies touch. Demand absolute softness in every garment. A secluded evening meal demands the exact same gentle standard as relaxing by the fire. Let cool, matt silver rest gently over deep teal cashmere to provide one clever contrast. Reject stiff construction entirely. Rely on the stark division between materials to establish form when shadows dissolve fine details.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the specific demands of close proximity and dim lighting.",
      "tests": [
        "a rainy Sunday paper run deserves the same gentle standard (Ripple)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Never suspend your standard for minor tasks. A quick trip to the pharmacy calls for strict adherence to your rules. Walking the dog in the frost still deserves the physical protection of heavy fibres. Build every outfit on crisp separation + quiet undercurrent + one clever contrast. Reach for dove grey brushed wool trousers and a matt cool silver watch. Test the drape of an inky navy cashmere knit. Dense materials pull cleanly against gravity. Pair deep teal silk with thick full-grain leather shoes. Let the tangible structure of the wool guide your choice. Reject anything that breaks your muted palette. Rely on the weave to support your posture.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat every mundane errand as a strict test of your physical baseline.",
      "tests": [
        "a rainy Sunday paper run deserves the same gentle standard (Ripple)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your hardware strategy leans entirely cool. Anchor your core garments with {metal_1} and {metal_2}. Introduce {metal_3} when a piece demands a quiet undercurrent. Steer clear of {excluded_finish} treatments entirely. Highly polished, mirror-like chrome cuts too sharply across soft, muted colours and distracts from the garment itself. Stick strictly to matt or brushed textures to maintain cohesion. Always test the physical reality of the components. Lift the buckle or chain off the table. Let the solid weight of the metal confirm its value. If a zip feels hollow or lightweight, leave the item on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every zip, buckle, and clasp as a rigid architectural decision.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select {stone_1} and {stone_2} for their opacity. Highly reflective facets flash and distract when paired with muted fabrics. Restrict yourself to flat and brushed surfaces to maintain a cohesive look. Hold the piece in your palm to evaluate its density. Do not rely on visual scale. A dense, unpolished {stone_1} provides the quiet undercurrent required for a cool wardrobe. Leave translucent gems in the display case. Choose {stone_2} because it absorbs light rather than scattering it, ensuring crisp separation against your textiles.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every stone and metal piece for physical weight and light absorption.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Lift every piece of {metal_1} hardware in your palm before you buy it. Gauge its sheer gravitational pull. Heavy, solid jewellery establishes a robust, quiet undercurrent. Next, evaluate the surface. Glossy chrome reflects a sharp glare that disrupts your muted colours. Select strictly matt metal instead. A flat finish prevents distracting shine and ensures crisp separation between your accessories and your cool garments.",
      "sectionIntro": "Weigh your hardware by hand to expose weak manufacturing.",
      "tests": [
