    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories provide the final equation. They supply the one clever contrast. They disrupt the deliberate crisp separation found in your tailoring. They sharpen that quiet undercurrent running through your dove grey and inky navy garments. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with handbags. Source full-grain leather finished with brushed matt hardware. Let your tactile response govern the purchase. Pick the bag up by its strap. Squeeze the leather to confirm its thickness. Heavy hides signal endurance. Apply the one-ember test here. A single dense piece of muted silver hardware resting on cool leather acts as a solitary spark in a dark grate.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your accessories through the lens of physical mass and absolute restraint.",
      "rankedItems": [
