    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select scarves woven from fine wool or heavy silk. Avoid anything that shines. Ensure the finish remains strictly matt. Crush the fabric in your fist. It should recover instantly. Maintain crisp separation in your styling by keeping these textiles completely flat and non-reflective. Apply the one-ember test to every printed design. Seek out a single muted spark of deep teal suspended in an expanse of cool inky navy or dove grey to serve as one clever contrast. Reject any pattern that spreads into a sprawling blaze. Trust your fingers to verify the density of the weave. If the silk slips away like thin water, leave it on the shelf.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every scarf to rigorous physical testing before it joins your collection.",
      "rankedItems": [
