      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Select belts cut from medium full-grain leather featuring a strictly matt buckle. Require crisp separation by securing this flat texture over brushed wool trousers. Restrict keepsake jewellery to aged silver and oxidised pieces. Pick up a ring or cuff and feel its resistance in your palm. Solid, cool metal grounds a garment. Before putting on your coat, execute the one-ember test. Assess the entire outfit and locate the single glowing point. If an oxidised silver chain and a heavy leather belt buckle fight for oxygen against your dove grey shirt, take one off. Leave only a single spark.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your finishing hardware and test it ruthlessly before putting on your coat.",
