    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Maintain crisp separation across your garments by restricting pattern to structural weave and low-contrast tonal dye. Tailored pieces must take their motifs strictly from the loom. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} or {recommended_pattern_2} woven directly into heavy matt cloth. Fluid garments require a different approach. Allow silk to carry {recommended_pattern_3} in cool tonal washes. Establish quiet undercurrents of solid cloth to anchor these pieces. Step away from {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} completely. Test every motif by taking the garment into a dim room lit by warm lamplight. If the design sharpens and jumps forward instead of deepening and receding into the shadow, trust your visceral reaction to that visual noise. Drop the hanger and leave it on the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your eye to read pattern as structural texture rather than applied decoration.",
      "tests": [
