    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Crisp separation anchors your working hours. Establish your baseline with stark navy cotton poplin or worsted wool. Maintain a strictly cool palette to keep the visual field sharp. Support this hard perimeter with hidden physical ease. Choose fine ribbed merino against the skin to sustain your focus through long meetings. Finish the look with a singular, unexpected shift in proportion or mixed metals. Apply the errand rule to every daily choice. Stepping out to grab coffee for the office kitchen in an icy grey jacket requires the exact same structural logic as pitching a new board. Do not soften your geometry just because the task is mundane.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your working hours as a strict problem of structure and physical ease.",
