  "venus_gemini__moon_virgo__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "crisp separation + honest fabric + one clever contrast",
    "closing": "Navigate every wardrobe decision by trusting your hands to find crisp separation + honest fabric + one clever contrast.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe is a toolset, not a static exhibit. Build your core slowly, securing foundational items that shift gears depending on the context. Trust the physical weight of a garment in your hands. Feel the difference between flimsy synthetics and dense, reliable cloth. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not. When you evaluate a new jacket or trouser, apply the combination test. Ask yourself if the piece pairs seamlessly with three radically different items you already own without fighting their cut or finish. If it demands a complete wardrobe overhaul, leave it on the hanger.\n\nYour daily uniform relies on crisp separation + honest fabric + one clever contrast. Picture a rigid utilitarian trouser anchoring a smooth, lightweight shirt, finished with an unexpected tailored layer. The garments remain distinct, and the actual weave does the talking. Keep your overall temperature cool. Mix a matt surface with a sleek finish to satisfy your balanced orientation. You are assembling components rather than matching them. Rely on this structural clarity every morning. Pick up an item, test its physical reality against your established shapes, and construct the outfit.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use this blueprint to establish the physical boundaries of your wardrobe, setting strict rules for what earns a hanger and what gets left behind.",
