    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe from the inside out using cool, honest fabric. Let tactile feedback guide your choices. Stretch the hem of a garment and release it to perform the snap test. If the material recovers immediately, it earns its place. If it sags, drop it. Apply this standard to {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Choose {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Rely on {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Finally, seek out {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. Your fingertips will expose poor weaves before your eyes catch the flaw. Prioritise the materials on this list.",
