      "text": "Reject materials that feel synthetic or flimsy against the skin. Pinch a cuff and pull. If the piece forgets its original shape or slumps lazily back into place, it fails. You need items that support crisp separation. Avoid {texture_bad_1} because it clings to the body and blurs your lines. Pick up {texture_bad_2} and rub it between your thumb and forefinger. If it generates static or feels slick and artificial, drop it. Steer clear of {texture_bad_3} as it traps heat and disrupts your cool temperature balance. Rely on touch to detect these cheap tells. Structure requires textiles that hold their boundaries rather than collapsing under pressure.",
