    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe runs on dark drama and mobile layers. To execute this, you must train your touch. Subject every garment to the pull test. Grip the fabric across your knuckles and gauge the immediate recovery. You need {texture_good_1} for shirting that holds a clean architectural boundary. Seek out {texture_good_2} for fitted base layers that stretch and bounce back instantly. When you require trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day, rely on {texture_good_3}. Build a warm polished shell using {texture_good_4} for lightweight outerwear that blocks the wind and anchors one molten flash of hardware. Let your hands lead you to the materials ranked below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the physical materials that will construct your foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Worsted wool",
          "role": "rank 3",
