    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Its surface absorbs light into a flat, matt void that kills your dark drama. Rub it between your thumb and forefinger. It drags instead of sliding. Reject {texture_bad_2} the second it feels limp in your hands. You require sharp edges, and this material refuses to hold a crease. Fold the collar and press it. If the fold collapses into a soft curve, the piece lacks structure. Subject every item to a recoil evaluation. Flick the hem sharply. If the cloth returns with a hollow, spongy movement rather than snapping cleanly into place, it will never hold a warm polish. Leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to recognise the materials that sabotage your structure before you even pick them up.",
