      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to anchor your dark drama. Twist a section of {texture_good_1} between your palms. Release your grip and observe the recovery. If the fabric remains crumpled, leave it behind. You require sharp edges to build a self-contained silhouette. The cloth must maintain its own rigid structure. Seek out a warm surface finish that catches the light against a severe, unforgiving line. Depend on your fingers to assess the snap and tension in the warp. Sight deceives, but the structural resistance of heavy cloth provides a true measure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact friction points between your chosen fabrics.",
      "tests": [
