      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is strictly warm. Build your foundation entirely from {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, {core_colour_3}, and {core_colour_4}. These core neutrals construct the dark drama necessary for your silhouette. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as an intentional jolt, never a blended wash. Keep your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over muddy pastel, icy grey, and dusty sage. Grasp the garment, recognise how those weak dyes drag you down, and put it back. Beware the trap of the restrictive, flat monochrome block. Wearing an unbroken void of pigment will stifle you. Fix it by carving out sharp edges. Break the heavy silhouette with a massive polished gold cuff or a striking {accent_colour_1} shoe.",
