    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let dark drama set the standard at the desk. Anchor the foundation with heavy wool twill in deep bronze and crisp golden camel poplin. Build sharp edges into the lapels and cuffs to keep the shape strictly self-contained. Finish with a singular strike of warm, highly polished gold or silver at the collar to cut through the matt cloth. A morning school run or a corner shop dash never justifies abandoning these rigid boundaries. Keep the lines severe. Pinch the lapel. If the material folds limply instead of snapping back to attention, leave it on the rail.",
