    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low-light settings, construct your dark drama meticulously. A quiet dinner at a dim corner table does not mean surrendering your sharp edges. Keep the construction precise. Swap stiff wool twill for heavy silk satin and feel how the smooth surface catches the ambient lighting. Close your eyes and run a hand over the material. If the finish is matt and absorbs light entirely, put it back. You need textiles that bounce illumination. Pair a deep bronze silk shirt with high-shine patent leather boots. Let a thick brass cuff rest directly against your wrist. The metal will provide a warm reflection in candlelight. Rely on rigid construction to maintain your boundaries when the lights go down.",
      "sectionIntro": "Calibrate your textiles to maintain control in close quarters and low lighting.",
      "tests": [
