      "text": "Picking up a prescription at the local chemist does not mean abandoning your discipline. A rushed trip to the supermarket does not demand surrendering your severe tailored pieces. Expect a polished finish for your most ordinary tasks. Pull on crisp cotton poplin in deep bronze. Layer a structured coat in warm golden camel. Grasp the garment to assess its heft. Solid materials prove their worth, whereas flimsy synthetics fail. Depend on your tactile response when pulling items from the hanger. Maintain the standard every single morning. Your baseline is exactly dark drama + sharp edges + one molten flash.",
