  "venus_leo__moon_cancer__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "dark drama + hidden depth + one molten flash",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on dark drama + hidden depth + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical sensation of sleek heat as your compass. If a garment feels tepid or rough in your hands, put it down. Build your wardrobe methodically and deploy it with precision. Your core formula is dark drama + hidden depth + one molten flash. Picture a heavy, sweeping overcoat layered over a sharply constructed inner jacket, finished with a single, high-shine sculptural cuff. The bold outer layer delivers the drama, the inner construction holds the depth, and the polished accessory brings the necessary warm flash.\n\nApply the entrance test to every new garment. Stand up and take a single step forward. The silhouette must announce its heavy volume and high-shine finish on the very first stride. If the piece relies on a second glance to register, leave it on the rack. It must carry enough physical weight and sharp construction to act as a bold, undeniable event immediately. Look for immaculate surfaces and warm reflections. Discard anything hesitant or safe. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical blueprint that governs your wardrobe construction.",
      "tests": [
        "the entrance test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "To build dark drama and hidden depth, your materials must hold rigid structure and a warm, polished surface. Look for {texture_good_1} for sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually. Anchor your core garments in {texture_good_2} for knife-edge tailoring that never begs for a steamer. This dense foundation sets the stage for one molten flash. Pick up {texture_good_3} for statement footwear and accessories that reflect maximum light. Choose {texture_good_4} for slip dresses and linings that gleam under low light. Always apply the shadow check before taking a piece to the till. Drag the garment into a poorly lit corner of the shop. If the folds turn into a flat, lifeless grey instead of rich ink, leave it on the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Let your hands filter your fabrics before your eyes do.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually"
        },
        {
          "name": "Sharp wool twill",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "knife-edge tailoring that never begs for a steamer"
        },
        {
          "name": "Patent leather",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "statement footwear and accessories that reflect maximum light"
        },
        {
          "name": "Heavy silk satin",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "slip dresses and linings that gleam under low light"
        },
        {
          "name": "Techno gabardine",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "wrinkle-resistant trousers and jackets that keep a rigid shape"
        },
        {
          "name": "High-shine taffeta",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "evening pieces that bounce light and cut a clear silhouette"
        },
        {
          "name": "Polished calfskin",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "footwear and accessories with a slick, radiant surface"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "To sustain dark drama, your fabrics require a slick, warm surface. Reject anything that diffuses your edge. Put {texture_bad_1} through the crush test. Squeeze it in your fist and inspect the resulting folds. If the shadows look matt and lifeless instead of casting a sharp, inky contrast, the material will drag you down. Trust your hands. Run your fingers over {texture_bad_2}. If it feels chalky or catches on your skin, it lacks the dense structure your aesthetic demands. Drop it immediately. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. Pick it up and watch it collapse into a shapeless slump, completely failing to hold a rigid line. Rely on your tactile responses. Visuals deceive, but a frail weave exposes itself instantly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to instantly reject materials that soften your edge.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This specific collision builds the dark drama your wardrobe requires. Let {texture_good_1} rest alongside them to catch a warm light. Subject your combinations to a harsh spotlight. Observe the material under a bright bulb. You are looking for deep pools of darkness settling into the folds, proving your hidden depth. If the cloth reflects light perfectly evenly and shows no valleys, leave it on the rail. You require severe structural tension. Trust your touch and sight to reject flat, featureless surfaces.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your wardrobe by pairing these exact textural extremes to build structural tension.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your colours are strictly warm. Build your foundation with heavy sweeps of {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Replace stark whites with {core_colour_3}, and link contrasting pieces together using {core_colour_4}. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a brief visual pause. When you strike, do so with singular focus using {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Leave muddy pastel, icy grey, and dusty sage on the hanger. The greatest threat here is the costume trap. Piling on thick leather, heavy studs, a red lip, bright hardware, and dark eye makeup all at once tips the outfit into fancy dress. Fix this error by subtracting elements. Anchor your dark drama by restricting metallic hardware to a solitary gleam, returning every other piece to a solid matt black.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your palette as a strict architecture.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Deep bronze",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Golden camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
