          "failure": "costume: leather, studs, red lip, gold hardware and a smoky eye all at once tips drama into fancy dress",
          "fix": "hold the line at one molten flash and return every other element to matt black"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, let hidden depth take the lead. Build the base with sharp wool twill trousers in a warm golden camel. Introduce dark drama through the severe cut of a heavy silk satin blouse. Finish with a polished bronze cuff to supply a single molten flash. Always apply the pharmacy test. If you find yourself queuing for a prescription on your lunch break, you must not feel trapped by your own clothes. Strict presentation never requires physical suffering. Test every piece physically before you commit. Reach up high and twist your torso. Trust your body to reject bad cuts. If the crisp cotton poplin binds your shoulders, leave the item on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply your visual strategy to the workplace without diluting its impact.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim environments, let dark drama dictate the evening. Build the foundation from heavy silk satin or sharp wool twill in deep bronze. Disregard your reflection momentarily. Shut your eyes and evaluate how the garment settles on your shoulders. The tension of the fabric dictates its worth. Introduce a single warm flash of heavy gold jewellery near the collar to catch ambient candlelight, delivering your required one molten flash. Employ the endurance check. If standing in a taxi queue at midnight means enduring a restrictive waistband to maintain a shape, change your clothes. Pain destroys posture. Select forgiving structures that maintain their sharp edge without binding your ribs.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master low-light settings by relying on garment weight and precise structural choices.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Build your morning choices around bold expression and high-shine polish. A mundane run to the post office does not mean you must abandon your standards or endure physical discomfort. Do not accept a compromise between mobility and impact. Check the mirror to confirm you have executed dark drama + hidden depth + one molten flash. Rely on thick wool crepe in golden camel rather than flimsy knits. Anchor the silhouette with deep bronze leather boots. Ensure every buckle and zip features a warm, reflective metal finish. Lift the items before you dress. The sheer weight of the textile guarantees its construction. Avoid anything limp, muted, or understated. Choose a high-gloss patent leather belt to secure the look.",
      "sectionIntro": "Approach your daily routine as a rigorous testing ground for structural precision and aesthetic discipline.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your strategy relies entirely on warm hardware to slice through the dark drama of your garments. Stick strictly to {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. These materials bring necessary heat. Lift every chain, clasp, and zip in your palm before you buy. The undeniable mass of the object in your grip provides the only proof of quality. Heavy hardware anchors a piece. Flimsy alloy destroys the hidden depth you are constructing. Reject the trap of {excluded_finish} components. Antiqued, hammered, or oxidised treatments look instantly exhausted and lack crisp boundaries. Require a severely polished surface instead. You need brilliant, unbroken reflections to supply your one molten flash.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as structural light.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Pick up the piece from the glass counter. Assess its physical weight immediately. If the setting feels hollow, leave it on the tray. Your jewellery demands a foundation of dark drama, anchored by stones that hold absolute density. Choose a heavy cabochon of {stone_1} or a faceted {stone_2}. These gems possess the necessary hidden depth. Mount them strictly in blindingly luminous warm metal that catches every stray beam of light. Reject porous or matt bezels. Dull casings suffocate the stone and ruin the sharp boundaries of your silhouette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate each gem for pure density and unyielding light.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Test every clasp and buckle for structural integrity. If a {metal_1} ring feels feather-light, drop it. Steer clear of brushed or scuffed finishes. These textured alterations read as careless and ruin the precision of your outfit. Seek out strictly flawless, warm metals that gleam intensely under any condition. A solid, brilliantly polished surface guarantees the correct tension to ground your dark drama and supply one molten flash.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate hardware through your hands before you put it on.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You establish a solid base of dark drama. You layer garments to build hidden depth. Your accessories exist solely to provide one molten flash. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Execute the deprivation test on every potential addition. Place the item in a poorly lit corner. If it vanishes into the background, abandon it. It must catch the faintest ambient light and gleam fiercely. Begin your search with statement jewellery. Look for a polished metal collar. Demand a warm, high-polish finish that behaves like a mirror.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your finishing elements with ruthless physical precision.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Statement jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "polished metal collar, high polish"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select footwear to anchor your silhouette in high shine. Look for patent leather that captures every available light source. Execute the match strike check before keeping any new pair. Take the shoe into a dim hallway and ignite a small flame. The patent gloss must bounce that warm light back with a sharp, mirrored edge. If the reflection breaks or goes matt, leave the shoe behind. Build dark drama through an absolute commitment to a polished surface. Run your bare thumb over the toe box. You want a slick, glass-like resistance. Trust this tactile feedback over any printed label.",
      "sectionIntro": "Ground your wardrobe with footwear that demands a flawless surface.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "patent leather, patent gloss"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Select eyewear carved from thick acetate. Demand a high-shine finish that catches light sharply. Deep bronze and warm golden camel frames with bright gold hinges carry enough physical weight to ground your face. Every piece must preserve that hidden depth. Before you leave, run the silhouette check. Stand with the window behind you and study your outline in the mirror. You must still see a sharp shape projecting dark drama against the glass. If the borders dissolve or the frames vanish into the shadows, swap them for a heavier pair.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your final hardware and test the entire silhouette before stepping out.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Eyewear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "acetate frame, high shine"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored garments demand precise architectural lines, taking their shapes directly from sharp {recommended_pattern_1}. Fluid pieces require a different strategy. Allow large-scale {recommended_pattern_2} to drape without losing structural impact. Anchor your wardrobe with strict, high-contrast graphic motifs. Pass over faded edges, blurred borders, and weak {avoid_pattern_1}. Demand visual clarity to support your expression. Apply your personal low-light rule. Stand ten feet away in a dim corridor. The print must still register as a deliberate geometric strike, never dissolving into a muddy wash. This exact clarity establishes true dark drama. Balance these intense graphic patterns with rich solids to secure crucial hidden depth. Keep the underlying pattern colour warm to maintain perfect cohesion.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your visual weight with deliberate graphic tension, stripping away anything that lacks distinct shape or clear intent.",
      "tests": [
        "the low-light rule (must still read as intent from ten feet in dim light)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Subject your prints to the distance trial. Hang your {recommended_pattern_1} garment at the far end of the shop. Step away and observe the edges. If the shapes merge into a chaotic smudge, drop the fabric. A polished aesthetic demands absolute structural clarity. The borders must stay crisp and the warm tones must assert themselves. This strict boundary separates deliberate dark drama from mere confusion. Pick up the garment and examine the threads for hidden depth. It must hold intricate detail at a proximity of two inches but project pure geometric intent from afar. If your eyes strain to decipher the design, leave the piece on the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every print for absolute visual clarity in poor lighting.",
      "tests": [
        "the low-light rule (must still read as intent from ten feet in dim light)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_leo__moon_capricorn__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "quiet grandeur + softness + one molten flash",
    "closing": "Trust the sheer weight of your garments to lead the way, mapping every physical instinct straight back to quiet grandeur + softness + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical weight of a garment as your compass. Heavy, fluid fabrics fall with purpose and move without catching. Pick up a piece and feel the density in your hands. If it feels brittle, put it back. Your core formula is quiet grandeur + softness + one molten flash. Picture a dense, sweeping overcoat draped over fine, brushed knitwear, finished with a single heavy piece of warm hardware resting against your collarbone. The matt layers absorb the light, and the hardware catches it.\n\nBuild your wardrobe slowly, but deploy it fast. Scrutinise the seams and the drape before you commit to a purchase. Once the pieces are yours, dress by physical instinct rather than rigid planning. Before you step out, apply the host test. Ask yourself if the garments support your structure or if they dictate your movement. If the clothing feels like a costume that wears you, take it down a layer. You are the host. The clothing merely sets the table. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "Commit this blueprint to memory. It is the filter for every garment you bring into your physical space.",
      "tests": [
        "the host test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Subject every garment to the wrist test. Press a sleeve against your inner arm before you look at the label. If it scratches or drags, drop it. True softness yields completely to the skin. Build your foundation on {texture_good_1} that compresses and springs back under pressure. Seek out {texture_good_3} for tailored coats that hold clean lines year after year. Anchor this quiet grandeur with bags and boots in {texture_good_2} that will mould to your shape. Slip {texture_good_4} underneath to catch a warm glow and provide fluid movement. These materials create the required canvas for your palette and that one molten flash of metal. Treat the following list as your permanent baseline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise physical quality before a garment ever reaches the fitting room.",
