    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Leave {texture_bad_1} on the rack. It feels hollow in the hand and destroys any attempt at quiet grandeur. Avoid anything that fails to soothe the delicate skin of your forearm. If the fibres stiffen or catch against you, reject the item. Dismiss {texture_bad_2} instantly. It reflects light with a synthetic glare and completely disrupts your warm palette. Walk away from {texture_bad_3} when it crackles under pressure. You require textiles that drape and collapse naturally. Let the sheer gravity of a good fabric guide your choices away from these inferior substitutes.",
