    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build a distinctly warm palette. Construct your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Bridge these deep shades by laying {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} over them. These elements supply the quiet grandeur you require. Deploy your relief tone sparingly when the base grows too dense. Limit your brights to {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Pass over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels. Watch out for the dense forest trap. Piling heavy, matt shades on top of each other will bury you. Lift the look. Place a light layer at the collar, introduce polished leather, or use your relief tone to break the darkness. Gauge your physical response to the hues rather than relying solely on reflections.",
