    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low-light settings, quiet grandeur leads. Pick up a rich toffee silk shirt and gauge its drop. It must hold its shape perfectly without bright illumination to explain the cut. A private dinner requires the exact same camel cashmere you wear during a solitary morning coffee. Abandon the habit of keeping lesser items for private hours. Mix warm gold jewellery with matt brushed wool to catch the dim light of a restaurant booth. Inspect the seaming on a full-grain leather jacket. If the construction feels weak, leave it behind. Trust the heavy weave of thick tweed to frame your silhouette when the lamps go down.",
