    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Drop anything that dilutes your required dark drama. Pick up a piece of {texture_bad_1} and run your thumb over the surface. If the fibres feel chalky or stick to your hand, put the item back. You require absolute sharpness. Execute a drape check with {texture_bad_2}. Hang the material over your arm in dim lighting. If it drags your crisp outline into a dull blur instead of catching a warm gleam, it is useless to you. {texture_bad_3} fails just as quickly. Squeeze the fabric tightly in your fist. If it collapses into a limp heap or retains every crease, drop it immediately. Rely on physical resistance. Appearance deceives. Gravity tells the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to drop inferior materials the second you touch them.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Find your anchor in {sweet_spot_keyword_1}. Pair it with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to channel dark drama. Examine a piece by draping it in the shadows. Watch how the folds catch the warm ambient glow. If the hollows sink into deep black while the ridges throw back a hard, polished glare, you have found the right tension. Add {texture_good_1} to ground the shape. Gauge the absolute mass when you pull a garment from the rail. Dense fibres confirm construction quality.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn how to combine materials to build structure and light.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is exclusively warm. Construct your base from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Replace pure white with {core_colour_3}, and deploy {core_colour_4} as your bridge neutral. Keep your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Strike your deliberate accent using {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Leave Muddy pastel, Icy grey, and Dusty sage on the rack. Beware the costume trap. Piling heavy zips over patent leather alongside a red lip and darkened lids turns an imposing silhouette into a theatrical outfit. Fix this immediately. Secure your required dark drama, but limit the shine to a solitary flash of hardware. Return every remaining garment to matt black. Evaluate an ensemble by the cut resting against your collarbones. Focus on the sharp edges of the cloth. Glass reflections warp proportions. The physical structure dictates success.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your foundation with a strict system of heat and depth.",
