    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let athletic space lead your working hours. Ground this mobility with dark drama in deep bronze wool twill. Anchor the neck with a single heavy gold collar for a warm focal point. Apply the desk evaluation to every item you consider for the office. A punishing diary does not demand rigid cages. It requires crisp cotton poplin that accommodates sudden movement. Assess the weave of the shirt. Ensure it holds its shape while you bend. Drop the piece entirely if the sleeves restrict your arms.",
      "sectionIntro": "Deploy your style elements strategically to meet the demands of the working day.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Low light strips a silhouette down to its bones. Let dark drama lead in intimate settings. A long evening demands flexible construction rather than stiff panels. Rely on how the material yields to your joints. Grab the silk and crumple it in your fist. If it remains crushed, leave it behind. Pair a crisp cotton poplin shirt in golden camel with slick patent leather. Finish with a heavy, warm gold collar to catch the dim lighting. Let the dense drape dictate your form.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master close quarters and low lighting by letting your material performance dictate your choices.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Queuing at the chemist is not an excuse to dilute your aesthetic. Every mundane exit from your front door requires the exact equation of dark drama + athletic space + one molten flash. Navigate a chaotic daily schedule in polished wool twill that lets you sprint for a bus. Choose warm, deep bronze performance fabrics cut with sharp precision. Layer a golden camel knit over garments that allow total bodily freedom. Finish the look with a high-shine patent leather shoe. Test the utility by simulating a full range of motion. If a shoulder seam restricts your reach to the top shelf, leave it on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your daily errands as a rigorous test of your aesthetic discipline.",
      "tests": [
        "a packed day does not require hard clothes; it requires soft ones that can sprint (Wren)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Commit to a strictly warm metal foundation. Anchor your hardware with solid {metal_1} and heavy {metal_2}, reserving {metal_3} for minor structural details. Lift every piece of jewellery or hardware before committing. Visual assessments deceive the buyer. Solid mass confirms quality. If a zip or buckle feels hollow, leave it on the counter. Avoid pieces treated to look weathered or aged. A {excluded_finish} surface registers as exhausted against your garments. Keep every clasp, watch casing, and chain strictly polished so it catches the sun from down the street. This gleaming finish cuts through the dark drama of your wardrobe, introducing vital structure into an athletic space.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your metals dictate the baseline sharpness of your entire collection.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Your clothing provides the dark drama, and your silhouettes carve out the necessary athletic space. The hardware must carry enough physical gravity to match. Pick a piece up in your palm. Sight misleads, but actual density confirms value. Trust your hands to gauge the sheer weight of a setting. Select stones like {stone_1} and {stone_2} for their uncompromising density and light-holding clarity. Steer clear of oxidised, hammered, or antiqued treatments. These artificially aged finishes look exhausted and strip away the crispness you require. Insist instead on a strictly polished warm metal finish that throws off blinding reflections in broad daylight.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your hardware choices in undeniable physical mass and pristine clarity.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Lift the {metal_1} off the counter. Optic tricks hide cheap coatings. Rely solely on the downward pull of the object to judge its worth. Reject any intentionally scuffed or distressed surface. These faux-worn effects drain the intense sharpness from your garments. Demand a flawless, high-gloss execution in warm metal that throws a single hard beam of light. This pristine execution sharply defines your athletic space.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate hardware through physical mass and high-gloss reflection.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Construct your dark drama. Claim your athletic space. Complete the equation with one molten flash. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with statement jewellery, specifically a polished metal collar. Demand a high polish on every surface. Execute the blindfold assessment on these additions. Close your eyes and hold the object. If you cannot immediately identify the piece by its warm, unyielding curve and sheer structural scale in the dark, drop it. Look for solid forms that carry actual mass. Pick it up and assess the tension. The metal must possess immediate physical presence.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware strictly to provide the final deliberate strike to your outfit.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Statement jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "polished metal collar, high polish"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Choose footwear constructed from rigid patent leather. Apply a sensory evaluation to every pair you consider. Shut your eyes and pass your thumb over the vamp. You must feel a slick, frictionless patent gloss rather than a porous hide. If the material catches your skin, put the shoe down. This stark reflection provides the sharp edge you need to build an athletic space. Anchor these high-gloss surfaces with warm metal hardware. Look for solid brass rings or heavy bronze zips. These dense additions keep your foundation firmly locked in a polished lane.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your foundation must uphold the exact material standards you apply to your garments.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "patent leather, patent gloss"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your dark drama with thick acetate frames. Demand a high shine finish. Avoid matt surfaces entirely. The material must gleam with a glossy, perfectly polished reflection. Choose warm tones like deep bronze or golden camel to frame the face. Finally, conduct a tactile check before you step outside. Turn off the lights and run your fingers over your chosen accessories. You must feel the sharp slickness of the eyewear and the heavy edge of your metals without seeing them. If the pieces disappear under your touch in the darkness, they lack the structural intensity you need. Swap them out.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finalise your hardware strategy with specific eyewear and a strict tactile exit check.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Eyewear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "acetate frame, high shine"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the blackout test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Construct tailored pieces around the strict geometry of {recommended_pattern_1}. Push fluid garments to carry the bold scale of {recommended_pattern_2}. Drive dark drama through high-contrast graphic motifs rather than safe repetitions. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}. They lack the sharp definition required to build athletic space. Subject every print to a rigorous low-light evaluation. Stand ten feet away in a dim room. Trust your immediate visual instinct in the shadows. If the shapes blur into a messy wash, drop the garment. The motif must read as absolute intent in poor lighting. Ensure the underlying colours remain warm and the final presentation stays entirely polished.",
      "sectionIntro": "Command the visual impact of your wardrobe through deliberate geometry and scale.",
      "tests": [
        "the low-light rule (must still read as intent from ten feet in dim light)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Conduct the squint test. Pin a garment featuring {recommended_pattern_1} to the wall and narrow your eyes. If the graphic loses its hard edges and turns into a muddy blur, reject the piece. The lines must cut sharply across the fabric to support true dark drama. This strict visual boundary protects the athletic space of your structure. Warm tones dissolve into sludge without severe geometry. Walk away if the design loses its crisp, polished impact upon a quick glance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every printed surface to a strict visibility threshold.",
      "tests": [
        "the low-light rule (must still read as intent from ten feet in dim light)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_leo__moon_libra__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "dark drama + cool composure + one molten flash",
    "closing": "Trust the strict weight of your materials and the smooth mechanics of your layers to build dark drama + cool composure + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Squeeze the fabric in your hand to test its structural flexibility. If the textile fights your grip or feels brittle against your skin, leave it on the rail. Your wardrobe must function as a reactive skin for your daily life. Keep the overall temperature of your foundation warm and adaptable, regardless of the dye. Memorise your styling equation. It is dark drama + cool composure + one molten flash. Build this by pairing a heavy, sweeping overcoat with a crisp, rigorously tailored shirt. Finish the look with a single, highly polished piece of hardware that catches the light when you hand a coffee cup to a friend.\n\nBuild your wardrobe slowly as a modular system and drift by mood each morning. Before you purchase any new item, put it through the flight test. Put the garment on and physically move around the fitting room. Sit down, reach for an overhead shelf, and simulate a fast walk to a departure gate. If the cut restricts your stride or traps your shoulders, take it off immediately. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Range of motion does not. Dress for the reality of your physical environment, not a static photograph.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural foundation, providing the exact tests and equations required to build a fully adaptable wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build for physical resilience. To ground your dark drama and sustain your cool composure, hunt for materials that respond to motion. Rely on tactile feedback. Assess a garment by bending the cloth. If the weave feels too rigid to navigate a crowded terminal, drop it. Look for {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Rely on {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement. Seek out {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Use {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. These fibres build the polished, warm canvas you require before adding one molten flash. Prioritise the elements ranked below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Hunt for tactile fibres that support your need for constant movement and sharp precision.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Worsted wool",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day"
        },
        {
          "name": "Technical nylon",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little"
        },
        {
          "name": "Lightweight gabardine",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "transitional jackets with rigid structure and no heavy drag"
        },
        {
          "name": "Matt silk",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "a frictionless fluid layer added without bulk"
        },
        {
          "name": "Crisp linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "breathable separation over fluid drapes in warmer weather"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} the moment it catches on your knuckles. It creates static friction instead of sliding clean. Your dark drama relies on heavy, deliberate draping. Drop the piece from chest height to watch how it falls. If it plummets like a stone or crumples in a lifeless pile, leave it on the shop floor. Avoid {texture_bad_2} when it squeaks under a pinched thumb and forefinger. This synthetic drag indicates materials that will trap heat and stifle your skin. Toss a piece onto a chair to see if it catches the air. Fabrics must breathe to sustain a warm palette. Let the scales dictate your choices. Visual appeal deceives, but physical heft tells the absolute truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your hands will tell you when a fabric will betray you before you ever put it on.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Build the core of your wardrobe on the strict intersection of {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This precise pairing anchors the required dark drama. Apply a strict aerodynamic check before making a purchase. Sweep the item through the air and watch it settle on a flat surface. It must cut cleanly and land with a definitive shape. If the fabric floats aimlessly or collapses into an indistinct pile, reject it entirely. Rely on {texture_good_1} only when it passes this exact standard. A matt, warm palette demands rigorous structural integrity to remain sharp.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down the exact tension required between your foundational fabrics.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your base is strictly warm. Build a foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} in worsted wool or fine ribbed merino. Substitute harsh white with {core_colour_3}. Apply {core_colour_4} as a bridge between contrasting shades. Introduce {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent. Treat your relief option strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over icy pastel, neon brights, and cold blue-grey entirely. Watch for the hard shell trap. When life speeds up, do not reach for armour, technical jackets, and stiff utility layers. Swap the shell for a brushed cotton layer that moves just as fast and warms you as well. This anchors dark drama in true physical utility.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your palette as a strict filtering system to eliminate guesswork at the rack.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Warm taupe",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
