    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the office, lead with dark drama. Build your foundation using warm taupe worsted wool trousers and a crisp cotton poplin shirt. Support this deep base with polished gold rings and camel outerwear. A quick coffee run does not require packing away the heavy gold. Keep the polished rings on and stay in your worsted wool. Avoid swapping sharp lines for shapeless basics just to leave the building. Let deep tones and crisp edges set the standard for the working day.",
      "sectionIntro": "Calibrate your style elements for the working week.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim light, let dark drama lead. Close settings demand garments that invite proximity without shouting. Put on a fine ribbed merino knit in warm taupe. Pair it with worsted wool trousers. This combination creates a dense surface that absorbs the room. Remember that a simple errand for a morning pastry does not require stripping away your entire atmosphere. A technical nylon shell worn over camel cotton poplin keeps that exact mood intact. Keep your jewellery close to the skin. A matt gold ring next to a steel watch face gives the eye a precise place to rest when the lights drop.",
      "sectionIntro": "Scale your proportions for closeness and low-light environments.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A brisk walk to the local bakery gives you no excuse to drop your atmosphere as you move among your neighbours. Waiting in the queue for a prescription demands the exact same baseline. Reach for a technical nylon jacket in warm taupe over a heavy camel knit. Assess the yarn in your fingers. The density of the textile dictates its true quality. Let gravity act as your absolute guide. Your daily equation remains strictly constant regardless of the venue. Build every single look using dark drama + cool composure + one molten flash. Mix silver and gold freely, and keep every garment meticulously smooth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering the mundane demands exactly the same discipline as dressing for an evening event.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "You operate on a dual metal system. Keep {personal_metal_1} and {personal_metal_2} reserved strictly for jewellery worn directly against the skin to establish a warm base. For clasps, zips, and buckles, deploy {structural_metal_1} or {structural_metal_2}. This strict division supplies the necessary dark drama without creating visual friction. Test the mass of every belt buckle and zip pull in your palm. A high gloss can mask cheap alloys, but heavy materials provide solid proof of quality. Leave fake patinas behind. Simulated age, distressed alloys, and hammered textures generate muddy clutter against a present-tense style. Stick to a highly polished finish for all hardware. Any {excluded_finish} element merely diffuses the precise structural impact you require.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as a deliberate mechanism, separating what touches your skin from what constructs your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Source your stones deliberately by evaluating their structural density. Hold the piece in your palm to register its gravity. Genuine gems provide a distinct, undeniable heaviness. Select {stone_1} and {stone_2}. Look for stones that project a warm clarity rather than cloudy inclusions. This builds dark drama through clean, absolute density. Reject any intentionally degraded mounts and rough edges. Such treatments introduce unwanted historical clutter against a present-tense wardrobe. Set your stones instead in a brilliant, mirror-finish {metal_1} or {metal_2}.",
      "sectionIntro": "Hardware operates as a dense physical anchor for your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Examine the {metal_1} piece before you commit to it. Heavy hardware grounds the dark drama of a silhouette. Do not accept lightweight alloys that rattle. Shun tarnished chains and heavily distressed clasps. Such calculated wear creates visual friction that interrupts cool composure. Demand highly polished surfaces instead. A gleaming mirror finish on a {stone_1} setting brings a warm, deliberate edge to the garment. Gauge the heft of every zipper pull between your fingers. Mixing ornamental and industrial registers requires solid materials. If a piece feels hollow, leave it on the shelf.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate the integrity of every piece of hardware through physical touch.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories provide the one molten flash necessary to anchor your dark drama and sharpen your cool composure. Enforce a strict limit of one or two primary pieces per look. Begin with eyewear. Look for substantial acetate frames carrying a highly polished finish. Hold the glasses to confirm their solid construction. Apply a subtraction check before you leave the house. Remove the final item you put on. If your warm taupe worsted wool trousers and crisp cotton poplin shirt still command their shape without it, leave that extra piece on the table.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your finishing touches by relying on physical weight rather than visual noise.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Eyewear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "acetate frame, polished"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the take-off test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Evaluate a smooth leather crossbody through strict physical interaction. Run your thumb along the polished zips. You need these fixtures to mix silver and gold tones, supporting a dual register metal strategy. Seek out a warm camel dye that saturates the hide evenly. Execute a full motion check in the shop. Fill the bag, swing it across your chest, and lift it clear over your head in one continuous arc. If the strap twists or the hardware snags, drop it. You demand absolute mechanical reliability to maintain your cool composure when navigating crowded public transit or assisting others in your community.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test practical accessories by checking their physical structure and hardware gleam.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "smooth leather crossbody, polished zips"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
