      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Ground your warm taupe knits with a smooth leather flat. Inspect the footwear surface. Demand a clean gloss, deliberately rejecting any matt or distressed finishes. This unbroken shine reflects light and builds the dark drama of the silhouette. Before stepping out, conduct a final material audit. Look in the mirror and physically remove the heaviest piece of dual-register jewellery. If the remaining outfit retains cool composure without it, leave that extra metal on the dressing table. Trust your hands to strip away the excess.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finish the silhouette at the floor and rigorously edit the final result.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "smooth leather flat, clean gloss"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the take-off test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Divide your patterns between structure and drape. Tailored items take their geometry from the weave. A heavy jacket requires {recommended_pattern_1} embedded deep in the warp and weft. Fluid pieces take their motif from surface dye. Look for {recommended_pattern_2} running across draped silk. Scale and contrast must remain adaptable. High-contrast graphics build dark drama. Low-contrast tonal variations provide a foundation for cool composure. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}. They disrupt the adaptability of a warm palette. Evaluate every print in action. Lift the garment from the rail and swing it. The motif must soften into a fluid, rhythmic surface as you move. It should blur gently into a continuous wave rather than sitting like a flat, rigid picture. Trust your immediate physical reaction to the fabric. If the geometry stays stiff while the cloth ripples, put the piece down. Anchor successful prints with {core_colour_1} to keep the foundation grounded.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering pattern requires you to dictate exactly how a motif behaves on the body.",
      "tests": [
        "the passing test (reads as soft, pleasant texture in motion)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Hang a {recommended_pattern_1} piece on a door and step ten paces away. Look at it while shifting your weight. The sharp edges must dissolve. A successful print melds into a warm, rhythmic grain from across the floor. If the motif remains glaringly legible at this distance, leave it on the rail. It should project cool composure from afar and reserve its dark drama for close quarters. The right motif acts as a subtle vibration in the cloth, never a rigid signpost.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply the ten-pace blur test to evaluate any print before buying.",
      "tests": [
        "the passing test (reads as soft, pleasant texture in motion)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_leo__moon_sagittarius__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "dark drama + fast movement + one molten flash",
    "closing": "Rely on the weight of the cloth, trust your tactile responses, and always construct your wardrobe around dark drama + fast movement + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust your physical instinct for velocity. When you pull a heavy wool coat over a crisp silk shirt, the resulting combination must propel you forward. Build your collection slowly. Deploy the garments fast. Rely on the hesitation test as your ultimate filter. If you put on a structural jacket and pause for even a second before securing the buttons, take the garment off immediately. That fraction of doubt proves the piece lacks the momentum your aesthetic requires. Looks lie. Your immediate physical commitment to the weight of a garment does not.\n\nEvery piece you acquire must serve a strict visual equation. Memorise it exactly. Your core formula is dark drama + fast movement + one molten flash. Picture a heavy, dark sweeping trench coat layered over a sharply tailored suit that cuts close to the body. Add a high-shine leather boot engineered for rapid walking. Anchor the silhouette with a single piece of heavy, warm, highly polished jewellery sitting at the collarbone. Never compromise this equation for understated basics. Demand a sharp finish that carries heavy physical weight and catches the light.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise the exact physical parameters and strict visual equations that dictate your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the hesitation test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation on textiles that deliver dark drama and fast movement. Let your hands execute the friction test. Drag your palm rapidly down a sleeve and demand an immediate, frictionless slip. If the surface creates drag, leave it behind. Demand polished, warm finishes. Look for {texture_good_1} for sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually. Choose {texture_good_2} for knife-edge tailoring that never begs for a steamer. Anchor the look with {texture_good_3} for statement footwear and accessories that reflect maximum light and guarantee one molten flash. Layer {texture_good_4} for slip dresses and linings that gleam under low light. Memorise these core performers.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to identify the core textiles that construct your wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually"
        },
        {
          "name": "Sharp wool twill",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "knife-edge tailoring that never begs for a steamer"
        },
        {
          "name": "Patent leather",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "statement footwear and accessories that reflect maximum light"
        },
        {
          "name": "Heavy silk satin",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "slip dresses and linings that gleam under low light"
        },
        {
          "name": "Techno gabardine",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "wrinkle-resistant trousers and jackets that keep a rigid shape"
        },
        {
          "name": "High-shine taffeta",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "evening pieces that bounce light and cut a clear silhouette"
        },
        {
