    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Evaluate every new garment by touch. Swipe your knuckles quickly across the fabric and search for absolute slickness. If the material catches your skin, abandon the piece. You need zero surface resistance to execute dark drama. Fabrics like {texture_bad_1} trap warm light in a dead, matt finish and stall your speed. Squeeze a length of {texture_bad_2} in your fist. If it crushes into dry wrinkles, it fails the grade. Run your fingers over {texture_bad_3}. It clings rather than gliding. Rely on physical feedback over visual appeal. If the cloth fights your grip, it fails the standard.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject materials that slow you down.",
      "tests": [
