        "the friction test (run your hand swiftly down the sleeve; seek the slip)"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is strictly warm. Build the foundation for dark drama with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Employ {core_colour_3} as your stark white substitute. Deploy {core_colour_4} to bridge gaps. Drive fast movement through this heavy base by striking it with a single deliberate jolt of {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Keep your relief tone scarce. Apply it only to give the eye a brief pause. Pass over muddy pastel, icy grey, and dusty sage entirely. Watch for the fade trap. Weak dyes steal your momentum and dilute your visual weight. If a piece washes you out, rescue the look right away with a saturated collar detail or a brilliant shoe.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your colour selection as a strict set of tools for building visual weight.",
