    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject materials that sit like a stiff shell. Demand that every garment yields to your shape. Put the piece on and wait thirty seconds to feel if it dissolves into your warm body heat or pushes back. {texture_bad_1} fails this instantly. Pinch it between your thumb and forefinger to catch the sharp, unyielding threads. It disrupts that essential quiet undercurrent with unwanted friction. Avoid {texture_bad_2} completely. Grip it tightly and listen for the hollow squeak. If the cloth feels cold, brittle, and refuses to drape smoothly over your bare skin, drop it. Let your fingertips make the final call. Visuals deceive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to catch the materials that actively reject your shape.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This precise contrast secures your quiet undercurrent. Squeeze a piece of {texture_good_1} blindly. Assess the resistance. The weave must surrender completely, collapsing into a heavy, warm puddle rather than retaining rigid folds. Reject stiff threads. Drop rigid constructions back on the rack. The sweet spot lives in the tension between a dense, matt surface and a yielding edge. Read the cloth by touch alone. Density offers hard proof.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your textural foundation by mastering these specific tactile pairings.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is strictly warm. Build your foundation upon {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} to anchor heavy coats or tailored trousers. Introduce {core_colour_4} as a grounding neutral. Apply {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate focal point. Deploy your relief tone exclusively as a soft note used sparingly near the face. Pass over stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. They will drain you. Watch for the swaddling trap. Stacking too many shapeless neutral pieces dissolves your silhouette into a vague cloud. Fix this immediately. Restore a sharp collar or a rigid cuff to maintain your quiet grandeur.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this precise colour system and reject outside trends entirely.",
      "rankedItems": [
