      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Test the density of every piece of {metal_1} before you acquire it. Forget the sheen. Grams offer proof. A genuinely heavy item grounds your look and serves as that essential quiet undercurrent. Avoid high-gloss, reflective finishes. Polished surfaces become sharp and visually distracting against your deep, warm clothing. Instead, look for a brushed or matt texture to maintain a cohesive aesthetic. Hold the item in your palm and gauge the heft. If it feels weightless, put it back.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware by weight to ensure it anchors your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
