      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "The heavy drape of your garments establishes quiet grandeur. Their precise construction provides a quiet undercurrent. Your accessories exist entirely to deliver the final requirement. They must provide one molten flash. Limit yourself to exactly one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with your handbags. Seek out structured full-grain leather. The body of the bag must remain entirely matt, broken only by a single polished clasp. Apply the heirloom test before you purchase anything new. Evaluate the object to see if it holds the warm density of a permanent artifact. If the hardware feels empty or the leather feels thin, leave it in the shop. True luxury relies on permanent, physical substance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Dictate the focal point of your outfit by selecting accessories with ruthless physical standards.",
      "rankedItems": [
