    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Turn to scarves. Seek out pure silk in a matt finish. Avoid anything shiny or slippery. Pick the piece up. Assess its drag and drape. Apply the keepsake test. Ask yourself if you would fold this length of bitter chocolate fabric into a tissue-lined box to preserve for fifty years. If the material feels temporary, leave it behind. Look for a dense weave that anchors your wardrobe with quiet grandeur. A scarf must wrap the neck securely and provide substantial, warm insulation. It functions as a self-contained layer of protection. Let the fabric speak through its construction rather than its sheen.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select scarves with strict attention to fabric weight and friction.",
