    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, your binding equation is quiet grandeur + sensory comfort + one molten flash. Build your baseline with garments that move without sound. A structured camel coat or a matt silk blouse establishes the silhouette. Support this standard with unseen softness. Rely on pure fibres. Finish the look with a single glint of warm yellow gold at the collarbone. Treat a long day of meetings as a physical endurance test. A heavy cashmere jumper and rich toffee trousers provide exactly what you need to remain focused. You dress with intention for every professional demand. Drop the careless corporate defaults.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the balance of your daily professional environment.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim dining rooms and close spaces, rely on quiet grandeur + sensory comfort + one molten flash. Trust the heavy drape of rich toffee silk and the soft friction of camel brushed wool. Pick a garment up and gauge its heft in the shadows. Avoid flat, matt synthetics. Visuals deceive in low light, but heavy cloth never does. Treat a quiet evening with close friends as a deliberate event. Layer a thick cashmere knit under a heavy full-grain leather coat. Warm, reflective gold supplies the necessary illumination when candlelight hits your wrist. Keep the silhouette simple and let the substantial weight of the weave do the work.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your evening and intimate wardrobe with physical weight and precise layers.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A Tuesday morning trip to the pharmacy does not suspend your rules. Buying vegetables from the local stall is still a specific event requiring a tactile response. Reach for a camel cashmere wrap coat instead of an unconsidered fleece. Pair it with a rich toffee silk scarf tied closely at the neck. Choose a single solid warm gold ring in a matt finish to ground the soft textiles. Your baseline requirement remains quiet grandeur + sensory comfort + one molten flash. Reject any garment that feels thin or rigid. Test the drape of your brushed wool trousers and ensure the weave yields easily.",
      "sectionIntro": "Maintain your stylistic discipline for every ordinary errand.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Anchor your aesthetic with a warm dominant hardware strategy. Rely on {metal_1} and {metal_2} for your belt buckles, zips, and jewellery. You can introduce {metal_3} sparingly as an accent. Lift every piece before you buy it. Appearance deceives, but gravity reveals the truth of the metal. Flimsy casting ruins a garment. Steer clear of {excluded_finish} surfaces. A highly polished blinding finish introduces a jarring glare that shatters your quiet grandeur. Fix this by demanding brushed or matt textures to keep the visual temperature cohesive. This disciplined approach ensures every structural detail supports your ultimate goal of sensory comfort.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate hardware as the structural foundation of your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "To achieve quiet grandeur, select stones that absorb light rather than refracting it aggressively. Seek out {stone_1} and {stone_2} for their warm opacity. Test the setting by running your thumb over the bezel. Ensure the construction feels entirely solid. Avoid mirrored, reflective hardware. Such finishes create a sharp disruption against soft textiles. Correct this error by anchoring your stones in matt or brushed metals. This maintains a cohesive visual line and guarantees unbroken sensory comfort. Reserve {stone_3} for moments requiring subtle depth rather than glaring brilliance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your jewellery choices in physical density and muted, warm light.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Grasp the clasp or buckle firmly. A substantial component will feel instantly cold and dense in your palm. Your physical intuition serves as the ultimate guide when assessing {metal_1} or {stone_1}. If an element feels hollow or sounds tinny when tapped, leave it on the shelf. Highly polished hardware snags the eye and ruins the quiet grandeur of your wardrobe. Sharp, mirrored finishes clash poorly with soft, warm textiles. Choose matt and lightly brushed metal components to blend seamlessly with your woven pieces.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply a strict physical threshold to all hardware before you put it on.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
