    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Build your foundation on quiet grandeur. Guarantee your base layers provide absolute sensory comfort. Then, use your accessories to strike exactly one molten flash. Restrict your arrangement to one or two strong pieces per look. Fasten your selected items, evaluate the total finish, and deliberately remove whichever detail fights for attention. A single heavy anchor is always enough. Start this practice with handbags. Seek out full-grain leather construction. Demand a warm, matt body interrupted by exactly one polished flash of hardware. Grasp the clasp or chain to test its density. True quality sinks heavily into your hand.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use your accessories as precision instruments to anchor your wardrobe and direct the eye.",
      "rankedItems": [
