      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Treat your warm keepsake jewellery as a structural requirement. Look for heavy aged brass mixed with a single molten gold accent. Trust the immediate physical weight of the metal to verify the sensory comfort of these pieces. A matt brass cuff paired with a polished gold pendant establishes quiet grandeur. If a piece feels hollow, discard it. Before stepping out, strip away the excess. Drop the secondary brass chain or the competing rings. A solitary, weighty brass element provides enough anchor on its own.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your final metal accents with a ruthless eye.",
      "rankedItems": [
