          "name": "Crisp linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "breathable separation over fluid drapes in warmer weather"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the edge test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Test every shirt and jacket by folding the collar or pinching the cuff. If the textile cannot maintain an angle and instead collapses into a puddle, reject it. {texture_bad_1} mimics heavy wool on the hanger but turns limp against the skin. {texture_bad_2} catches under your fingernails and pills after a single cool wash. {texture_bad_3} appears matt from a distance but develops a plastic shine when subjected to friction. Let your tactile response dictate your choices. If the cloth feels spongy or refuses to snap back into a hard crease, leave it on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and eliminate the materials that actively fight your structural requirements.",
      "tests": [
        "the edge test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build a cool foundation. Run your fingers down the seams. You are looking for absolute precision. If the material folds limply or loses its shape, drop the piece immediately. A successful {texture_good_1} will hold a firm boundary. Heaviness indicates structural integrity. Squeeze the hem. It must fight back slightly. This resistance confirms the weave has enough structure.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify the precise material combinations that anchor your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the edge test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is definitively cool. Build your base out of {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Reach for {core_colour_3} as a white substitute. Anchor the look with {core_colour_4} as a structural dark. Deploy {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accents. Apply your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green. Train your eye to spot hidden warmth in any dye. Reject it immediately. Beware the total ice trap. An unbroken slab of {core_colour_1} on {core_colour_2} will read as a blank void instead of deliberate control. Shatter this flat freeze with a high-shine interruption. Fasten a mirror-finish cuff, pull on a patent boot, or inject a single strike of {accent_colour_1} to carve out sharp edges.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your colours as architectural materials with strict jobs.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Stark navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Icy grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Optical white",
