    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} the moment you touch it. Wring the hem between your knuckles. If it crinkles and stays crushed, it will warp over the course of an afternoon. Steer clear of {texture_bad_2}. Drag your fingernail across the surface. If it snags or feels like a synthetic film, put it back. To maintain balanced proportions, your garments must hold their own architecture. Throw a piece across your bed. If it drifts down slowly and collapses into a shapeless mound, it lacks the necessary weight. You need materials that cut through the air and land with a solid thud. {texture_bad_3} clings unpredictably to the body and destroys any clean, cool lines. Demand cloth that falls smoothly and retains its structural integrity.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every material by how it reacts in your hands before it ever touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Pair {sweet_spot_keyword_1} against {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build hidden depth into your collection. Assess every new cloth with your hands. A mirror can trick your eye, but the immediate tactile response of a fabric is absolute. Trust your grip over your reflection. Twist the material for ten seconds and let go. If it retains deep creases, abandon the item. Your {texture_good_1} must survive a transatlantic commute confined in a narrow aeroplane seat and emerge perfectly crisp. A cool surface temperature signals a tight, resilient weave. Notice how the material shifts over your skin as you sit. Seek out textiles that snap back into shape instantly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the tactile combinations that dictate the structure of your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your strictly cool palette with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} as your white substitute, and {core_colour_4} as your structural dark. Restrict deliberate accents to {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Deploy your relief tone sparingly as a soft note to break up solid colour. Avoid Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green entirely. Construct outfits with balanced proportions. Beware the urge to armour up. When your schedule accelerates, you might instinctively grab stiff utility garments or rigid technical coats. Drop them. Exchange that severe exterior for a thick brushed cotton layer. It responds to your pace, giving you structure without restricting movement. Let your hands dictate your choices. Pick up the garment, judge its true weight, and rely on your grip.",
