    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the desk, balanced proportions take the lead. Establish your frame first with a structured dove grey trouser. This sets a precise boundary. Once the shape is set, layer in softness through a washed silk shirt or a muted boiled wool knit. The materials sit quietly. Complete the garment formula with one refined touch. Consider a cool silver cuff or a single matt lapel pin. Rely on your hands to gauge the finish. Even on a frantic deadline day, maintain your geometry. Stepping away for coffee does not excuse a collapsed silhouette. Keep the lines deliberate. Select every piece by its shape first.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your working uniform with deliberate structure, relying on shape to set your boundaries.",
      "tests": [
