    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, softness leads. Close quarters require cloth that yields to the hand rather than holding rigid space. Reach for cloud-soft lambswool or washed silk in cool deep teal. Avoid anything stiff. Rely on matt surfaces that absorb dim light. An unexpected evening errand provides no reason to drop your standards. Keep your balanced proportions intact even in private. Frame the look with a subtle white gold chain as your one refined touch. Grasp the material tightly. Your fingers detect true quality. If the weave feels harsh or brittle, discard it immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is how you translate your visual language into close quarters.",
