    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat routine tasks as your baseline. Walking down the road to buy paracetamol does not excuse abandoning your silhouette. Demand the absolute consistency of balanced proportions + softness + one refined touch everywhere you go. Reach for dove grey boiled wool instead of unconsidered fleece. Pull on a deep teal knit instead of defaulting to shapeless cotton. Trust your hands when you prepare for a simple outing. If an item feels rigid or asks for an audience, leave it on the hanger. Fasten your collar with a heavy silver pin instead of relying on plastic buttons. Maintain your cool, muted palette rigorously. Every choice must serve your self-contained nature. Construct quiet armour that yields strictly to your own touch.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your mundane routine as a strict practice ground for your personal standard.",
