    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Look for stones that absorb rather than scatter light. Opt for the cloudy depth of {stone_1}, the dense opacity of {stone_2}, or the cool weight of {stone_3}. Weigh the object in your palm to confirm its actual mass. Sight misleads, but physical density is undeniable. You require substantial heft to anchor the softness of your woven fibres. Avoid glossy chrome. A sharp mirror finish cuts a distracting glare against any muted colour. Such severe reflections fracture the look. Instead, specify brushed or matt hardware to maintain cohesive, balanced proportions.",
