    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Once you secure the necessary balanced proportions and anchor the garments in deep softness, your hardware provides that final one refined touch. Limit your additions to exactly one or two strong pieces per look. Begin this process with your handbags. Source full-grain leather or thick suede fitted with matt, brushed hardware. Put every bag through the closed-eye diagnostic. Grasp the metal clasp in your fingers and shut your eyes. You are evaluating whether the piece feels like a singular, cool anchor, offering quiet density rather than uncontrolled noise. Let your bare hands trace the hide. Unyielding quality in your grip remains your truest guide.",
