    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Treat scarves as structural extensions of your clothing. Seek out generous silk or fine wool with a strictly matt finish. Wrap the material closely to maintain balanced proportions around your collarbone. Rely on the inherent softness of washed silk or cloud-soft lambswool to provide necessary texture. Avoid anything that shines or slips out of place. Apply the focal-point test to the dye. Gather the dove grey or deep teal fabric in your fists. The colour must hold a concentrated area of cool, quiet intensity deep in the folds, rather than projecting a broad surface glare. Trust your fingers to gauge the thickness. If the textile feels insubstantial or requires constant readjustment, leave it behind.",
