    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your garments with belts cut from wide full-grain leather, secured by a matt, heavily brushed buckle. This solid hardware introduces necessary weight against the softness of washed silk or boiled wool. Approach keepsake jewellery with identical strictness. Seek out a deep stone set in cool, aged silver. Before finishing, subject your look to a final visual diagnostic. Keep only a single highlight active. If an aged pendant competes with your leather belt, remove the weaker piece. Maintaining balanced proportions means choosing one focal point and strictly removing all others.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply a final strict filter to the objects you carry and wear.",
