    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in low-contrast tonal prints to maintain a cool reserve. Force tailored garments to take {recommended_pattern_1}, using the crisp cut to anchor the geometry. Let fluid pieces take {recommended_pattern_2}, allowing the drape to manipulate the shapes. Scan the rail and pass over stark graphics, harsh colour blocking, and {avoid_pattern_1}. Demand balanced proportions in every repeat so the design never overrides the garment. Trust your hands to check the underlying softness of the fabric. Then apply the lamplight test. Bring the piece into a dark space next to a dim bulb. The pattern must cool and recede into the shadows, sinking into the cloth rather than sharpening into aggressive lines. Reject it if the contrast spikes.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every print to rigorous physical testing before it enters your wardrobe.",
