  "venus_libra__moon_gemini__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust your physical response to a garment before you check the mirror. When you put a piece on, test its mobility. Lift your arms and twist your torso. If the cloth restricts you, drop it. Your wardrobe functions as a responsive toolkit for shifting environments. Anchor your choices in a cool temperature palette and build your daily outfits around your core formula of balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch. Picture a neatly tucked top, a wide-leg fluid trouser that sways as you step, and a single crisp collar. This combination anchors you while leaving you entirely free to engage with the people around you.\n\nBuild your collection steadily through careful curation, then deploy your pieces quickly based on the context of your day. To guarantee a garment will perform under pressure, run the seam test. Turn the piece inside out and trace your fingers along the interior stitching. Ensure the joins are fully bound and lie flat against the fabric. If the internal construction feels rough or looks rushed, leave the item on the rack. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master these baseline rules to evaluate garments and construct outfits that function in any environment.",
      "tests": [
        "the seam test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe from fibres that deliver light movement and maintain balanced proportions throughout a demanding day. Your materials must adapt to changing environments while holding a crisp, cool structure. Rely on {texture_good_1} for shirting that provides pure separation between garments. Layer {texture_good_2} against the skin for close-to-body lines that stretch easily as you engage with others. Anchor these with {texture_good_3} trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing. Add {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind without adding bulk. Before you buy, apply the recovery test. Crush a handful of the fabric in your fist, let go, and watch how fast it snaps back to a smooth finish. Choose from the materials ranked below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical fabrics that construct your silhouette and support your daily momentum.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
