    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Leave {texture_bad_1} on the hanger if it feels brittle or stiff. A rigid textile fights the body and ruins any chance of adding one refined touch to your day. Check {texture_bad_2} for resilience. Squeeze a section tightly and let it fall. If the material retains sharp creases instead of dropping out smooth, put the garment down. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely when it traps heat or clings to the skin. You need textiles that breathe and respond. Trust your hands. If a surface feels clammy or refuses to drape properly, it will fail you in practice.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and reject the materials that sabotage your daily comfort.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your signature tactile combination pairs {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This pairing guarantees light movement while maintaining strict physical discipline. Seek out {texture_good_1} that springs back to a smooth state immediately after being gripped. Cool tones demand resilient surfaces that refuse to fatigue. Maintain a mixed finish across these layers to prevent visual flatness. Let your hands confirm what the eyes cannot see.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the precise tension between different tactile surfaces to build your daily uniform.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is entirely cool. Treat {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} as your foundation. Use {core_colour_3} as your stark light substitute. Reserve {core_colour_4} for dark utility elements. Rely on {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as deliberate focal points. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Completely reject Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green. Avoid the beige-out. This error happens when every garment shares the exact same pale value, leaving the look unfinished rather than minimal. Rescue it by introducing a heavy {core_colour_4} coat or a sharp {accent_colour_1} detail. Let a sudden shift in weave restore the missing depth. Securing balanced proportions and light movement relies on this strict discipline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your wardrobe around this precise range of tones to guarantee every item coordinates on sight.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Stark navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Icy grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
