    "coreFormula": "balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch",
    "closing": "Navigate every physical choice by trusting your hands to locate balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust your physical sense of equilibrium as your primary filter. Pick up a garment and test its ease in your hands. If it feels stiff, restrictive, or overly heavy, put it down. Your wardrobe relies on the exact intersection of balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch. Picture a softly structured overcoat sitting smoothly over fluid trousers, grounded by a sharp, polished loafer. The silhouette must breathe while retaining clear boundaries. You are looking for garments that respond to motion without losing their engineered shape.\n\nBuild your collection slowly. Allow garments to drift across different lanes as your daily requirements shift. Every new addition must pass the treaty test. Ask yourself if a jacket negotiates peacefully with your existing pieces, or if it dictates exactly what must accompany it. Reject the dictator. You need versatile elements that form easy alliances and lean into a cool temperature without clashing. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. If a piece requires constant adjustment to sit correctly, leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your foundational parameters before you acquire a single piece.",
