      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} immediately. It feels clammy on the collarbone and traps heat instead of remaining cool against the skin. Test the resilience of your garments. Gather a length of {texture_bad_2} in your fists and crush it. If it holds a dead wrinkle and refuses to spring back, drop it. Static fibres fight your shape. Step away from {texture_bad_3}. Notice how it snags on a rough cuticle and feels entirely lifeless in your grip. Materials like these drag your look down, guaranteeing you will never achieve one refined touch.",
