    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, let balanced proportions take the lead. Support this strict geometry with light movement. Pick up a worsted wool blazer and check the drape. Avoid stiff technical nylon that restricts your shoulders. A stark navy jacket requires a yielding knit underneath, like a fine ribbed merino polo. Leaving your icy grey cotton poplin shirts at the dry cleaner does not excuse a drop in discipline. You never get a pass to wear inferior garments just because your best pieces need pressing. Rely on the drape of the fabric rather than the reflection in the glass. Keep the temperature strictly cool. Introduce contrast through mixed metals, placing a polished silver watch beside a matt gold ring.",
