    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "You have complete freedom to mix {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} across your rings, buckles, and zips. Keep the baseline temperature strictly cool. Your wardrobe requires balanced proportions. Achieve this by ensuring no single piece of hardware overwhelms the garment. Test every item in your hands before wearing it. Gauge the mass directly. Pick up a chain or a watch case to confirm its heft. Avoid artificially aged pieces. Hammered copper and antiqued brass read as visual clutter next to clean worsted wool. Fix this by insisting on polished silver, white gold, and mirror chrome to support light movement. Reject any {excluded_finish} hardware completely.",
