    "coreFormula": "balanced proportions + sensory comfort + one refined touch",
    "closing": "Trust the weight in your hands to guide you back to balanced proportions + sensory comfort + one refined touch.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical instinct of immediate relief when trying on a garment. If the fabric restricts your movement or the cut requires constant adjustment, leave it on the rail. Your dressing logic relies on a strict equation of balanced proportions + sensory comfort + one refined touch. Picture a fluid, relaxed trouser paired with a breathable knit, anchored by a single structured belt. The silhouette sits evenly on the body. The fabrics yield. The finishing element provides sharp focus without overwhelming the senses. Ensure every piece carries a cool temperature to maintain absolute harmony across your collection.\n\nBuild your foundation slowly. Dress fast according to the demands of the day. An adaptable wardrobe allows you to shift your styling depending on your mood and environment without friction. Mix your finishes freely. Pair a matt surface against a polished trim to keep the overall effect grounded rather than rigid. Before purchasing any garment, apply the flight test. If you cannot imagine sitting in a long-haul airline seat wearing the item without desperately wanting to change, put it back. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Constriction does not.",
