      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1} entirely. Pick it up and crush the material in your fist. If it resists your grip and refuses to drape, drop it. Rigid backing destroys any chance of fluid movement. Reject {texture_bad_2}. Press your palm against the weave. If it feels clammy and traps heat rather than keeping your temperature cool, it fails your core requirements. If the yarn scratches your neck after five minutes, it does not belong on your body. Trust your hands. Bad materials distract you and ruin your base. You need absolute ease to serve as a blank canvas for one refined touch. Leave {texture_bad_3} alone if it snags on your fingernails.",
