    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Low-light rooms and close quarters strip away visual noise. In these intimate settings, sensory comfort leads. An evening spent reading by the fire demands the exact same yielding standard as a late supper. Anchor the outfit in stark navy. Pull on fine ribbed merino. Let the knit sit directly against the skin. Pair it with worsted wool trousers that drape cleanly without restricting movement to maintain balanced proportions. Keep the tones strictly cool. Icy grey layers recede well in dim spaces. Leave the crisp cotton poplin collar open. Mix your finishes and metals freely. A brushed steel watch casing provides one refined touch alongside a matt silver ring. You are dressing for proximity. Select materials that yield immediately to a blind touch. Trust your skin to verify the weave.",
