    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In intimate settings, sensory comfort takes the absolute lead. Low lighting flattens visual depth. To compensate, build your base from heavy silk crepe or cloud-soft lambswool. The lack of illumination makes texture your primary tool. Rely on cool tones like deep teal and dove grey to absorb shadows. Keep your silhouette exact. A quiet evening reading at home demands the identical precise drape as a formal dinner. Anchor the look with brushed silver or white gold hardware. Choose a matt finish over high polish. You want the metal to glimmer faintly under dim bulbs rather than flash. Test the garments by feel alone. Run your fingers over the hem with your eyes closed. If the weave feels stiff in the dark, discard it. Trust your tactile instincts completely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical realities of dim lighting and close quarters.",
      "tests": [
