      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A quick walk to the local post office deserves the exact same precise cut as a formal event. Do not suspend your standards just because you are out of the public eye. Demand balanced proportions + sensory comfort + one refined touch across every hour of the week. Pull on a cool dove grey jumper crafted from plush lambswool. Check how the sleeves fall against your wrist. Run your thumb over the cuff. If the yarn feels scratchy against your skin, take it off immediately. Look for a muted silver watch or a crisp seam that structures an otherwise simple outfit. Trust your skin when it signals that a garment sits correctly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your most mundane errands as a rigorous test of your clothing's actual structural integrity.",
      "tests": [
