      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Your hardware strategy relies on cool tones to maintain balanced proportions across your wardrobe. Build your foundation around {metal_1} and {metal_2}, reserving {metal_3} for subtle accents. To guarantee sensory comfort, evaluate how the metal feels in your palm. Lift every buckle, zip, and chain. Density reveals the true grade of the material. Avoid the common trap of highly polished hardware. A reflective, gleaming finish pulls focus and actively clashes with your softer fabrics like boiled wool. Instead, demand brushed, matt textures and reject any {excluded_finish} entirely. A solid, muted piece of metal anchors {core_colour_1} securely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your wardrobe with hardware that feels as substantial as it looks.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
