          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Choose stones that absorb light rather than refract it. Look for the dense, cloudy depth of {stone_1} or the cool opacity of {stone_2}. Avoid highly faceted gems. High-shine metal looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted fabrics. Demand brushed or flat matt textures to keep the look cohesive and establish balanced proportions between your jewellery and your garments. Pick the piece up in your bare hand. The unmistakable gravity of a genuine mineral guarantees the sensory comfort you require.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select stones and hardware to anchor your clothing, not to compete with it.",
      "tests": [
