    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Weigh the item in your closed fist. A camera lies, but true mass cannot be faked. If {metal_1} feels hollow or fragile, leave it on the table. You need substantial density to anchor your layers and secure sensory comfort. Pay close attention to the surface treatment. A highly polished mirror finish creates a sharp glare that distracts from your muted palette. Choose a brushed or matt {metal_1} instead. This subdued finish blends smoothly with cool tones, keeping your entire look cohesive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test the integrity of your hardware with your own hands before you wear it.",
      "tests": [
