    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "After securing sensory comfort and locking in balanced proportions, your hardware delivers that final one refined touch. Restrict your finishings to one or two strong pieces per look. Start this process with handbags. Seek out full-grain leather structures anchored by brushed matt hardware. Pick up the bag and run your thumb across the clasp. The cool metal must absorb light rather than reflect it. Strip away the excess. If a thick chain fights your collar, leave the chain in the drawer. One deliberate piece is enough to anchor the silhouette.",
