      "text": "Source your scarves in fine wool or washed silk. Trust your hands to evaluate the yarn. If the textile feels rigid, discard it. Drape the fabric around your collar to confirm true sensory comfort. Demand a strictly matt texture in cool tones like dove grey or deep teal. Fold the material to verify it creates balanced proportions. Enforce a strict edit before you step outside. Put on the scarf and check the glass. If the fabric battles your earrings, take the jewellery off. A single strong focal point suffices.",
