      "text": "Draw the pattern for your tailored coats directly from the structural weave. Let your fluid garments pull their motifs from subtle tonal threads. Enforce a low-contrast, tonal rule across every piece. Keep the overall temperature cool and the finish muted. Seek out {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2}. To evaluate a print, step back and soften your focus. The design must blur into texture. If the shape remains sharp, leave it on the rack. Maintain balanced proportions by rejecting visual disruptions. Demand sensory comfort from the physical cloth itself. Let the raw drape of the fabric guide your final decision. Pass over stark, high-contrast graphics. Skip {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely.",
