    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Pick it up and run your fingers across the grain. If the surface snags on dry skin, it will disrupt your sharp edges. Leave it on the hanger. Reject {texture_bad_2} entirely. Trap the fabric against your palm. If it feels like a sealed synthetic barrier, the piece will retain body temperature and suffocate you. A cool, muted aesthetic requires fluid drape. Skip {texture_bad_3} when it feels rigid in your grip. A stiff weave will never fold correctly to catch one pearl of light. Rely on your bare hands to locate structural flaws before you even approach a fitting room.",
