    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat a Tuesday morning milk run with the exact same material rigour as a scheduled appointment. Dashing to the high street chemist does not require surrendering your dove grey cashmere. Avoid reaching for thick cotton or stiff fabrics when rushing out the door. Require the strict combination of weightless layers + mobile layers + one pearl of light regardless of the destination. Build everyday outfits from fluid inky navy silk worn under a matt, brushed wool coat. Add cool white gold to illuminate the face. Never compromise on movement. If a piece pulls or feels heavy, leave it in the wardrobe.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply your material standards to every mundane task.",
