      "text": "Select your minerals to anchor your mobile layers. Lift the piece from the counter before you commit to it. The raw density of a real {stone_1} or {stone_2} provides a necessary grounding point against your weightless layers. Avoid glossy chrome or highly reflective stone cuts. A glassy, mirror-like polish distracts from your soft, muted colours. Anchor your cool metals with a matt or brushed surface to maintain absolute cohesion. Keep the finish muted and let the sheer mass of the stone do the work.",
