    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold every piece of {metal_1} or {stone_1} against your skin before wearing it. Rely on temperature as your primary guide. Real stone and dense metal will feel noticeably cold to the touch. A high-gloss, reflective polish creates a harsh glare against soft, cool fabrics. Counteract this by selecting a heavily oxidised or matt finish. A quiet texture anchors weightless layers without catching distracting reflections or interrupting the drape of the garment.",
