      "text": "Treat scarves as tools to add weightless layers around the collar. Source fine wool and pure silk. The surface must remain strictly matt. Avoid any fabric that catches the light. Subject each piece to the knot test. Tie the fabric loosely around your neck. If the material feels bulky or chokes the collarbone, put it back. You require a textile that collapses effortlessly. Anchor these garments in cool tones like inky navy or dense charcoal. Drape them to generate mobile layers across your shoulders.",
