      "text": "When adding structure to weightless layers, secure the waist with a medium full-grain leather belt featuring a matt buckle. Restrict your jewellery to cool metals. Pick up aged silver and oxidised pieces to ensure the finish remains muted. These dense accents ground the fluid movement of mobile layers. Apply the acoustic test before you leave the house. Drop the ring or pendant onto a wooden dresser and listen to the impact. If the metal clinks thinly or sounds hollow, take it off immediately. Solid material strikes the surface with a heavy thud, providing an undeniable anchor.",
