    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your fabrics must insulate without suffocating. Build your foundation on weightless layers that breathe with you. Apply the breath test before you buy. Hold the fabric to your mouth and exhale sharply. If the air bounces back into your face, leave the garment on the rack. Seek out {texture_good_1} for knitwear that compresses under a cool coat and bounces back. Choose {texture_good_3} for your tailored outerwear to ensure it holds a clean shape. Look for {texture_good_4} in your linings and blouses to provide softness and fluid movement against the skin. Anchor these pliable pieces with {texture_good_2} for your bags and belts. These accessories must mould to your grip and develop a muted, matt patina. Rely on the immediate tactile response of the hide to guide your choice.",
