    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Test {texture_bad_1} against your cheek and exhale. If warm air traps instantly against your skin, drop the item. Synthetic fibres suffocate. Run your thumb over {texture_bad_2}. If it produces a high squeak or feels slick with an artificial coating, leave it on the rail. Scrutinise {texture_bad_3} for unwanted shine. You only permit one pearl of light near your face. Anything else that glints, reflects, or seals off your body heat violates your self-contained boundaries. You require cool, matt materials that regulate your temperature naturally.",
