    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build your base with {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Rely on {core_colour_4} as your strict white substitute. Keep the temperature strictly cool. Inject {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as your sole deliberate accent. Reserve the relief tone as a rare, solitary note to break visual tension. Demand softness in the drape of every piece. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon. Watch out for the dense earth trap. Stacking flat brown and murky green in thick, matt weaves will drag you under. Break that density immediately. Place a sliver of {core_colour_4} at the collar, introduce the polished edge of glazed calfskin, or deploy the relief tone near your face to restore clarity.",
