    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Squeeze the sleeve tightly. If it springs back with a dry, synthetic crunch, leave it on the rail. True quality succumbs to pressure, while cheap fibres hold a stiff, hollow shape. Reject {texture_bad_2} the moment it feels slick or traps heat against your skin. You require open room to breathe. A surface that flashes with a hard, aggressive shine will drown out your delicate accents. Run your thumb across the weave. If the cloth scratches the skin or feels like cool plastic, drop it immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "Eliminate any material that pushes back against your skin or disrupts the eye.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Find your sweet spot exactly between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Let a length of {texture_good_1} fall into your hand to check its behaviour. The cloth must collapse instantly into a cool, fluid pool. If it holds a rigid shape or stands away from your skin, put it back. You need weaves that bow entirely to movement. This lack of stiffness builds your athletic space. Combine these pliable materials to construct weightless layers. The finish must remain completely matt and silent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every fabric to find the exact point where rigid structure dissolves into fluid movement.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is strictly cool. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_3} as base anchors, and rely on {core_colour_2} for structural depth. Let {core_colour_4} serve as your strict bright substitute. Pass over hard black, harsh neon, and heavy earth brown. Relying on an unbroken column of dark dye serves as a quick exit strategy, but it communicates defeat. Break a monolithic silhouette by interrupting the line with a {core_colour_1} strap or a {accent_colour_1} collar. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent within your structured volumes. Drop in the relief tone sparingly to grant a soft visual rest. Stack these shades through weightless layers, and let a lone cool metal detail act as one pearl of light against the matt cloth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your palette by defining every shade by its functional role.",
      "rankedItems": [
