          "failure": "the all-earth sink: brown on olive on bark, all matt and all heavy, can swallow you whole",
          "fix": "lift it: an oatmeal cream layer at the collar, one piece of polished leather, or the washed blue relief"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "For business, let blurred edges dictate your direction. The harsh lines of standard corporate uniforms serve no purpose here. Use fine silk and brushed wool to soften your outline. Supporting this lead, deploy weightless layers to build visual depth. A fine cashmere knit worn with a deep teal suit provides insulation without stiff bulk. Complete the approach with one pearl of light. A small, matt silver pendant offers a single cool focal point. Reviewing a quarterly budget does not require compressing your frame into a rigid box. Reject any item that traps your body. Assess the drape by moving your arms. If a sleeve restricts your reach, walk away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Corporate environments demand discipline, but they do not require you to surrender your physical ease.",
      "tests": [
        "paying a utility bill does not require collapsing your silhouette (Blaze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In intimate, low-light settings, let one pearl of light dictate your approach. Keep your foundation anchored in matt fabrics like inky navy brushed wool or deep teal cashmere. Introduce a solitary point of illumination. Pick up a cool silver pendant or a small diamond ring to draw the eye. Test your evening garments for basic function. Settling a restaurant tab does not mean forfeiting your shape. If a silk blouse restricts your chest when you reach for a menu, discard it entirely. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Drape a dove grey shawl over your shoulders and confirm it yields completely to your motion.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the close quarters of evening settings by letting your materials dictate the terms.",
      "tests": [
        "paying a utility bill does not require collapsing your silhouette (Blaze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat collecting a prescription at the local chemist exactly as you treat a scheduled meeting. Paying the council tax does not mean you must abandon your standard or collapse your silhouette into careless shapes. Your discipline remains absolute. Execute weightless layers + blurred edges + one pearl of light on a simple Tuesday morning. Build the outfit from deep teal brushed wool and dove grey silk. Anchor the look with a matt silver chain. Evaluate garments by how they fall over your frame. Let the cloth settle naturally. Refuse rigid cottons. Reserve harsh lines for other people. Dress for the reality of your day using pure materials in strictly cool tones.",
      "sectionIntro": "Demand the same aesthetic precision from your morning errands as you do from major events.",
      "tests": [
        "paying a utility bill does not require collapsing your silhouette (Blaze)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Anchor your hardware in cool dominance. Select {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} to support your muted palette. Choose an item and test its heft in your palm. A heavy buckle or solid chain confirms quality. Keep all surfaces matt. Highly polished finishes create a sharp glare that shatters the calm of your styling. Counter this distraction by seeking out oxidised, tumbled, or satin textures to keep the composition cohesive. Soften your visual impact by maintaining blurred edges around your neckline and wrists. Avoid {excluded_finish} options entirely. They disrupt your quiet focus.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your hardware choices to support your aesthetic without overpowering it.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
