    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Choose {stone_1} and {stone_2} for their quiet depth. Lift the ring or pendant to gauge its value. Heaviness confirms the truth of a cuff or chain. A stark, highly reflective setting cuts harshly against subdued tones. Seek out matt, frosted, or oxidised edges to keep the visual field continuous. You need minerals that glow internally rather than glittering outwardly. A single cabochon of {stone_3} serves perfectly as your one pearl of light. This physical gravity anchors the airy drape of your attire.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select every piece of hardware for its density and its strict refusal to sparkle.",
      "tests": [
