    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold the piece to gauge its density. A flimsy {metal_1} cuff feels hollow and betrays poor construction. Close your fingers over the object to assess the weight. Substantial items drape securely. Steer clear of high-shine surfaces. Brilliant metal looks sharp and distracting next to muted colours. Stick to sandblasted textures to keep the look cohesive. Build the ensemble around these understated choices. Add an opaque {stone_1} to finish the silhouette. This singular detail illuminates the cool palette without generating a harsh glare.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate the mass and texture of your hardware before you put it on.",
      "tests": [
