    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You have constructed your foundation of weightless layers and blurred edges. Now position one pearl of light. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Apply the solitary-star test. When your garments sit as a sweep of cool twilight, the accessory acts as the single beacon drawing the eye. Begin this process with handbags. Demand full-grain leather constructions finished exclusively with brushed matt hardware. Grasp the closures and evaluate their surfaces. The metal must yield a muted sheen rather than a highly reflective glare.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select and place your accessories as deliberate tools rather than scattered afterthoughts.",
