    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Assess your scarves by gripping the textile and stepping out of direct illumination. Pick up pure silk or fine wool and examine the finish. It must pass the solitary-star test. Look for a strictly matt surface in deep teal or dove grey. The colour should emerge from within like a solitary beacon. This singular visual depth functions as the one pearl of light against your cool garments. If the cloth reflects a broad sheen or catches the overhead shop lamps, leave it behind. The material must absorb the ambient room to anchor your neck properly.",
