    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your waist with medium full-grain leather belts. Secure the strap and ensure the buckle is strictly matt. Discard high-shine hardware. For your keepsake jewellery, select cool, aged silver. Inspect the metal closely for an oxidised finish. These darkened recesses ground the pieces without disturbing your deep teal or dove grey garments. Before stepping out, apply the single glint test. Strip away the excess. Remove rings and chains until only a solitary piece of aged silver remains against the fabric. That isolated piece acts as your one pearl of light.",
      "sectionIntro": "Hardware requires strict curation to maintain the quiet balance of your wardrobe.",
