    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Your tailored garments must draw their structure from {recommended_pattern_1}. Your fluid pieces require {recommended_pattern_2} to maintain their drape. Enforce a strict low-contrast rule for every print. Choose muted, tonal shifts over sharp geometry to keep the contrast low. Pursue blurred edges where the dye meets the cloth. Pass over harsh lines, stark graphics, and stiff borders entirely. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} on the rack. Apply the twilight test to any prospective acquisition. Bring the garment near a low bulb. The cool tones must deepen and settle in the dim lamplight. If the pattern flattens out, drop it. Continue building weightless layers with only the prints that pass this standard.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your eye to read pattern as another form of texture.",
