    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Carry the garment to a corner lit only by a solitary lamp. Under this dim bulb, evaluate your {recommended_pattern_1}. The print must deepen into the shadows and take on a gentle depth without losing its cool foundation. If the tones turn muddy against the faint glow, abandon the piece. Examine the motif for blurred edges. The design must dissolve into the surrounding silk or brushed wool. Step back three paces. A harsh graphic shape will look rigid when the light fades. Your chosen print must soften and recede as the room darkens, keeping its quiet legibility intact.",
