  "venus_pisces__moon_pisces__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "weightless layers + blurred edges + one pearl of light",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on weightless layers + blurred edges + one pearl of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Let the absence of friction guide your hand. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. If a fabric drags against your collarbone or catches on your wrist, leave it. Build slowly. Wait months for the flawless cut rather than accepting a temporary compromise. Apply the host test to every new acquisition. When you slip into a garment, ask if it leaves you feeling entirely self-sufficient, like the person who owns the house and needs nothing from the guests. If the clothes make you feel like a visitor hoping to impress, take them off immediately.\n\nYour aesthetic architecture rests entirely on weightless layers + blurred edges + one pearl of light. Picture a fluid silk shell resting beneath a fine-gauge, matt wrap. The transitions between garments should be impossible to define, melting together without sharp lines. Keep the overall temperature inherently cool. Finish this soft column with a single luminous focal point near the face, perhaps a solitary pale stone or a sliver of cool metal catching the light. If an outfit introduces harsh geometry or heavy, structured volume, you have lost the thread. Return to the silence of the materials.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this framework before you acquire a single new garment.",
      "tests": [
        "the host test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Run every new garment through the candlelight test. Hold the fabric near a dim bulb. If it bounces a hard glare, leave it. You want materials that absorb illumination into a cool glow. Rely on the drape over your arm to judge quality. Choose {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns completely matt. Build weightless layers using {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without mass. Seek out {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Top it all with {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. These blurred edges create a quiet canvas for your one pearl of light. Anchor your wardrobe in the specific materials below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise fabrics that drape and float over the body.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Washed silk",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cloud-soft lambswool",
