  "venus_pisces__moon_virgo__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "weightless layers + honest fabric + one pearl of light",
    "closing": "Let tactile instinct dictate the physical boundary between you and the room, assembling every self-contained silhouette from weightless layers + honest fabric + one pearl of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in how a garment moves against your skin. You are building an inventory of shifting components anchored in a strictly cool temperature. Acquire pieces slowly, but deploy them fluidly according to the morning's exact requirement. When considering a new acquisition, apply the flight test. Lift the garment from the hanger and ask if you could sleep through a long-haul flight in it without adjusting a single seam. If the cut restricts your shoulders or the cloth drags heavily across your collarbone, put it back. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.\n\nYour aesthetic operates on a precise equation. Memorise it as weightless layers + honest fabric + one pearl of light. Picture a fine gauge merino crewneck worn over a fluid silk camisole, paired with raw denim jeans and a single reflective pendant resting against the collar. The wool and silk provide breathable insulation. The denim offers structural integrity without stiffening your stride. The pendant adds a sharp disruption to the matt surfaces. Dress exclusively for your own internal state. If an outfit requires constant adjustment, discard the combination.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is the foundational logic of your wardrobe, the strict physical criteria that dictate what you carry and what you leave behind.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation entirely on honest fabric. Toss a piece of {texture_good_1} upward and watch how it falls. If it plummets rigidly to the table, leave it. Gravity reveals the truth about construction. Keep {texture_good_2} close to the body as a base layer for sharp lines. Rely on {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a cool day. Seal the system with {texture_good_4} as mobile outerwear to block the wind. These materials stack perfectly into weightless layers. Fasten the final layer with one pearl of light in mixed metal.",
      "sectionIntro": "Examine every material with your hands to ensure it serves your physical autonomy.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Worsted wool",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day"
        },
        {
          "name": "Technical nylon",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little"
        },
        {
          "name": "Lightweight gabardine",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "transitional jackets with rigid structure and no heavy drag"
        },
        {
          "name": "Matt silk",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "a frictionless fluid layer added without bulk"
        },
        {
          "name": "Crisp linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "breathable separation over fluid drapes in warmer weather"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Crush the cloth in your fist. If it squeaks or resists your grip, drop it. Assess {texture_bad_2} by letting it slide off your palm. If it hits the floor stiffly, abandon it immediately. You require weightless layers. Dense materials destroy that structure. Steer clear of {texture_bad_3}. Run your hand across the surface. If it traps heat instead of remaining perfectly cool against the skin, leave it on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the materials that actively sabotage your system.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your signature texture pairing sits exactly between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Drape the item over a chair. Watch how the cloth settles. If it catches the air and drifts down softly, it works. If it collapses in rigid folds, leave it on the rack. Rely on tactile feedback to feel the difference. Combine {texture_good_1} with a cool, matt finish. Anchor your choices in honest fabric. You need materials that move with your own rhythm. This self-contained approach guarantees your clothes serve your needs.",
      "sectionIntro": "Locate the exact point where your materials start working for you.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette temperature runs strictly cool. Construct the foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Substitute standard white with {core_colour_3}. Save {core_colour_4} for heavy structural outerwear. Inject {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent. Keep a soft note used sparingly for visual relief. Reject Mustard, Rust, and Warm olive green on sight. Beware the hard shell trap. When your schedule accelerates, you may reflexively grab stiff performance coats or rigid tactical gear to feel protected. Drop them. Exchange that rigid carapace for a brushed cotton overshirt. It offers the same rapid utility but actively grounds you. Render these combinations in honest fabric and stack them as weightless layers. Complete the system with one pearl of light.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your palette as a strict operating system.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Stark navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Icy grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Optical white",
          "role": "white_substitute"
        },
        {
