    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Run your bare fingers over the surface. If the cloth feels stiff or traps heat, discard it immediately. Reject {texture_bad_2}. Squeeze the material in your fist. If it crunches rigidly rather than draping cool and fluid, it fails. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. Evaluate the sheen of every potential purchase under soft shadows. You require fabrics that maintain one pearl of light without glaring. If a piece sits entirely dead, swallowing every trace of radiance to the point of dullness, put it back.",
