    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is strictly cool. Build your foundation from {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Treat {core_colour_4} as your alternative to a stark plain shirt. Reserve {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as deliberate focal points. Introduce the relief tone exclusively as a soft note used sparingly when an outfit feels too severe. Hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon are entirely off-limits. Ensure your colour choices align with the textile's physical drape. Beware the default uniform of solid black. Relying on unbroken black signals a lack of intent. Break the severity with a {core_colour_2} pullover, an {accent_colour_1} scarf, or a {core_colour_3} belt to ensure visual depth while maintaining true sensory comfort.",
