    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the desk, pure sensory comfort must dictate your choices. Gauge your immediate physical response to a collar or cuff. Glass reflections lie, but the actual drape of brushed wool tells the truth. Assess the cloth's density before getting dressed. Build your working foundation entirely on how the fibre rests against your body, allowing weightless layers of inky navy cashmere and dove grey silk to support your focus. Anchor this muted, cool base with one pearl of light via a matt metal pin or watch. Avoid any extra adornment that disrupts your self-contained framework. Apply this strict standard rigorously. A solitary afternoon coffee requires the exact same structural precision as a client pitch. If a waistband needs adjusting when you sit, take the trousers off.",
