      "text": "Ground your accessories in a strictly cool palette. Build your foundation with {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Treat these elements as structural tools rather than loud decorations. Steer clear of brilliant mirror polishes. A highly reflective gloss creates a jarring, sharp interruption against your muted textiles. Eliminate {excluded_finish} surfaces from your wardrobe entirely. Instead, demand a matt or brushed finish to keep the overall appearance unified. Before purchasing any belt buckle or chain, weigh the piece in your palm. Mass indicates quality. The metal must feel heavy and dense in your grasp. Keep the execution self-contained. Apply hardware sparingly, using a solitary brushed clasp or ring as one pearl of light at the wrist or collar.",
