      "text": "Test the physical heft of every setting. Rely on your grip to assess the true density of a pendant or ring. Seek out the solid opacity of {stone_1} or the clouded clarity of {stone_2} to absorb rather than bounce ambient room illumination. Keep your metal pairings firmly in the cool spectrum. High-shine silver pulls focus and shatters the cohesion of your muted garments. Ground your choices by demanding brushed or matt settings instead. Treat these substantial stones as a precise anchor for your weightless layers, functioning as your one pearl of light without generating sharp, distracting flashes.",
