      "text": "Hold every piece of {metal_1} or {stone_1} before making a purchase. A photograph cannot convey structural integrity. If an item feels flimsy or hollow in your palm, reject it immediately. You require deep sensory comfort from your hardware, which demands substantial, solid construction. Next, inspect the outer coating. Glossy, polished metals act like cheap mirrors, generating harsh glares that clash violently with a cool, muted wardrobe. Always insist on a matt or brushed exterior. A frosted face absorbs the room's glow rather than reflecting it, keeping the overall effect strictly self-contained.",
