    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Hold any potential purchase up to a window. If the textile bleeds into a fuzzy border rather than a clean cut, drop it. This proves the weave will betray your sharp edges. Run your palm down {texture_bad_1}. If it feels limp and collapses under its own weight, it lacks the tension you need. Grip {texture_bad_2} tightly in your fist. If the surface crushes into a permanent wrinkle, discard it. Rely on your fingertips when they hit a dry, draggy nap. You require tension and polish. If a thread swallows the light and leaves a dead, matt surface, leave it on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject fabrics that dilute your structure before you even put them on.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Lock down {sweet_spot_keyword_1} alongside {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to establish your structural baseline. Pick up {texture_good_1} and assess its rigid drape. You require sharp edges to maintain a warm, polished form. To prove a cloth works, observe its geometry in motion. If the crisp hem collapses into limp folds as you stride, put it back. The perimeter must remain absolute. Trust your hands over the sales tag. Unyielding weight tells the truth. Grab the fabric and crush it hard. If it refuses to bounce back instantly, walk away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master this specific pairing and the rest of your decisions become obvious.",
      "tests": [
        "the shadow test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your baseline temperature is strictly warm. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} for deep anchoring blocks. Opt for {core_colour_3} instead of stark white. Deploy {core_colour_4} to bridge disparate elements. Inject {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as deliberate focal points. When you require a subtle visual break, use your relief tone as a soft note applied sparingly. Bypass Muddy pastel, Icy grey, and Dusty sage entirely. Piling a heavy lip, bright brass hardware, and studded patent leather onto one body shifts high drama into stage costume. Secure your sharp edges. Anchor the silhouette with a single gleaming strike, then drop every remaining piece into matt black.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorize your exact tones to ensure every piece you select performs on command.",
