    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your formula relies on polished, warm surfaces to project expansive colour. Construct your base with {texture_good_1} for shirting that holds a crisp crease. Add hidden depth through structural {texture_good_2} in your tailoring, securing a knife-edge shape that never begs for a steamer. This provides the architecture for your one theatrical finish. Execute that final strike with {texture_good_3} on statement footwear to reflect maximum light, or {texture_good_4} as a lining that gleams under low light. Always apply the friction test in the shop. Sweep your fingers down the sleeve. Seek an absolute, unbroken slip. If the material catches or creates drag, abandon the garment. Hunt for these specific fibres.",
