    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Lead with depth at your desk. Let heavy silk satin or sharp wool twill form the foundation of your working garments. Build upon this heavy base with expansive warm tones, using golden camel and deep bronze to flood the silhouette. Support the entire shape with a theatrical finish, perhaps a substantial mixed-metal cuff or polished patent leather boots. Walking out for a midday coffee demands the exact same rigour as a formal board presentation. Never compromise your garments for a quick exit. Assess the physical heft in your grip. Mirrors distort reality, but woven fabric confirms it. If the pieces feel flimsy or like a concession for a minor task, abandon them immediately.",
