    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light, hidden depth takes the lead. Do not downgrade your garments just because the audience shrinks. Pouring a glass of wine at home requires the same rigorous measure as a public event. Let a heavy silk satin shirt in golden camel catch the dimmest amber bulb. Ground the ensemble with sharp wool twill trousers. Mix your metals without hesitation. Stack a warm brass cuff over a silver watch. Introduce deep bronze earrings to catch the candlelight. Dim environments require high reflectivity. Choose patent leather boots to bounce the shadows. You know the strict construction required for a crowded gallery. Hold your solitary evenings to that exact standard.",
