  "venus_sagittarius__moon_capricorn__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "expansive colour + softness + one theatrical finish",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on expansive colour + softness + one theatrical finish.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe with deliberate patience. Acquire pieces slowly as you find the exact drape you need. Deploy them instantly. Trust your hands as your sensory compass. Run your fingers across every hem and collar before you look in the mirror. Looks lie. Weight does not. Your core formula is expansive colour + softness + one theatrical finish. Picture a heavy brushed knit in a blended dye falling cleanly over a fluid slip, anchored by a single oversized, sculptural cuff. The foundation is simple. The execution relies entirely on how the fibre behaves when you move.\n\nGround every choice in a warm palette. If the fabric feels sterile or flat against your skin, leave it on the rack. Apply the shelter test to everything you consider. Put the garment on and close your eyes. Notice your breathing and your posture. A successful piece acts as a physical refuge. If the cut leaves you feeling exposed, rigid, or dependent on tension to hold its shape, take it off. If it drops over your frame with a protective, enveloping gravity, keep it. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this physical baseline before you evaluate another garment.",
      "tests": [
        "the shelter test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe relies on expansive colour and profound softness. Build this foundation by letting your hands filter your garments before your eyes do. Apply the wrist test to every new piece. Press the material against the sensitive skin of your inner wrist. If it scratches or catches, leave it on the rail. Rely on your tactile response to guide your purchases. Seek out {texture_good_1} for knitwear that compresses and recovers its shape. Rely on {texture_good_2} for bags and belts that patinate and mould to your routine. Anchor your warm palette with {texture_good_3} for coats that hold a clean shoulder. Finish these layers with {texture_good_4} for blouses that add fluid movement. Start your search with these four core materials.",
      "sectionIntro": "Let your hands filter your wardrobe before your eyes do.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Suede",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "shoes and accessories with quiet matt texture"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine merino",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers soft against the skin and resilient through washes"
        },
        {
