      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Train your hands to spot a hollow weave. Pick up {texture_bad_1} and crush the material. If it springs back with a synthetic crunch, drop it. You need a warm, matt baseline to support one theatrical finish. Brittle fibres ruin the effect. Press the woven surface directly to the thin skin where your pulse sits. If it bites or drags, the piece is worthless. Rigid threads trap heat and create awkward, bulky shapes. A weak {texture_bad_2} often gleams like cheap plastic under overhead lighting. Leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject any material that lies to the skin.",
