        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your signature pairing merges {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. You require expansive colour, absolute softness, and one theatrical finish to construct a complete outfit. Drag every piece of {texture_good_1} directly across your inner arm before purchasing. If the yarn feels rough, reject the garment immediately. The density of the textile reveals its true value. Combine a matt weave with subtle, warm variations in thread. Keep the combinations balanced.",
      "sectionIntro": "Find the precise intersection of weight and weave.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in a definitively warm temperature. Build your foundation exclusively with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Use {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} to bridge these base shades and construct depth. Reserve {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} for your single deliberate accent. Treat your relief tone purely as a quiet note, deploying it sparingly to calm a busy silhouette. Leave icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels on the rack. These shades drain you. Watch out for the trap of sinking into an unstructured, entirely black uniform. Sunder that dark mass immediately. Pierce the monochrome with a flash of warmth, reaching for a heavy hammered gold wristband or a mottled tortoiseshell clip. Ground your strategy in softness. Ignore the label and squeeze the fabric. Let the sheer mass of the garment dictate your decision.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your palette requires discipline and a strict adherence to your core neutrals.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
