    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Demand density from your accents. Rest the object in your palm and evaluate the drag against your skin. Optics deceive. Mass delivers the facts. Choose heavy minerals like {stone_1} and {stone_2} to project a warm temperature. A single dense gem provides one theatrical finish. Avoid oxidised metals entirely. Beaten copper and blackened brass read as messy historical debris against a contemporary wardrobe. Restrict your foundations to highly reflective platinum, bright silver, polished white gold, and mirror chrome. These pristine finishes keep your hardware adaptable.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware through physical weight and high-shine finishes to ground your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
