    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Test the drop of every necklace before you wear it. Hold the {metal_1} in your open hand and judge how it falls. A heavy plunge proves the piece has the substance required to balance your outfits. When combining metals, reject any tarnished materials. Hammered copper and dull brass register as pure clutter. They disrupt the sharp focus required to support your expansive colour. Keep to pristine, highly polished surfaces instead. Gleaming platinum, mirror chrome, and bright warm gold interact seamlessly when the finish remains entirely uniform. Rely strictly on the solid drop of a piece in your palm to decide if it earns a place in your collection.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every piece of jewellery to this physical evaluation before you buy it.",
      "tests": [
