    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, expansive colour leads your garment selection. Build the foundation by choosing a crisp cotton poplin shirt in golden camel. A busy morning inspecting heavy deep bronze shipments does not mean dropping strict proportion for shapeless fleece. Keep the silhouette intact. Support this lead element with physical room and one theatrical finish. Layer sharp wool twill trousers that allow your body to operate, then secure the waist with a thick patent leather belt bearing a warm brass and silver buckle. Rely on kinetic testing to verify the fit. Lift your arms and twist your torso. If the poplin restricts your shoulders, reject the piece. Restriction always signals a faulty cut. Maintain a polished surface to ground the garments.",
      "sectionIntro": "Here is how to enforce your aesthetic constants in a working environment.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low-light gatherings, push the contrast further. Anchor your evening with heavy silk satin in deep bronze. Let the material catch the warm ambient lighting. Sharing a table with your community does not mean abandoning bold proportion. Keep the cut exact. Select crisp cotton poplin or sharp wool twill that maintains its architecture when you sit. Mix your metals freely here. Stack silver rings alongside a heavy gold cuff to reflect maximum light up close. Frame the silhouette with golden camel pieces to lock in the aesthetic.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is how you calibrate your wardrobe for close quarters and low light.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Build your morning around movement and neighbours. Buying milk at the corner shop never justifies surrendering your scale. Maintain your baseline. Rely entirely on expansive colour + athletic space + one theatrical finish. Let heavy silk satin trousers drape generously around your stride. Pair a golden camel sweatshirt with gleaming patent leather trainers. Mix bright gold hoops with a chunky silver watch. Keep the surfaces highly polished and the overall temperature strictly warm. Rely on the heavy drag of deep bronze fabric across your shoulders to confirm the fit. Mirrors deceive you. The tension in the seam tells the absolute truth. Do not blur your silhouette with understated basics. Demand structure from every piece you touch.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat the Tuesday morning coffee run as a strict design exercise.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "You have absolute freedom to stack {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. Treat this warm mixture as your permanent baseline. Apply a strict weight check to every buckle and clasp before you buy. Flimsy fixtures break the structural integrity of your silhouette. Demand extreme gloss across all your hardware. A weathered, {excluded_finish} surface dulls the garment and lacks sharp intent. Require intensely mirrored warm metals that flash from half a block away. A massive, gleaming {metal_1} zip easily serves as your one theatrical finish.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your metal strategy and demand heavy, highly reflective hardware.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Evaluate jewellery by its heft. Reject any aged, battered, or blackened hardware. These weathered treatments appear exhausted and lose all sharpness. Restrict yourself to highly reflective warm metal that beams from the opposite pavement. Mix your components freely, provided every element maintains an unbroken, mirror-like gloss. This pristine gleam provides a dramatic stage for your larger silhouettes. Select dense, light-catching minerals like {stone_1} and {stone_2}. You need substantial, heavy stones to anchor your boldest outfits.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select gems and hardware that anchor your look with heavy, gleaming certainty.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold the chain or cuff loosely in your hand. Physical gravity provides an immediate answer about manufacturing quality. If the item feels hollow, put it back. Antiqued, oxidised, or hammered finishes look tired and lack crispness. You require intense reflection instead. Stick strictly to polished warm {metal_1} that catches the light from across the street. This unbroken gleam acts as a sharp anchor for expansive colour and clarifies the entire silhouette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every piece of hardware by its physical heft and surface reflection.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "oxidised, hammered, or antiqued finishes look tired and lack crispness",
          "fix": "stay strictly in polished warm metal that catches the light from across the street"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Build your base with expansive colour, secure movement through athletic space, and deploy exactly one theatrical finish. Enforce the principle of one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with statement eyewear. Pick up oversized acetate frames and verify they carry a glossy warm tone. Run the spotlight test. Place the frames under a direct beam. If the surface fails to bounce a brilliant reflection across a crowded table, drop them. True polish requires absolute visibility.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select accessories to punctuate your outfit with deliberate weight and absolute intent.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Statement eyewear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "oversized acetate, glossy warm tone"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the spotlight test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Anchor your layers with a substantial belt. Look for wide leather straps equipped with massive polished brass buckles. When you wear expansive colour across your garments, a heavy brass closure gives the eye a solid place to rest. Mix your metals freely here. Place warm gold tones right next to bright silver hardware. Check the reflection on every buckle before you buy it. If a bright beam hits your waist, the metal must flash back with a hard glare rather than a dull matt surface. A highly polished finish acts as a beacon, catching the light and giving the crowd a clear focal point.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your silhouette with hardware that catches the light and demands attention.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Substantial belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "wide leather, massive polished brass buckle"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the spotlight test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your stance with a high-shine calfskin platform. This slick surface provides a rigid, polished foundation under a warm deep bronze trouser. Pick the shoe up and feel the solid block of the sole. The heavy base builds athletic space into the bottom of your silhouette. Before stepping out, audit your accents. Stand in front of your mirror and isolate the single piece pulling the focal point. If a shoe or jewel competes with your expansive colour rather than supporting the total shape, take the lesser accessory off. Maintain exactly one theatrical finish.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your foundation and run a final diagnostic on the complete silhouette.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "high-shine calfskin platform, high shine"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the spotlight test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor tailored garments with structured geometries like {recommended_pattern_1} or {recommended_pattern_2}. Let fluid pieces take their visual weight from {recommended_pattern_3}. Bold expression demands high-contrast graphic impact. Pass over anything small or hesitant like {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}. Apply the distance test. Step back across the shop floor and check the mirror. The print must remain crisp, loud, and legible from afar. If the motif blurs into an indistinct wash of warm tones, leave the garment on the hanger. Demand expansive colour in every print to maintain absolute clarity and scale.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select prints that demand attention and project scale.",
      "tests": [
        "the ten foot rule (stay crisp, loud, and legible from across the room)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Move away from the mirror and squint at the weave. Look for absolute legibility. If {recommended_pattern_1} dissolves into a muddy smudge from across the room, leave the garment on the rack. Proximity softens flaws, but distance exposes them. A print must remain fiercely distinct. Frame this impact with clear athletic space, giving the motif room to breathe. Always anchor the entire scale in expansive colour, letting heavy warm dyes project outward without blurring at the seams.",
      "sectionIntro": "Execute the ten-foot clarity check before committing to any print.",
      "tests": [
