  "venus_sagittarius__moon_libra__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "expansive colour + cool composure + one theatrical finish",
    "closing": "Trust the raw gravity of your garments to navigate your physical instincts toward expansive colour + cool composure + one theatrical finish.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the shift in your posture when a garment lets you breathe and move with the group. Build your wardrobe to drift by mood. Let the environment dictate your starting point. Keep your foundation warm. Pick up a piece and test its weight in your hands. If it feels too rigid, leave it on the rack. Your ultimate compass is the half-mirror test. Catch your reflection in a passing window. If you notice the structure of the clothes before you see a person ready to engage with the room, strip off the heaviest layer. Looks lie. Your peripheral vision does not.\n\nMemorise your formula: expansive colour + cool composure + one theatrical finish. Picture this in action. A sweeping overcoat in a broad wash of pigment, layered above clean, sharply cut trousers, anchored by a single oversized collar. The coat sets the mood, the trousers hold the line, and the collar serves as the focal point. Rely on this combination when you need to recalibrate. Trust your hands when mixing matt and polished elements together. Let the finishes clash. Your clothes must work for you, not against the people you meet. Dress to integrate, but retain your own physical boundaries.",
      "sectionIntro": "Internalise this blueprint to strip away the noise and calibrate your physical instincts.",
      "tests": [
