      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation on {texture_good_1} for shirting that establishes clean boundaries and carries expansive colour. Add {texture_good_2} for base layers that deliver sharp lines and easy movement. Rely on {texture_good_3} for trousers that drop straight to the shoe and resist creasing through long hours. When assessing {texture_good_4} for outerwear, guarantee your cool composure by letting the fabric's recovery guide you. Snap the sleeve outward. The cloth must settle immediately and hold a warm weight against the wind. If the fabric flutters or catches the air, leave it on the rack. Form can deceive, but gravity remains reliable. Start with the materials below.",
      "sectionIntro": "These are the materials that construct the physical architecture of your style.",
