    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Learn to identify the fabrics that fail your frame. Drop {texture_bad_1} immediately. The tell is in the stiffness. Test the sleeve's tension. Pull the cuff sideways and release it. If it drops with a dull thud instead of snapping back to life, leave it on the hanger. It will ruin the warm flow you need. Avoid {texture_bad_2} for similar reasons. Grab a handful of the cloth and squeeze. If it feels sticky or rigid in your palm, it cannot serve as the base for one theatrical finish. Visuals deceive. Touch reveals the truth. Your instincts know when a fibre fights your movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to drop the wrong fabric the second it hits your hands.",
