        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is warm. Base your selections on expansive colour. Build your core with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Substitute {core_colour_3} wherever you expect a standard light neutral. Deploy {core_colour_4} to bridge competing pieces. Inject {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your deliberate accent. Add the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over icy pastel, neon brights, and cold blue-grey completely. Watch for the trap of unanchored prettiness. Wearing exclusively pale or entirely soft shades reads charming at breakfast but forgettable by lunch. Fix this drift immediately. Give the eye a firm anchor. Slip on a sharply tailored blazer in worsted wool, step into a structured flat, or layer a densely dark piece exactly where the gaze lands first.",
