      "text": "You have total freedom to stack {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. A warm temperature anchors this mix. Cradle the piece in your palm. A shiny coating hides cheap alloys, but mass confirms value. Let the sheer density of the hardware dictate your choice. Artificially aged pieces act as noise against your wardrobe. Skip hammered copper, tarnished brass, or faux patina entirely. Instead, insist on polished silver, pure white gold, solid platinum, or mirror chrome. These high-gleam choices secure your cool composure. Reject {excluded_finish}.",
