    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Test materials against your bare skin before putting them on. Run your fingers over {texture_bad_1}. If the fibres seem to dissolve into a slick, waxy film from your body heat, drop the piece immediately. This structural collapse betrays your quiet undercurrent. Press {texture_bad_2} to the inside of your wrist. It must never trap warm air. If it feels stifling or brittle, leave it on the rail. Assess {texture_bad_3} by gripping it tightly in your hand. If it springs back with a rigid, unnatural glare rather than a muted, matt drape, it will ruin your balanced silhouette. Your skin detects cheap blends instantly. Depend on that immediate sensory feedback to protect your wardrobe's integrity.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and reject the materials that actively sabotage your proportions.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Grasp a prospective garment and squeeze the hem. If it yields entirely to your fingers, keep it. If it remains stiff, drop it outright. Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build a warm foundation. This pairing provides a quiet undercurrent. Throw {texture_good_1} over the top to add heavy drape. Seek matt weaves that swallow the light. Let the layers merge into a muted whole. You need weight without rigid structure. Every thread must bend to your body instantly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your core texture combination to establish an exact, repeatable foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature requires a purely warm palette. Construct your base with {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, {core_colour_3}, and {core_colour_4}. Use {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} for your single deliberate accent. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. This systematic approach forms the quiet undercurrent of your wardrobe. Pass over stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. Avoid the comfort collapse. Soften every item without restraint, and you soon find yourself in sleepwear. Fix this error by reinstating a single architectural line. Select a defined lapel, a pressed trouser crease, or a rigid leather satchel to intercept the drape.",
      "sectionIntro": "Hold every item to your skin and watch the true reaction.",
