    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the desk, let a quiet undercurrent dictate your approach. Build a warm, muted base using boiled wool. Let a broad wash of dark mahogany and a single theatrical element support this foundation. Depend on the drape of washed silk to soften the lines. Keep your silhouette strictly balanced. A chaotic morning transit does not mean surrendering your shape. Add your final piece deliberately. Fasten a thick mixed-metal brooch to a lapel.",
      "sectionIntro": "Approach your working hours by letting your foundation dictate the terms.",
