    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Anchor your jewellery with {stone_1} and {stone_2}. Hold every piece in your bare hand before buying. A clever surface finish often masks poor quality construction. If the setting feels hollow, put it back. You require dense, warm opacity to match the visual weight of your wardrobe. Pay close attention to the metal setting. Avoid highly reflective, polished alloys. A sharp, high-shine silver pendant acts like a disruptive flare against muted textiles. Insist on matt or brushed hardware to keep the entire look cohesive. These heavy, grounded components provide essential stability when you wear a garment in an expansive colour.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your stones and metals by their physical gravity and surface restraint.",
