      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "a flat monochrome look that bores you by midday",
          "fix": "add a crisp white poplin collar, a silver architectural ring, or a bright geometric sneaker"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, rely on expansive colour + honest fabric + one theatrical finish. Build the base with warm taupe and camel worsted wool. Rely on pure textiles like crisp cotton poplin to provide structural ease, and add a singular theatrical detail to break the neckline. Pick up a heavy brass and sterling silver mixed collar to cut the soft wool. Treat the office as a canvas for comfort. Avoid stiff tailoring that pinches. Let the weight of fine ribbed merino fall without restriction. Mix your metals freely. Keep your surfaces shifting constantly between flat matt and high gloss.",
      "sectionIntro": "Dictate the terms of your workwear through strict comfort and uncompromising intent.",
      "tests": [
        "a rainy Sunday paper run deserves the same gentle standard (Ripple)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light, anchor your silhouette with expansive colour. Let a warm taupe or camel garment set the baseline. Demand an honest fabric like worsted wool or fine ribbed merino for comfort. Test the drape by folding your arms. The yielding standard you set for daily errands applies equally to a private dinner. Mix your jewellery freely to deliver one theatrical finish. Pair a silver chain with a brass ring. Combine a matt surface with a polished stone. Evaluate the physical heft before you dress. Close proximity calls for materials that respond instantly to movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Recalibrate your choices for low light and close proximity.",
      "tests": [
        "a rainy Sunday paper run deserves the same gentle standard (Ripple)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat a basic morning commute as a precise calibration exercise. Even a quick dash in the rain deserves rigorous attention. Build these everyday layers using warm taupe worsted wool or a camel technical nylon shell. Weigh the cloth in your palms before putting it on. Anchor the look with mixed metals in matt or polished surfaces. Your foundation remains constant across all contexts. Apply your core formula of expansive colour + honest fabric + one theatrical finish whether you are boarding a train or standing at the checkout counter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your simplest daily routines as the primary proving ground for your style.",
      "tests": [
        "a rainy Sunday paper run deserves the same gentle standard (Ripple)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Because your palette runs warm, you have the absolute freedom to blend {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} across your buckles and rings. A base of expansive colour demands precise metallic details. Reject {excluded_finish} outright. Artificially weathered alloys and beaten bronze generate visual noise next to sharp garments. Restrict your selections strictly to highly polished silver, solid platinum, bright white gold, and reflective chrome. Lift every chain and clasp before buying. Surface reflections trick the eye, but pure gravitational pull reveals actual density.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your hardware acts as the precise structural skeleton, grounding your garments with deliberate weight.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Anchor your expansive colour with dense, light-capturing gems like {stone_1} and {stone_2}. Evaluate every ring or pendant purely by touch before buying. A stone must feel unexpectedly heavy in your palm to qualify. Faux patinas and tarnished brass read as visual debris against clean lines. Discard that clutter entirely. Instead, freely combine polished metals and brilliant facets to bring a pristine, reflective edge to your warm palette. Mount {stone_3} in these highly reflective settings to create one theatrical finish that catches the light.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select dense gems and brilliant metals that bring sharp light and physical gravity to your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Evaluate every buckle, zip, and link. Assess the sheer weight of the object. Heavy hardware validates the garment. Pre-distressed finishes create visual clutter against an honest fabric. Keep your details in the present tense. Rely on mirror-polished platinum, clean chrome, or gleaming {metal_1} to ground your look. This discipline keeps your warm selections precise. Drop {stone_1} into your palm to confirm its dense reality before you put it on.",
      "sectionIntro": "Weigh your hardware to measure its true worth.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Ground your foundation in expansive colour paired with an honest fabric. Once that base is secure, apply one theatrical finish to complete the silhouette. Limit yourself to a single strong focal point per look. Start this process with silk scarves. Seek out a crepe de chine square with a matt surface to sit against a warm taupe or camel knit. Apply the rotation test to every addition. Inspect the item from all angles. If the piece looks flat or loses its structural presence from the side, put it down. You require details that maintain their physical depth in three dimensions.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the final layer of your silhouette by selecting structural additions that demand physical space.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Silk scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "crepe de chine square, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the rotation test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Fine jewellery demands physical scrutiny. Select thin gold and silver chains to wear together. Combine a polished silver ring with a brushed gold band. These mixed metals introduce subtle friction when paired with expansive colour. Always conduct a movement check on every piece. Spin the ring around your finger. Turn the bracelet on your wrist. If a setting snags the cuff of your worsted wool jacket, leave it on the counter. If an edge digs into your knuckle during a full revolution, walk away. You need elements that move seamlessly with your anatomy. Keep your palette warm and your finishes varied.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess the structural mechanics of your fine jewellery.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Fine jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "thin mixed gold and silver, mixed polished and brushed"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the rotation test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Select a small structured bag in kid suede or smooth leather. A top-handle shape forces discipline on what you carry. Demand fine mixed hardware on the closures. Combining warm brass clasps with brushed steel rivets gives you absolute freedom with your rings and watches. Conclude your dressing sequence with a full silhouette check. Turn slowly in front of a floor-length glass. If the bag interrupts the drape of your honest fabric or fights the expansive colour across your frame, leave it behind. The piece must act as your one theatrical finish, never an overpowering distraction.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your daily carry and test the final balance of your silhouette.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Small structured bag",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "kid suede or smooth leather top-handle, fine mixed hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the rotation test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your tailored pieces with structured motifs like {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2}. Let your fluid garments carry {recommended_pattern_3}. Because your style is versatile, scale your contrast to the garment. Rely on high-contrast graphics for heavy coats, then drop to low-contrast tonal prints for soft blouses. Base these choices on expansive colour from a warm palette. Subject every print to the squint test. Stand ten feet back and narrow your eyes. If the motif turns into a muddy blur in that first split second, put it back on the rail. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as a structural tool rather than mere decoration.",
      "tests": [
        "the blink test (not muddy or confusing in the first split second from ten feet)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Assess every print using the flash test. Drape the {recommended_pattern_1} over a chair and step back. Shut your eyes tightly, flash them open for a single heartbeat, and snap them shut. If the design dissolves into a confusing blur in that instant, reject the garment. You require immediate recognition. Build your outfits around an honest fabric to ensure the pattern remains structurally sound. Providing a warm background allows the motif to stand out sharply instead of retreating into noise. If the shapes bleed together from across the room, the piece fails.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every pattern for immediate visual clarity before it enters your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the blink test (not muddy or confusing in the first split second from ten feet)"
