  "venus_scorpio__moon_aries__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "close drape + sharp edges + one warm point of light",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on close drape + sharp edges + one warm point of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical weight of the garment in your hands as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. Pick up a coat or a knit and feel how it drops. If it feels flimsy or hollow, put it back. Your core formula is close drape + sharp edges + one warm point of light. Anchor this with a heavy worsted overcoat cut with strict shoulders. Layer it over a fine-gauge knit that sits directly against the skin. Finish the look with a single reflective pin. Every piece must pull its own structural weight. Build the silhouette from the inside out, ensuring the matt finish of the cloth creates a warm, dense barrier.\n\nConstruct your wardrobe with slow, methodical precision, allowing you to deploy the pieces fast. Curate garments that construct an immediate boundary between you and the surrounding noise. Run the shelter test before you purchase anything. Put the item on and ask if it builds a protective, structural wall around your personal space. If the garment feels exposed, fragile, or requires constant adjustment to maintain its shape, reject it. You are buying architecture for the body. Trust this physical instinct to guide you toward pieces that stand firm and keep your daily movement entirely self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this foundational logic to bypass visual noise and anchor your physical instincts.",
      "tests": [
        "the shelter test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe on materials that master a close drape. Run your fingers over {texture_good_1} to find slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. This muted surface creates the foundation for your one warm point of light. Pick up {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without bulk. Look for {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Rely on {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. Always apply the breath test to verify the quality. Hold the fabric to your mouth and exhale. If the air passes through smoothly, the fibre will protect your contained warmth. If the air hits a wall and bounces back damp, drop the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the fibres that build your foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Washed silk",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cloud-soft lambswool",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Heavy silk crepe",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth"
        },
        {
          "name": "Boiled wool",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed alpaca",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "enveloping winter coats and oversized cardigans"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fluid modal jersey",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers that follow the body without ever gripping it"
        },
        {
