    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Treat {texture_bad_1} with total suspicion. Press the cloth to your mouth and exhale directly into the fibres. If your breath hits a solid wall and bounces back wet against your lips, leave the garment on the rail. This synthetic suffocation completely ruins a close drape. Your geometry relies on sharp edges, and {texture_bad_2} will betray you by collapsing into formless wrinkles the moment you sit down. Crush the fabric tightly in your fist. If the material stays crumpled like discarded paper when you open your hand, it fails. Ignore the shop mirror. If a fabric fights your own body heat or refuses to hold a pristine line, it has no place on your skin.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject fabrics that fight your geometry and stifle your skin.",
      "tests": [
