      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build your system entirely in a warm temperature. Lay the foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} for boiled wool coats, and let {core_colour_4} serve as a secondary base. Deploy your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Leave stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel on the rack. Reserve {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} for single, deliberate items like a heavy silk crepe scarf or a structured leather bag. Beware the trap of sinking into an unshaped, totally dark silhouette. Correct this error by anchoring the outfit with an amber ring or a heavy brass pendant. Maintain sharp edges in your lapels and collars to keep the matt finish entirely disciplined.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat this palette as a strict physical boundary for your wardrobe.",
