    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe requires a close drape. Avoid {texture_bad_1}. It stands away from the body in stiff, unyielding peaks. Pinch {texture_bad_2} and notice how the synthetic fibres squeak under your thumb. Subject suspicious materials to an exhalation trial. Hold the cloth to your lips and blow outward. If your warm breath traps and bounces directly back to your face, drop the item immediately. Stay clear of {texture_bad_3}. Notice how it reflects a harsh glare instead of holding a muted surface. You require materials that move as you move. Reject anything that builds a rigid, suffocating wall over your skin.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands and skin to immediately reject substandard materials.",
