  "venus_scorpio__moon_capricorn__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "close drape + softness + one warm point of light",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on close drape + softness + one warm point of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Treat your wardrobe as a closed ecosystem. Build slowly and evaluate every piece in isolation. Before you bring a new garment into this space, apply the melt test. Close your eyes and crush the fabric of the collar and cuffs in your fist. The material must surrender entirely to your grip and feel inherently warm to the skin. If the weave holds stiff memory or resists your hand, leave the item on the hanger. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Touch does not.\n\nConstruct every outfit around your core formula of close drape + softness + one warm point of light. Picture a fine-gauge knit sitting perfectly flush against the ribs. Layer an unlined jacket over it, ensuring the shoulder seam drops gently without rigid scaffolding. Finish the combination with a single pendant resting at the collarbone. The entire silhouette stays muted and contained. It anchors your physical presence without broadcasting to the street.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this framework to anchor your decisions and shut out external noise.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation from materials that yield to your hands. Rely on {texture_good_1} for knitwear that compresses under an outer coat and bounces back with essential softness. Ground these layers with {texture_good_2} across your shoes and bags to build a matt finish that moulds to your physical routines. Depend on {texture_good_3} for tailored jackets that hold their clean lines across years of wear. Introduce {texture_good_4} to your linings and blouses to guarantee a close drape that moves freely. Always apply the breath test before purchasing. Press the fabric against your mouth and exhale. If the material chokes the hot air back into your throat, drop the garment immediately. Combine these approved pieces to build a self-contained uniform of close drape + softness + one warm point of light. Target these primary materials first.",
      "sectionIntro": "Source these reliable fibres as the physical foundation of your wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Suede",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "shoes and accessories with quiet matt texture"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine merino",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers soft against the skin and resilient through washes"
        },
        {
          "name": "Linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "warmer-weather pieces whose natural wrinkle reads as authentic"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Watch for the trap. When evaluating {texture_bad_1}, gauge the resistance. If the material holds rigid over your shoulder instead of settling into a close drape, discard it. Perform a breath check on {texture_bad_2}. An impenetrable warp that traps hot air against your mouth will suffocate you. {texture_bad_3} requires a friction test. Drag the pad of your thumb down the sleeve. A squeaking or catching surface destroys the muted, self-contained environment your foundation demands. Let your skin decide between yielding fibres and stiff, synthetic cages.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn the precise sensory cues that tell you to leave an item on the rail.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Pair {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to anchor your wardrobe. Let {texture_good_1} construct the exact shape you require. Put the item on and inhale a full lungful of air. If the seam fights your expanding ribs, leave it on the rail. You demand strict softness to hold a structured silhouette without rigid armour. Seek a warm, matt surface that absorbs room glare. Rely on physical density to reveal the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Combine your key elements to build a wardrobe that respects your anatomy.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your entire wardrobe relies on a strictly warm undertone. Build your base using {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, {core_colour_3}, and {core_colour_4} as heavy anchoring blocks. Select {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} strictly for a solitary, intentional hit of intensity. Deploy your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to break a solid block of colour. Pass over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels. Inspect the depth of the dye. Shallow pigments wash out, but dense colour grounds the garment. Monitor the balance of your silhouette. When every item yields completely, the look dissolves into sleepwear. Reclaim your self-contained structure by adding a heavy matt brass buckle or a stitched lapel edge. You must demand close drape to prevent formless volume.",
      "sectionIntro": "Curate your palette as a strict system of deliberate tones.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Rich toffee",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Taupe",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
