    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Test the surface tension of every weave. If the yardage fights your grip, drop the garment immediately. {texture_bad_1} often fails this test. It creates a rigid, hollow shell rather than a close drape. {texture_bad_2} carries a similar trap. It builds thick bulk that obscures your frame and denies any fluid connection to your skin. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. It reflects a harsh glare instead of absorbing light into a warm, matt surface. Your fingers will always detect a cheap, stiff weave long before your eyes register the flaw.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise and reject fibres that will fight against your frame.",
