    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your optimal pairing grounds {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This combination anchors the light movement your silhouette demands. Give every piece the blindfold test before trying it on. Squeeze the hem in your fist. You want a substantial droop. A stiff ledge means the material will stand away from your body. Tactile sensation must guide you. If a material feels artificially treated against your palm, leave it behind. Heavy cloth falls correctly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Let your hands filter your options before your eyes even register the silhouette.",
