    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "You operate on a warm temperature scale. Anchor your foundation in {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Bridge these bases with {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} to build depth. When you require a deliberate focal shift, deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Treat your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly for visual breathing space. Reject icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels completely. Beware the deep soil trap. Stacking murky earthen shades from collar to hem will consume your frame. Correct this collapse by placing a lighter cream layer near your face. You can also interrupt the block with one piece of polished hide or your relief tone. Ensure the garments maintain close drape to keep the silhouette defined.",
