    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Test scarves by gathering the textile in your fist. You are looking for light movement when the silk or fine wool slips free. A stiff weave resists shaping. Drop it immediately. Demand a completely matt surface to absorb light rather than reflect it. Assess the depth of every scarf you consider. Ask yourself if the warm dye glows like a single, quiet coal in a hearth. If the fabric catches sharp reflections or shines like plastic, put it back. The silk must hold heat in its weave without flashing outward. Fold the wool to secure close drape against your collar and confirm the pile remains flat.",
