        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the one-ember test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Run your hands over medium full-grain leather belts, choosing a flat matt buckle that absorbs rather than reflects. Fasten it firmly to preserve close drape, leaving enough slack for light movement in the fabric above. Pick up your keepsake jewellery and inspect the finish. Rely on aged silver and oxidised metals to keep the surface strictly muted. Strip away every competing piece of hardware until only a single, warm point of light remains alive against your heavy fibres.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finish your look by selecting the final grounding hardware and testing the overall balance.",
