      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_scorpio__moon_pisces__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "close drape + blurred edges + one warm point of light",
    "closing": "Rely entirely on touch to evaluate your garments until your instincts naturally construct close drape + blurred edges + one warm point of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe with deliberate slowness. Curate piece by piece and rely on physical weight to make your decisions. Pick up a garment and test its density in your hands. Quiet luxury demands substantial fabrics that fall smoothly against the body. If the cloth feels flimsy or hollow, drop it. Your instincts are anchored in touch and temperature. Run your fingers over the surface to check for a warm, matt finish. If the textile catches the glare too sharply, leave it on the hanger. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.\n\nRun the melt test on every combination before you step outside. Put the garments on and study the boundaries between them. The fabrics must visually dissolve into one another without stark stops or rigid breaks. Your core style formula is close drape + blurred edges + one warm point of light. Picture a dense cashmere rollneck sitting softly against the skin, tucked into heavy wool trousers, and finished with a single matt gold ring. The fabric hugs the body. The hems fall softly without sharp creases. The metal provides the solitary gleam. Avoid stiff collars.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this blueprint before you evaluate another piece of clothing.",
      "tests": [
