    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your materials dictate how a garment behaves. Crush the fabric in your fist. It should yield immediately and warm to your skin, never fighting back. This physical reaction guarantees a close drape. Build your foundation with {texture_good_1} for winter knits that compress and bounce back. Seek out {texture_good_2} for shoes and belts that mould to your shape and patinate gracefully. Rely on {texture_good_3} for tailored coats that hold clean lines for years. Contrast these heavier weights with {texture_good_4} for blouses and linings that add fluid movement. These fibres allow you to create blurred edges through a matt texture alone, leaving room for one warm point of light in your styling. Prioritise the materials listed below.",
