    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject materials that stand away from your body. Pick up a piece of {texture_bad_1} and hold it tightly in your fist. Notice how it resists your body heat and remains completely stiff. You require a close drape to maintain your self-contained silhouette. Drop it. Now touch {texture_bad_2}. Feel how it sits on the surface like a rigid shell instead of yielding to your warm skin. Test every item by squeezing the textile to see if the material dissolves and melts into a soft puddle. If it springs back with a synthetic snap, leave it on the rack. Let the tactile resistance dictate your boundaries.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the materials that will fight your silhouette by testing them directly in your hands.",
