    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "In professional spaces, close drape leads. Let rich toffee silk and brushed wool sit near the skin. Support this structure with soft hems and a muted, warm gold ring. Keep your garments strictly private. Leaving the office for a quick meeting does not require stripping away your chosen atmosphere. Leave the camel cashmere layer on. Reject the urge to project outward. Build an enclosed system that serves you first. Notice how the fabric folds in motion. Evaluate each garment by how it shields you from the room.",
