    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low-light settings, blurred edges lead. Rely on fibres that soften a room. Slide a camel brushed wool wrap over a silk slip. The contrast between a matt surface and a subtle sheen does the work. Assess a rich toffee cashmere sleeve by gathering it in your palm. If it feels stiff, leave it. Trust this physical reaction. Anchor your wrist with a heavy yellow gold cuff. Intimate hours extend to early mornings. Moving to the kitchen or greeting a guest is no reason to shed your muted shell. Keep the close drape constant. Let one warm smoky quartz ring catch the eye.",
