    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Establish the core of your outfit with a strict close drape and clean, fast movement. Finish the construction by adding exactly one warm point of light. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with handbags. Seek out full-grain leather or thick suede finished with matt, brushed hardware. Run the pressure test before purchasing. Push your thumb firmly into the hide. If the surface puckers loosely or folds over itself like empty packaging, drop it. True density pushes back. Rely on your fingertips to read the material. A photograph can fake luxury, but structural integrity confirms it.",
