    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your foundation in {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. These form your baseline. Soften the transition with {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Keep every hue fundamentally warm. Apply your relief tone sparingly as a soft note to break up solid blocks of colour. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} strictly as your single deliberate accent. Pass right over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels. Watch out for the sofa drift. If you soften every piece far enough, one day you are simply dressed in loungewear. Fix this by restoring exactly one line. Incorporate a rolled but real lapel, a trouser with a soft crease, or a firm leather bag against all that give. Ensure your garments rely on a close drape to trace your frame.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your palette by assigning strict roles to your shades and maintaining consistent warmth across your garments.",
