    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, sensory comfort must lead. Do not compromise for rigid suiting. Trust your hands. If the tweed feels harsh, leave it on the hanger. Build your tailored garments from brushed wool and heavy silk. The close drape follows, keeping the silhouette neat and self-contained to frame your focus. Add a warm glint of matt gold near the collar. Apply the same rigour to your off-duty hours. Walking the hound at dawn requires the exact same standard of dress as a board meeting. Throwing on a camel overcoat for a brief errand must demand the same deliberate choice as putting on bespoke trousers. Pick up every garment and gauge its heft before you buy.",
