    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light, close drape takes the lead. Forget high-contrast shapes. Choose a rich toffee silk blouse or a camel cashmere sweater. Let the fabric sit near the body. Maintain strict consistency in your private hours. A heavy brushed wool coat worn for a quiet evening drink serves perfectly for the morning frost. Rely on warm metals in matt finishes to catch dim illumination. Pick up a solid gold pendant. Feel its dense heft in your palm. Evaluate the weave through direct touch when selecting these layers. If the material feels cold or rigid, leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the environments where the lighting drops and proximity increases.",
