    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pick up a piece of {texture_bad_1} and rub it between your thumb and forefinger. When the cloth pushes back against your hand or yields a synthetic squeak, drop it. It lacks the density needed to maintain sharp edges. Test {texture_bad_2} against your bare neck. If it scratches or bites, it fails. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. A high-shine finish reflects far too much light, betraying your preference for matt, warm, self-contained subtlety. Trust your hands over a mirror. Cheap fibres look convincing from a distance but surrender under tension. Visual inspection fails against physical reality. Mass never deceives.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the fabrics that fail your standards before they ever touch your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your signature tension relies on pairing {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Build your foundation using {texture_good_1} to deliver structure. Introduce sharp edges through the precise cut of a collar rather than rigid cloth. Test every item by gripping the fabric firmly in your hands. If the surface resists your hold or produces a high friction noise under pressure, drop it immediately. A warm wardrobe demands cloth that yields cleanly to your grasp while remaining completely matt. Rely on your fingertips to guide you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact textural tension that makes your style function.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your overall palette is decidedly warm. Anchor your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Bridge these heavy neutrals using {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} exclusively as a single deliberate accent, reserving the relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels entirely. Watch for the trap of dissolution. Layering pale, sheer garments atop bare skin erases your outline completely. Fix this immediately by restoring one definitive line. Slip a fitted base layer underneath to reclaim your sharp edges. Trust your own physical reaction when combining these elements to ensure the weight holds.",
