    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Sharp edges lead your working hours. Support them with matt fabrics in warm tones. When selecting garments for the office, seek out crisp lapels and clean cuffs in rich toffee wool. Avoid anything that drapes loosely over your frame. Drafting a Tuesday afternoon email does not excuse surrendering your silhouette to slouchy garments. A camel cashmere jacket maintains your perimeter just as easily as an oversized knit. Keep your layers self-contained and securely anchored. Pair a crisp collar with brushed wool to bring in quiet depth. Test the shoulders of a coat by pressing the seam. It must hold a rigid line. Trust the cloth to work for you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Frame your working hours around precise boundaries.",
      "tests": [
