      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low lighting, let your sharp edges lead. Select warm camel cashmere cut with strict precision rather than draped loosely. Reach for a rich toffee silk shell layered under a stiff brushed wool blazer. Answering a late-night phone call does not mean you must collapse into limp loungewear. Keep the shoulders defined. Look for lapels that press flat and cuffs that finish squarely. A matt gold watch or brushed platinum chain will catch the dim light gently. Avoid heavily beaded pieces. Grasp the garment and trust the firmness of its seams.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master intimate spaces and dim lighting by keeping your lines strictly defined.",
