    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You have established structure. You have defined the sharp edges. Accessories must now deliver a touch of quiet depth. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Handbags provide the ideal starting point. Seek out warm full-grain leather or thick suede finished with matt, brushed hardware. Put every potential purchase through the drop test. Drop the empty bag onto a wooden bench. If it seems to hover lightly or feels hollow upon impact, leave it on the shelf. The right item lands with a heavy, dead thud. Rely entirely on the sheer density of the object. Real quality sinks.",
