    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Put every new piece through a shadow check. Hold the material near a warm flame. If it throws back a harsh, blinding glare rather than sinking into a rich, matt shadow, drop the item immediately. {texture_bad_1} often fails here, revealing a cheap, brittle sheen. Run your bare palm over {texture_bad_2}. If the fibres catch your cuticles or feel entirely lifeless, leave it on the hanger. True textiles pull light inward, granting your silhouette a touch of quiet depth. Search for materials that offer genuine ease. When a cloth refuses to yield or feels artificially stiff, it shatters your self-contained aesthetic. Trust your fingers to detect the unyielding weaves that ruin precise tailoring.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn the precise tactile failures that betray your wardrobe.",
