      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is distinctly warm. Construct your foundation from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} as your bridge neutrals. Drop icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels entirely. Leave them on the rack. Introduce {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} to provide a touch of quiet depth. Trust your eye when a combination feels too dense. Avoid the trap of piling heavy woodland shades on top of each other. A solid block of completely matt earth tones will drag your outfit into the mud. Break this sinking effect with a fine knit collar, a sliver of brushed hardware, or a soft note used sparingly.",
