    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Structure leads your work wardrobe. Anchor your outfits in heavy brushed wool tailoring and firm, warm camel overcoats. Softness supports from the inside out. Rely on fine cashmere knits and heavy silk shirts worn close to the skin to temper rigid outlines. Introduce a touch of quiet depth through matt full-grain leather briefcases in rich toffee. Never partition your garments into professional and casual tiers. A Sunday trip to the hardware shop demands the exact same precise cut as a Monday morning strategy session. Let your fingers evaluate the drape. Cloth behaviour reveals the truth, while hanger appeal deceives. If the lapel collapses under your grip, leave the item on the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your professional uniform strictly through cut and cloth.",
      "tests": [
