          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "shirts and loungewear that feel like a remembered embrace"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the candlelight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Subject every new fabric to a shadow check. Take the item into an unlit corner of the shop. If it dies into a flat void instead of holding a warm blur, leave it behind. Pick up {texture_bad_1} and crush it in your fist. If it crinkles aggressively and refuses to bounce back, it lacks the cool composure you require. Avoid {texture_bad_2} entirely. Run your thumb across the surface. If it catches on the slightest dry skin or feels distinctly synthetic, it fails. A harsh thread never softens against your collarbone. Rely entirely on your tactile reactions to enforce these strict boundaries.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your hands will tell you exactly which materials to leave on the hanger.",
      "tests": [
        "the candlelight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Seek the exact intersection of {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Crush them together in your hands. The right combination always yields soft structure. Take {texture_good_1} into a darkened room and strike a match. The material must drink the warm illumination. It must sink into deep shadow rather than flashing back. If the surface throws glare into your eyes, drop the piece. You want textiles that absorb low light and remain entirely matt. This is your baseline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your signature texture combinations by checking their reaction to a naked flame.",
      "tests": [
        "the candlelight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in a definitively warm palette. Rely on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} as your primary base neutrals. Ground your outfits using {core_colour_3} as a dark anchor, and bring in {core_colour_4} as an earthy green neutral. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent to channel cool composure. Treat your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Leave stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel on the rack. Wearing head-to-toe black reads like a default uniform chosen in defeat. Break that void immediately with a {core_colour_1} layer, a {accent_colour_1} scarf, or a {core_colour_2} belt.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your palette before it controls you.",
