    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Leave {texture_bad_1} on the rack. Lift the hanger and feel the rigid, unyielding drag against your palm. That stiffness kills any chance of fast movement. Avoid {texture_bad_2} for a different reason. Crush the fabric in your fist. The synthetic friction generates a stifling, artificial heat against your skin. Inspect the weave closely. Ask yourself if the cloth will ease into a warm, trusted shape over the years, or if it will simply shed plastic threads. Authentic fibres earn their character. Fake ones merely disintegrate. Evaluate the integrity of the yarn before you buy.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to instantly identify the materials that fight against your body.",
