      "text": "In dim lighting and close quarters, fast movement continues to dictate the silhouette. Drive this pace with heavy brushed wool trousers and a rich toffee silk shirt. Rely on matt bronze or brushed yellow gold. Avoid glaring finishes that reflect harsh light. Weigh the garment to confirm its substance. A heavy full-grain leather jacket provides a solid boundary in crowded rooms. Do not abandon your tailored camel cashmere just because the evening is casual. Stay strictly within a warm palette. Keep your fibres tactile.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical mechanics of dressing for low lighting and close proximity.",
