    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Anchor your silhouette with stones that possess genuine density. Seek out {stone_1} and {stone_2} in muted, warm tones. Hardware provides the final point of structure. Weigh the item in your bare hands to verify its mass. Discard lightweight imitations instantly. Faux patinas and distressed edges read as messy distractions against a sharp style. Stick to unblemished mirror finishes. Your dual register approach allows flexibility in placement, provided the materials themselves remain heavy and resolute.",
      "sectionIntro": "Choose hardware that anchors your garments through undeniable mass and density.",
