    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Grasp the item and judge its density. Visuals trick the eye, but gravity provides a definitive answer. If a piece feels hollow, drop it. Solid metal delivers the exact structure your fastenings require. Steer clear of hammered surfaces, false oxidation, and simulated wear. That visual noise disrupts a clean aesthetic. Keep to polished {metal_1} and simple, flat surfaces. A modern, straightforward finish will always complement a warm palette and respect your choice of honest fabric.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply this physical test to ensure your hardware carries genuine weight.",
      "tests": [
