    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments provide the structure and the honest fabric. Accessories introduce a touch of quiet depth. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Interrogate the utility of every item before you leave. Ask yourself if the piece actively secures the silhouette together or merely decorates it. If it performs no real physical job, leave it behind. Begin with silk scarves. Choose a crepe de chine square or a slim band. Feel the density in your hands. The silk must hold a firm knot and prove its utility. Keep the tones warm and demand an entirely matt surface. True utility always feels deliberate.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the art of selecting accessories that perform a tangible function and reinforce your core style formula.",
