    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Treat fine jewellery as a strictly functional detail. Choose a thin chain and small drops cast in brushed silver. The muted surface integrates smoothly with your warm clothing palette. Subject every piece to a strict mobility check. Ensure the metal rests flat without snagging on a worsted wool lapel or catching on a technical nylon collar. If it fails this practical requirement, return it to the box. Handle the silver directly. The item must possess enough internal integrity to hold its shape during use. Combine these subtle metals with honest fabric. Look for sturdy links and reliable clasps that perform their task silently.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select fine jewellery with strict attention to its physical performance.",
