    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Apply the desk test to every printed piece. View the garment from a distance of an arm length and a half. If the print fails to read as a clean texture and instead creates chaotic noise, reject it. Tailored shapes take their cues from architectural lines, making {recommended_pattern_1} highly effective. Fluid garments better absorb the softer transitions of {recommended_pattern_2}. Keep your contrast adaptive. You can dial the variations up for sharp focus or sink them tonally into a warm, muted {core_colour_1} base. Let honest fabric carry the visual weight. Demand crisp structure from your woven grids. Skip over {avoid_pattern_1}. Pass over any rail displaying {avoid_pattern_2}.",
      "sectionIntro": "Filter every pattern through a strict lens of scale and texture.",
      "tests": [
        "the desk test (read as clean texture at arm's length and a half)"
