    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Execute the distance check on {recommended_pattern_1}. Hang the garment over a chair, step back roughly five feet, and evaluate the surface. The motif must dissolve into a flat, warm tone. Up close, the weave provides clear visual structure. At this working distance, it must read simply as solid worsted wool or clean ribbed merino in a muted {core_colour_1}. If the lines or shapes remain sharply legible from across the room, the scale is too large. Demand motifs that recede entirely into the warp and weft, leaving only the impression of pure honest fabric. Trust this spatial instinct. Visuals deceive when viewed without proper space.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce a strict distance boundary to control how pattern operates.",
      "tests": [
