  "venus_virgo__moon_cancer__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "precise fit + hidden depth + one meticulous detail",
    "closing": "Listen exclusively to the structural tension beneath your fingers, selecting only those pieces that deliver precise fit + hidden depth + one meticulous detail.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Treat garment weight and absolute silence as your true north. Run your thumb over the inner seams and feel the tension of the thread. If a piece feels flimsy or demands outside attention, leave it on the rail. Your neutral wardrobe relies entirely on absolute structure and gravity. Your formula is precise fit + hidden depth + one meticulous detail. Picture a heavy structured coat tailored to exact shoulder measurements, cut with a dense interior lining known only to you, and finished with a single hand-stitched lapel hole. That is the standard.\n\nConstruct this wardrobe deliberately over months and years. Sourcing pieces with this level of internal architecture takes patience. Once the foundations are set, dress in seconds. You are dressing to remain entirely self-contained. Evaluate every new addition by its interior construction and its matt surface rather than its sheer hanger appeal. If a garment pulls your focus outward or asks you to perform, listen to the immediate tightening in your stomach. Trust that sudden physical rejection and walk out of the shop empty-handed. Construction and weight will never lie to you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this core logic to anchor your physical instincts before you purchase a single garment.",
      "tests": [
        "trust your gut and walk away"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "True quality reveals itself in the hand before it ever touches your skin. Demand a precise fit from fabrics that possess hidden depth. Reach for {texture_good_1} when you need knitwear that compresses under pressure and bounces back to its original shape. Rely on {texture_good_2} for your bags and belts, allowing the material to mould to your habits while developing a neutral, muted patina. Choose {texture_good_3} for your tailored pieces to guarantee clean lines that anchor your silhouette. Add {texture_good_4} as a lining or blouse for fluid movement against the body. Run every new garment through the collapse test. Drop the fabric onto a table. If it pools into a heavy, substantial shape, keep it. If it skitters away, leave it on the hanger. These four materials form your baseline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the fibres that will carry your wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
