    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} when it feels slick and hollow between your fingers. It will trap heat against your skin and refuse to hold its intended shape. Assess {texture_bad_2} by gripping it tightly in your fist. If the material crushes into a lifeless heap and fails to spring back, it lacks the internal tension your aesthetic requires. A weak fibre will never support one meticulous detail, such as an engineered cuff or a heavy zip. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. It catches the light with a cheap glare that ruins a muted, matt finish. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.",
