    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Handle scarves as structural additions. Choose generous silk or fine wool. The surface must be strictly matt. Search the weave for hidden depth, looking for subtle variations in an oatmeal thread. Tie it once and leave it alone. Then apply a ruthless reduction test. If the scarf competes with a silver watch or introduces clutter to your neutral palette, remove the scarf entirely. A self-contained wardrobe demands unyielding editing. Your garments already deliver a precise fit. Do not ruin that geometry with unnecessary accessories. Feel the textile drape. A heavy matt silk needs no accompanying decoration.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply strict parameters to your secondary pieces to ensure they anchor rather than distract.",
      "rankedItems": [
