    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Your neutral palette requires strict, low-contrast tonal variations. Tailored garments draw their pattern from structural weaves. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} in heavy jackets. Fluid pieces take soft, quiet repetitions. Choose {recommended_pattern_3} for lightweight shirting. Always verify the scale before buying. Evaluate the fabric from a distance to ensure the design reads as a continuous texture. If the motif separates into aggressive individual shapes, put the garment back. A precise fit demands fabrics that ground the silhouette. Pass over high-contrast graphics entirely. Avoid {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern strictly as a structural element rather than a surface decoration.",
