    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Step back from the mirror and soften your focus. A successful {recommended_pattern_1} must blur into pure hidden depth. If the motif remains sharp from three paces away, it breaks your perimeter. Look for geometry that registers as a solid block of neutral yarn until someone stands close enough to inspect the stitching. Your clothing relies on a precise fit to define its shape. The pattern must never fight that structure. Trust your physical reaction over the sales floor lighting. If staring at the weave forces your eye to track contrasting lines instead of resting on the drape, leave the piece on the hanger.",
