    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on precise fit + hidden depth + one meticulous detail.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust physical equilibrium as your ultimate compass. A garment must feel entirely self-contained the second it settles on your shoulders. If you have to adjust a collar or tug at a hem to make it sit right, leave it. Your operating logic relies on a strict equation. Build every look around precise fit + hidden depth + one meticulous detail. Picture a tailored wool jacket cut precisely to your ribs, lined in heavy silk, finished with a single horn button at the cuff. The exterior is neutral and matt. The internal geometry does the work.\n\nBuild your wardrobe systematically, then deploy fast. Buy slowly to ensure every component interacts flawlessly. Rely on the combination test to protect this system. Before acquiring any new garment, mentally force it into three distinct outfits using items you already own. It must anchor a layered winter coat, sit seamlessly under a structured jacket, and stand alone against bare skin. If it requires a specific supporting cast to function, it fails the combination test. You need garments that retain their structural integrity regardless of the context. True versatility demands ruthless editing.",
