          "role": "accent"
        },
        {
          "name": "Pale butter",
          "role": "relief"
        }
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "the hard shell: reaching for armour, technical jackets, and stiff utility layers when life speeds up",
          "fix": "swap the shell for a brushed cotton layer that moves just as fast and holds you besides"
        }
      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, precise fit takes the absolute lead. Build your garments around sharp tailoring and worsted wool that hold their shape. A neutral temperature supports this architecture, using soft stone or oatmeal to keep the visual noise low while the cut does the work. Avoid the trap of softening your edges for mundane tasks. Answering routine emails does not require collapsing your silhouette into a baggy cardigan. Maintain the physical tension. Ensure your foundation provides a quiet undercurrent. Let a matt silver watch case or a crisp cotton poplin collar act as your one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Let cut and strict proportions dictate the shape of your working hours.",
      "tests": [
        "paying a utility bill does not require collapsing your silhouette (Blaze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Evening alters the rules of visibility. In low lighting, colour recedes and a precise fit becomes your primary language. Let the sharp shoulder of a worsted wool blazer define your space. Shadows obscure subtle weaves. Depend on the cut. A soft stone ribbed merino knit worn close to the body reads clearly in candlelight, establishing a quiet undercurrent. Review your private hours. Drafting an evening correspondence does not mean retreating into an oversized hoodie. Hold your lines. Introduce cool metals like a brushed platinum watch or a matt silver cuff to serve as one meticulous detail. These subdued finishes catch dim light without flashing. Stay self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your evening choices for close proximity and low lighting.",
      "tests": [
        "paying a utility bill does not require collapsing your silhouette (Blaze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat your daily routine as a proving ground. Standing in the queue at the local chemist demands the exact discipline you apply to formal obligations. Settling a local council bill does not give you permission to abandon your shape to slumping fleece. Your standard demands constant application of precise fit + quiet undercurrent + one meticulous detail. Anchor yourself in sturdy trousers or a technical nylon shell. Keep your palette strictly neutral. Rely on soft stone or oatmeal cotton poplin. Finish the look using a matt steel zip or a brushed platinum watch clasp. Do not compromise.",
      "sectionIntro": "Maintain strict discipline in your ordinary hours.",
      "tests": [
        "paying a utility bill does not require collapsing your silhouette (Blaze)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Lock your hardware into a cool-dominant strategy. Build your foundation entirely on {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}, ensuring every zip and watch case shares the exact same tone. Maintain a strict neutral balance. Your finish lane demands entirely muted surfaces. Reject any highly reflective {excluded_finish}. Distressed copper, faux-vintage brass, and artificially oxidised alloys inject visual clutter when worn against worsted wool or technical nylon. Eliminate them. Rely instead on unblemished {metal_1}, platinum, or white gold, ensuring the metal remains strictly matt. Evaluate every piece before wearing it. Weigh the item in your cupped hand to gauge its density. Optics deceive. Solid mass tells the absolute truth. A heavy clasp acts as one meticulous detail needed to anchor a self-contained look, while the muted finish maintains your quiet undercurrent. Ensure a precise fit on any watch strap.",
      "sectionIntro": "Audit your hardware with the same rigid physical criteria you apply to your tailoring.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Ensure your choices establish the quiet undercurrent of your wardrobe through deliberate density and clarity. Seek {stone_1} that absorbs rather than shatters light, maintaining a strictly neutral palette. When evaluating {stone_2}, look for strict, contained geometry. Avoid ornate filigree and elaborate settings. These elements introduce visual clutter into a self-contained aesthetic. Mount your stones in clean white gold or solid platinum with a brushed, matt surface instead. Assess every mineral by holding it flat against your fingers. Photography misleads, but physical resistance provides facts. A genuine rock carries a grounding heft that synthetic alternatives cannot replicate. Let this density act as one meticulous detail to finish a garment boasting a precise fit.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your hardware selections in strict geometry and unyielding density.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Check the specific gravity of every component. Optical illusions abound in hardware, but mass remains objective. A precise fit requires pieces that sit with genuine substance against your body. Steer clear of pre-weathered coatings and artificially rusted links. They register as unnecessary visual clutter. Keep your metalwork confined to pristine {metal_1}. This clean surface establishes the quiet undercurrent your self-contained aesthetic demands. Test every clasp and hinge. If a {stone_1} setting or belt buckle feels suspiciously hollow, discard it immediately. The objects you retain must carry undeniable physical density to act as one meticulous detail against your neutral garments.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply this physical standard to immediately filter out substandard hardware.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Anchor your garments with a precise fit, then rely on fine tailoring to establish that quiet undercurrent. Accessories complete the equation. They deliver one meticulous detail. Always restrict yourself to a single strong piece per look. Begin with a watch. Run your thumb over the surface and check for a brushed steel case secured by a dark leather strap. Ensure the metal carries a matt finish to keep the temperature strictly neutral. Before purchasing, perform the removal check. If you anticipate a sudden urge to unbuckle the heavy strap halfway through a long afternoon, leave it on the counter. Rely on bodily comfort to guide you. Glossy finishes trick the eye, but enduring comfort provides certainty.",
      "sectionIntro": "This section dictates how you finish a look using your hands, testing mass and finish before you put anything on.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Watch",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "brushed steel case, leather or steel strap, matt brushed"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the take-off test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Belts serve as a structural anchor. Select a medium width in vegetable-tanned leather to keep the texture grounded and neutral, feeding into a quiet undercurrent. The hardware must remain cool and muted. Seek out a matt brushed steel buckle to serve as one meticulous detail. Fasten it and evaluate the tension. Achieving a precise fit ensures the belt supports your tailored trousers without cinching or distorting the fabric. Execute the omission drill before stepping out. Unfasten the leather and pull it from the loops. If the waistline looks entirely unresolved, the accessory stays. If the garment holds its shape perfectly and the silhouette feels sharper without the extra horizontal line breaking your torso, return the strap to the drawer.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your structural accessories with the same physical rigour.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "vegetable-tanned leather, medium width, matt brushed buckle"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the take-off test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Select a canvas and leather tote or a structured briefcase in a neutral tone like soft stone to maintain a quiet undercurrent. Scrutinise the fixtures. Ensure every zip and buckle features matt steel or titanium hardware, acting as one meticulous detail. Assess the construction by hoisting the empty bag. Depend on muscular feedback. Photographs disguise flimsy materials, but a sturdy handle proves structural integrity. Your aesthetic relies on a precise fit, and a bulky bag ruins that silhouette. Before leaving the house, apply the subtraction rule. Take off the final item you added. If the remaining garments feel entirely self-contained and functional without it, leave the discarded piece behind.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finish your look with functional carrying pieces and an absolute rule for restraint.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "canvas and leather tote or briefcase, matt hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the take-off test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Pattern provides structure, not decoration. Anchor tailored pieces with {recommended_pattern_1}. Let fluid layers carry adaptable {recommended_pattern_2}. Versatility demands a shifting approach to contrast. Scale your pattern intensity to the garment, but maintain your quiet undercurrent through a neutral palette. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} on the rail entirely. Give every printed garment the motion trial. Swing the fabric sharply through the air and watch the surface. The design must resolve into a soft, pleasant texture in movement. If the motif flashes or reads as a sharp graphic, drop the garment. A precise fit demands clean lines. Establish one meticulous detail in a matt physical weave, not an aggressive print.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the rules of visual scale and let pattern do the heavy lifting for your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the passing test (reads as soft, pleasant texture in motion)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Apply the peripheral vision check. Hang the {recommended_pattern_1} garment on a door frame and walk rapidly past it. The motif must lose its distinct edges and merge into a gentle, tactile blur as your sight slides over it, feeding into your quiet undercurrent. If the shapes stay legible and fight for attention, leave the piece on the rail. Your style requires self-contained control. Keep the palette completely neutral. The print should simply provide subtle visual depth, allowing a precise fit to anchor the eye while a single matt button acts as one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Execute this physical check to filter out distracting prints before they breach your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the passing test (reads as soft, pleasant texture in motion)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_virgo__moon_pisces__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "precise fit + blurred edges + one meticulous detail",
    "closing": "Trust the physical tension of the cloth in your hands as your permanent compass, reducing every choice down to precise fit + blurred edges + one meticulous detail.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust your hands to find garments that shift with your environment rather than fighting it. Feel the weight and drape of the cloth. If it restricts your movement or dictates exactly how you must sit, put it back. Your core framework operates on precise fit + blurred edges + one meticulous detail. Picture a tailored jacket cut exactly to your shoulder line, layered over a pliable, unstructured undershirt, finished with a single piece of flawlessly engineered hardware. The temperature of your entire wardrobe remains neutral. This grants you the freedom to move between contexts without resistance.\n\nBuild your collection modularly and deploy the pieces according to the day's physical demands. Your ultimate compass is the flight test. Ask yourself if you could pack the garment into a soft travel holdall, pull it out after a long haul, and put it straight on. If an item requires extensive steaming, complex styling rules, or limits your stride across a terminal, it fails the test. Leave it on the hanger. A truly self-contained wardrobe prioritises sheer agility. Keep your finishes matt. Ensure your garments work entirely for you.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this foundational framework before you evaluate a single new garment.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your materials must hold a precise fit without restricting your movement. Run every potential purchase through a compression check. Pick the garment up, crush it in your fist, and let it drop. If the fabric springs back into shape immediately, it will survive twenty hours of transit and still look deliberate. Build your shirting from {texture_good_1} for clean boundaries and pure separation. Layer this over {texture_good_2} to maintain sharp lines close to the body. Anchor the lower half in {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish with {texture_good_4} as lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks the wind. This combination guarantees blurred edges where layers meet, leaving the focus entirely on one meticulous detail. Look for the materials below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select fibres that hold their shape and demand zero ongoing maintenance.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
