    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid materials that trap heat or lose their shape. Squeeze {texture_bad_1} tightly. If it retains a hard crease, put it back. A neutral wardrobe requires fabrics that recover instantly. Assess {texture_bad_2} against your neck. If it scratches or clings, it disrupts your physical baseline. You need a precise fit. Unforgiving rigid weaves work against your anatomy. Drop {texture_bad_3} if it generates static or snaps back aggressively. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Visuals deceive, but the actual weight does not. Choose substantial matt materials that hold an exact shape while maintaining blurred edges, allowing room for one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and eliminate fabrics that fail against your skin or lose their physical structure.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Hold {sweet_spot_keyword_1} in one hand and {sweet_spot_keyword_2} in the other. Compare the density directly. You are looking for a matt finish that absorbs light. Your exact zone relies on pairing these weaves to secure a precise fit. Test every piece before buying. Determine if you could endure a lengthy commute wearing this cloth and stand up unwrinkled. If the fabric pinches or holds a crease, leave it on the rack. Keep the underlying palette neutral. {texture_good_1} serves as a reliable baseline for this rule. Anchor the cut close to the body to establish blurred edges, completing the look with cool hardware as your one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master this specific tactile combination to anchor your daily choices.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your overall colour temperature rests at absolute neutral. Build your foundation from {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, {core_colour_3}, and {core_colour_4}. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} strictly as your single deliberate accent. Apply your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly when an outfit feels too severe. Leave neon brights, glitter finishes, and sugary pastels on the rail. Every choice must support a precise fit with blurred edges. Beware the hard shell trap. When your schedule accelerates, do not grab rigid outerwear and inflexible utility layers. Substitute that stiff barrier with a heavy brushed cotton piece. It adapts to your pace while providing structural protection. Rely on the garment's kinetic resistance rather than its visual appeal. Restrictive seams give away poor construction. If an item shortens your stride, discard it. Finish the silhouette with one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assign strict roles to your shades to eliminate hesitation.",
