    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You have established a precise fit. You have softened the boundaries with blurred edges. Now, you must finish the process with one meticulous detail. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Begin your hardware selection with a watch built around a brushed steel case. Fasten it with either a leather or steel strap. Ensure the metal holds a muted matt brushed surface to absorb the light. Trust your hands to measure the balance. Execute the subtraction check before you step outside. Unclasp the watch and set it down on the table. If your clothing suddenly feels hollow without that solid physical heft, pick the item back up. Fasten it securely.",
