  "venus_virgo__moon_taurus__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "precise fit + sensory comfort + one meticulous detail",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on precise fit + sensory comfort + one meticulous detail.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe deliberately over time. Deploy these pieces fast, adapting to the day's demands. Trust physical equilibrium as your sensory compass. When you put on a garment, check how the weight settles across your shoulders. Your guiding equation is precise fit + sensory comfort + one meticulous detail. Picture a densely woven cotton shirt resting cleanly against the shoulder bone, tucked into heavy wool trousers that drape without clinging. Finish it with a thick leather strap featuring a muted, matt buckle. The neutral temperature of these pieces ensures they interact without friction.\n\nTurn the garment inside out before you buy it. Apply the seam test as your ultimate compass. Run your bare fingers along the interior stitching and the hidden hems. If the thread scratches your skin or the internal binding feels rigid, leave the piece on the rail. Looks lie. Construction does not. A poorly finished interior destroys the physical ease you require. Trust your hands over the mirror. Put the garment on and reach your arms forward. If the shoulder pinches, the structure fails. Demand flawless interior architecture to maintain your physical balance.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your architectural blueprint, the foundational logic you must apply before any garment touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the seam test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Seek out fabrics that guarantee both precise fit and sensory comfort without demanding constant maintenance. Keep the temperature neutral and the finish muted across your choices. Trust your hands to perform the recovery test before buying. Squeeze a handful of the cloth tightly in your palm and release it. If the wrinkles remain, drop the garment. You need resilient materials. Build your foundation with {texture_good_1} for shirting that holds clean boundaries. Layer {texture_good_2} close to the body for sharp lines and easy movement. Rely on {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing. Finish with {texture_good_4} for mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. The list below isolates the textures that pass this physical standard.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the resilient materials that build your foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Worsted wool",
