    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Apply the memory check before acquiring anything new. Pinch {texture_bad_1} sharply between your thumb and forefinger, then let go. If it retains those creases and refuses to snap back into shape, leave it on the rack. Avoid {texture_bad_2} entirely. It feels slick, trapping heat and sticking to you as the day wears on. Reject {texture_bad_3} for similar reasons. It lacks core structure and will sag at the elbows by noon. You require reliable weaves that maintain their integrity. Even when you secure one meticulous detail, a substandard base material ruins the attempt. Trust your fingertips as your primary gauge. Mirrors flatter, but tactile reality delivers the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and ruthlessly eliminate materials that fail on contact.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe by pairing {sweet_spot_keyword_1} alongside {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This combination builds a tactile foundation for any neutral palette. Test every piece before you buy it. Pull a section of {texture_good_1} taut across both hands, stretch the textile horizontally, and let go. Watch how quickly the fibres return to their original shape. If the material stays slack or warps, drop it. You need clothes that hold their structure through heavy wear. Combining reliable shape retention with sensory comfort guarantees a precise fit that endures.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your fabric pairings to anchor your wardrobe in tactile reality.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your colours sit at a strict neutral temperature. Ground your wardrobe using {core_colour_1} as a heavy anchor, pairing it with {core_colour_2} and {core_colour_3} for daily wear. Let {core_colour_4} bridge the gap between them. Add {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} only when you require a single deliberate accent. Deploy your relief tone sparingly as a soft note to break up heavy blocks. Bypass neon brights, glitter finishes, and sugary pastels entirely. Watch out for the pale blur trap. Styling every item in the same light value looks unresolved. Rescue this error by adding a heavy {core_colour_1} piece or a sharp {accent_colour_2} strike, then let a switch to crisp cotton poplin restore the lost depth. Rely on a precise fit to make these muted choices effective.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your palette strictly, relying on value and weight to create impact rather than loud shades.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Graphite",
