    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Feel the surface of {texture_bad_1}. If it catches on your knuckles or traps heat, drop it. Your look demands one meticulous detail to anchor it, and inferior materials blur that focus. Evaluate the seam density of {texture_bad_2}. If the boundary feels bulky, weak, or refuses to fold flat, discard the piece. A sharp silhouette requires structure. Materials like {texture_bad_3} often fail this immediately because they lack inherent mass. Drape the piece over your forearm. It must settle cleanly instead of clinging to the skin. Base your decisions strictly on tactile feedback.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to drop inferior materials the moment they touch your hands.",
