    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, an honest fabric takes the lead. An exacting fit and a singular point of focus support it quietly. A relentless schedule does not require stiff, rigid layers. It requires pliable garments that can sprint from morning until evening. Pick up the item and test the give. If the material restricts your shoulders, leave it on the hanger. A physical restriction ruins a precise fit. Select crisp cotton poplin or worsted wool in oatmeal. These materials absorb the stress of movement while retaining their shape. Keep the finish muted and matt, with cool metal hardware. A brushed silver watch case provides exactly one meticulous detail. Let the cloth carry the weight while the cut provides the framework.",
      "sectionIntro": "Approach your working hours as a practical challenge of physical stamina rather than a visual presentation.",
