      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Low light strips away colour and contrast. In these intimate settings, one meticulous detail always leads. Rely on a muted finish to absorb ambient light. Keep the palette neutral, anchored entirely by soft stone and oatmeal. Apply the Wren test to your evening choices. A long night does not require hard garments. It requires a soft fine ribbed merino that endures the hours. Inspect your jewellery. Any silver must remain cool and matt, catching shadows rather than reflecting the bulb. Rely strictly on tactile evidence to evaluate the cloth. Avoid anything stiff or restrictive. Pick it up and discard it immediately if it refuses to yield. Let the cut frame you without constraint. Keep your presence internal and self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the transition into low-light settings, where close proximity amplifies every choice.",
      "tests": [
