    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Base your hardware strategy entirely in cool tones. Focus your jewellery and structural zips on {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. These metals preserve a strict, neutral temperature against the skin. Avoid distressed brass and heavily oxidised copper. These artificially aged elements introduce historical static to a self-contained aesthetic. Clear the noise by insisting on polished silver, platinum, white gold, or mirror chrome. When assessing a heavy belt buckle or a watch casing, pick the piece up. Weight proves quality better than sight. Reject any hollow, {excluded_finish} items. Solid metal brings necessary gravity to a garment, completing a precise fit with absolute conviction.",
      "sectionIntro": "Metals dictate the structural integrity of your garments and provide the final resolution for your look.",
