    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select {stone_1} and {stone_2} for their subdued clarity and neutral tone. Demand a precise fit from every ring and cuff. Lift the setting in your palm before committing. Heavy density indicates true value. A dense, matt cabochon needs no explanation. Omit patinated settings altogether. Dull alloys clutter a self-contained profile. Fix this by keeping your metalwork strictly in the present tense. Rely solely on polished silver, white gold, platinum, and mirror chrome. These cool alloys frame your chosen stones efficiently and act as one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate stones and hardware by their physical density rather than visual complexity.",
      "tests": [
