    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Establish your base using a precise fit and a resilient, honest fabric. Accessories supply the final variable. Select exactly one meticulous detail to calibrate the look. Restrict yourself to one or two substantial pieces per outfit. Begin with a watch. Look for a brushed steel case paired with a matt steel or leather strap. Ensure any additional hardware remains neutral and cool. Run the one-signal test before stepping outside. Check the mirror and verify that only a single item acts as a focal point. If a second accessory fights for attention, take it off immediately. Confirm the calibre of the steel on your wrist by feeling its heavy drag.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your accessories as the final calibrating mechanism of your uniform.",
