    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Secure a precise fit with medium-width belts in vegetable-tanned leather. Press your thumb into the hardware to assess its mass. Dense, solid metal proves its worth immediately. You want a matt brushed steel or palladium buckle, never a high-shine finish. Apply the focal check before securing the strap. Look at the leather and the metal together. If the belt features contrast stitching alongside a decorative closure, it speaks twice and fails. Choose silence. Avoid excess branding or tooling. Let the muted cool-toned metal blend seamlessly into your neutral garments, defining the waist without breaking your visual line.",
