    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Select a neutral canvas and leather tote, or a briefcase with strictly matt hardware. Inspect the straps and handles to guarantee a precise fit against your ribs. A bag must operate as a contained unit of utility. Examine the metal components for cool finishes like brushed steel. Finally, stand at the door and evaluate your visual anchors. Look at your combined accessories. If your tote features heavy structural stitching, your watch strap must remain entirely plain. Remove any piece fighting for dominance. A single meticulous detail holds ground. Multiple points simply create noise.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your functional items and apply a strict filter to your final presentation.",
