    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Scrutinise the physical reaction of every garment. Avoid {texture_bad_1} when it feels hollow or catches on the skin. You require fabrics that can hold their sharp edges without tipping into brittle rigidity. Do not compromise with {texture_bad_2}. Pick the item up and crush it in your palm. If it retains a stiff, paper-like crease rather than dropping back into a fluid drape, leave it behind. Reject {texture_bad_3} immediately if it feels slick or artificial. A cool, matt textile must still possess life. If the material feels dead in your hand, it fails.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify the textiles that will actively sabotage your wardrobe before you make a mistake.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your signature tension lives in the friction of {sweet_spot_keyword_1} paired with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Run your hands over {texture_good_1} to verify its integrity. Grip the cloth and squeeze. It must yield to your hold but retain a strict silhouette. This action isolates fabrics that construct your soft shelter while preserving sharp edges. Avoid anything flimsy or transparent. The cloth must insulate you from the outside world. Look for a dense, matt surface that drapes without clinging. Combine a heavy woven structure with a densely knitted yarn. Add your one sentimental keepsake in a cool, solid metal to anchor the entire combination.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to combine fabrics that build your soft shelter while maintaining strict boundaries.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your foundation is resolutely cool. Build your base from {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}, using {core_colour_4} to map out crisp boundaries. Treat {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as your deliberate accents. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly to create visual breathing room. Pass over hard black, harsh neon, and heavy earth brown. They swallow your intended shape. Watch for the trap of vanishing into an unstructured, monolithic mass of dark fabric. When you catch yourself fading into this block, introduce sharp edges with your styling and fracture the void with a solitary glint of light. A heavy metallic cuff or a carved hair comb provides the necessary tension against a muted, matt background.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce your visual boundaries by adhering strictly to your designated foundation and leveraging structural contrast.",
      "rankedItems": [
