    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, sharp edges lead. Establish a clear boundary with a strictly tailored lapel in dove grey. Let yielding fibres do the underlying work. A relentless schedule does not require rigid suiting. It demands a heavy silk crepe blouse or a boiled wool jumper that can sprint through a twelve-hour shift. Anchor these pliant fabrics with a cool, matt platinum watch worn on your wrist. The tailoring defines your perimeter. The yielding fabrics keep you moving. The metal grounds your focus.",
      "sectionIntro": "Structure your working hours as a calculated system of boundaries and mobility.",
      "tests": [
