    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Let sharp edges take the lead when the lights go down. A dim room demands structure to catch the shadows. Choose a deep teal heavy silk crepe blazer with a crisp lapel. Apply the endurance test when selecting the layer closest to your skin. A long night of conversation does not require rigid eveningwear. It requires pliable washed silk that can adapt to hours of sitting and moving without restricting your lungs. Feel the garment against your ribs. If the seams bind or pinch, put it back on the hanger. Wear a matt silver cuff or a faceted white gold ring. Rely on subdued, cool tones to reflect whatever minimal light remains in the room.",
