    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "An overbooked Tuesday demands forgiving fabrics that move rapidly. Refuse stiff armour when managing a heavy itinerary. Layer cloud-soft lambswool over washed silk, relying on the natural drape and give of the fibres. A mundane trip to the chemist to collect a prescription requires the exact same standard. Your core logic applies regardless of the destination. Build the outfit using soft shelter + sharp edges + one sentimental keepsake. Let muted silver hardware on a structured bag provide a necessary boundary. Keep your colours cool and reserved. Anchor the look with an inherited platinum ring. Grasp the fabric directly. Trust your hands to verify that the material supports constant motion.",
      "sectionIntro": "Approach your daily routine as the true testing ground for your garments, demanding rigorous performance from every piece.",
