      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Base your hardware entirely in cool tones. Depend on {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} to construct the sharp edges your wardrobe demands. Avoid reflective polish. A high-shine surface acts as a glaring distraction next to your muted fabrics. Insist on matt or brushed textures, rejecting {excluded_finish} completely to ensure a cohesive look. Always lift a piece of jewellery or a buckle off the table to gauge its heft. Assess the physical density directly in your palm. Depend on this actual weight to anchor your soft shelter, letting solid metal sit securely on your frame.",
