    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Your jewellery must respect the boundaries of your soft shelter. Look for dense, opaque minerals that absorb light rather than refracting it. Seek out {stone_1} or {stone_2} to anchor your rings and pendants. Pick the piece up and assess its mass in your hand. Superficial sparkle offers no grounding. The heavy, physical weight of a true stone provides the anchor you need. Steer clear of highly polished metalwork. A gleaming setting looks jarring and fights your cool, muted colours. Demand brushed or matt hardware to secure your stones and keep the entire composition cohesive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your stones with the same strict physical criteria you apply to your textiles.",
      "tests": [
