    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Your core aesthetic demands absolute tactile safety to ground one sentimental keepsake. Let your fingers do the auditing. Squeeze the hem and notice how it recoils. Avoid {texture_bad_1} if it snags on your fingertips. Reject {texture_bad_2} the moment it squeaks or traps body heat. Discard {texture_bad_3} when it feels brittle or aggressively flat. These rigid materials disrupt your self-contained calm. They draw attention through irritation rather than providing deep comfort. A true cool, matt textile yields immediately to your hand. Leave the abrasive imposters on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject failure before a garment ever reaches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build your soft shelter. These two opposing weights create a self-contained environment. Evaluate every new garment with the graze test. Brush your bare hand over the weave. If the surface lacks inherent softness, leave the item on the rack. A {texture_good_1} outer layer provides structure, but it must rest on a foundation of pure comfort. Require every layer to stay cool and completely matt.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your texture pairings by anchoring every outfit on two contrasting weights.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in a strict foundation of cool tones. Assess every colour in natural daylight to ensure it aligns with your base of {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Trust your eyes to identify the correct undertone. Reach for {core_colour_4} as your definitive white substitute. Introduce your single deliberate accent using {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly to ground an outfit. Reject hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon immediately. Watch out for the lounge slide. Relax every item too far and you accidentally wear sleepwear. Correct this mistake by enforcing just one sharp boundary. Combine a structured collar, a pressed trouser fold, or a rigid handbag alongside a soft shelter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Filter your wardrobe through a rigorous editing process to isolate your exact tones.",
