    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Soft shelter leads your decisions at the office. Establish a protective perimeter with dense brushed wool or heavy cashmere. Support this outer layer with yielding interiors, using fluid silk against the skin. Finish with a solitary inherited steel ring. Let heft verify the quality of your tailoring. Lift the jacket to gauge its density. Maintain these boundaries relentlessly. Apply the desk test. Sit down and ensure the waistband does not cut into your torso. Keep your cool, matt finishes and dove grey layers intact.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is how you enforce your personal boundaries during business hours.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Let softness dictate your approach to close quarters. In dim lighting, rigid tailoring creates an unwanted barrier. Choose garments that pool and drape. Reach for a dove grey cashmere jumper or a deep teal silk shirt. Test the textile by bunching it in your fist. It must yield completely, bouncing back without severe creasing. Hosting a private dinner demands the same exacting standard as public life. Keep your metals cool and matt. A single platinum ring or a brushed silver pendant catches low light without throwing a harsh glare.",
