    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "When choosing {stone_1} or {stone_2}, test their physical density. Lift the piece in your palm. The stone must feel substantial enough to anchor the heavy silks and brushed wools you wear. If it feels hollow or light, leave it behind. A high-gloss polished setting reads as harsh and distracting against muted colours. It introduces a sharp glare that shatters visual calm. Insist on matt or heavily brushed bezels to keep the surface cohesive. Combine these dense, cool stones with deep layers of softness.",
