    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Anchor the soft shelter and the inner layer of softness with absolute restraint. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look, culminating in one sentimental keepsake. Start your evaluation with handbags. Demand thick suede or heavy full-grain leather, finished strictly with matt brushed hardware. Subject the material to the ripple test before you carry anything home. Press and drag your thumb firmly across the main panel of the bag. If the surface shivers, warps, or forms loose waves under the friction, reject it immediately. You require dense, self-contained materials that resist deformation. Choose a hide that pushes back against your grip and remains structurally smooth under pressure.",
