    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, your visual logic remains unchanged. Let inky navy cashmere and dove grey brushed wool form a primary protective layer between your skin and the office environment. Base every choice on your core formula: soft shelter + blurred edges + one sentimental keepsake. Fluid hems soften the rigid lines of typical corporate wear, and a cool silver pendant grounds the muted fabrics. Subject your morning selection to the chemist queue test. Picture yourself standing under harsh fluorescent lights waiting for a prescription. If your deep teal silk blouse pulls at the shoulder or your trousers pinch, remove the item immediately. Office attire never requires physical misery to function. Rely on quiet drape rather than stiff tailoring to build a self-contained presence.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use these directives to navigate professional dress codes without compromising your physical autonomy.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low light and close proximity, blurred edges lead. Rely on the drape of heavy silk or the dense pile of brushed wool in deep teal to absorb the dim light. Keep the finish matt. High-shine materials reflect aggressively in intimate spaces. Opt for cool, brushed silver resting quietly at your collarbone to serve as your keepsake. Before leaving the house, evaluate your physical range of motion. If the waistband pinches or the sleeves restrict your reach across a small dining table, take the piece off immediately. You never endure discomfort for an evening out. Lean on dove grey cashmere that shifts with you, preserving your baseline of soft shelter + blurred edges + one sentimental keepsake. Comfort secures your boundary. If the item demands constant adjustment, it fails the brief.",
      "sectionIntro": "Format your evening choices for close proximity and low light by prioritising ease over rigid structure.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A walk to the post office does not require abandoning your visual logic for default activewear. Build an outfit for picking up a parcel in the rain using the exact same principles you apply to an evening engagement. Your daily baseline must be soft shelter + blurred edges + one sentimental keepsake. Choose an inky navy wool sweater with a matt finish. Layer it over dove grey brushed cotton trousers. Add a single platinum ring. Keep the entire palette cool. Look for pieces that move without restriction. Evaluate the drape of a heavy silk scarf against your neck. If it pulls or snags, discard it. Every item you put on must feel entirely self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat ordinary errands as the primary testing ground for your aesthetic logic.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Metals act as the structural anchors of your wardrobe. Commit entirely to a cool foundation. Demand {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} for every visible zip, belt buckle, and ring. Build your soft shelter with deliberate hardware choices. Mirror-polished chrome slices harshly through muted textiles. Reject any {excluded_finish} finish and insist on matt surfaces to maintain visual cohesion. Always weigh the buckle or clasp in your bare palm. Hollow components compromise your quiet luxury. Solid metal anchors your quiet boundaries.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your hardware rules to ensure every zip and ring serves your aesthetic.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Assess your stones by their physical density. Press the piece against your collarbone. A genuine gem provides a heavy, grounding sensation that serves as your private anchor. Select opaque stones like {stone_1} or {stone_2} that absorb light rather than throwing it across the room. These elements must remain self-contained. A glossy, mirror-polished silver setting cuts too sharply against your muted colours, disrupting your soft shelter. Stick strictly to matt or brushed metal mounts to maintain cohesion. Wear one dense stone that carries physical weight, keeping the entire composition cool and resolved.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your wardrobe with dense stones and heavy hardware that absorb light rather than reflecting it.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Inspect every ring, clasp, and buckle for true substance. Heavy, dense pieces anchor your clothing. A hollow chain feels entirely wrong against brushed tweed and silk. Examine the finish closely. High-gloss surfaces cut too sharply against a muted wardrobe. They create harsh lines where you require blurred edges. Preserve cohesion by insisting on heavily oxidised or matt {metal_1}. Combine this subdued finish with {stone_1} that draws light inward. Rely on physical heft to verify quality before you bring a piece home.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate all hardware by weight before you judge its appearance.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments create soft shelter and rely on blurred edges. Accessories anchor this quiet foundation. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look, culminating in one sentimental keepsake. Begin with handbags. Demand full-grain leather or thick suede finished with matt brushed hardware. Apply the drop test before purchasing. Release the bag from a short height onto a hardwood floor. Observe the material as it strikes the ground. A superior skin collapses and puddles instantly. Stiff hides bounce or retain a hollow, rigid shell. Trust this material reaction over a printed label.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your hardware and leather with the same strict criteria you apply to your textiles.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Handbags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather or thick suede, matt brushed hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Creating soft shelter requires generous silk or fine wool scarves in deep teal. Demand a completely matt finish. Glossy fabrics reflect the outside world. You need textiles that stay entirely self-contained. Assess the quality of the drape through the banister check. Gather the scarf in your hands and sweep it over a wooden rail. Heavy, quality fibres plunge downwards and settle into dense folds. Flimsy material floats, catching the air and forming sharp angles. Reject anything that refuses to surrender to gravity. You want blurred edges, never sharp boundaries. Notice how true weight behaves in motion.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your accessories through their physical behaviour, trusting your hands to find proper weight.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "generous silk or fine wool, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your waist with a wide full-grain leather belt featuring a matt brushed buckle. The hardware must recede entirely. Choose a deep stone set in oxidised silver or aged brass for your primary item of jewellery. This grounds the cool tones of your garments. Apply the flash check before stepping outside. Stand before the mirror and scan the reflection for any bright glare that disturbs your blurred edges. If a gleaming clasp or a polished pendant breaks the visual surface tension of your soft shelter, remove the offending item immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your layers with grounding elements and eliminate visual disruptions before finishing your sequence.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "wide full-grain leather, matt brushed buckle"
        },
        {
          "name": "Keepsake jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "deep stone set in aged silver or brass, oxidised"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored garments must draw their pattern from structural weaves. Fluid pieces must rely on tonal dyes to construct blurred edges. Keep your contrast strictly low. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2}. Pass over rigid geometry. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} on the rack. Apply the twilight blend rule. Seek out a cool, moving texture that recedes gently into the shadows as ambient light drops. Let your tactile response guide you. A true pattern embeds itself in the fibre rather than sitting flat on top.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control the visual rhythm of your garments to maintain a quiet, self-contained aesthetic.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Conduct the distance check. Hang the garment across the room and dim the overhead lighting. Look at {recommended_pattern_1} from ten paces away. If the design remains crisp and legible as a distinct graphic, leave it on the rail. You need blurred edges to maintain your quiet boundaries. The motif must dissolve into a continuous, muted texture in the shadows. Choose prints that withdraw rather than projecting outward. A successful pattern behaves like a dense woven cloth. It obscures its own geometry, offering you a private retreat rather than making a public statement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply this visual test to ensure any pattern respects your need for quiet containment.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_cancer__moon_scorpio__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "soft shelter + quiet undercurrent + one sentimental keepsake",
    "closing": "Trust your physical instincts to map your boundaries, relying on absolute comfort to construct your soft shelter + quiet undercurrent + one sentimental keepsake.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build slowly and acquire garments with severe deliberation. Treat every potential addition as a rigorous test of your boundaries. Look for construction that feels like absolute silence against your skin. Run your hand down the sleeve and gauge the friction. If the material catches, scratches, or rustles, drop it immediately. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Tactile response does not. You are constructing a strictly self-contained environment. The weight must sit evenly on your shoulders without pulling or shifting. When a piece feels restrictive or demanding in the fitting room, trust your gut and walk away.\n\nMemorise your structural foundation and repeat it without variation. Your core formula is soft shelter + quiet undercurrent + one sentimental keepsake. Test every combination against this equation before you get dressed. Picture an enveloping, densely structured outer layer worn over a fluid, seamless foundation garment, anchored quietly by an inherited pendant resting coolly against your collarbone. Maintain a strictly cool temperature across your entire wardrobe. Seek out surfaces that are deeply matt to absorb ambient light rather than reflect it. You are dressing purely for your own internal calibration. Ignore outside noise.",
      "sectionIntro": "Internalise this core logic before you evaluate another garment.",
      "tests": [
        "trust your gut and walk away"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe as a soft shelter. The materials you wear must protect your quiet undercurrent without suffocating it. Apply the breath test before you buy. Hold the fabric to your mouth and exhale. If the air hits a solid wall, the garment will trap you. If you feel the cool air move through the fibres, keep it. Look for {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Source {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Trust {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Seek out {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. Choose your materials from the list below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the materials that build your foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
