    "closing": "Trust the heavy drape of warm cloth to guide your hands toward enduring structure + hidden depth + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe slowly, and rely on strict editing to wear it decisively. Trust the physical weight and density of a garment before you look in the mirror. Your aesthetic thrives on precise construction and warm, matt finishes that do not demand immediate attention. Your formula is enduring structure + hidden depth + one living texture. Picture a heavy tailored coat with an impeccable shoulder, worn over a densely knitted sweater, finished with a heavy, brushed scarf sitting softly against your neck. The appeal is entirely self-contained. You are not dressing for an audience.\n\nApply the melt test to every new acquisition. Pick the item up and put it on. Close your eyes and wait three seconds. The garment must settle and fuse with your frame. If it sits rigidly on your shoulders or feels distinctly separate from your body, take it off. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. Rely on garments that feel like a seamless extension of your own shape. Choose pieces that quietly anchor you rather than projecting outward.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this core blueprint and use these physical tests to evaluate every garment before it enters your wardrobe.",
