    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Assess a garment by running your bare palm across the weave. Rely on this tactile warning over any visual promise. If the material feels slick or entirely flat, put it back on the rail. {texture_bad_1} slides off the hand with an artificial glide, trapping heat against your skin rather than breathing. Weigh the piece by lifting the hem. {texture_bad_2} collapses immediately, lacking the hidden depth required to ground your silhouette. Reject {texture_bad_3} the moment it scratches or catches on your knuckles. These failing fibres create a harsh friction that disrupts a self-contained aesthetic. Require materials that respond to your touch with a muted, warm consistency.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn the precise tactile warnings that signal a garment will fail your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Unite {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Ground these fabrics with {texture_good_1} to establish enduring structure. Judge every textile by its resistance. Press the fabric between your palms. If the yarn feels hollow, slick, or synthetic, drop the garment immediately. A dense, matt weave and a muted finish communicate self-contained warmth. Your skin recognises true substance. Rely on this direct pressure to confirm the required hidden depth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your materials through strict physical standards.",
      "tests": [
        "the touch test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette relies upon a warm baseline. Anchor your choices with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Add {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} to bridge gaps without breaking your muted boundaries. For your single deliberate accent, introduce {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Apply the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to lift the outfit. Pass over sharp electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels entirely. Watch for the couch slide. Relax every item completely and you lose all borders, drifting into pure domestic comfort. Correct this error by reclaiming one crisp edge. Implement a folded but firm collar, a pressed trouser leg, or a rigid bag to provide the hidden depth that anchors soft shapes.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock down your colours to map your limits, treating everything outside this system as irrelevant.",
