    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Enduring structure sets the pace at work. Build the framework first. Reach for camel brushed wool trousers or a stiff toffee leather belt to create a clear boundary. Let hidden depth support this framework through a heavy silk lining that only you feel. Never dilute this intention for brief errands. A morning coffee run still requires your warm, self-contained shell. Keep the tailored coat securely fastened. Let the heavy drape of thick cloth dictate your posture. Inspect prospective purchases by pinching the cuffs and lapels. If those edges buckle under pressure, discard the piece. Maintain that firm, matt outline from your first appointment to your last.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply deliberate weight and form to govern your work wear choices.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In intimate, low-light settings, hidden depth takes the lead. Dim lighting neutralises sharp silhouettes, requiring one living texture to command the space. Rely on tactile reality over visual contrast. Select a rich toffee cashmere jumper or a matt silk shirt. Sweep your knuckles across the grain. The garment must reward someone standing mere inches away. Let warm gold jewellery glow softly against the collar rather than flash. Relocating to a quiet bar does not invite relaxed standards. Keep your pieces strictly calibrated to this close radius at all times.",
      "sectionIntro": "Calibrate your garments for close proximity and dim lighting.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Routine errands do not mean suspending your discipline. Buying a newspaper never justifies abandoning your warm, insulated atmosphere of camel cashmere and rich toffee leather. Rely on the heavy drape of brushed wool and the soft friction of matt silk against the skin. Test any casual garment by feeling its pure mass. If the knit feels weightless or hollow, reject it entirely. Your daily choices demand enduring structure + hidden depth + one living texture to maintain absolute consistency. Keep your layers close to the body. Limit your hardware to muted gold or bronze. Demand that every item you put on passes a strict tactile evaluation.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your ordinary routines with the exact same material discipline you apply to rare events.",
      "tests": [
        "a walk to the bakery does not require abandoning your atmosphere (Mist)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Anchor your hardware choices with {metal_1} and {metal_2}. You can introduce {metal_3} sparingly for subtle contrast. Treat these components as the final lock on your self-contained presentation. Avoid {excluded_finish} entirely. Evaluate every buckle, zip, and clasp by its actual heft. Lift the item from the display. Polished surfaces deceive, but solid density provides true hidden depth. A highly reflective metal acts like a glaring error against your warm fabrics. It pulls focus and undermines a garment's enduring structure. Correct this by insisting on brushed or matt textures. This strict standard ensures every fastening remains quiet and cohesive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Hardware acts as the foundational rivet of your wardrobe, demanding the same rigorous selection as your heaviest coat.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Look for opaque stones that absorb light rather than fracture it. Seek out the cloudy density of {stone_1} or the solid, warm tone of {stone_2}. Avoid brilliant facets. Highly polished surfaces generate a restless glare that fights against your quiet, muted palette. Rely solely on matt finishes and tumbled treatments to ensure every element blends seamlessly. Gauge the stone by letting it rest in your palm. A proper gem feels distinctly heavy and dense, anchoring your outfit with true hidden depth. This satisfying gravity provides enduring structure without demanding attention.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select dense, opaque stones that ground your outfit and absorb light.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Demand substantial castings over hollow metallic shells. Shiny plating masks a lack of substance, but absolute weight guarantees true hidden depth. Check the heft to ensure the piece offers enduring structure and grounds the fastening against your body. Reject high-gloss reflective surfaces entirely. A mirror-like finish flashes inappropriately and shatters your muted harmony, competing directly against the soft, warm fibres of your garments. Anchor your hardware choices in deeply brushed {metal_1} to keep the entire aesthetic strictly self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate hardware by weight and finish before you ever put it on.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories supply the one living texture required to finish a foundation built on enduring structure and hidden depth. Keep your focus tight. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Begin your selection with handbags. Seek out dense full-grain leather or thick suede. Ensure the metal accents feature matt brushed hardware in warm tones, entirely avoiding reflective shine. Always perform the compression test before purchasing. Push your thumb firmly into the flat side of the leather. The hide must gather in heavy, yielding waves rather than buckling into rigid creases. Let the pure density of the material dictate your final decision. Genuine quality always carries tangible mass.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your accessories as the final physical weights that lock your garments into place.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Handbags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "full-grain leather or thick suede, matt brushed hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Look for generous silk or fine wool scarves with a strictly matt finish. Avoid anything with a high sheen. Select a camel or rich toffee scarf to execute the cascade test. Bunch the material in your fist and let it drop over your forearm. Watch how the fabric falls. It must drop heavily, creating thick rolling folds rather than a lifeless puddle. A scarf with genuine weight drapes with an enduring structure. Arrange it around your neck and confirm the fabric holds a defined shape while offering hidden depth against the collarbone. Restrict your collection to heavy cashmere or brushed wool that actively retains its form.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your soft accessories strictly by weight and drape.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Scarves",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "generous silk or fine wool, matt"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Source wide full-grain leather for belts. Fasten them with a matt brushed brass buckle to establish enduring structure at the waist. For keepsake jewellery, seek out a deep garnet or amber stone set in oxidised brass or aged silver. These pieces offer hidden depth against a warm camel knit. Before leaving the house, perform a movement audit to catch any imbalance. Sit down, twist your torso, and walk briskly. If a pendant swings wildly out of rhythm with your step, or a rigid buckle digs into your ribs, remove the offending item immediately. Demand absolute harmony between your garments and accessories. A single physical distraction shatters a self-contained composition.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply strict mechanical standards to your finishing touches before you step out the door.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "wide full-grain leather, matt brushed buckle"
        },
        {
          "name": "Keepsake jewellery",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "deep stone set in aged silver or brass, oxidised"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the ripple test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Your tailored coats and trousers take their motif strictly from the weave itself. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} in brushed wool to provide an enduring structure. Your fluid silk pieces carry {recommended_pattern_2}. Demand low-contrast, tonal transitions across every garment. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. Subject any new print to the twilight evaluation. Assess how the textile behaves as daylight fades. If the design stays rigid or stark, reject the garment. The motif must soften and settle into a warm, moving blur in the evening shade. This guarantees your choices retain true hidden depth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the rules of pattern to introduce subtle rhythm without breaking your muted tone.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Execute the low-light check on {recommended_pattern_1}. Stand in fading illumination. The pattern must soften into a unified surface rather than fracturing your silhouette into contrasting shapes. It should sink back into the fabric to become a warm, shifting shadow. Trust this visual shift to supply one living texture. If the print stays sharp and high-contrast as the light drops, leave it on the hanger. A successful motif always retreats. It becomes a subtle grain that provides hidden depth rather than a flat graphic.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every print to a strict physical filter to ensure it serves your need for self-contained boundaries.",
      "tests": [
        "the dusk test (settle into a warm, moving texture)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_capricorn__moon_gemini__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "enduring structure + light movement + one living texture",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on enduring structure + light movement + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical weight of the garment in your hands. If the fabric feels synthetic or fleeting, put it back. Build slowly. Assemble your wardrobe piece by piece over seasons. Look for balance and a warm undertone in every weave. Your aesthetic register demands discretion. This means investing in substantial garments with a matt finish rather than chasing frivolous trends. Rely on the tension between firmness and give.\n\nYour formula is enduring structure + light movement + one living texture. Picture a tailored cashmere overcoat layered over a fine silk shirt, anchored by a raw leather belt. That is your template. When judging a new addition, apply the decade test. Inspect the cut and ask if it would have made sense ten years ago. Then ask if you will still reach for it ten years from now. If the answer is no, leave it on the hanger. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise this foundational logic to govern every garment you choose.",
      "tests": [
        "the decade test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Anchor your foundation in enduring structure and light movement. Ground these elements with one living texture to give your warm palette physical weight. Look for {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Use {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Keep {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without stifling. Finish with {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every seam. Always apply the wrist test before purchasing. Press the textile against the thin skin of your inner arm. If it feels rigid or artificial, leave it on the rail. Let the tactile feedback guide your final decision. Choose from the fibres below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your wardrobe relies on materials that absorb light and invite touch, grounding your aesthetic in physical reality.",
      "rankedItems": [
