    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Perform a heat check on questionable garments by bringing the hem to the inside of your forearm. If it traps warmth unnaturally or feels slick against your warm skin, drop it. {texture_bad_1} clings when you need light movement and suffocates when you demand enduring structure. Run your fingers over {texture_bad_2}. If the surface feels artificially smooth or catches on a rough thread, leave it on the hanger. Materials like {texture_bad_3} hold rigid shapes but lack the necessary give, presenting a hard shell instead of a responsive layer. Train your hands to recognise these failures immediately. The tactile response never lies.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject materials that fail against the skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Pair {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to build enduring structure. This combination grounds your wardrobe. Gauge every piece against the sensitive skin of your neck. If the yarn bites or scratches, leave it on the rack. Your materials must provide a warm, matt surface. Avoid stiff synthetics completely. Lift {texture_good_1} and test the drape in your hands. The piece should feel dense in your grip but yield entirely to your form when worn. Count on your fingers to verify the quality before you buy.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to combine materials that physically support your shape.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your colours run strictly warm. Build your daily foundation on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Lean on {core_colour_3} for heavy tailoring, reserving {core_colour_4} for items needing an earthy shift. Treat {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent, deployed only for a sharp focal point. Inject your soft relief tone sparingly to lift a dense ensemble. Walk straight past stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. Beware the trap of metallic saturation, where rich detail degrades into cheap flash. Confine your shine to a solitary molten point. Force every secondary metal element to remain tiny, matt, and quietly functional. Ground the look with enduring structure, introduce light movement through soft draping, and let one living texture hold the eye.",
