    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, enduring structure leads to establish a firm baseline. Let gentle drape and a single tactile element support this foundation by providing necessary give. A long day of meetings requires responsive layers, never a rigid casing. Pick up a tailored piece and fold the sleeve. If it fights your grip, drop it. Anchor your weekday choices in bitter chocolate and dark mahogany. Seek out boiled wool blazers worn over heavy silk crepe trousers. The palette temperature must stay warm. Keep every surface strictly matt. Mix gold and silver hardware on briefcases freely, provided both metals share a muted reflection.",
      "sectionIntro": "Construct your weekday outfits by making your tailored layers the softest pieces you own.",
      "tests": [
