      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim, warm lighting, your focus shifts entirely to light movement. A lengthy dinner does not require rigid cloth. It demands soft layers that yield and flex as the night progresses. Choose heavy silk crepe or washed silk in your deepest foundation colours. Let these garments pool slightly at the cuff and neckline. Sit down in the fitting room before you buy. The cloth must fold without restricting your breath. Add a matt gold pendant and a brushed silver ring to catch the candlelight. Rely on your fingers when evaluating these pieces. If the fabric feels brittle, leave it on the hanger.",
