      "text": "You operate on a strict dual register for metals. Keep warm tones like {personal_metal_1} and {personal_metal_2} directly against your skin for your jewellery. For the hardware on your garments, rely on {structural_metal_1} and {structural_metal_2} for zips, buckles, and clasps. This division builds enduring structure across your wardrobe. Avoid {excluded_finish} pieces. Highly polished hardware pulls focus and clashes with soft muted colours, so stick strictly to matt or brushed surfaces. Lift the item and feel the hardware in your palm. A heavy cast confirms quality while hollow alloys reveal cheap construction. Solid metal grounds a garment. It provides the anchor necessary to support light movement. Finish the outfit with one living texture.",
