    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select {stone_1} and {stone_2} to cut through your warm palette. You need gems that provide enduring structure rather than a delicate glint. Pick up the setting. Judge the piece by its specific gravity. If the metal feels hollow, put it back on the tray. You require a heavy, solid centre of gravity to ground your garments. Reject fake patina and weathered hardware. Tarnished brass, battered copper, and artificially aged alloys read as clutter against a sharp outfit. Instead, mount your {stone_3} in flawless polished silver, platinum, white gold, or mirror chrome. These pristine finishes keep the presentation firmly in the present tense.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess every stone by how it intercepts the light and how it anchors your hand.",
      "tests": [
