      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1} at all costs. Grab a sleeve and crush it in your fist. If it springs back feeling slick or sharp, leave it on the rack. True quality ages into a soft, matt bloom over years of wear. Cheap {texture_bad_2} just degrades, pilling into a stiff mess instead of breaking in. You require garments that drape perfectly under cool light to execute one clever contrast in your outfit. A lifeless, brittle {texture_bad_3} ruins that balance. Let your knuckles assess the weave. If a piece catches on your skin or feels hollow, drop it instantly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to spot the fakes before they reach your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the patina test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Build crisp separation by layering {sweet_spot_keyword_1} beside {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Pick up {texture_good_1} and drag your thumb across the weave. Ask yourself how the cloth will handle years of friction. If the threads will yield and earn a soft grace over time, buy it. If the surface will fuzz or pill under your palm, leave it on the rack. The sweet spot relies on cool, matt finishes that absorb light rather than reflect it. A muted wardrobe demands weaves that age gracefully.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to combine weaves that serve your core aesthetic.",
      "tests": [
        "the patina test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep the overall temperature strictly cool. Build the foundation by pairing {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_3}. Ground these shades using {core_colour_2} to create depth. When you require a lighter touch, select {core_colour_4} instead of a plain white. Introduce {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a deliberate focal point. Deploy the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to prevent stiffness. Ignore hard black, harsh neon, and heavy earth brown entirely. They destroy the balance. Watch out for the trap of excessive softness. When you rely exclusively on boiled wool and heavy silk crepe, the boundaries between garments blur. You drift slowly into shapeless territory. Fix this by restoring a single rigid line. Pair a sharp lapel or a structured leather bag with your soft knits. This rigid element ensures crisp separation between pieces while retaining your required sensory comfort.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your colours as architectural materials, building from a strict foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Dove grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "structural_dark"
