    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close settings under low light, crisp separation remains crucial. Feel the layers against your skin. A quiet evening at home demands the identical standard of tactile care as a late dinner. Pull on a fine ribbed merino sweater. Pair it with technical nylon trousers. Mix your metals freely. Place a polished silver cuff next to a matt gold ring. Keep the tones resolutely cool. Avoid heavy stiffness. Test the drape by rolling the cuffs. The fabric must yield to your grip while maintaining enough athletic space for total comfort. Add one clever contrast via a mixed-finish buckle.",
      "sectionIntro": "Close quarters require a strict tactile edit.",
