    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "You have complete freedom to combine {metal_1} right next to {metal_2} and {metal_3}. Your cool palette requires metals that slice cleanly across your base layers. Steer entirely clear of faux-weathered copper, tarnished brass, or purposely degraded alloys. These vintage finishes look muddy against your modern garments. Rely exclusively on pristine sterling, white gold, and mirror-like chrome. Feel free to contrast a high-shine ring with a strictly {excluded_finish} buckle. Pick up every clasp, chain, and watch before buying. Evaluate the item blindly in your palm. True quality carries obvious density. If the hardware feels hollow, leave it alone. Give your heavy jewellery room to breathe on the body. Demand athletic space between a cuff and a ring, ensuring crisp separation without any tangled clutter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your hardware and jewellery as if sourcing precise industrial fixtures.",
      "tests": [
