    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your accessories deliver that necessary one clever contrast. Once worsted wool trousers and woven cotton layers establish crisp separation, and the gaps between garments grant you athletic space, your hardware finishes the equation. Anchor your approach on one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with eyewear. Choose a thick acetate frame in a mixed finish, placing a polished rim beside matt arms. Rely entirely on your tactile judgement. Try the rotation test. Whip your head rapidly left and right. If those frames slide down your nose or pinch your temples during sudden movement, abandon them. Keep your accessory palette resolutely cool. Mix your metals without rules, letting untreated steel rub directly against bright silver.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware through movement and touch to select items that ground your silhouette.",
