    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Select a technical nylon crossbody bag. Test it using the friction check. Sling the strap over a worsted wool coat and pull the bag sharply around your torso. If the webbing snags the fabric, put it down. You need materials that slide cleanly across your back. Keep the hardware mixed freely. Choose cool brushed metal zips against an icy grey shell, interrupted by one polished ring at the strap joint. This hardware mix guarantees crisp separation from your base layers. Look for dense shapes that hold their own geometry. Trust your hands when you fill the compartments. If the shell balloons outward and destroys the athletic space at your ribs, leave it on the shelf.",
      "sectionIntro": "Secure your carry items with absolute structural discipline.",
