    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored pieces take their structure from strict geometries like {recommended_pattern_1}. Fluid items demand {recommended_pattern_2} to enforce crisp separation against softer drapes. Because your approach is highly adaptable, scale your contrast to the environment. Keep tonal shifts subtle for quiet integration, but deploy stark graphic differences when the context requires it. Anchor these choices in a cool {core_colour_1} base. Give the print athletic space by keeping intense motifs strictly below the collarbone. Run every garment through a distance check. Walk away from the mirror. If the motif turns muddy or confusing in the first split second, drop it immediately. Pass over indistinct florals, chaotic motifs, and fuzzy borders. Avoid {avoid_pattern_1} entirely. Reject {avoid_pattern_2} without a second thought.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as a functional tool to control the eye, not a decoration.",
