        "the blink test (not muddy or confusing in the first split second from ten feet)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Conduct a blink evaluation before purchasing any print. Shut your eyes tightly, then open them for a fraction of a second. A successful {recommended_pattern_1} must read immediately as intentional geometry. If the motif smears into a puddle or loses its cool definition, leave it on the hanger. Your style requires crisp separation. A blurred print destroys that clarity entirely. The design needs enough athletic space within its own repeat to register instantly from across a studio to provide one clever contrast. Trust your immediate visual reaction. If the shape hesitates or scrambles in that first glance, it fails the test.",
