  "venus_leo__moon_aries__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "dark drama + sharp edges + one molten flash",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on dark drama + sharp edges + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical weight and strict construction of a garment against your skin. Your wardrobe operates on a clear physical mandate. The foundation must feel substantial and precise. Your exact formula is dark drama + sharp edges + one molten flash. Picture a heavy tailored overcoat with exact, unyielding shoulders layered over a dense knit, finished entirely by a single highly polished, light-catching cuff on the wrist. Favour a warm overall temperature. The finish must remain rigorously polished from collar to hem.\n\nCurate your pieces methodically over time, then assemble them each morning on pure instinct. Subject every garment to the hesitation test. If you put on a structured jacket and immediately want to push up the sleeves, soften the collar, or diminish the impact, take the item off immediately. You require absolute conviction in your clothing. If your hands want to fidget or soften the blow of a sharp silhouette, the piece fails. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Sharp geometry does not.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural foundation, the physical baseline you must return to every time you build an outfit.",
      "tests": [
        "the hesitation test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "To build dark drama, your fabrics must take and hold a hard line. Start with {texture_good_1} for shirting that snaps visually and anchors your sharp edges. Move to {texture_good_2} for tailoring that holds a permanent crease without demanding a steamer. Apply the friction test before you buy anything. Run your bare hand swiftly down the sleeve and seek the immediate frictionless slip. Let this tactile feedback dictate your choices. Heavy drape reveals true quality. Build your polished surface with {texture_good_4} for base layers that gleam under warm lighting, and use {texture_good_3} for statement footwear that provides your one molten flash. Study the ranked list below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to hunt for materials that construct structure and catch warm light.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "sharp shirting that holds a crease and snaps visually"
        },
        {
          "name": "Sharp wool twill",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "knife-edge tailoring that never begs for a steamer"
        },
        {
          "name": "Patent leather",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "statement footwear and accessories that reflect maximum light"
        },
