    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Leave {texture_bad_1} on the hanger. It eats light and turns your warm palette muddy, destroying the dark drama of your silhouette. Pinch a fold of {texture_bad_2} between your thumb and forefinger. If the cloth crushes into a stubborn wrinkle, it lacks the structural tension to hold sharp edges. Evaluate every surface with the drag check. Sweep your open palm fast down the sleeve of a jacket. You are hunting for a clean, rapid glide. {texture_bad_3} fails this instantly. It catches on the skin, pulling the garment out of alignment and ruining the lines.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject fabrics that drag down your structure.",
      "tests": [
        "the friction test (run your hand swiftly down the sleeve; seek the slip)"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Building dark drama requires strict control over how cloth catches light. Your sweet spot lives in the direct clash between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Confirm a smooth, uninterrupted finish across the weave. Photography can be fooled, but dense material always proves structural integrity. You need textiles that hold their rigid form while throwing a warm reflection under bright bulbs. Anchor an exacting collar against a heavy {texture_good_1} body. This deliberate tension delivers sharp edges without stiffness. Drop anything that creates friction against your skin or swallows illumination into a dead void.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your aesthetic by forcing extreme material contrasts to work together.",
      "tests": [
        "the friction test (run your hand swiftly down the sleeve; seek the slip)"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep your palette uniformly warm. Anchor your wardrobe using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Treat {core_colour_3} as your primary white substitute, using {core_colour_4} to bridge gaps. Deploy your relief tone only as an isolated note used sparingly to break up solid shapes. Bring dark drama into the mix with {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Pair these saturated shades with sharp edges in your tailoring. Pass over murky pastels, icy grey, and dusty sage completely. Beware the fade trap. Weak, pale dyes strip your visual impact. Correct this error instantly by positioning a dense block of pigment near your face or anchoring the outfit with a brightly polished, intense shoe.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your wardrobe by building it on a strict foundation of deliberate heat.",
      "rankedItems": [
