    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, dark drama leads. Build the foundation with a warm bitter chocolate boiled wool jacket or a dark mahogany heavy silk crepe trouser. Bring in support using a fluid washed silk blouse underneath. A chaotic morning commute does not demand abandoning proportion. Ensure the volume of that loose top remains tethered by sharp tailoring. Complete the uniform with a single brass cuff or a chunky gold ring. Assess the weight of every item in your hands before dressing. Touch the cloth. Dense matt materials drape correctly. Flimsy fabrics warp and cling. Let tactile intuition guide your choices. Look for precise seams and robust linings.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your working parameters before reaching for a hanger.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Let dark drama lead when the lights dim. Cut away stiff layers and rely on heavy silk crepe against the collarbone. Close, candlelit tables demand tactile fibres over loud shapes. Grasp the fabric. If it stays rigid, put it back. Trust the heft in your hands. A dense textile confirms its quality through pure gravity. An intimate dinner setting does not excuse sloppy construction. Keep the cut exact even when the setting softens. Ground the base in bitter chocolate washed silk. A warm polished gold cuff paired with a dense silver ring catches the low room light. Let the silk pool and settle.",
      "sectionIntro": "Prepare for close-quarters lighting by stripping away visual noise and relying entirely on the drape of your materials.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat a mundane errand to the chemist with the same rigorous logic as a formal appointment. A 7 AM bakery run demands the same structural consistency as a board meeting. Step directly into a stiff headwind to see how the fabric reacts. If the breeze distorts the cut, leave the piece behind. Assess the textile's drop against the wind to gauge its true performance. Your daily choices require strict execution. You must build dark drama + light movement + one molten flash into every single combination. Layer cloud-soft lambswool in bitter chocolate over an inner shell of washed silk. Fasten the waist with a dual-register buckle in polished brass and steel. Keep the entire palette warm.",
      "sectionIntro": "Maintain rigorous physical standards across your everyday routines.",
      "tests": [
        "a market morning does not require abandoning proportion (Breeze)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Separate the metals that touch your skin from the metals that hold your garments together. For personal jewellery resting against your collarbone, rely on warm {personal_metal_1} and {personal_metal_2}. For the structural mechanics of your wardrobe, including zips, buckles, and bag clasps, use {structural_metal_1} or {structural_metal_2}. Avoid {excluded_finish} surfaces. Hammered, oxidised, or deliberately aged hardware reads as visual noise against a present-tense style. Keep your surfaces highly reflective and strictly polished. This gleam delivers a molten flash against your dark drama. Finally, gauge the heft of every chain or clasp before buying. Heavy, solid hardware provides necessary grounding for your light movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Split your hardware strategy into two distinct lanes.",
      "tests": [
