    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Test every piece of {metal_1} in your bare hand. Focus on the literal gravity of the object. Lift the item to measure its weight before putting it on. If it feels hollow, reject it immediately. You require dense, substantial jewellery to offset any dark drama in your garments. Avoid distressed hardware, artificially tarnished elements, and hammered surfaces entirely. These textured effects read as visual clutter. Instead, demand strict boundaries around a highly polished, warm finish. A pristine, reflective surface catches ambient illumination, directing clear light movement exactly where you require it.",
