    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Complete the combination of dark drama and light movement using exactly one molten flash. Accessories act as this precise final strike. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with silk scarves. Knot a silk band at the collar to introduce a polished soft glow. Maintain a warm temperature across your hardware, blending different metals to capture a dual register finish. Execute the take-off test before you finish dressing. Remove the final addition from your neck or wrist. If the overall silhouette loses its necessary tension, put the item back on. If the garments retain their heavy drape and momentum standing alone, leave the extra piece on the table. Trust your physical senses to confirm the balance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the final strike of an outfit by restricting your additions to highly deliberate touches.",
      "rankedItems": [
