    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Reach for fine jewellery to resolve the silhouette. A thin gold chain in a high polish finish introduces essential light movement, lifting the dark drama of a dark mahogany layer. Execute the subtraction check when you secure the clasp. Roll your shoulders and step forward. If the chain catches on the collar or feels stiff against the skin, remove it immediately. It must glide. Assess the surface strictly by touch. A smooth finish behaves correctly against the skin. Warm tones belong against bitter chocolate threads. Mix your metals by combining this pristine gold with a secondary polished silver element. This dual approach works because both surfaces share the same flawless gleam.",
      "sectionIntro": "Turn to fine jewellery as the final precise calibration of your silhouette.",
