    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, lead with balanced proportions. Support this foundation with pieces that swing and sharp metallic accents. A crisp cotton poplin shirt tucked into worsted wool trousers establishes the strict geometry you need. A technical nylon trench coat provides movement without disrupting your cool palette of icy grey and stark navy. Even a Friday afternoon at the desk demands a sharp outline. Never settle for amorphous cuts. Pick up an item and fold it. Avoid anything that collapses. The physical tension of the material reveals its structural integrity. Rely on dense fabrics to build the formal boundaries required for the office. Mix silver and gold across your watch and rings to deliver those final accents.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your workplace attire around strict geometry and reliable movement.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In low-light environments, your strategy pivots. Let one refined touch lead. Close settings demand tactile scrutiny. Judge the garments by feel alone. The drape of a piece dictates its success. Run a thumb over a fine ribbed merino sleeve to verify the structure. Keep the temperature cool with stark navy or icy grey. Dim lighting obscures dye but amplifies surface tension. Apply the Cinder test. Stepping out into a poorly lit restaurant corridor still requires a deliberate shape. Avoid heavy outerwear. Select an unlined technical nylon jacket over your knitwear. Scale down the hardware to mixed metals. Contrast a high-shine zipper against a matt worsted wool collar. Drop the bulk and let the construction speak.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering evening dressing requires scaling down the silhouette without losing your structural foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A late-night drive to buy milk at the corner shop demands an intentional shape. Never drop your standards for a mundane errand. You must maintain your exact baseline equation of balanced proportions + mobile layers + one refined touch, whether you are crossing a wet pavement or sitting behind the wheel. Anchor your choices in a cool palette of stark navy and icy grey. Pull a technical nylon shell over a fine ribbed merino knit. Mix your metals and finishes freely. Clasp a polished silver pendant and slip on a matt brass ring before you step outside. Feel how worsted wool trousers drape onto your boots. Demand structure from every item.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your ordinary routines as the primary testing ground for your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "a midnight petrol station run still deserves a silhouette (Cinder)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "A cool wardrobe provides the ideal foundation for absolute hardware freedom. You can combine {metal_1} with {metal_2} and {metal_3} across a single outfit. Lift any clasp or buckle in your palm before you buy it. Gauge the density of the item directly. If a piece lacks substantial heft, put it back. Avoid manufactured antiquity. Chemically patinated brass, hammered copper, and artificially weathered details register as unnecessary visual clutter. Restrict your selections to gleaming silver, pure platinum, pristine white gold, and reflective chrome. You can introduce a flat matt {excluded_finish} detail for contrast, but only if the underlying core feels dense. Choose heavy, functional zips to anchor your mobile layers. Ensure your balanced proportions stay sharp by selecting substantial, cleanly cast buckles.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess every clasp, zip, and ring using strict physical criteria.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select stones that deliver absolute clarity or absolute density. Demand the sharp refraction of a {stone_1} or the solid, cool mass of a {stone_2}. Lift the piece in your palm to test its integrity. Manufactured flaws act as visual debris against clean lines. Demand pristine, highly polished settings instead. This strict filtering ensures your balanced proportions remain undisturbed by unnecessary clutter.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every stone and setting by its physical mass and refractive precision.",
      "tests": [
