  "venus_libra__moon_libra__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "balanced proportions + cool composure + one refined touch",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on balanced proportions + cool composure + one refined touch.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your style operates on precise equilibrium. Feel the weight and drape of the fabric before you put it on. Your daily framework demands balanced proportions + cool composure + one refined touch. Picture a heavy structured coat worn over a fluid silk shirt and crisp tailored trousers, anchored by a single architectural watch. The contrast between rigid structure and soft fluidity gives the look its foundation. Pick up a garment and assess its physical tension in your hands.\n\nBuild your wardrobe foundation systematically over time, but deploy the combinations fast according to your immediate environment. Maintain a cool temperature across your fabrics to anchor your versatile framework. When evaluating a new garment, use the fall test. Lift the fabric from the hanger and drop it onto a solid surface. Watch how it hits the wood. It must drop with immediate gravity, pooling solidly rather than crumpling. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural blueprint. Memorise these operating principles.",
