    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Maintain a cool temperature across your wardrobe by trusting your hands to evaluate every garment. Rely on {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Turn to {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement. When assessing trousers, seek out {texture_good_3}. This material drapes cleanly and resists creasing through a long day. Finish your foundation using {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. Always apply the edge test before buying. Pinch the hem between your thumb and index finger to ensure the boundary finishes sharply without rolling. This strict physical check guarantees your textiles will deliver balanced proportions, project cool composure, and always provide one refined touch.",
