    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject any cloth that feels hollow against your skin. Trust your hands when evaluating {texture_bad_1}. Assess the structural integrity of a seam. If it collapses or feels brittle under pressure, drop the shirt immediately. Weak cloth compromises your cool composure. You require fabrics that hold a definitive shape. Investigate {texture_bad_2} with identical scrutiny. Squeeze the cuff in your fist. If the sleeve retains a sharp crease when released, it fails. Avoid {texture_bad_3} completely. Its rigid surface creates loud friction and catches the light poorly. Demand uncompromising substance from your materials.",
