      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Assess every piece against your bare skin. Rub the material against your collarbone. If {texture_bad_1} scratches or catches on that sensitive area, drop it. Your hands detect cheap construction immediately. Appearances manipulate. Density tells the truth. Squeeze {texture_bad_2} in your fist. If it crinkles like plastic, squeaks, or traps unnatural heat, leave it on the rail. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. It catches the light with a hard, artificial glare that destroys a quiet, matt finish. Let your hands govern your wardrobe. Heavy, cool materials belong on your back. Thin, stiff synthetics do not.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify poor materials before you even put them on.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot rests at the junction of {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Let a layer of {texture_good_1} provide a quiet undercurrent to your daily dressing. Test every new item against your bare arm. Swipe the cuff across your bare forearm. If it scratches or drags, leave it on the rail. You require a yielding touch that wears in rather than wearing out. The friction between a matt {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and a smooth {sweet_spot_keyword_2} holds all the necessary tension. Keep the tactile profile cool and deliberate.",
      "sectionIntro": "Pin down your exact texture pairing to anchor your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette is strictly cool. Build your foundation from {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}, substituting harsh whites with {core_colour_4}. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your deliberate accent. Treat your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon entirely. Watch for the comfort collapse. When you remove too much structure, you slide directly into shapeless loungewear. Correct this mistake by restoring a single crisp edge. Pick up a properly folded lapel, a trouser with a pressed crease, or a rigid calfskin bag to anchor the yielding materials. Rely entirely on physical grip when assessing new items. Reflections fabricate reality. Heft provides absolute proof. Marry this tactile certainty with balanced proportions to ground your silhouette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Execute your precise colour strategy with discipline to build a wardrobe that works relentlessly for you.",
