    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, let the quiet undercurrent lead the ensemble. Start with a heavy silk blouse in deep teal or a structured dove grey wool trouser. Build balanced proportions around this piece to ensure the garments fall cleanly, avoiding sharp hems or severe angles. Once the shape is set, add one refined touch. A matt white gold watch face or a single platinum ring finishes the look. Rely on the drape of your clothing to guide your choices. Glass distorts reality. Thick hide confirms it. Remember that a morning walk for a pastry does not mean shedding your cool, enveloping fog. Maintain your muted foundation at all hours.",
      "sectionIntro": "Build your working garments by elevating a single leading element and structuring the rest of the outfit to support it.",
      "tests": [
