    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim lighting and close quarters, your quiet undercurrent takes the lead. Reach for pieces that invite proximity. Choose a deep teal cashmere knit or an inky navy silk shirt. Let your fingertips overrule your eyes. Pick up the fabric. Let its density guide you. Visuals mislead. A heavy hemline speaks facts. Ground the outfit with a single piece of matt silver jewellery. Even a brief errand for an evening espresso does not require shedding this cool, muted atmosphere. Rely on the thick weave of a dove grey brushed wool coat rather than loud contrasts.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is how you calibrate your wardrobe for low light and close proximity.",
      "tests": [
