    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Build your hardware strategy around cool metals. Choose {metal_1}, {metal_2}, or {metal_3} to establish a quiet undercurrent across your garments. High-gloss surfaces catch the light too aggressively, jarring against your muted fabrics. Reject {excluded_finish} entirely. Stick to brushed or matt textures to ensure every piece integrates seamlessly. Lift a clasp, zip, or watch case in your palm to test its mass. Surface shine distracts. Pull dictates value. A heavy, solid metal component confirms its quality and earns its keep.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select hardware that anchors your wardrobe rather than competing with it.",
