    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments build balanced proportions. They lay down your quiet undercurrent. Let accessories deliver the one refined touch. Commit to one or two strong pieces per look. Start with your handbags. Seek out full-grain leather and brushed matt hardware. Apply the ripple test. Bend the hide back on itself. The material must roll like a cool wave, smooth and unbroken. It should never crinkle or crease sharply like a coated synthetic. Run your thumb across the metal clasps. They must feel heavy and dense, absorbing the light rather than flashing it back. Leave rigid, hollow bags on the shelf. Require thick skins that drape naturally under their own weight.",
      "sectionIntro": "Audit your accessories strictly to ensure they anchor your silhouette and ground your materials.",
