    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Treat scarves as your method for establishing the required quiet undercurrent. Execute the drop test when assessing any piece. Gather a length of deep teal or inky navy silk in your fist, then release it. The material must collapse into a fluid, heavy puddle immediately. If it holds its rigid shape, leave it on the shelf. Light plays tricks, but the downward pull of thread never falters. Rely on this physical evidence to select an accessory that delivers exactly one refined touch while preserving balanced proportions. A fine wool scarf in a cool dove grey, finished with a strictly matt surface, anchors your silhouette without adding unnecessary bulk.",
