    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Quiet luxury requires strict adherence to low-contrast, tonal repeats. Anchor your tailored garments in subtle woven grids. Let your fluid pieces take their motifs from faint, organic lines. Keep your balanced proportions intact by selecting {recommended_pattern_1} or {recommended_pattern_2} in cool, matt finishes. Apply the dusk test to every piece before buying. View the fabric in dim evening light. The design must settle into a shifting, tactile surface rather than glaring back at you. Base your decisions entirely on this fading illumination. Pass over harsh graphics. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} on the rail. They disrupt your steady quiet undercurrent and destroy the visual calm.",
      "sectionIntro": "Pattern demands strict policing to keep your wardrobe functional and entirely deliberate.",
