    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "To keep your finish muted, utilise the twilight check. Drape a garment featuring {recommended_pattern_1} across a dim room just as the natural light fades. Step back. A successful print loses its sharp edges in the shadows. It must blur into a cool, shifting surface rather than a stark geometry. Maintain balanced proportions by ensuring the individual motifs merge seamlessly into the base cloth. If the shapes remain aggressively legible from ten paces, leave the piece on the hanger. Allow the deepening shadows to expose the true nature of a design.",
