  "venus_pisces__moon_gemini__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "weightless layers + light movement + one pearl of light",
    "closing": "Listen to the physical feedback of the cloth as you navigate the changing atmosphere, trusting that your true baseline relies entirely on weightless layers + light movement + one pearl of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Let your hands assess the cool surface of the fabric before you check the mirror. Versatility demands a wardrobe that breathes with your shifting environment. Your formula is weightless layers + light movement + one pearl of light. Picture a translucent silk tunic drifting over fine gauge ribbed knitwear, catching the air as you turn. Anchor the combination at the collarbone with a single luminous drop suspended on a fine chain. Combine matt and polished textures freely to keep the look alive. If the outfit feels stiff or static, take it off.\n\nCurate your collection methodically over time. Dress swiftly each morning by trusting your atmospheric instincts. When evaluating a new piece, rely on the flight test. Toss the garment lightly from your hands. Watch the descent. If it plummets in a rigid heap, discard it. It lacks the essential mobility your system requires. If it catches the current, floats briefly, and folds softly onto the bed, keep it. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your structural logic, the physical standard every garment must meet before it touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the flight test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "To construct weightless layers, source materials that breathe and shift. Your foundation relies on a cool palette and textiles that refuse to restrict motion. For shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation, seek out {texture_good_1}. Build close-to-body base layers from {texture_good_2} to guarantee sharp lines and light movement. Select {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Pick {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. Always perform a drop check in the shop. Release the garment over your forearm. Fabric finishes deceive the eye. Gravity provides the truth. If the textile settles gently, buy it. If it lands heavy, drop it. Prioritise the fibres below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to read the weight and weave of a fabric before you try it on.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
        },
        {
