    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette runs strictly cool. Build the foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Bring in {core_colour_3} when you need a white substitute, and anchor the edges with {core_colour_4} as your structural dark neutral. Drop in {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent. Deploy the relief tone solely as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green without hesitation. When the pace of a day accelerates, watch for the hard shell trap. Do not reach for armour, technical jackets, or stiff utility outerwear. Rigid fabrics block the light movement your style demands. Swap the shell for a brushed cotton top that adapts instantly and holds you besides.",
