    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} immediately. Squeeze a sleeve in your fist. If the material crinkles sharply or feels rigid, it will disrupt your physical ease. Test every piece by holding it from the shoulder seam. If the shape caves inwards and sags lifelessly toward the floor, leave it on the rail. Steer clear of {texture_bad_2} entirely. The physical tell is a brittle, stiff resistance against your bare forearm. This harsh surface traps heat and refuses to breathe. Anything with a high-gloss sheen distracts from your focal point of a single luminous accessory. Insist on cool, matt finishes instead. Decline {texture_bad_3} when it clings aggressively. A cheap weave always betrays itself through poor drape, regardless of its appearance on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify and reject the materials that fail against your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your sweet spot lives in the tension between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Pair them to establish depth. To check a new piece, lift it by the collar and drop it onto a wooden table. Watch the way it lands. If the cloth surrenders into a flat puddle, walk away. You require materials that remember their own shape. Anchor this structure by combining {texture_good_1} with a cool, matt finish.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your core pairings by observing how materials behave under gravity.",
      "tests": [
