    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep the temperature rigorously cool. Anchor your foundation in {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, and {core_colour_3}. Reach for {core_colour_4} instead of blinding tones. Inject {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} precisely when you want a focal point. Treat your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to provide breathing room. Pass over hot saturated red, stark optic white, and harsh neon. Creating hidden depth relies on clear boundaries. Rely on your eye to gauge these precise limits. Watch for the comfort drift. If you soften every element too far, you end up in pure loungewear. Stop the slide by restoring exactly one tailored edge. Carry a rigid leather tote, wear a trouser with a crisp crease, or choose a jacket with a proper rolled lapel.",
