    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, weightless layers lead your approach. Silk shells under brushed wool blazers establish a quiet luxury that speaks through movement, not volume. Concealed depth supports this structure. A deep teal silk lining or a complex weave in a dove grey trouser does the work quietly. A single point of cool metal or a pale stone completes the uniform. Apply the pharmacy test to every item you consider for the office. If you cannot stand in a slow queue at the pharmacy in a pair of tailored trousers without longing for your pyjamas, leave them on the hanger. True luxury demands complete physical ease. Look for full-grain leather bags that sit softly on the shoulder and cashmere knits that breathe.",
