  "venus_pisces__moon_sagittarius__water_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "weightless layers + fast movement + one pearl of light",
    "closing": "Dress by touch, trusting your hands to find weightless layers + fast movement + one pearl of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Look for garments with a muted, matt surface that feel like cool water slipping through your fingers. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. If a piece feels rigid or thick against your skin, drop it and walk away. Apply the host test to every new purchase. Ask whether an item serves as a generous host that links your current collection together, or if it behaves as a difficult guest demanding entirely new outfits. Build your wardrobe slowly and symmetrically, but dress each morning with fast, fluid momentum.\n\nYour decisions must anchor firmly to your formula: weightless layers + fast movement + one pearl of light. Picture a fine-gauge knit slipping effortlessly over a smooth underlayer, paired with wide-leg trousers that ripple when you step. This combination ensures nothing clings or catches. Finish the structure with a single piece of reflective hardware at the neck or wrist. Trust your hands. Pick up every potential purchase and bunch the fabric in your fists. If it lacks an instant, liquid drape, leave it on the hanger.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish the physical rules that dictate everything you will ever wear.",
      "tests": [
        "the host test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe through touch. To achieve weightless layers, pass every garment through the melt test. Crush the cloth in your fist. It must dissolve into your palm without fighting back. If it feels stiff, leave it on the rail. Hunt for {texture_good_1} for slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight. Source {texture_good_2} for jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight. Require {texture_good_3} for dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth. Finish with {texture_good_4} for unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge. These materials build a cool, matt, muted foundation. Focus on the ranked fabrics below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to filter the rails before your eyes make a decision.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Washed silk",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "slips and blouses softened until the sheen turns to candlelight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cloud-soft lambswool",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "jumpers and cardigans that shelter without weight"
        },
        {
          "name": "Heavy silk crepe",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "dresses that trace the body with fluid, hidden depth"
        },
        {
          "name": "Boiled wool",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "unstructured protective coats that stay soft at every edge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed alpaca",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "enveloping winter coats and oversized cardigans"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fluid modal jersey",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers that follow the body without ever gripping it"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed cotton flannel",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "shirts and loungewear that feel like a remembered embrace"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Check the drape of {texture_bad_1} against your bare arm. If it feels like a rigid shell, it blocks fast movement. Leave it behind. Assess the memory of {texture_bad_2}. Clench a handful of the material tightly. When you open your fingers, the cloth should collapse back into a soft puddle. If it holds a stiff crease or springs back like plastic, it fails the standard. Reject {texture_bad_3} the moment you grab it. A harsh, gritty surface traps shadows and entirely breaks the effect of one pearl of light. Rely on tactile feedback over the label.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject materials that fight your body or disrupt your silhouette.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your tactile baseline pairs {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Find this exact calibration in {texture_good_1}. Test every new piece by dropping it onto a table. Watch the structure fail. The textile must pool like liquid water. If the fabric props itself up or forms rigid peaks, abandon the purchase. Gravity exposes the truth about a weave. You require absolute structural surrender to achieve fast movement. Stick exclusively to cool, matt textiles that absorb light. The cloth must yield the second you bend an elbow. Let the drape do the work.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical tension between your primary textiles.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is strictly cool. Construct the base using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_3} for your weightless layers. Rely on {core_colour_2} for structural shaping. Use {core_colour_4} as a bright substitute neutral to preserve a muted finish. Keep {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a solitary, deliberate accent. Deploy your relief tone sparingly as a soft note to break dense blocks. Pass over hard black, harsh neon, and heavy earth brown. Beware the all-matt sink. Stacking thick, dense shades creates a heavy mass that drags down the silhouette. Lift it immediately. Place a {core_colour_4} washed silk layer at the collar, add one piece of polished leather, or bring in your relief tone.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your palette as a structural tool, choosing shades for the precise visual weight they carry.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Dove grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Inky navy",
          "role": "structural_dark"
        },
        {
          "name": "Deep teal",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Oyster",
          "role": "white_substitute"
        },
        {
          "name": "Pale aqua",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Smoked mauve",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Faded rose",
          "role": "accent"
        },
        {
          "name": "Deep berry",
          "role": "accent"
        },
        {
          "name": "Soft oatmeal",
