    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Start your work uniform with honest fabric. Begin with worsted wool or crisp cotton poplin in stark navy. Use these solid items to set a cool temperature. Expand with weightless layers in icy grey merino or technical nylon to adapt to shifting environments. Finish the sequence with one pearl of light. Add a mixed metal watch or a polished silver pin to disrupt the matt surface of the wool. Maintain a rigid baseline across your entire schedule. Reviewing contracts at a desk demands the identical standard as a formal client briefing. Do not hoard premium garments exclusively for meetings.",
      "sectionIntro": "Focus your work wardrobe by leading with your primary styling element.",
      "tests": [
