    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "You hold the freedom to mix {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} across your collection. Execute this mixed approach while maintaining a strictly cool temperature. Avoid tarnished brass, beaten copper, and artificially weathered accents. Pre-aged hardware registers as visual noise against a modern aesthetic. Secure your garments instead with sleek silver, bright white gold, and reflective chrome. Reject any {excluded_finish} details that dull this sharp impact. When evaluating a new zip or buckle, lift the object to assess its density. A gleaming finish means nothing without internal mass. Dense, solid metal grounds your weightless layers and provides exactly one pearl of light.",
