    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Construct your weightless layers using honest fabric. Your accessories must then step in to provide that vital one pearl of light. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Apply your personal one-signal test to every item. If an object throws competing textures and shiny hardware at the eye simultaneously, drop it. It must transmit a solitary, clear intention. Begin this practice with silk scarves. Seek out a cool crepe de chine square with a flat, matt finish. Scrunch the textile in your fist to check its spring. Fingers grasp the real character of a thread long before a mirror can.",
