    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Evaluate fine jewellery with the same rigorous standard. Hold a thin chain in your closed hand. Ask yourself if it delivers exactly one clear message against a backdrop of honest fabric. A piece must not compete with itself. Mix metals freely. Thread thin strands of cool silver beside slender lengths of gold. Let a highly polished ring sit next to a brushed pendant. Your strategy relies on balance. Combine contrasting finishes, ensuring each item remains distinctly delicate. If a bracelet tries to offer heavy texture and a complicated shape, put it down. Trust your immediate tactile feedback. Keep the metal components light so they stack cleanly over weightless layers.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your secondary accessories by isolating their core physical properties.",
      "rankedItems": [
