    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Pick up {texture_bad_1} and snap your hand forward at the joint. If the textile drops like lead or resists the gesture, discard it immediately. You need materials that yield. Avoid {texture_bad_2} completely. Run your thumb over the weave. If it catches on your skin or lacks a warm touch, it fails. A stiff piece of {texture_bad_3} might hold its shape on a hanger. Put it on your shoulders. If it restricts your reach, take it off. Build a foundation of textiles that drape well, leaving room to apply one theatrical finish to complete the silhouette.",
      "sectionIntro": "Identify the materials that actively fight your body.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your tactile sweet spot sits exactly between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Anchor a {texture_good_1} coat over your shoulders to evaluate the weight. Look for light movement in the sleeves. Flick your hand sideways to test how the cuff catches the air. A stiff weave will stall instantly. A responsive material will ripple and drop back against your skin. Let your fingers detect this kinetic response. Build warm combinations by layering a matt sweater over a smooth shirt. Weight dictates how the piece hangs. Tension dictates how it moves.",
      "sectionIntro": "Isolate your core texture pairing to anchor your wardrobe in physical reality.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep your foundation warm. Trust this temperature rule unconditionally. Build your base from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. These are your reliable daily tools. Add {core_colour_3} for dark structure and {core_colour_4} as an earthy neutral. Your wardrobe formula demands expansive colour. Execute this by deploying {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent against those deeper bases. Employ your relief tone, a soft note used sparingly, to break up solid blocks. Pass over stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel completely. Avoid the trap of ungrounded prettiness. An outfit built entirely from pale, soft tones reads charming at breakfast and forgettable by noon. Fix this by injecting a solid foundation. Add a sharply tailored jacket, a structured flat shoe, or a dense {core_colour_3} garment placed right where the eye lands first. This dark structural piece secures the lighter tones and stops the outfit from floating away.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every garment against this precise palette to build a cohesive and functional wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bitter chocolate",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Dark mahogany",
          "role": "warm_base"
