        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories finalize your styling sequence. Secure the close drape. Add mobile layers. Finish with one warm point of light. Enforce a strict rule of one or two strong pieces per look. Start with handbags. Demand full-grain leather finished with brushed matt hardware. Apply the drop test before making a purchase. Release the bag gently onto a wooden counter. The leather must settle and pool with a quiet, fluid weight. If the structure clatters rigidly against the surface, leave it on the shelf. Genuine material acts like a liquid, never a rigid box.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce strict material standards when selecting your final additions.",
