    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Scarves act as essential mobile layers. Seek out pure silk or fine wool. Always insist on a matt finish. Test every piece before purchasing it. Hold the fabric at shoulder height and release it over a table. Watch how it falls. A correct piece catches the air and drifts down slowly. If it hits the surface like a heavy stone, put it back. This is the float test. A warm scarf must feel alive as it descends. Let the behaviour of the descending cloth make your final decision.",
