    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Pattern is texture made visible. Restrict pattern in tailored garments strictly to the weave. Fluid pieces carry the printed motifs. Maintain a low tonal contrast across every warm colour. Build the foundation with close drape. Let the pattern live solely within mobile layers. Apply the underwater test to every printed garment. The design must read like light moving on the seabed. It must never read like harsh signage. Seek out {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} that blur subtly as you move. Drop {avoid_pattern_1} immediately. The edge is too sharp. Pass over {avoid_pattern_2} completely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control the visual noise of your garments by filtering every print through strict physical tests.",
