    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Stand ten feet away from a {recommended_pattern_1} garment and squint. The print must blur into an ambient field of warm shadow, mimicking organic texture. If you can clearly read distinct shapes or rigid geometry at this distance, leave the piece on the rack. Graphic sharpness fights the physical reality of close drape. Successful printing relies on illegibility. A strong motif melts under scrutiny. It must blend naturally into the background as you add mobile layers over it, acting as a textured neutral rather than street signage.",
