  "venus_taurus__moon_cancer__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "structure + hidden depth + a touch of quiet depth",
    "closing": "Navigate your wardrobe by physical weight and tactile truth, demanding that every choice delivers structure + hidden depth + a touch of quiet depth.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your compass is weight and reserve. Run your hands over a garment and assess its physical density. It must feel substantial, grounding you within your own space rather than projecting outward. Build your wardrobe slowly, selecting single garments over months, then wear them instantly. If an item demands attention, put it back. You require garments that maintain a strict boundary. Look for a matt finish that absorbs light. Keep the overall temperature warm, relying on heavy fibres that hold their architectural shape.\n\nYour exact equation is structure + hidden depth + a touch of quiet depth. Picture a rigidly tailored overcoat worn over a fine-gauge knit that only reveals its complex weave up close, finished with a heavy, unpolished leather document case. Every choice must pass the melt test. Put the garment on and stand still. The piece must dissolve into your own warm, self-contained architecture. If it feels like an imposition sitting on top of your frame, or if it requires constant adjustment, it fails. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.",
      "sectionIntro": "This is your foundational strategy for evaluating and acquiring every piece you touch.",
      "tests": [
        "the melt test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe from materials that deliver structure and a touch of quiet depth. Trust your hands to guide you. When you handle a new piece, rub the material between your thumb and forefinger. If the surface resists your touch or feels synthetic or catches slightly, leave the garment on the rail. Seek out {texture_good_1} for heavy winter layers that compress and spring back instantly. Look for {texture_good_3} in your tailored coats to lock in clean, sharp lines that last for years. Use {texture_good_4} for blouses that bring liquid movement to the inside of an outfit. Anchor these garments with heavy belts cut from {texture_good_2} that will soften and patinate with age. Keep all finishes warm and matt. Target these top options.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise materials that serve your style.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
        {
          "name": "Suede",
          "role": "rank 5",
          "useCase": "shoes and accessories with quiet matt texture"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine merino",
          "role": "rank 6",
          "useCase": "base layers soft against the skin and resilient through washes"
        },
        {
          "name": "Linen",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "warmer-weather pieces whose natural wrinkle reads as authentic"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "You are cultivating hidden depth. Poor textiles reveal everything at first glance. Inspect {texture_bad_1} for an unnatural surface. If it catches on dry skin or reflects a harsh glare instead of a warm, matt finish, leave it on the rail. Assess {texture_bad_2} by crushing the cloth in your fist. If the material pushes back against your grip or produces a faint squeak when rubbed between your fingers, drop it. Avoid {texture_bad_3} entirely. It creates a stiff shell rather than a living layer. Rely on gravity and friction to make your decisions. Poor construction always reveals itself through a lack of substance.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject cheap materials before you even check the care label.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Anchor your style by pairing {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. This combination delivers the strict structure you require. Test every piece by gathering the fabric tightly in your palm. Drop any material that fights your hand. If a surface rubs with an unnatural slickness or repels your grip, walk away. Rely entirely on warm, matt textures that absorb light. Introduce {texture_good_1} to ground the mix and build self-contained weight. Substance proves worth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your material pairings provides your style with its literal foundation.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette operates strictly on a warm temperature. Construct your base from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Connect these elements using {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Choose {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent. Deploy a soft note sparingly to break up heavy blocks of tone. Pass over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels immediately. Beware the comfort slide. Soften every element completely and your garments collapse into shapeless leisurewear. Counteract this error by establishing one distinct boundary. Pair your yielding fibres with a rigid collar, a sharply pressed leg, or a stiffened leather holdall. This singular tailored line provides the hidden depth your presentation demands.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your colours as a strict operating system to keep your garments focused.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Rich toffee",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Taupe",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Stone grey",
          "role": "warm_cool_bridge"
        },
        {
          "name": "Soft cream",
          "role": "white_substitute"
        },
        {
          "name": "Olive",
          "role": "earthy_green"
        },
        {
          "name": "Moss green",
          "role": "earthy_green"
        },
        {
