      "text": "Test any prospective garment against your bare skin. A proper textile stays temperate. {texture_bad_1} fails by immediately trapping a clammy layer of heat. It ruins your required close drape, replacing it with stiff, unyielding static. {texture_bad_2} gives itself away with a harsh, brittle finish that catches on your hands. Grasp {texture_bad_3} in your palm. It will feel hollow and springy, lacking the dense drop of a natural fibre. Let your own touch reject these synthetics. Leave them on the rail and insist on pure weaves with a rich, warm, matt finish.",
