          "name": "Brushed cotton flannel",
          "role": "rank 7",
          "useCase": "shirts and loungewear that feel like a remembered embrace"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject any material that competes for attention. Avoid {texture_bad_1} completely. Pick it up and feel the harsh surface resist your grip. It lacks a touch of quiet depth and creates a rigid barrier. Check the porosity of {texture_bad_2}. Press the weave against your face and exhale sharply. If the yarns choke the airflow and trap warm moisture on your skin, drop the piece. True luxury breathes. Steer clear of {texture_bad_3} when it presents a flat, unyielding matt finish. You require textiles that yield. Rely on touch over sight. Photographs deceive, but physical stiffness always reveals the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the physical failures that compromise your comfort and style.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to establish your baseline. This exact pairing builds soft structure around your frame. Layer {texture_good_1} over the top to create blurred edges where the two pieces overlap. The gentle friction introduces a touch of quiet depth to a matt surface. Always verify airflow before purchasing. Force a breath through the taut textile. The current must pass through the weave without resistance. If the heat rebounds into your face, leave the item behind. You require discreet, porous layers that hold a warm microclimate close to your body while releasing excess heat.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your fabric pairings to build presence without stiffness.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette temperature is strictly warm. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Introduce {core_colour_3} when a piece requires a dark anchor, and rely on {core_colour_4} as an earthy grounding neutral. Select either {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} for your single deliberate accent. Deploy your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. They dilute your focus. This aesthetic relies on soft structure to communicate intent. Beware the lounge slide. Push the ease of your boiled wool and washed silk too far, and your garments devolve into pyjamas. Correct this by restoring exactly one rigid line. Bring in a distinct lapel, a trouser with a defined crease, or a firm leather bag to anchor the softness.",
      "sectionIntro": "Trust your hands and eyes to build a strictly warm foundation that serves your physical reality.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bitter chocolate",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Dark mahogany",
          "role": "warm_base"
