    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let athletic space dictate your professional choices. Tailoring must allow absolute room to breathe and pivot. A brushed wool blazer should drape with easy volume rather than binding your shoulders. Support this physical ease with structured lines and a touch of quiet depth. Matt camel and rich toffee trousers provide a grounded foundation. Anchor your cuffs with warm yellow gold. Evaluate your office garments strictly by their function. Shrug into a jacket and check the mobility across the back. If the seams dig in when you reach forward, discard it. Professional attire requires identical standards of physical comfort as your casual wear.",
      "sectionIntro": "Let physical ease dictate your professional choices, refusing any piece that restricts your stride.",
      "tests": [
        "a farmers' market run is still a small occasion (Hearth)"
