    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, let athletic space take the lead. Dim environments require physical ease, so give your body room to flex. Reach for a rich toffee silk shirt with a generous cut, and pair it with heavy full-grain leather trousers to establish a touch of quiet depth. The warm, matt finish of the silk absorbs ambient light beautifully. Apply the Hearth test before stepping out for dinner. Sit in a low chair and observe how the fabric behaves. Use the heavy drop of the material to guide your decisions. Avoid stiff seams that pinch when you sit. Let dark camel tones complete the structured shape. Rely entirely on your own tactile comfort to verify the drape.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the shift in your formula when the room gets small.",
      "tests": [
