      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Ground your hardware in warm tones. Rely on {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} for everything from watch cases to bag zips. Highly reflective finishes cut too sharply against your soft, muted wardrobe. Anchor the look with dulled, matt surfaces to maintain a touch of quiet depth. Steer clear of {excluded_finish}. Always handle a piece of jewellery before wearing it. Evaluate the density in your palm. If a buckle feels light, hollow, or flimsy in your grip, leave it behind. Real quality carries undeniable physical presence.",
      "sectionIntro": "Hardware demands the same rigorous selection as the garments resting against your skin.",
      "tests": [
