    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Suspend every piece of {metal_1} hardware from your fingers. Visuals deceive easily, but the downward pull of a solid object provides an honest answer. A dense, heavy item brings structure and a touch of quiet depth to warm textiles. Beware the trap of high-shine lacquers. Bright reflections look excessively sharp against soft, muted layers. Fix this clash by choosing only honed or sanded surfaces. Unpolished hardware keeps your overall look cohesive. Demand flat finishes that complement your athletic space.",
