    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Apply the Soft Focus Test to any piece claiming to feature {recommended_pattern_1}. Hang the garment on a wall. Step back ten paces. Relax your eyes until the room blurs. If the print still jumps out as a distinct graphic, leave it on the rack. The right pattern will dissolve into a unified texture. This visual integration is vital. It ensures the motif respects the tailoring's inherent structure rather than fighting the seams. A perfectly muted, warm pattern also guarantees athletic space within the silhouette. It allows the fabric to move without the design distorting, introducing just a touch of quiet depth. Trust your peripheral vision to judge the fade. If the graphic stays sharp, the piece fails.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every printed fabric to a strict visual filter before it enters your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
