  "venus_virgo__moon_aries__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "precise fit + sharp edges + one meticulous detail",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on precise fit + sharp edges + one meticulous detail.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Your ultimate compass is physical precision. Trust your hands to feel how a garment is structured before you put it on. Weight does not matter if the architecture is sloppy. Look for garments that hold their shape on a hanger and feel crisp to the touch. Your entire approach rests on one rule. Memorise this formula. It is precise fit + sharp edges + one meticulous detail. Picture a tailored jacket cropped exactly at the waist, worn with trousers featuring a razor-sharp crease, finished with a single, perfectly cast cold metal closure. The proportions must lock together without requiring constant adjustment. Build your wardrobe methodically piece by piece, but adapt your outfit instantly to match your environment.\n\nMaintain this neutral baseline so your styling can pivot seamlessly. Assess every potential purchase using the seam test. Run your fingers over the interior construction. A garment fails if the shoulder seam drifts past your anatomical joint, or if the side seams twist when the fabric hangs flat. The internal architecture must map your physical boundaries flawlessly. Look for flat, reinforced stitching and clean interior binding. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Construction does not. If the seams fight your geometry, leave the item on the rack.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your physical baseline before you allow any garment into your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the seam test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your neutral, self-contained aesthetic demands fabrics that hold a precise fit without constant adjustment. Look for {texture_good_1} when building shirting with clean architectural boundaries. Use {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers that allow easy movement. Anchor your lower half with {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly. Finish the look with {texture_good_4} to build lightweight mobile outerwear. Always apply the recovery test before purchasing a new garment. Bunch a handful of the cloth tightly in your fist for ten seconds and release it. The material must bounce back instantly to retain its sharp edges. This structural integrity allows the garment to support one meticulous detail, like a crisp collar or a blind hem. Let the density of the weave steer you toward the following materials.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to identify the cloths that support your chosen structure.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
