    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, sharp edges take the lead. Crisp cotton poplin collars and worsted wool hems must cut a clean line. The overall shape remains exact to support those lines, while a single muted, matt silver buckle on a belt provides your one meticulous detail. Keep the temperature strictly neutral. Reviewing structural blueprints on a Friday morning demands the same uncompromising precise fit as a Tuesday board meeting. Do not switch personas. Pull on a fine ribbed merino sweater with rigidly constructed cuffs. Test the construction yourself. Grasp the collar and check for absolute rigidity. A self-contained approach means you dress for your own standards, ignoring outside approval.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your working hours demand rigorous execution, not a separate costume.",
      "tests": [
        "a hardware store run deserves the same clean fit as a Monday meeting (Flint)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "Low light swallows weak outlines. Let sharp edges lead in dim settings. Select garments cut close to the skeleton in soft stone worsted wool or a matt cotton poplin. Keep the hardware restricted to a silver or white gold watch casing, reflecting a low gleam rather than a loud flash. A late-night private dinner demands the same flawless precise fit as a high-profile daytime event. Provide one meticulous detail through a perfect cuff or a heavy zip. Do not rely on complicated styling to carry an outfit in the shadows. Run your fingers along the lapel. If the points hold their shape against the collarbone without collapsing, the piece is ready for the evening.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your silhouette when the lights go down.",
      "tests": [
        "a hardware store run deserves the same clean fit as a Monday meeting (Flint)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A run to the local hardware shop for screws requires uncompromising structure. You dress strictly for your own internal parameters. Rely on your immediate physical response to seams and drape. Reach for an oatmeal cotton poplin shirt and pair it with worsted wool trousers. Let a muted silver belt buckle finish the outfit. Keep your base palette perfectly neutral to guarantee complete adaptability across varying daily environments. A quick trip to the pharmacy to collect a prescription never excuses soft lines or sloppy construction. Anchor every choice to your core operating standard. Always require precise fit + sharp edges + one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your daily baseline by ignoring the occasion entirely.",
      "tests": [
        "a hardware store run deserves the same clean fit as a Monday meeting (Flint)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Confine your hardware strictly to a cool-dominant spectrum to keep the overall temperature completely neutral. Steer entirely clear of any {excluded_finish} treatments. Artificially aged hardware and hammered finishes read as visual clutter against a present-tense style. Rely instead on highly polished {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} to enforce sharp edges. Pick the garment up and evaluate the zips. A flimsy fastening will buckle and distort the garment line. Every clasp must feel cold and substantial in the palm. Heavy components guarantee a precise fit.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat hardware as the final structural component of a garment rather than an afterthought.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Your clothing demands sharp edges. Apply this standard to your jewellery. Lift a piece to evaluate its construction. Evaluate the stone through its sheer density. A solid cut of {stone_1} or {stone_3} provides the correct heft to support a self-contained aesthetic. Keep the overall temperature neutral and the surface finish matt and muted. Reject any porous or artificially weathered gems that introduce unnecessary texture. Stick to the clean surfaces of highly cut minerals framed in polished silver, white gold, platinum, or mirror chrome. Provide one meticulous detail through a single flawless ring or pendant.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware and gems by their physical density and visual clarity.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Lift every piece of {metal_1} jewellery or buckle to gauge its mass in your palm. Weight acts as your primary quality control. Avoid pitted, tarnished, and brushed vintage treatments. Such worn finishes register as messy interference against a contemporary silhouette. Keep exclusively to flawless cool metals like platinum and mirror chrome. A reflective, neutral finish underscores the sharp edges of your garments. Substantial hardware directly grounds a precise fit. Ensure every item you choose feels decidedly heavy.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply this tactile check to evaluate every fastening and metal accent before you purchase it.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your clothing establishes your precise fit and sharp edges. Accessories exist solely to supply your one meticulous detail. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Anything more dilutes the focus. Begin with a watch. Select a brushed steel case with a matt finish on a leather or steel strap. Evaluate every addition with the function test. Ask yourself if the item actively fastens, measures time, or secures a load. If the piece merely sits on the body as an ornament, take it off. Rely on tactile feedback as your compass. Icy steel and dense construction indicate true quality. Let these cool components rest against your neutral base layers without extra decoration.",
      "sectionIntro": "Accessories must serve a strict mechanical purpose, never just decorate.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Watch",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "brushed steel case, leather or steel strap, matt brushed"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Subject belts to a strict mechanical check. Pull the strap and secure the prong. The tool must anchor the garment firmly without warping under tension. If the leather stretches or the buckle jingles, leave it behind. Demand vegetable-tanned leather in a medium width to support your neutral tones. Examine the strap for sharp edges rather than thick glued borders. The hardware requires a cool metal with a matt brushed finish. A precise fit relies on structural pieces that perform their primary task flawlessly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your structural accessories by their mechanical utility before you consider their appearance.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Belts",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "vegetable-tanned leather, medium width, matt brushed buckle"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Assess your bags through their architecture. Choose a canvas and leather tote or a structured briefcase with matt silver hardware. The metal should reflect a neutral temperature without catching the light. Judge the item blindly by its feel. Pick up the bag and carry it. Feel for sharp edges on the leather handle and a precise fit against your hip. Before leaving the house, run through a practical assessment. Open the main compartment, retrieve your keys, and close the clasp. If you wrestle with the zip or feel the canvas collapsing, abandon the piece. A bag must serve your mechanics seamlessly and act as your one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your daily bags entirely on their structural integrity and operational ease.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "canvas and leather tote or briefcase, matt hardware"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Your pattern contrast must adapt to the garment. Tailored pieces in worsted wool take their character from low-contrast, woven-in micro-motifs. Fluid layers like a technical nylon overshirt can carry slightly wider geometry. Rely on the strict lines of {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} to support a precise fit. Use {recommended_pattern_3} and {recommended_pattern_4} purely as deliberate accents. Assess every new print with the distance check. Toss the item over your chair and step back an arm's length and a half. At that range, the motif must vanish into a clean texture of matt, neutral colour. Grip the weave firmly. Your fingers will feel when a busy print is trying to mask cheap construction. Skip {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. They blur what must remain sharp edges.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your visual volume by testing how patterns resolve at a distance and under your hands.",
      "tests": [
        "the desk test (read as clean texture at arm's length and a half)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Use a visual shrinking technique to assess your prints. Hang the shirt across the room and walk away. From a distance, a {recommended_pattern_1} must dissolve into a matt, solid field. If the design remains clearly visible, leave the item on the rail. Your wardrobe relies on a precise fit to build structure. A high-contrast motif disrupts that architecture and softens your sharp edges. Rely on a neutral palette to keep the focus inward. Up close, the warp and weft show their complexity. From afar, they blend into a flat wash of {core_colour_1}. This ensures the pattern serves as your one meticulous detail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use the desk test to lock down your pattern scale.",
      "tests": [
        "the desk test (read as clean texture at arm's length and a half)"
      ]
    }
  },
  "venus_virgo__moon_capricorn__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "precise fit + softness + one meticulous detail",
    "closing": "Always trust your physical instincts to evaluate every garment, demanding an unwavering commitment to precise fit + softness + one meticulous detail.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the structural integrity of your garments. Your physical instinct is your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not. Look for clothes that adapt to your movement without losing their shape. Build your wardrobe systematically over time, but deploy your outfits fast each morning. Your foundation relies on a strict equation. It is precise fit + softness + one meticulous detail. Picture a sharply tailored trouser cut from a fluid, yielding fabric, worn with a fine-gauge knit, and finished with a single, perfectly calibrated closure at the waist. The tension between structure and ease creates a completely self-contained system.\n\nApply the half-mirror test to every new acquisition. Stand close to the glass and check if the garment respects your physical boundaries. If the collar fights your jawline or the shoulder dictates your posture, put the piece back. Keep your overall palette strictly neutral and ensure your finishes remain permanently matt. Your jewellery strategy must lean cool and functional. Avoid anything that demands constant adjustment. Trust your hands when examining a seam. If the construction feels rigid or hollow, reject it immediately. Your clothes must serve as an adaptable baseline, never an interruption.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise these operating principles before you evaluate another piece of clothing.",
      "tests": [
        "the half-mirror test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your uniform requires a strict balance between precise fit and softness. Trust your hands to verify this tension in the shop. Pick up a garment cut from {texture_good_1} for shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation. Snap the hem sharply to apply the wrist-flick test. If the fabric drops sluggishly instead of settling with a crisp break, leave it on the rack. Seek out {texture_good_2} for close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement. Ground your lower half using {texture_good_3} for trousers that drape cleanly and resist creasing through a long day. Finish the exterior with {texture_good_4} for lightweight mobile outerwear that blocks wind and weighs little. Let the actual drape of the textile guide your purchases. Target the materials below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select fabrics that marry structural integrity with complete physical autonomy.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
