      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is neutral. Build your foundation entirely on {core_colour_1}, {core_colour_2}, {core_colour_3}, and {core_colour_4}. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent. Treat the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Pass over neon brights, glitter finishes, and sugary pastels. Beware the trap of ungrounded lightness. An entirely pale outfit reads charming then forgettable by lunch. Fix this by giving the look a heavy focal point. Add a structurally tailored blazer, a firm leather flat, or the {core_colour_1} garment worn where the eye lands first. Always demand a precise fit to give these muted tones an undeniable physical shape. Select only matt finishes to reinforce this strict approach.",
