    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let precise fit dictate your workwear. Start with worsted wool trousers or a crisp cotton poplin shirt in a neutral palette like soft stone or oatmeal. These pieces establish a firm boundary. Use supple materials to ease the structure. A fine ribbed merino crew neck absorbs the rigidity of an office day. Finish the look with one meticulous detail. A matt silver watch case or a concealed button placket provides focus. Test every item by asking if you could climb three flights of stairs without adjusting your waistband. Moving through the building demands the exact same yielding standard as sitting in a Tuesday meeting. Discard anything that feels stiff or restrictive.",
