    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject any material that fails in your grip. Pick up a piece of {texture_bad_1} and notice its slick, hollow drape. Conduct an airflow check. Force your breath directly through the weave. If the pressure rebounds against your lips, drop the garment immediately. Leave {texture_bad_2} on the rack when it catches on your cuticles or feels rigid in the palm. True style requires relentless scrutiny. You must verify the integrity of the fibre before checking for one meticulous detail in the seams. Discard any item finished with stiff, matt {texture_bad_3}. Rely entirely on your own skin to filter out synthetics.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to spot poor quality before a garment even touches your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Build your core combinations around {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Let a piece of {texture_good_1} sit on your collarbones. Notice what happens to your shoulders and ribs when you pull it on. If your lungs expand and your muscles drop, keep it. If you tighten up, take it off. That bodily reaction is all the proof you need. Combine a neutral structured garment with a softer inner layer to achieve a precise fit. A matt surface keeps the visual volume low. Let the shape do the heavy lifting.",
      "sectionIntro": "Lock in your signature texture combinations by paying attention to how they physically alter your posture.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette temperature is neutral. Build your foundation with {core_colour_1}, bridging into {core_colour_2} and {core_colour_4}. Pull {core_colour_3} strictly when you need a stark substitute for white. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} solely as your single deliberate accent. Apply your relief tone sparingly as a soft note. Always reject neon brights, hard jet black, and glitter finishes. Beware the swaddling trap. Piling on endless volumes of cloudy grey deletes your shape completely, reducing heavy silk crepe to a formless mound. Correct this error immediately. Reclaim a sharp boundary, fold a crisp collar, taper a sleeve, or drop a cool dominant metal pendant at the collarbone. This discipline guarantees a precise fit.",
