    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, a precise fit leads your decisions. A boiled wool jacket must anchor perfectly on your shoulders before you evaluate the sensory comfort of its washed silk lining. Build your professional uniform around a neutral palette like pewter grey, ensuring the cloth takes the structural strain. Apply your own uncompromising baseline. Carrying files down the hall in soft lambswool demands the exact same standard of construction as presenting a formal review in heavy silk crepe. Never downgrade your clothing for a routine task. Grip the fabric to judge its density. If the mass feels insubstantial, leave the garment behind. Finish the look with a matt platinum watch, letting the cool metal sit quietly on your wrist.",
      "sectionIntro": "Mastering your professional uniform requires absolute discipline in cut and cloth.",
      "tests": [
