    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim lighting, sight steps back and touch takes over. Let sensory comfort lead. When selecting evening pieces, discard anything rigid. Choose fluid washed silk trousers or a dense lambswool knit in a neutral pewter grey. Maintain your fundamental rule behind closed doors. Reading alone by the fire requires the exact same structural integrity as a public dinner. A poorly cut sleeve remains unacceptable in any context. Always demand a precise fit across the shoulders. Anchor the look with the muted finish of a matt platinum ring or a single cool sapphire to catch the low light. Test the material against your bare wrist. If it scratches or restricts, take it off.",
