      "text": "Your hardware strategy leans entirely into cool tones. Ground your pieces with {metal_1} and {metal_2}. Because your palette temperature remains neutral, these cool metals provide quiet structure rather than stark contrast. A mirror-like polish creates a harsh glare. High-shine hardware fractures the visual unity of subdued fibres. Specify brushed or matt textures to meld the metal cleanly into the cloth, and bypass any {excluded_finish}. When evaluating a zip or watch case, lift the piece in your bare hand to test its density. Visual impressions deceive, but the steady gravity of a dense cast is absolute. Rely on that solid drop into your palm to verify its quality. Let a weighty {metal_3} buckle do the work of securing a precise fit.",
