    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold the {metal_1} cuff in your open palm to gauge its heft. An unyielding weight confirms the integrity of the piece. A flimsy clasp or a hollow chain compromises your sensory comfort instantly. Only keep jewellery that feels cold and substantial. Avoid highly polished, reflective chrome. A gleaming finish creates a sharp glare that interrupts the quiet harmony of a neutral palette. Prevent this harsh contrast by sourcing strictly unpolished, matt surfaces. Let the dense, heavy metal ground the precise fit of your garments.",
