    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Start by guaranteeing crisp separation. Establish your sharp edges. Finish the overall geometry with one clever contrast. Enforce a strict limit of one or two distinctive pieces per look. Begin your selection with silk scarves. Pick up a crepe de chine square. Assess the matt surface. Rely on your tactile response to judge the material. Trust the physical drop of the cloth. Execute the last-look test before leaving. Examine your reflection. If the accessory disrupts the cool temperature rather than clarifying the silhouette, remove it immediately.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your accessories by focusing on precision, applying strict limits to finalise your silhouette.",
      "rankedItems": [
