    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Let tailored garments hold strict geometric motifs. Assign fluid pieces a softer, dispersed scale. Your pattern strategy remains highly adaptable. Scale the visual contrast up for immediate impact or drop it to a tonal whisper depending on the room. Enforce crisp separation by placing a structured {recommended_pattern_1} directly next to a solid {core_colour_1} boundary. Introduce a subtle {recommended_pattern_2} to build depth, offering one clever contrast. Apply the arm's-length test to every new item. From a distance, the piece must resolve into a calm, continuous block of cool colour. Step closer to verify the exactness of the woven thread. Pass over anything that relies on scattered designs, muddy proportions, or applied inks. Avoid {avoid_pattern_1} entirely. It blurs the visual borders you require. Reject {avoid_pattern_2} the moment it disrupts the sharp edges of your overall geometry. Trust your physical read of the fabric.",
      "sectionIntro": "Deploy pattern strictly as a structural tool to establish and enforce your visual boundaries.",
