      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Apply the distance blur test to {recommended_pattern_1}. Hang the garment across the room and step back. At three metres, the visual noise must dissolve entirely into a flat field of cool colour. This optical flattening provides the strict grounding needed to ensure crisp separation between your layers. Now close the distance. The print must snap into focus, revealing distinct geometry with sharp edges. If the motif remains a muddy wash from afar or lacks absolute precision up close, drop the hanger. You require dual utility. A functional pattern acts as a solid foundation at a distance, while delivering one clever contrast straight to your own eye.",
