    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Crush a piece of {texture_bad_1} in your fist and release it. This proves its resilience. If the material drops flat and limp, leave it on the rail. It provides no enduring structure. Genuine fibres retain a warm memory of their shape. Avoid {texture_bad_2} for the exact same reason. It feels thin against the skin and clings rigidly. Test {texture_bad_3} by letting it hang over a chair. If it slides off rapidly instead of maintaining a slow drape, it fails. Rely on your grip to catch this flaw. Appearances deceive.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every new material to a ruthless physical evaluation before it ever touches your skin.",
