      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your ideal intersection combines {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Select {texture_good_1} to build your mobile layers. Gather the textile in your arms and release it onto a bed. Observe the resulting form. If it creates stiff peaks, leave it behind. The fabric must pool into a soft liquid puddle. Let your fingers dictate the decision. Photographs offer false promises. Physical interaction reveals reality. Keep every finish warm and matt to complete the equation.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical tests that separate your true pieces from mere approximations.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Build your foundation on {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Anchor them with the darker grounding of {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Together, these build a reliably warm base. Deploy {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} strictly as a single deliberate accent. Treat the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to break up heavy blocks of colour. Pass over stark optic white, harsh neon, and icy pastel. Watch for the swaddling trap. Stacking shapeless matt garments dissolves your frame entirely into a soft blur. Break the haze by returning a sharp boundary to the body. Turn up a crisp collar, fold a clean cuff, or place a polished pendant right at the neckline. This anchors your mobile layers and restores clear intent.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assess your palette as a disciplined toolkit, building heat from the foundation up.",
