    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} the second you touch it. Feel how it traps heat on the skin and stiffens at the elbow. Discard {texture_bad_2} the moment it scratches your neck. Check the resilience of every cloth before bringing it home. Squeeze the yardage forcefully and observe the release. If the material stays crumpled and dead, leave it on the rail. Trust your hands over the shop mirrors. You require adaptable textiles that bounce back seamlessly. When clothes fail this test, they demand constant attention. A successful outfit recedes, letting your one sentimental keepsake hold focus without distraction.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to identify the materials that will actively fight your body.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to construct your core outfit. Layer a matt, cool {texture_good_1} under structured cotton. This exact combination delivers the soft shelter your routine demands. Assess the tension of the weave physically. Bunch the fabric together, then let it drop. Watch closely as you release your grip. If sharp creases remain in the material, walk away. You need clothes that snap back to their original shape immediately. This physical reaction tells you the material holds enough tension to stay sharp all day. Rely on this fast check to screen out weak fabrics.",
      "sectionIntro": "Find your optimal material pairing by testing how every cloth reacts under pressure.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your spectrum remains permanently cool. Construct a base from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Use {core_colour_3} as your strict contrast point, and deploy {core_colour_4} for rigid grounding. Introduce light movement with a single shot of {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2}. Treat your relief tone with extreme caution. Assign it solely as a soft note to break a dense block of dark. Pass over mustard, rust, and warm olive green entirely. Watch for the flat void. Piling pale tones at an identical value creates a blurry mass rather than a minimal base. Rescue this error immediately. Anchor the base with a {core_colour_4} jacket or a sharp {accent_colour_1} collar. Force a sudden shift to fine ribbed merino to restore the missing depth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your palette by enforcing a strict hierarchy of tones, keeping your foundation rigid so your accents can work.",
