    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, soft shelter leads. Reach for a fine ribbed merino top in stark navy. Evaluate the knit by rolling the cuffs to your elbow. Rely on tactile feedback over visual impressions. The fabric must fall cleanly over your ribs without gripping. Reading on the sofa does not mean surrendering your shape to a heavy fleece. Keep the outline distinct but yielding. Finish with a single muted silver ring. Let the matt, cool metal sit flat on your hand. Test the drape of an icy grey worsted wool trouser when seated. It must drop straight over a leather loafer. Dress strictly for your own internal parameters.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your shape and materials when preparing for low-light, intimate spaces.",
      "tests": [
