    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Base your hardware strategy on a strictly cool foundation. Limit your selections to {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3}. You need these hard materials to cut through your soft shelter. Reject any piece treated to look old or weathered. Hammered textures and faux-antique patinas create unnecessary noise, disrupting a modern finish. Correct this error by demanding pristine, highly reflective surfaces. Anchor the light movement of your garments with solid, dense buckles and zips. Evaluate the density of each fastening directly. A light clasp feels hollow and compromises the garment. Protect your boundary by eliminating any {excluded_finish} hardware.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as the deliberate structural anchor for your clothing.",
      "tests": [
