    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Lift the piece off the counter. Appearance deceives, but mass never lies. Rely on this tactile assessment to gauge true quality. Even when your garments prioritise light movement, your hardware must feel strictly substantial. Keep the temperature cool. Avoid artificially aged metals, hammered copper, and antiqued brass. They introduce visual clutter to a self-contained aesthetic. Anchor your collection with {metal_1}, white gold, platinum, or mirror chrome. A matt finish functions well here, provided the underlying material carries undeniable weight.",
