    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Source belts in a medium width cut from smooth vegetable-tanned leather. Check the hardware carefully. You need a cool, brushed silver buckle with a flat, matt face. Assess the utility of the belt in motion. Thread it through the loops of icy grey worsted wool trousers and pace the floor. If the leather binds or the metal catches reflections, reject it immediately. The piece must hold the garment silently, permitting uninterrupted light movement as you step. A belt is a practical tool, designed strictly to secure the boundary of any soft shelter.",
