    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Pick up a canvas and leather tote or a structured briefcase. Inspect the metal fixtures. Ensure every buckle and zipper features cool, muted matt hardware. Assess the physical geometry. The bag must provide a secure soft shelter for your tools, facilitating light movement through the shoulders as you navigate. Check the load-bearing capacity directly. Load the bag fully with your heavy items and carry it down a hallway. Notice the physical friction. If the strap slips, cuts into your collarbone, or forces you to tilt your spine to compensate, discard it. Keep only the piece that maintains a self-contained shape without fighting your natural posture.",
      "sectionIntro": "Run a final physical diagnostic on your everyday carry to ensure the mechanics serve your posture.",
      "rankedItems": [
