    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Keep your visual contrast adaptable to suit the shifting demands of the day. Tailored garments must draw their pattern strictly from the physical weave of the cloth to build a reliable soft shelter. Let fluid items carry the printed motifs, allowing the drape to break up the geometry and generate light movement. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2}. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and high-glare prints on sight. Apply the desk test to check your choices. Drape the garment over a chair and step back an arm and a half in distance. The motif must read as a clean, unified texture from there. If the lines or shapes still demand individual attention, drop the item. A muted, cool palette depends on this visual integration to remain versatile.",
