  "venus_leo__moon_taurus__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "dark drama + sensory comfort + one molten flash",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on dark drama + sensory comfort + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Build your wardrobe modularly and slowly. Deploy it fast. Your sensory compass is the stretch and yield of the garment. Pick it up and grip the fabric. If it fights your hand, it will fight your body. Leave rigid construction on the rack. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. When evaluating a new piece, apply the half-mirror test. Stand close to the glass so you only see the drape of the shoulder and the line of the collar. If the architecture holds its own without your face selling it, the garment passes.\n\nYour core style formula is dark drama + sensory comfort + one molten flash. Picture a heavy, draping wide-leg trouser anchored by a dark, closely ribbed knit. Add a single warm, highly polished cuff at the wrist. The base provides the necessary shadows and ease. The polished finish catches the light. Keep the layers balanced. Do not let heavy structure overwhelm the yielding base. The outfit must work immediately without needing adjustment. Let the molten element do the work of drawing the eye.",
