    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Reject {texture_bad_1} entirely. Squeeze a handful of the cloth tightly. If it produces a brittle synthetic squeak, drop it. Subject {texture_bad_2} to a harsh physical check. Flick a sleeve sharply downward away from your body. If the material hesitates, floats, or traps warm air like a parachute, it will ruin your dark drama. You require textiles that drop with decisive gravity. Treat {texture_bad_3} with the exact same scrutiny. Anything that clings statically to your limbs, drags roughly across your skin, or looks artificially matt under bright lighting fails immediately. Let your tactile response vet every new garment.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to eliminate any material that fights against your body or betrays a cheap construction.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} with {sweet_spot_keyword_2} to establish a reliable baseline. Take a {texture_good_1} sleeve in your hand and flick the hem against your bare forearm. Listen for a sharp crack, like a small sail catching an unexpected gust of wind. If the fabric flops in silence, abandon it on the rail. This deliberate friction between strict edges and yielding layers anchors pure dark drama. Look for polished yarns that hold an unyielding crease. A warm finish requires materials that obey your hands entirely. Ensure the textile delivers essential sensory comfort before assessing the cut.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the exact tension between rigid surfaces and yielding layers to dictate your daily choices.",
      "tests": [
        "the wrist-flick test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is warm. Establish a foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2} as heavy bases. Substitute stark tones with {core_colour_3}, and use {core_colour_4} to bridge awkward gaps. Deploy {accent_colour_1} and {accent_colour_2} strictly as deliberate accents. Treat your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly. Reject icy pastel, neon brights, and cold blue-grey completely. Test every colour. If it reads cold, leave the garment on the rail. Watch for the trap of drifting softness. Dressing entirely in pale items feels pleasant initially but fades from memory by midday. Correct this lack of gravity by injecting dark drama. Ground a fine ribbed merino knit with a sharply tailored {core_colour_1} jacket or a rigid flat shoe placed precisely where the eye lands first. This provides structure, allowing sensory comfort to govern the rest.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your colour palette as a strict sorting mechanism.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Warm taupe",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Camel",
