    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, light movement takes the lead. Let worsted wool trousers swing freely at the ankle and anchor them with crisp cotton poplin shirting. You dress for a shared space, so build an approachable cool temperature using icy grey fine ribbed merino. Mix silver bands with a brass watch dial, keeping the finish matt in places and polished in others. Apply the chemist line test to every tailored piece you own. If you cannot stand waiting for twenty minutes at the pharmacy counter in a stark navy jacket without tugging at the collar or adjusting the sleeves, abandon the item entirely. Nothing you wear during the day requires suffering to maintain its shape. Carry a technical nylon tote to secure your tools without added rigidity.",
      "sectionIntro": "Establish your daily uniform by prioritising utility over rigid construction.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close quarters and dim lighting, balanced proportions lead. Pair a stark navy worsted wool trouser with a crisp cotton poplin shirt to build shape without creating a barrier. Avoid restrictive seams that force you to adjust your posture. Apply the dinner table test. If a stiff waistband makes a two-hour meal feel like a punishment, take the piece off. Trust your comfort over the mirror. Pick up a cool silver chain and pair it with a matt gold ring. Mix metals freely to catch the ambient room light. Carry a technical nylon layer for the walk home, and rely on an icy grey silk scarf to anchor the neck.",
      "sectionIntro": "For close quarters and low lighting, let your proportions dictate the read.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Build your morning around garments that respond immediately to your step. Pull on worsted wool trousers and a cool icy grey sweater. Pick up a mixed metal watch on your way out the door. A quick walk to the local greengrocer does not demand a departure from your standard or suffering in tight fabrics. Your clothes must work with you as you navigate a busy neighbourhood market. Assess the stretch of a jacket across your shoulders before paying. If the fabric catches or restricts your stride, leave it on the rack. Apply your core metric daily. Every outfit must deliver balanced proportions + light movement + one refined touch. Combine a matt silver ring with polished gold hardware to ground the look.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your morning routine as an immediate physical commitment to your aesthetic.",
      "tests": [
        "the pharmacy line: a trip to the pharmacy does not require suffering for the aesthetic (Slate)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Treat {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} as an open toolkit. You have complete freedom to blend these across your watch face, belt buckle, and collar pins. Your only boundary is temperature. Keep every alloy cool. To ensure balanced proportions across your hardware, anchor a thick steel chronograph with a slender silver cuff on the opposite wrist. Allow for light movement by leaving a fraction of breathing room between stacked bands. Lift the chain from the tray and weigh it in your palm. A shiny surface deceives the eye. True density never lies. Steer clear of deliberately weathered bronze, beaten copper, and mock-vintage patinas. These finishes introduce visual debris. Confine your selections to pure platinum, bright white gold, mirror-finish steel, and a matt {excluded_finish} texture.",
