      "text": "Anchor your aesthetic with stones that ground your look through sheer mass. Let the physical drop of {stone_1} against your collarbone dictate its value. You need minerals that channel light movement rather than scattering it. Seek out the pristine clarity of {stone_2} to maintain a strictly cool temperature across your hardware. Avoid artificial aging techniques that read as historical clutter and disrupt your balanced proportions. Keep your metals strictly present-tense by relying entirely on polished silver, white gold, platinum, and mirror chrome. Combine these highly reflective elements freely with {stone_3} to build a solid visual structure.",
