    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Evaluate hardware by its temperature and friction. Close your fingers around the metal. If a piece feels hollow or flimsy, drop it. Faux-tarnished alloys and patinated finishes disrupt your balanced proportions with unnecessary visual clutter. They drag a look into the past. Anchor your aesthetic in the present tense instead. Rely on pristine {metal_1}, gleaming platinum, or mirror-polished chrome to maintain a cool tone. Clean, reflective surfaces ensure your mixed pieces function properly. They provide structure without interrupting the light movement of your garments.",
