    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Apply the transit test before purchasing a new bag. Load the compartments with heavy objects, swing the strap over your shoulder, and walk briskly. Rely on your bodily feedback over visual appeal. If the pouch slaps clumsily against your hip or the awkward weight ruins your balanced proportions, drop the item. The design must facilitate light movement while keeping your hands free to assist others. Choose technical nylon for your crossbody in icy grey to align with your cool colour palette. Demand brushed metal zips paired with one polished ring to mix your finishes freely. Check for matt webbing straps that grip the shoulder securely. The structure must adapt to your pace without interference.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test your functional hardware rigorously before trusting it to carry your daily provisions.",
