    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Maintain balanced proportions by locking your tailored pieces to {recommended_pattern_1}. When you require light movement, let your fluid garments carry {recommended_pattern_2}. Your contrast strategy remains adaptable. Push the contrast higher in casual settings. Pull it down to subtle tonal shifts when the environment demands restraint. Ensure the underlying dye base stays cool. Apply the desk test to every new print. Step back a metre and a half from your mirror. The design must resolve into a clean, uniform texture at this distance. If it shouts, it fails. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} entirely. Leave {avoid_pattern_2} on the rack. Trust physical evidence over a striking photograph. If the pattern breaks your visual line from across a room, drop it.",
