  "venus_gemini__moon_sagittarius__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "crisp separation + fast movement + one clever contrast",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on crisp separation + fast movement + one clever contrast.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Let speed and structural clarity be your sensory compass. When you pick up a garment, test its weight and its capacity for motion. Your exact formula is crisp separation + fast movement + one clever contrast. Picture a rigid, structured jacket sliced precisely at the waist, sitting over a fluid base layer that drops straight down. Add a heavy utility boot to break the formality. That is the contrast at work. The temperature remains inherently cool throughout. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight does not.\n\nBuild an adaptive wardrobe that drifts by the mood of your community. You require pieces that shift between different spaces without losing their distinct geometry. Apply your own structural seam test before you purchase anything. Turn the garment inside out and run your thumb firmly down the interior stitching. If the construction feels weak or the finishing is unstable, drop the item entirely. A piece must be fundamentally sound to survive constant wear and rapid transitions. Mix your finishes freely, letting polished elements sit directly against flat, matt surfaces. Do not lock yourself into rigid matching.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise your fundamental style mechanics before you add another piece to your wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the seam test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your clothing must support fast movement while maintaining crisp separation between your layers. Build your foundation with {texture_good_1} for shirting that creates clean architectural boundaries. Layer it over {texture_good_2} for sharp lines that shift easily as you engage with your community. For trousers, rely on {texture_good_3} to secure a drape that resists creasing through long hours. Finish with {texture_good_4} for a lightweight outer shell that blocks wind without adding bulk. When assessing a garment, always execute the recovery check. Crush the fabric in your fist, hold it tightly, and release. If it springs back to a cool, smooth surface instantly, buy it. If wrinkles remain, drop it. Start with the textiles ranked below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Prioritise fabrics that bounce back from friction and hold a defined edge.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Crisp cotton poplin",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "shirting with clean architectural boundaries and pure separation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fine ribbed merino",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "close-to-body base layers with sharp lines and easy movement"
