    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Evaluate {texture_bad_1} by squeezing it tightly. Once you open your hand, inspect the surface. If the weave stays crumpled in your palm, abandon it. You require textiles that snap back into shape instantly. Rely entirely on tactile feedback to judge quality. Surfaces deceive the eye, but gravity reveals the truth. Pick up {texture_bad_2} and feel the dead drag it creates across your shoulders. It anchors your stride. Notice how {texture_bad_3} feels sticky against the skin and traps body heat instead of maintaining a cool climate. Build one clever contrast into an outfit using reliable pieces rather than wrestling stubborn threads.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to identify the textiles that fight your physical instincts before they ever touch your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Build your outfits around crisp separation. Pair {sweet_spot_keyword_1} alongside {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Introduce {texture_good_1} when you require a structural shift. Probe every piece before you buy it. Wring the material forcefully, then let go. If the weave retains sharp creases, leave it on the rail. You require fabrics that return immediately to their original form. This tension allows the fast movement your routine demands. Keep the underlying temperature cool.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master your signature material combinations to anchor your daily wardrobe.",
      "tests": [
        "the recovery test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your temperature is cool. Build your foundation from {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Rely on {core_colour_3} as your blank slate, and drop in {core_colour_4} when a garment demands strict definition. Introduce fast movement by isolating {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a solitary focal point. Apply your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly to interrupt heavy blocks. Bypass mustard, rust, and warm olive green. Watch for the beige trap. A stack of identically pale garments reads as unfinished instead of minimal. Rescue it with a {core_colour_4} anchor piece or an {accent_colour_1} addition. Let one tactile shift restore the depth to guarantee crisp separation.",
      "sectionIntro": "Assign a strict job to every tone in your wardrobe to eliminate guesswork.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Stark navy",
          "role": "cool_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Icy grey",
          "role": "cool_base"
