    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At work, crisp separation takes the lead. Establish clear lines using worsted wool trousers and a tucked cotton poplin shirt. This sharp geometry allows fast movement to act as your support structure. Choose lightweight technical nylon jackets that keep you agile for long collaborative meetings. Finish the look with one clever contrast. Combine matt silver hardware with polished gold cufflinks on an icy grey base to provide that final spark. Running errands at the local post office does not pause your baseline. Maintain your cool standards at all hours.",
      "sectionIntro": "Work demands physical focus, so your clothes must act as precise tools.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close quarters, enforce sharp borders. Push stark navy worsted wool directly beside icy grey cotton poplin to guarantee crisp separation. Run your fingers over the cloth before you dress for dinner. The cool, dense drape of fine ribbed merino provides an undeniable measure of quality. Collecting takeout the next morning does not suspend your baseline rules. You maintain structural integrity at all hours. Mix polished silver rings with a matt titanium watch case to deliver one clever contrast. Avoid muddy shades. Pick up your evening coat and inspect the interior lining. Your companions deserve clear visual definitions. Keep the shapes distinct and allow for fast movement.",
      "sectionIntro": "Close settings demand absolute precision.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "A quick walk to the local pharmacist does not mean you abandon your stark navy worsted wool. Treat your community with respect. Evaluate the density of a crisp white poplin shirt. Feel the actual mass of the cloth. If the fabric feels flimsy, leave it on the bed. Keep your colours strictly cool. Mix a high-shine silver ring and a matt gold chain over a heavy cashmere crewneck to provide one clever contrast. Your standard applies to every single morning. You must execute crisp separation + fast movement + one clever contrast. Dress with exact intent every day.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your daily standard is an unbreakable contract.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip to the dry cleaner does not suspend your standards (Frost)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "You possess absolute freedom to mix {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} across your watch case, rings, and jacket zips. This mixed strategy demands a cool baseline to prevent chaos. Maintain crisp separation between these elements by enforcing strict quality control over density. Lift the metals off the tray. Polished veneers hide cheap manufacturing. The cold, heavy mass in your palm delivers the final verdict. Reject pre-distressed alloys, beaten copper, and patinated brass. They drag down a highly current aesthetic and register as mere visual noise, ruining any chance for fast movement. Anchor your hardware instead in high-shine chrome, pristine white gold, sleek platinum, or polished silver. Since you mix surface textures freely, deploy {excluded_finish} as a deliberate choice rather than avoiding it to secure one clever contrast.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your hardware as structural engineering rather than simple decoration.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Select {stone_1} and {stone_2} for their hard, refractive clarity. Weigh every piece of jewellery before you commit. The undeniable heft against your skin provides the only reliable measure of true density. If a stone setting feels hollow, leave it on the table. Pass over manufactured patinas and matt hammered surfaces entirely. These treatments create visual clutter that drags against your need for fast movement. Keep your selections strictly to highly polished, reflective finishes. This sharp surface slices cleanly through a cool palette to establish crisp separation, ensuring your hardware functions as a precise tool rather than a muddy distraction.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware and stones as functional tools built for absolute clarity.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Test the physical resistance of the piece. Optics mislead, but gravitational pull confirms the quality. If the object lacks substantial weight, put it back. You require crisp separation in your hardware. Scuffed edges and coarse textures read as visual clutter against your modern clothing. Maintain fast movement by sticking to a highly polished, cool {metal_1} or a brilliantly clear {stone_1}. Clean, reflective surfaces introduce one clever contrast against a flat textile, keeping the entire composition deliberate.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test your hardware by lifting it before you put it on.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You rely on crisp separation for structure. You demand fast movement from your garments. Accessories exist to provide one clever contrast. Restrain your choices. Limit yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with eyewear. Seek an acetate frame in a mixed finish, blending polished rims with matt arms. Run a kinetic check in the mirror. Put the frames on your face and drop your chin abruptly. If they slide down your nose or pinch your temples, leave them on the tray. They must remain completely secure while you navigate your community. Evaluate the cool metal hinges with your fingers. The joints must feel stiff and substantial. Because you anchor the face with this neutral material, you can mix silver and gold tones freely elsewhere.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the final layer of your wardrobe by treating hardware as a functional tool.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Eyewear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "acetate frame, mixed"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Carry a technical nylon crossbody bag. Look for brushed metal zips paired with a single polished ring. This mixed hardware provides one clever contrast against the matt fabric. You must enforce fast movement. Gauge the practical utility by loading the piece with your heavy daily items and striding at full pace. If the bag swings wildly against your ribs or catches on your garments, drop it immediately. The strap needs to sit flat to preserve crisp separation across your chest. Operate the fastenings directly. If the zips stick or resist your pull, the item fails. Keep the metals grounded in cool temperatures to match your stark navy foundation.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your bags ruthlessly for utility and speed.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Bags",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "technical nylon crossbody, brushed metal zips, one polished ring"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Anchor your stride with a clean leather boot. Seek out a minimal profile featuring cool mixed metal hardware alongside a hybrid matt and polished finish to introduce one clever contrast. A strict ankle shaft creates crisp separation beneath a technical nylon trouser, ensuring fast movement as you cross the street. Always execute a strict mobility trial before leaving the house. Lace the boots tight and pivot sharply on a solid floor. If the heavy sole catches or the rigid leather bites into your instep, take them off. Trust your bodily feedback to dictate your final choices. Mirrors lie. Sensation is absolute.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your footwear strictly for mobility and tactile finish.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Footwear",
          "role": "accessory category",
          "useCase": "clean leather boot, clean"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "the function test"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Tailored garments derive their pattern from strict architectural grids. Fluid garments take theirs from continuous linear flow. Maintain an adaptive approach so your layers shift easily across different environments. Choose mid-scale motifs that bridge the gap between subtle and stark. Assess every print visually. Drop the item on a table and walk several paces away. If the design dissolves into a messy blur, leave it. It must register as a clean texture from a distance to establish one clever contrast. Secure crisp separation by layering {recommended_pattern_1} against a solid block of colour. Enable fast movement with {recommended_pattern_2} or {recommended_pattern_3}. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. Keep the underlying dye temperature strictly cool to anchor your choices.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your visual noise to define clear boundaries across your garments.",
      "tests": [
        "the desk test (read as clean texture at arm's length and a half)"
      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Run the desk test on any {recommended_pattern_1}. Drape the garment over a chair and step back an arm's length and a half. Look at the cloth. At this range, the motif must blend into a cohesive, cool wash of colour. If the individual shapes still demand attention, the scale is too large. You require fast movement across the fabric, not a disruptive graphic. A functioning pattern reads as a flat texture from across the floor and only reveals its actual geometry when a colleague sits next to you. This optical shift introduces one clever contrast and guarantees you retain crisp separation when pairing the printed piece with solid trousers.",
      "sectionIntro": "Use this strict distance check to measure whether a print belongs in your rotation.",
      "tests": [
        "the desk test (read as clean texture at arm's length and a half)"
      ]
    }
