  "venus_scorpio__moon_cancer__air_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "close drape + hidden depth + one warm point of light",
    "closing": "Always rely on the uncompromising weight of your materials to build a wardrobe anchored in close drape + hidden depth + one warm point of light.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Curate your wardrobe with relentless patience. Build slowly over years. Deploy your garments fast when you dress. You do not need validation to justify your choices. Your focus is strictly internal. Run your palm over a garment before you check the label. If the fabric catches or feels hollow, drop it. You are searching for a heavy, silent slide against the skin. That physical sensation of weight and insulation is your primary filter.\n\nYour governing equation is close drape + hidden depth + one warm point of light. Picture a dense, matt knit worn tight to the ribcage under a heavy overcoat with invisible seams, finished with a single brushed metal ring catching the light. Apply the physical test of hesitation. If a garment requires you to adjust the collar in the mirror or makes you seek a second opinion, your gut already knows the piece fails. Turn on your heel and leave it on the rail. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't.",
      "sectionIntro": "Memorise these principles to build a foundation that relies entirely on your own physical intuition.",
      "tests": [
        "trust your gut and walk away"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation from materials that guarantee a close drape and contain hidden depth. Let your fingers gauge material integrity. Perform the drop test. Release the garment onto a flat surface. If the textile maintains a memory of its own structure, keep it. If it flattens into a two-dimensional layer, leave it. Hunt for {texture_good_1} in your knitwear to guarantee it compresses and springs back. Select {texture_good_2} for bags that mould to your grip and build a warm, matt patina. Rely on {texture_good_3} for coats that hold strict lines. Slip {texture_good_4} underneath for fluid movement. Memorise the hierarchy below.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to recognise the materials that construct your wardrobe.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
          "role": "rank 3",
          "useCase": "tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years"
        },
        {
          "name": "Silk",
          "role": "rank 4",
          "useCase": "blouses and linings that add fluid, effortless movement"
        },
