    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Squeeze the fabric in your fist before checking the price tag. Release your grip. If the material deflates into a shapeless puddle, it cannot provide your required close drape. {texture_bad_1} fails this assessment on contact. It clings and sags instead of holding a firm boundary around you. Avoid {texture_bad_2} for the opposite structural failure. It refuses to mould to your frame, standing rigid and stiff. Inspect {texture_bad_3} under shop lighting. If the finish reads as a cheap synthetic glare rather than reflecting one warm point of light, walk away. A self-contained style relies on strict material integrity. Flimsy threads shatter that quiet boundary.",
      "sectionIntro": "Learn to recognise the materials that fail your structural requirements before they even touch your skin.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Anchor your style in the tension between {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Drape a piece of {texture_good_1} over your forearm. If it forms stiff peaks and holds an empty shape, leave it on the rack. You require materials that yield instantly to gravity, pooling into a heavy heap. This ensures the close drape necessary for your silhouette. Build tension by pairing this yielding weight against thicker, matt surfaces. The contrast provides structure without rigid stiffness. Keep the finish muted and the temperature warm. Avoid anything that throws a hard reflection or stands away from the body.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test materials by their weight and yield before you wear them.",
      "tests": [
        "the collapse test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your overall palette remains fundamentally warm and matt. Build your close drape around {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Add {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} as bridge neutrals to ground the look and create hidden depth. Rely on {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} to act as your single deliberate accent. Treat your relief tone as a soft note used sparingly when the eye needs rest. Pass over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels on sight. Avoid the trap of a solid dark uniform that signals resignation. Intervene by breaking up the visual block with a {core_colour_1} cashmere layer, a woven scarf in {accent_colour_1}, or a {core_colour_2} leather belt.",
      "sectionIntro": "Control your aesthetic by filtering every piece through a strict colour strategy.",
