    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "Let close drape lead your weekday mornings. Anchor the outfit with brushed wool trousers in rich toffee, keeping the cut near the body to maintain your self-contained lane. Support this foundation by building hidden depth through matt silk blouses in camel rather than sharp contrasts. Finish the collarbone with one warm point of light in matt gold. A brief trip to the post room or a coffee errand does not require abandoning your heavy knits. Pinch the hem of a prospective office garment. If the material feels stiff, leave it on the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Structure your office dressing by letting your silhouette take the lead.",
      "tests": [
