    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In dim spaces, close drape leads. Let the fabric fall directly onto the skin. Gauge a new piece by how the material pools in your fingers. Do not abandon the yielding quality of your garments just because a setting drops in formality. A late flight or a quiet evening at home demands the same rigorous standard. Pick up a rich toffee silk slip or a dark camel cashmere wrap. Evaluate the matt surface in low lighting. Keep the silhouette tight and entirely self-contained. Rely on the physical drop of the textile over visual styling.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the close quarters of evening wear and low lighting.",
