    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Walking the dog at dawn does not excuse flimsy outerwear. Treat the pavement as an extension of your own private space. Reach for camel trousers cut from brushed wool and pair them with a rich toffee silk shirt. Your baseline remains constant across all environments. It is always close drape + hidden depth + one warm point of light. Run your thumb over the lapel of your coat. It must remain utterly matt. If a garment feels brittle, leave it in the wardrobe. Anchor your collar with a single brass pin. You dictate the terms of your daily movement. Let the substance of the textiles do the work.",
