    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Build your hardware strategy around warm metals. Prioritise {metal_1}, {metal_2}, and {metal_3} to harmonise with your wardrobe. Weigh every buckle, clasp, and chain in your palm before you wear them. Substantial hardware grounds your garments and supports a close drape. Avoid {excluded_finish}. High-shine, polished chrome silver creates a sharp, distracting glare against soft muted textiles. Stick exclusively to brushed and matt textures to keep the look cohesive. This discipline guarantees your metal accents provide hidden depth rather than superficial flash.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat your metals as structural anchors rather than decorative additions.",
      "tests": [
