    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "Press a piece of {stone_1} against your skin before putting it on. Temperature and density confirm its authenticity. Choose stones that carry hidden depth within their structure rather than surface-level flash. Avoid highly polished {stone_2} that throws off sharp, distracting reflections. Such aggressive brilliance shatters the quiet, warm harmony of your muted wardrobe. Seek out matt or tumbled {stone_3} instead. These finishes absorb light rather than refracting it. Rely on this heavy, self-contained presence to anchor your look.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate the density and finish of your stones to ensure they anchor your wardrobe rather than distracting from it.",
      "tests": [
