    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Your garments establish the close drape and build the quiet undercurrent. Your accessories deliver the one warm point of light. Stick to one or two strong pieces per look. Put on your chosen items, face the mirror, and take off the final piece you added. If the outfit retains its focus without it, leave the item behind. One strong piece is enough to anchor your frame. Apply this exact restraint to your handbags. Select structured pieces cut from full-grain leather or thick suede. Require matt brushed hardware. Test the construction by setting the bag on a flat surface. It should support its own shape. Depend entirely on the structural integrity of the leather rather than external branding.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the physical tests required to select and edit your daily accessories.",
      "rankedItems": [
