    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Demand a generous silk scarf or fine wool wrap in muted camel. Run the textile through your fingers. The fabric must possess a completely matt finish. If the surface catches the light and flashes back at you, drop it. You are dressing to secure your close drape. Anchor the scarf near the collarbone to supply a quiet undercurrent beneath your brushed tweed layers. Execute a strict removal check before concluding the outfit. If the woven length fights your gold earrings or introduces a second focal element, take one item off. You only require a solitary warm element near the face. Everything else must step back.",
      "sectionIntro": "Audit your secondary additions to ensure they strictly obey your foundational requirements.",
