    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "For tailored pieces, draw pattern directly from the woven fibre. Fluid garments take their scale from warm, matt tonal repeats. Enforce a strict low-contrast rule. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2}. You need motifs that build upon your quiet undercurrent rather than disrupt it. Step back and soften your focus. A successful design must blur into pure texture at five paces. Rely on this optical test before committing. Look for {recommended_pattern_1} and {recommended_pattern_2} to anchor your close drape without visual noise.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test every pattern against your need for visual silence.",
      "tests": [
