    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Hang the {recommended_pattern_1} on a rail. Step back ten paces and uncross your eyes slightly. If the print reads as distinct shapes competing for attention, leave it on the rack. Your quiet undercurrent requires patterns that dissolve. They must melt into a single, muted surface texture. Give your eyes a moment to adjust. If the design refuses to merge into a rich, warm wash of colour, it will disrupt the close drape of your garments. Look for weaves that retreat into the background. Trust the blur.",
      "sectionIntro": "Put every print through a strict focal test before you buy it.",
