          "useCase": "warmer-weather pieces whose natural wrinkle reads as authentic"
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Screen out inferior weaves immediately. You require garments that yield seamlessly to the body. Discard any item that feels brittle or rigid. If {texture_bad_1} lacks give or makes a synthetic noise under your thumb, walk away. Your warm palette demands honest materials. Notice how {texture_bad_2} creates a stiff, artificial barrier on the skin. It traps heat and forces an unnatural shape. Reject {texture_bad_3} the moment it catches on your knuckles. Poorly made fabrics mask their flaws visually but always reveal their true nature upon contact. Your touch remains your most accurate gauge of quality.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject dishonest materials before you even look at the price tag.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Aim for the exact midpoint of {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Layer a warm piece of {texture_good_1} over dense, matt weaves to establish structure. Pinch the cloth between your thumb and index finger. The material must fold cleanly over the collarbone without tension. Seek pieces that maintain crisp outlines while offering total ease against the skin, grounding your outfit completely.",
      "sectionIntro": "Pinpoint the precise overlap of materials that makes your clothing work.",
      "tests": [
        "if a fabric resists your touch or feels squeaky between your fingers, leave it behind"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette demands a strictly warm temperature. Build your foundation using {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}, then bridge the gap with {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Deploy {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as your single deliberate accent, and apply your relief tone strictly as a soft note used sparingly. Keep all finishes matt and muted. Pass over icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels. Defaulting to an unbroken block of {core_colour_1} reads as a rushed oversight. Break it apart using a {accent_colour_1} scarf, a {core_colour_3} knit, or a {accent_colour_2} strap. This method provides structure, ensures sensory comfort, and brings a touch of quiet depth.",
