      "text": "Your hardware strategy relies on warm tones. Build your foundation heavily on {metal_1} and {metal_2}, pulling in {metal_3} only when an item requires minimal contrast. Metals deliver defining boundaries to your wardrobe. Avoid any piece featuring a {excluded_finish} finish. Highly reflective hardware breaks the cohesion of your muted palette and disrupts the garment. Seek out a matt or brushed surface to keep the presentation integrated. Judge metals entirely by their density. Solid, weighty buckles and substantial clasps ground the piece and prove their underlying quality.",
      "sectionIntro": "Your hardware selection demands the same rigorous physical criteria as the garments themselves.",
