    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Accessories provide a touch of quiet depth. They act as the final anchor for the architectural lines and the woven physical ease of your garments. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. A single substantial focal point is always enough. Start this process with handbags crafted from warm full-grain leather. Inspect the buckles and closures. You require brushed matt hardware that absorbs light rather than reflecting it. Evaluate the gauge of the leather with your bare hands to confirm its durability.",
