    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Assess your scarves as tools for both insulation and visual weight. Choose fine wool or heavy silk with a pure matt surface. The fibre must provide deep sensory comfort. Drape a camel or rich toffee scarf over your collar and step back. If the piece competes with your warm gold rings, take it off. A carefully chosen addition yields the exact dimension required. Let these muted textiles communicate through their drape and physical quality alone.",
