    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your tailored wool garments in patterns built directly into the weave, such as a subtle {recommended_pattern_1}. Let fluid silk pieces carry patterns designed as low contrast tonal jacquards or a soft {recommended_pattern_2}. Keep your palette strictly muted and tonal. Sharp contrast disrupts the garment line. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and any harsh {avoid_pattern_2} entirely. Look for motifs that merge seamlessly into a gentle, warm texture. Seek out a {recommended_pattern_3} that reads almost as a solid colour from a distance. This discipline provides necessary shape without demanding unwarranted attention.",
