    "closing": "Let your hands locate the heaviest materials, trusting your physical instinct to build quiet grandeur + hidden depth + one molten flash.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Trust the physical weight of a garment before you check the mirror. Close your eyes and feel the fabric drop from your shoulders. Looks lie. Weight does not. Build your collection slowly, inspecting every inner seam and blind hem, but dress fast in the morning. When you pull a garment on, it should settle into place with heavy intent. Your anchor is a warm temperature. Every piece you buy must carry a warm undertone in its construction to align with your natural contrast.\n\nYour exact equation is quiet grandeur + hidden depth + one molten flash. Picture a heavy, unlined overcoat dropping straight to the calf. Layer this over a fine knit that reveals its complex weave only when touched. Finish the look with a single heavy link catching the light at the cuff. To verify any combination, rely on the wrist test. Put your entire look together and lift your arm. If the sleeve catches, if the cloth resists, or if the flash at your hand feels disjointed, change the garment. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass.",
