    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Execute the lamplight test on any {recommended_pattern_1} before buying. Take the garment into a room with low illumination. Drape the fabric over a chair, step back five paces, and squint. Watch the print carefully. A poor pattern stays rigid and flat. A correct pattern dissolves entirely. It must melt into an indistinct texture that reads as a woven solid from across the room. This visual shift provides necessary hidden depth. If the motifs remain highly legible in the shadows, the piece fails. Return the item to the rail.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply the lamplight test to evaluate how a print behaves in physical space.",
      "tests": [
