  "venus_capricorn__moon_pisces__fire_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "enduring structure + blurred edges + one living texture",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on enduring structure + blurred edges + one living texture.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Anchor your wardrobe in weight and quiet friction. Trust your hands to find fabrics that absorb light rather than reflect it. A surface must feel substantial but hushed. Build every look on enduring structure + blurred edges + one living texture. Picture a heavy tailored overcoat worn over a dense brushed knit, finished with a matt leather belt. The coat provides the architecture. The knit softens the perimeter. The leather gives the eye a place to rest and breathe. This combination creates a warm visual field that asks nothing from the outside world.\n\nConstruct this foundation slowly. Source each piece with deliberate care, edit ruthlessly, and deploy the final garments fast. Drift between shapes according to your mood. When evaluating a new addition, apply the host test. Put the garment on and notice your immediate physical reaction. Ask yourself if the piece makes you feel like the owner of the house receiving visitors, rather than a guest anxious to impress. If a garment makes you want to adjust your posture, check a mirror, or seek approval, take it off immediately. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. You require garments that hold their shape and keep you firmly rooted.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply these foundational principles to anchor your wardrobe and sharpen your physical instincts.",
      "tests": [
        "the host test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Build your foundation with {texture_good_3} for coats that hold an enduring structure. Anchor these tailored garments with {texture_good_2} for your bags and belts, allowing the surface to patinate quietly over time. Soften the interior with warm {texture_good_4} for linings and blouses that rest against the skin, and rely on {texture_good_1} for knitwear that compresses and recovers its shape. This is how you introduce blurred edges and one living texture into a self-contained wardrobe. Before acquiring any new piece, perform the breath test. Press the material directly over your mouth and exhale. If the air traps and bounces back, the fabric will suffocate you. Leave it on the rack. Rely on your bodily response. True luxury supports your internal heat rather than smothering it. Here are the textures that pass.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate every material by its ability to hold form and breathe with your body.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Cashmere",
          "role": "rank 1",
          "useCase": "knitwear and winter layers that compress and bounce back"
        },
        {
          "name": "Full-grain leather",
          "role": "rank 2",
          "useCase": "bags, shoes, and belts that mould to your life and patinate"
        },
        {
          "name": "Brushed wool and tweed",
