      ]
    },
    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Exhale through any prospective cloth before buying. If that warm air rebounds to smother your face, the material fails. Drop it. {texture_bad_1} feels aggressively slick against the hands and refuses to yield. It sits rigidly rather than draping, completely disrupting your blurred edges. {texture_bad_2} is similarly suffocating, sealing the body inside a harsh shell. Keep your fingers tightly attuned to the matt finish of every textile. If {texture_bad_3} catches the light with a cheap sheen or feels like a plastic film, leave it on the rail. You require materials that absorb light and quietly contain your heat, never rigid synthetic traps.",
      "sectionIntro": "Train your hands to reject materials that fight your self-contained warmth.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Your material sweet spot requires {sweet_spot_keyword_1} layered with {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Combine these to build enduring structure. Run your bare hand over {texture_good_1}. Seek warm, matt finishes that remain entirely self-contained. Protect your space by verifying the weave's porosity. The air must pass through the fibres freely when you breathe into them. If a material traps your exhalation, leave it on the rack. Dense synthetics block airflow and stifle the body. Prioritise fabrics that regulate your temperature naturally.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master the precise material baseline that defines your wardrobe, and refuse to compromise on how cloth behaves.",
      "tests": [
        "the breath test"
      ]
    },
    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Your palette temperature is strictly warm. Build your foundation with {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}. Bridge these base layers using {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4} to shift the outfit's balance. Rely on your immediate physical response when selecting a shade. If a stark dye feels wrong in your hands, drop the garment. Merge foundation pieces gently to create blurred edges. For a sharp focal point, apply {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} as a single deliberate accent. Leave icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels on the rack. Watch out for the all-earth sink. Piling a matt {core_colour_1} coat over a dense {core_colour_2} jumper can swallow you whole. Lift this heavy density by slipping a pale knit collar near your face, holding a piece of firm leather, or threading in the relief tone as a soft note used sparingly.",
      "sectionIntro": "Take control of your palette by learning how to balance depth and intensity with your own hands.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
          "name": "Camel",
          "role": "warm_base"
        },
        {
          "name": "Rich toffee",
          "role": "warm_base"
