      ]
    },
    "occasions_work": {
      "text": "At the desk, let enduring structure take the lead. A heavy camel coat or a strict wool trouser provides the necessary boundary for a self-contained day. Support this firm outline with blurred edges near the face. Use a matt silk blouse or a brushed scarf in a warm, rich toffee to soften the geometry. Dipping out for a pint of milk does not require shedding your tailored silhouette entirely. Keep the heavy overcoat on, even if the underlayers relax. Anchor the look with a single organic finish, like an aged leather belt with a brass buckle that grounds the composition. Trust your own instincts as your primary guide. Appearance deceives, but the heft of a garment tells the truth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Navigate your working hours by letting your silhouette hold the line.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip for milk does not require abandoning your silhouette (Tide)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "In close, low-light settings, your blurred edges take the lead. Dim lighting swallows sharp cuts. Rely on the physical heft of heavy silk or the dense pile of brushed wool to cast deep shadows. Pick up a rich toffee overshirt. Close your eyes and trust your hands to verify the heavy drape. Assess the garment by its actual mass. Even a sudden step outside does not justify collapsing your shape. Maintain your perimeter. Swap stiff lapels for a warm camel cashmere knit that sits close to the collarbone. Keep all finishes strictly matt to deaden the ambient glow. Evaluate every piece by touch. If the weave feels thin between your fingers, drop it.",
      "sectionIntro": "Calibrate your evening wear by testing every piece strictly by touch.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip for milk does not require abandoning your silhouette (Tide)"
      ]
    },
    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Running casual errands is no reason to abandon your foundation. A Tuesday morning trip to the chemist demands the exact same equation as an evening appointment. Demand total consistency. You must execute enduring structure + blurred edges + one living texture, every single day. Pull on a heavy camel cashmere knit over straight-leg brushed wool trousers. Anchor the foot with a warm toffee full-grain leather boot. The garments must hold their own shape before they touch your skin. Grip the knitwear in your fist. The yarn must possess enough internal density to support the shoulder line without drooping. If a piece collapses under its own mass, drop it back into the drawer.",
      "sectionIntro": "Anchor your mornings in the exact same discipline you apply to formal appointments.",
      "tests": [
        "a trip for milk does not require abandoning your silhouette (Tide)"
      ]
    },
    "hardware_metals": {
      "text": "Focus your hardware on a warm palette. Base your jewellery and functional clasps on {metal_1} and {metal_2}. These tones provide enduring structure without breaking the quiet continuity of your wardrobe. Rely on your own grip to judge quality. Lift every piece to gauge its density. Evaluate metal strictly by its physical drag in your palm. Reject highly polished materials. High-shine {excluded_finish} creates a sharp, distracting glare that clashes with soft, muted garments. Fix this by demanding matt and brushed textures exclusively. A brushed {metal_3} watch case or a matt belt buckle drinks the light, keeping the entire look grounded and self-contained.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your hardware as strictly as you choose your heaviest winter coat.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_stones": {
      "text": "When selecting stones, demand opaque depth and warm resonance. Pick it up and weigh a {stone_1} or {stone_2} cabochon in your palm. Judge a setting by its solid physical presence. Anchor your wardrobe with this undeniable heft, ensuring the jewellery acts as an enduring structure against your fabrics. Avoid high-gloss, polished finishes. A glaring mirror surface feels sharp and aggressively distracting next to your muted garments. Stick to heavily brushed or matt metals to keep the visual temperature cohesive and grounded.",
      "sectionIntro": "Test and select hardware that anchors your silhouette without screaming for attention.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "hardware_tip": {
      "text": "Hold every piece of warm {metal_1} in your bare palm before you buy it. Only accept items that sink heavily into your skin. A solid cast piece provides enduring structure, while a hollow item merely rattles. Avoid high-gloss finishes entirely. A glaring, polished surface cuts too sharply against your quiet garments and shatters the harmony. Demand a brushed or matt finish to protect your blurred edges. The metal must sink into your fabrics, never flash above them.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your hardware by weight and finish.",
      "tests": [
        "pick it up: looks lie, weight doesn't (the pick-it-up weight test)"
      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "high-shine, polished chrome silver looks sharp and distracting next to soft muted colours",
          "fix": "stick to matt and brushed textures to keep the look cohesive"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "Treat your accessories as the final provider of one living texture. They must ground the blurred edges of a soft layer and reinforce the enduring structure of your tailoring. Restrict yourself to one or two strong pieces per look. Begin with handbags. Demand full-grain leather or thick suede fitted with matt brushed hardware. Apply the one-ember test. Evaluate the finish. If the piece flashes with a bright polish, leave it behind. It must remain quietly warm, holding a steady, contained glow from within. Trust the heavy drag of solid hardware and thick hide in your hands to confirm its quality.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select your finishing elements with strict, physical discipline.",
      "rankedItems": [
