    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Seek out generous silk or fine wool for your scarves. Choose only matt finishes that refuse to shine. Pick it up and crush the fabric in your fist. Rely on your tactile judgement over visual appeal. True quality responds with a heavy, fluid drape when you let the cloth fall. You need this generous volume to supply blurred edges against tailored outerwear. Look for a single strike of rich toffee glowing deep within a muted background, like a solitary warm coal holding its heat. Avoid high-contrast prints. Let the piece remain self-contained, a private layer of warmth rather than a public display.",
      "sectionIntro": "Dictate the final shape of your silhouette by selecting fabrics that respond strictly to gravity.",
      "rankedItems": [
