    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Enduring structure in your tailoring demands patterns woven directly into the thread. Look for a tonal {recommended_pattern_1} or a low-contrast {recommended_pattern_2}. Fluid garments tolerate dyed motifs, but you must keep the transitions strictly tonal. Pass over {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} without a second thought. Trust your physical instincts over visual noise. Pick the garment up and apply the firelight test. The pattern must deepen and turn exceptionally warm by lamplight. If the contrast feels stark or flat under a simple bulb, drop it. Demand blurred edges where the dyes meet. You are wearing quiet, matt shifts of shade.",
      "sectionIntro": "Pattern is an architectural decision rather than a decorative afterthought.",
