      ]
    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Examine any {recommended_pattern_1} under a low, warm lamp before bringing it home. If the lines sharpen into harsh geometry, leave the garment on the hanger. The contrast must soften in the shadows. Look for shapes that retreat gracefully into the weave. This visual shift guarantees the blurred edges necessary for your privacy. High contrast prints demand external attention. A truly muted pattern keeps its secrets. Trust your eyes when the light fades to assess the true depth of the motif.",
      "sectionIntro": "Subject every pattern to a strict environmental lighting check.",
