  "venus_taurus__moon_capricorn__earth_dominant": {
    "coreFormula": "structure + softness + a touch of quiet depth",
    "closing": "Your style guide is a map of your own instincts, built on structure + softness + a touch of quiet depth.",
    "style_core": {
      "text": "Judge a garment by its physical weight and the way it anchors your posture. Trust this physical instinct as your ultimate compass. Looks lie. Weight doesn't. Your foundation relies on a matt, muted finish and a warm temperature that keeps the result entirely self-contained rather than externally demanding. To achieve this balance, your core formula is structure + softness + a touch of quiet depth. Picture a heavy outer layer with a sharply tailored shoulder worn over a yielding fine knit, grounded by a dense, unreflective accessory.\n\nBuild your wardrobe slowly and methodically. Gather pieces over seasons, but deploy fast each morning. When considering a new acquisition, always apply the decade test. Pick the item up and ask yourself if its silhouette and construction will still serve your routine in ten years without betraying the exact year you bought it. If the garment requires current proportions or fleeting styling tricks to make sense, it fails. Leave it on the rail and continue the search for something with true permanence.",
      "sectionIntro": "Master these foundational principles to anchor your wardrobe decisions and eliminate second-guessing.",
      "tests": [
