      ]
    },
    "textures_good": {
      "text": "Your wardrobe demands materials that build structure while maintaining absolute softness. Depend on your fingers to find this equilibrium. When evaluating a new piece, execute the candlelight test. Hold the fabric in dim, warm light and watch how the matt surface absorbs illumination to reveal a touch of quiet depth. Avoid any finish that glints or distracts. Look for {texture_good_3} for tailored coats and blazers that hold clean lines for years. Anchor these outer shells with {texture_good_1} for knitwear that compresses and bounces back against the palm. Keep {texture_good_4} close to the skin for blouses and linings that add fluid movement. Finish the foundation with {texture_good_2} for bags and belts that mould to your shape and patinate over time. Master this specific list.",
