    "textures_bad": {
      "text": "Avoid {texture_bad_1}. Squeeze the material in your fist. If it springs back with a brittle, synthetic resistance, it fails the skin. You require garments that grant true structure and softness, never a rigid cage. Stay away from {texture_bad_2}. Run your thumb across the grain. If the weave feels slick or hollow, it will never hold a touch of quiet depth. Test any new piece under a single warm lamp. If the surface throws off a harsh glare instead of settling into a rich, matt shadow, drop the item entirely. Rely on bodily feedback over visual appeal. Optics deceive, but tactile mass never falters.",
