    "textures_sweet_spot": {
      "text": "Combine {sweet_spot_keyword_1} and {sweet_spot_keyword_2}. Take a piece of {texture_good_1} into a shadowed corner. The material must drink the scant, warm glow and remain entirely matt. If it shines, walk away. A heavily muted cloth secures a touch of quiet depth and keeps the silhouette strictly self-contained. Rely on dense threads that hold a clean line without making a sound. Keep your layers heavy and silent.",
