    "palette_narrative": {
      "text": "Assess every garment by its temperature. Your palette is decisively warm. Anchor your foundation in {core_colour_1} and {core_colour_2}, then bridge these heavy bases using {core_colour_3} and {core_colour_4}. Apply {accent_colour_1} or {accent_colour_2} only for a deliberate focal point. Treat your relief tone as a subtle note used sparingly to break up heavy layers. Reject icy electric blue, neon brights, and fleeting trend pastels. Beware the trap of metallic excess, where too much shiny hardware turns an imposing silhouette into a cheap display. Mirrors deceive, but physical gravity always tells the truth. Let your bodily reaction to heavy chains warn you. Anchor your look with a single gleaming element. Demand that all remaining hardware stays tiny, matt, and strictly in the background. This exact discipline secures structure, softness, and a touch of quiet depth.",
