    "occasions_intimate": {
      "text": "A touch of quiet depth leads in dim settings. When proximity closes in, the eye yields to the hand. Let brushed wool and camel cashmere do the heavy lifting in a close room. Keep the palette temperature warm. Swap crisp daytime garments for a rich toffee silk shirt that absorbs ambient light rather than reflecting it. Ensure every textile remains matt. Mixed metal jewellery provides the only gleam. Retain your form even behind closed doors. Paying a late utility bill at the kitchen table does not require collapsing your frame into a slouchy dressing gown. Maintain your self-contained boundaries. Keep the structure in your shoulders with a dense knit, then introduce softness through the drape of the sleeve.",
