    "occasions_daily": {
      "text": "Treat your mundane routines as the testing ground for your discipline. Going to the local pharmacy for paracetamol is no excuse to swap tailored edges for sagging joggers. Disputing a council tax bill at the post office demands no collapse of your silhouette into unstructured cotton. Maintain your boundaries. Pick up a warm camel cashmere jumper instead of a hoodie. Pair it with a matt gold chain, polished silver rings, and a brushed wool coat. Everything you put on your body must serve your internal standard. Your baseline never suspends itself for mere errands. Whether you are buying milk or reviewing documents at home, the daily mandate remains exactly the same. You always need structure + softness + a touch of quiet depth.",
      "sectionIntro": "Enforce your personal standard across every mundane errand.",
