      ],
      "traps": [
        {
          "failure": "antiqued brass, hammered copper, and artificially aged metal read as clutter against a present-tense style",
          "fix": "keep to polished silver, platinum, white gold, and mirror chrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "accessory_1": {
      "text": "You have built the foundation with balanced proportions. You have anchored the silhouette in honest fabric. Now you introduce one refined touch. Restrict your additions to one or two strong pieces per look. Put your completed outfit on and execute the take-off test. Remove a single item from your frame. If the structure holds its ground, leave that extra piece on the table. Begin your selection with silk scarves. Seek out a crepe de chine square with a deliberately matt surface. Trust your hands as you manipulate the material. Feel the cool friction of the woven threads against your collarbone.",
      "sectionIntro": "Select and edit your finishing elements through strict physical testing.",
      "rankedItems": [
