      ]
    },
    "accessory_2": {
      "text": "Build your fine jewellery collection from thin, mixed gold and silver pieces. Combine polished and brushed metals freely. This strategy relies on balanced proportions across your hands and neck. Wear a slender brushed gold chain with polished cool silver rings. Do not stack them so high that they clink. Edit your selections strictly before you leave the house. Strip away the final bracelet or necklace you added. If the remaining combination feels intentional, walk away from the mirror. Let the mixed finishes provide the visual friction. Do not let heavy metal slabs overwhelm an honest fabric like washed silk or boiled wool. The simple contrast of polished and brushed surfaces functions perfectly as one refined touch.",
      "sectionIntro": "Evaluate your secondary pieces to ensure they serve the whole.",
      "rankedItems": [
