    },
    "accessory_3": {
      "text": "Source a small structured bag. Pick a top-handle shape in smooth leather or kid suede. Inspect the closures. You want fine mixed hardware uniting cool silver and rose gold. Check the entire profile before you exit. Stand completely still and assess the final composition. If this final object disrupts your balanced proportions, remove it immediately. Leave the bag behind if its straps snag on an honest fabric like a lambswool cuff or if the chain fights your neckline.",
      "sectionIntro": "Finish the look by verifying that every addition serves your structural foundation.",
      "rankedItems": [
        {
