    "pattern_narrative": {
      "text": "Anchor your print strategy in a cool temperature. Because your architecture requires balanced proportions, give tailored garments strict motifs like {recommended_pattern_1}. Let fluid pieces carry softer designs like {recommended_pattern_2}. As an adaptive dresser, shift the contrast scale to suit the environment. Build your looks by mixing a low-contrast tonal weave with a sharper graphic element as the context demands. Pass over anything flat or stiff. Leave {avoid_pattern_1} and {avoid_pattern_2} on the hanger entirely. Apply the passing test. Walk across the floor and watch the garment move. The motif must read as a soft, pleasant texture in motion rather than a static block of ink. Rely on a visibly honest fabric to ground the design.",
      "sectionIntro": "Treat pattern as an extension of texture, using it to serve the physical architecture of your clothing.",
