    },
    "pattern_tip": {
      "text": "Test a print by observing it in motion. Put the {recommended_pattern_1} piece on and stride past a large mirror. Do not focus on the individual shapes. Assess the moving whole. A successful design blurs into a cohesive, fluid surface as you walk. If the graphic leaps out and disrupts your balanced proportions, leave the item on the hanger. You require a genuinely honest fabric that supports the structural cut rather than fighting it. Keep the ink cool and strict to ensure the motif acts as a subtle background rhythm.",
      "sectionIntro": "Apply the passing test to judge print scale and visual impact.",
